obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (27111)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27111&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `1. Short title, extent and commencement.—(1) This Act may be called the Delhi Municipal Corporation Act, 1957.`
  line
  line `(2) Except as otherwise provided in this Act, it extends only to Delhi.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of this Act, except this section which shall come into force at once, shall come into force on such date^1 as the ^2[^3[Central Government]] may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoints:`
  line
  line `Provided that different dates may be appointed for different provisions of this Act and any reference in any such provision to the commencement of this Act shall be construed as a reference to the coming into force of that provision.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 2nd January, 1958, vide notification No. F. 20/3/58/SR (R), dated 31st December, 1957, in respect of S. 2, Chap. II,`
  line `ss. 54, 55, 56, 57, 58, 59, 89 and 97, Chap. XXIII, ss. 485, 487, 488, 491, 500, 509, 513 and 515, see Gazette of India,`
  line `Extraordinary, Part IV.`
  line
  line `15th February, 1958, vide notification No. F. 20/3/58/SR (R), dated 11th February, 1958, in respect of S. 510, see`
  line `Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part IV.`
  line
  line `7th April, 1958, vide notification No. F. 20/3/58/SR (R), dated 5th April, 1958, in respect of All the provisions of the`
  line `Act (other than those which have already been brought into force), see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part IV.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for “Central Government” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “Government” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (27112)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27112&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `^1[(1) "Administrator" means the Lieutenant Governor of the National Capital Territory of Delhi;[`
  line
  line `^2[(1A) "annual value" means the annual value of any vacant land or covered space of any building determined under section116E;]`
  line
  line `^3[^4[(1B)] "Appellate Tribunal" means an Appellate Tribunal constituted under section 347A;]]`
  line
  line `(2) "budget-grant" means the total sum entered on the expenditure side of a budget estimate under a major head and adopted by ^5[^6[the Corporation]] and includes any sum by which such budget-grant may be increased or reduced by transfer from or to other heads in accordance with the provisions of this Act and the regulations made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(3) "building" means a house, out-house, stable, latrine, urinal, shed, hut, wall (other than a boundary wall) or any other structure, whether of masonry, bricks, wood, mud, metal or other material but does not include any portable shelter;`
  line
  line `(4) "bye-law" means a bye-law made under this Act, by notification in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(5) "casual vacancy" means a vacancy occurring otherwise than by efflux of time in the office of a councillor an alderman or in any other elective office;`
  line
  line `^7[(6) "Commissioner" means the Commissioner of ^5[^6[the Corporation]];]`
  line
  line `^8[(7) "Corporation" means ^9[the Municipal Corporation of Delhi] established under this Act;]`
  line
  line `(8) "corrupt practice" means any of the practices specified in section 22;`
  line
  line `(9) "dangerous disease" means---`
  line
  line `(a) cholera, plague, chicken-pox, small-pox, tuberculosis, leprosy, enteric fever, crebrospinal meningitis and diphtheria; and`
  line
  line `(b) any other epidemic, endemic or infectious disease which the Commissioner may, by notification in the Official Gazette, declare to be a dangerous disease for the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(10) "Delhi" means the entire area of the Union territory of Delhi except New Delhi and Delhi Cantonment;`
  line
  line `(11) "Delhi Cantonment" means the area for the time being within the local limits of the Delhi Cantonment Board;`
  line
  line `^10* * * * *`
  line
  line `^11* * * * *`
  line
  line `^12* * * * *`
  line
  line `^13* * * * *`
  line
  line `(15) "drain" includes a sewer, a house drain, a drain of any other description, a tunnel, a culvert, a ditch, a channel and any other device for carrying off sewage, offensive matter, polluted water, waste water, rain water or sub-soil water;`
  line
  line `^14[(15A) "Election Commission" means the Election Commission of the National Capital Territory of Delhi referred to in section 7.`
  line
  line `(15B) "Election Commissioner" means the Election Commissioner of the National Capital Territory of Delhi appointed by the Administrator under section 7;]`
  line
  line `(16) "entertainment" includes any exhibition, performance, amusement, game or sport to which persons are ordinarily admitted on payment;`
  line
  line `(17) "factory" means a factory as defined in the Factories Act, 1948 (63 of 1948);`
  line
  line `(18) "filth" includes offensive matter and sewage;`
  line
  line `^15* * * * *`
  line
  line `^16* * * * *`
  line
  line `(21) "goods" includes animals;`
  line
  line `^17[(21A) "Government" means the Government of the National Capital Territory of Delhi;]`
  line
  line `(22) "house-gully" or "service passage" means a passage or strip of land constructed, set apart or utilised for the purpose of serving as or carrying a drain or affording access to a latrine, urinal, cesspoolor other receptacle for filth or other polluted matter, by municipal employees or other persons employed in the cleansing thereof or in the removal of such matter therefrom;`
  line
  line `(23) "hut" means any building which is constructed principally of wood, bamboo, mud, leaves, grass, cloth or thatch and includes any structure of whatever material made which 1 2the Corporation may declare to be a hut for the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(24) "land" includes benefits to arise out of land, things attached to the earth or permanently fastened to anything attached to the earth and rights created by law over any street;`
  line
  line `(25)"licensed architect", "licensed draughtsman", "licensed engineer", "licensed plumber", "licensed surveyor" and "licensed town planner" mean respectively a person licensed under the provisions of this Act as an architect, draughtsman, engineer, plumber, surveyor and town planner;`
  line
  line `(26) "market" includes any place where persons assemble for the sale of, or for the purpose of exposing for sale, meat, fish, fruits, vegetables, animals intended for human food or any other articles of human food whatsoever, with or without the consent of the owner of such place notwithstanding that there may be no common regulation for the concourse of buyers and sellers and whether or not any control is exercised over the business of, or the persons frequenting, the market by the owner of the place or by any other person;`
  line
  line `(27) "member" in relation to ^5[^6[the Corporation]] means a councillor ^18***;`
  line
  line `(28) "municipal authority"means any of the municipal authorities specified in section 44;`
  line
  line `(29) "municipal market" means a market vested in or managed by the Corporation;`
  line
  line `(30) "municipal slaughter house" means a slaughter house vested in or managed by the Corporation;`
  line `^19[(30A) "Municipal Taxation Tribunal" means the Municipal Taxation Tribunal constituted under section 169;]`
  line
  line `^19[(30B) "Municipal Valuation Committee" means the Municipal Valuation Committee constituted under section 116;]`
  line
  line `^20* * * * *`
  line
  line `(32) "New Delhi" means the area within the boundaries described in the First Schedule;`
  line
  line `(33) "nuisance" includes any act, omission, place, animal or thing which causes or is likely to cause injury, danger, annoyance or offence to the sense of sight, smell, or hearing or disturbance to rest or sleep, or which is or may be dangerous to life or injurious to health or property;`
  line
  line `(34) "occupier" includes`
  line
  line `(a) any person who for the time being is paying or is liable to pay to the owner the rent or any portion of the tent of the land or building in respect of which such rent is paid or is payable;`
  line
  line `(b) an owner in occupation of, or otherwise using his land or building;`
  line
  line `(c) a rent free tenant of any land or building;`
  line
  line `(d) a licensee in occupation of any land or building; and`
  line
  line `(e) any person who is liable to pay to the owner damages for the use and occupation of any land or building;`
  line
  line `(35) "offensive matter" includes animal car cases, kitchen or stable refuse, dung, dirt and putrid or putrefying substances other than sewage;`
  line
  line `(36) "Official Gazette" means the Official Gazette of the Union Territory of Delhi;`
  line
  line `(37) "owner" includes a person who for the time being is receiving or is entitled to receive, the rent of any land or building whether on his own account or on account of himself and others or as an agent, trustee, guardian or receiver for any other person or who should so receive the rent or be entitled to receive it if the land or building or part thereof were let to a tenant and also includes`
  line
  line `(a) the custodian of evacuee property in respect of evacuee property vested in him under the Administration of Evacuee Property Act 1950 (31 of 1950); and`
  line
  line `(b) the estate officer to the Government of India, the Secretary of the Delhi Development Authority, constituted under the Delhi Development Act, 1957 (61 of 1957); the General Manager of a railway and the head of a Government department, in respect of properties under their respective control;`
  line
  line `(38) "premises" means any land or building or part of a building and includes--`
  line
  line `(a) the garden, ground and out-houses, if any, appertaining to a building or part of a building; and`
  line `(b) any fittings affixed to a building or part of a building for the more beneficial enjoyment thereof;`
  line
  line `(39) "private street" means any street, which is not a public street and includes any passage securing access to two or more places belonging to the same or different owners;`
  line
  line `(40) "private market" means a market which is not a municipal market;`
  line
  line `(41) "private slaughter house" means a slaughter house which is not a municipal slaughter house;`
  line
  line `(42) "public place" means any place which is open to the use and enjoyment of the public, whether it is actually used or enjoyed by the public or not;`
  line
  line `(43) "public securities" means any securities of the Central Government or a State Government or any securities guaranteed by the Central Government or a State Government or any securities issued under this Act or any debentures issued by the Bombay, Calcutta or Madras Municipal Corporation;`
  line
  line `(44) "public street" means any street which vests in ^5[^6[the Corporation]] as a public street or the soil below the surface of which vest in ^5[^6[the Corporation]] or which under the provisions of this Act becomes, or is declared to be, a public street;`
  line
  line `^21[(44A) "public utilities" include water-supply, sewerage and drainage, solid waste management, energy and telecommunication services, gas distribution system, and public transport system, whether managed by Government or otherwise;]`
  line
  line `(45) "railway administration" has the meaning assigned to it in the Indian Railway Act, 1890, (9 of 1890);`
  line
  line `(46) "rate layer" means a person liable to pay any rate, tax, cess or licence fee under this Act;`
  line
  line `^22* * * * *`
  line
  line `(48) "regulation"means a regulation made ^23[by ^5[ ^6[the Corporation]]] under this Act, by notification in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(49) "reside"--`
  line
  line `(a) a person shall be deemed to "reside" in any dwelling house which or some portion of which he sometimes, although not uninterruptedly, uses as a sleeping apartment, and`
  line
  line `(b) a person shall not be deemed to cease to reside in any such dwelling house merely because he is absent from it or has elsewhere another dwelling house in which he resides, if there is the liberty of returning to it at any time and no abandonment of the intention of returning to it;`
  line
  line `(50) "rubbish" includes ashes, broken bricks, broken glass, dust, malba, mortar and refuse of any kind which is not filth;`
  line
  line `(51) "rule" means a rule made by the and the Central Government ^24[and the Government] under this Act, by notification in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(52) "rural areas" means the areas of Delhi which immediately before the establishment of ^5[^6[the Corporation]] are situated within the local limits of the District Board of Delhi established under the Punjab District Boards Act, 1883, (Punjab Act XX of 1883), but shall not include such portion thereof as may, by virtue of a notification under section 507, cease to be included in the rural areas as herein defined;`
  line
  line `(53) "Scheduled Caste" means any of the Scheduled Castes specified in Part I of the Scheduled to the Constitution (Scheduled Castes) (Union Territories) Order, 1951;`
  line
  line `(54) "sewage" means night-soil and other contents of latrines, urinals, cesspools or drains, and polluted water from sinks, bathrooms, stables, cattle sheds and other like places, and includes trade effluents and discharges from manufactories of all kinds;`
  line
  line `(55) "shed" means a slight or temporary structure for shade or shelter;`
  line
  line `(56) "slaughter house" means any place ordinarily used for the slaughter of animals for the purpose of selling the flesh thereof for human consumption;`
  line
  line `(57) "street" includes any way, road, lane, square, court, alley, gully, passage, whether a thoroughfare or not and whether built upon or not, over which the public have a right of way and also the roadways or footway over any bridge or causeway;`
  line
  line `(58) "trade effluent" means any liquid either with or without particles of matter in suspension therein, which is wholly or in part produced in the course of any trade or industry carried on at trade premises, and in relation to any trade premises means any such liquid as aforesaid which is so produced in the course of any trade or industry carried on at those premises, but does not include domestic sewage;`
  line
  line `(59) "trade premises" means any premises used or intended to be used for carrying on any trade or industry;`
  line
  line `(60) "trade refuse" means the refuse of any trade or industry;`
  line
  line `(61) "urban areas" means the areas of Delhi which are not rural areas;`
  line
  line `^25[(61A) "vacant land"means the land within a premises excluding the land occupied by the plinth of any building erected thereon.]`
  line
  line `(62) "vehicle" includes a carriage, cart, van, dray, truck, hand-cart, bicycle, tricycle, cycle-rickshaw, auto-rickshaw, motor vehicle and every wheeled conveyance which is used or is capable of being used on a street;`
  line
  line `^26[(62A) "Voting machine" means any machine or apparatus whether operated electronically or otherwise used for giving or recording of votes and any reference to a ballot box ballot paper in this Actor the rules made here under shall, save as otherwise provided, be constructed as including a reference to such voting machine wherever such voting machine is used at any election.]`
  line
  line `(63) "ward" means a municipal ward provided by order made under section 5 for the purpose of election of councillors;`
  line
  line `^27[(63A) "Wards Committee" means the Wards Committee referred to in section 50;]`
  line
  line `(64) "water course" includes any river, stream or channel whether natural or artificial;`
  line
  line `^28* * * * *`
  line
  line `(66) "workshop" means any premises (including the precincts thereof) other than a factory, wherein any industrial process is carried on;`
  line
  line `(67) "year"means a year commencing on the 1st day of April;`
  line
  line `^25[(68) "Zone" means a Zone referred to in section 3A.]`
