obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (27113)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Establishment of the Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27113&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) ^2[With effect from such date as the ^3[Government] may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint, there shall be ^4[ ^5[the Corporation]] charged with the Municipal Government of Delhi, to be known as the Municipal Corporation of Delhi.]]`
  line
  line `^6[(2) ^7[ ^8[The Corporation]] so established shall be a body corporate with the name duly notified by the ^3[Government] having perpetual succession and a common seal with power, subject to the provisions of this Act, to acquire, hold and dispose of property and may by the said name sue and be sued.]`
  line
  line `^9[(3)(a) ^7[^8[The Corporation]] shall be composed of the councillors;`
  line
  line `(b) the following persons shall be represented in ^4[^5[the Corporation ]], namely:`
  line
  line `(i) ten persons, who are not less than 25 years of age and who have special knowledge or experience in municipal administration, to be nominated by the Administrator:`
  line
  line `Provided that the persons nominated under this sub-clause shall not have the right to vote in the meetings of ^4[^5[the Corporation ]];`
  line
  line `(ii) members of the House of the People representing constituencies which comprise wholly or partly the area of the Corporation and the members of the Council of States registered as electors within the area of ^4[^5[the Corporation ]];`
  line
  line `(iii) as nearly as possible one-fifth of the members of the Legislative Assembly of the National Capital Territory of Delhi representing constituencies which comprise wholly or partly the area of ^4[^5[the Corporation ]] to be nominated by the Speaker of that Legislative Assembly, by rotation every year:`
  line
  line `Provided that while nominating such members by rotation the Speaker shall ensure that as far as possible all the members are given an opportunity of being represented in ^4[^5[the Corporation]] at least once during the duration of the Corporation;`
  line
  line `(iv) the Chairpersons of the Committees, if any, Constituted under sections 39, 40 and 45, if they are not councillors.]`
  line
  line `(4) Councillors shall be chosen by direct election on the basis of adult suffrage from various wards into which Delhi shall be divided in accordance with the provisions of this Act; ^10***.`
  line
  line `^11[^12[(5) The total number of seats of councillors and the number of seats reserved for the members of the Scheduled Castes in ^4[^5[the Corporation]], shall, at the time of establishment of Corporation, be as determined by the Central Government by notification in the Official Gazette.]]`
  line
  line `(6) Upon the completion of each census after the establishment of ^4[^5[the Corporation]], the number of seats shall be on the basis of the population of ^13[Delhi] as ascertained at that census and shall be determined by the Central Government by notification in the Official Gazette and the number of seats to be reserved for the members of the Scheduled Castes shall, as nearly as may be, bear the same ratio to the total number of seats as the population of Scheduled Castes bears to the total population of ^13[Delhi]:`
  line
  line `Provided that the total number of seats shall in no case be more than two hundred and fifty and the number of seats in ^4[^5[the Corporation]] shall be determined by the Central Government at the time of the establishment of ^4[^5[the Corporation]]:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the determination of seats as aforesaid shall not affect the then composition of the Corporation until the expiry of the duration of the Corporation: :`
  line
  line `Provided also that the seats reserved for the Scheduled Castes may be allotted by rotation to different wards in such manner as the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, direct.]`
  line
  line `^14[(7) Seats shall be reserved for women belonging to the Scheduled Castes, from among the seats reserved for the Scheduled Castes, the number of such seats being determined by the Central Government by order published in the Official Gazette which shall not be less than ^15[one-half] of the total number of seats reserved for the Scheduled Castes.]`
  line
  line `^16[(8) Seats shall be reserved for women, the number of such seats being determined by order published in Official Gazette by the Government which shall not be less than the ^15[one-half] of total number of seats other than those reserved for the Scheduled Castes:`
  line
  line `Provided that such seats reserved for women shall be allotted by rotation to different wards in such manner as the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, direct in this behalf.]`
