obj_root_law_sections_7_d_content:
  string
  line `The persons entitled to be registered as electors in the electoral roll`
  line `of ^1[an assembly constituency] in Delhi as relates to the area comprised within a ward shall be entitled to`
  line `be so registered in the electoral roll of that ward and the provisions in this behalf in the Representation of`
  line `the People Act, 1950 (43 of 1950) shall apply to the registration of electors in the electoral roll of a ward`
  line `as they apply to the registration of electors in the electoral roll of ^1[an assembly constituency].`
  line
  line `Explanation—In this section, in sub-section (1) of section 7E and in clause (ag) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 31, the expression ^1[an assembly constituency] has the meaning assigned to it under the`
  line `Representation of the People Act, 1950 (43 of 1950).`
obj_root_law_sections_7_e:
  sectionId (27124)
  sectionNo 7E
  orderNo 14
  title `Preparation and revision of electoral rolls.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_e_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_e_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27124&sectionno=7E&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_7_e_content:
  string
  line `(1) The electoral roll for each ward shall be`
  line `prepared before each general election in such manner as may be prescribed by rules by reference to the`
  line `qualifying date and shall come into force immediately upon its final publication in accordance with the`
  line `rules made for the purpose:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the ^1[Election Commission] is satisfied that, instead of preparing a fresh electoral roll`
  line `of a ward before a general election, it would be sufficient to adopt the electoral roll of ^2[the assembly`
  line `constituency] for the time being in force as relates to the ward, it may, by order, for reasons to be`
  line `specified therein, direct that the electoral roll of ^2[the assembly constituency] for the time being in force`
  line `as relates to the ward shall, subject to any rules made for the purpose, be the electoral roll of the ward for`
  line `the general election.`
  line
  line `(2) The electoral roll prepared or adopted, as the case may be, under subsection (1) shall—`
  line
  line `(a) unless otherwise directed by the ^1[Election Commission], for reasons to be recorded in`
  line `writing, be revised in the manner prescribed by rules by reference to the qualifying date before each`
  line `bye-election to fill a casual vacancy in a seat allotted to the ward; and`
  line
  line `(b) be revised in any year in the manner prescribed by rules by reference to the qualifying date if`
  line `such revision has been directed by the ^1[Election Commission]:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the electoral roll is not revised as aforesaid, the validity or continued operation of the`
  line `said electoral roll shall not thereby be affected.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (2), the ^1[Election Commission] may, at any`
  line `time, for reasons to be recorded in writing, direct a special revision of the electoral roll for any ward or`
  line `part of a ward in such manner as it may think fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that the electoral roll for the ward as in force at the time of the issue of any such direction`
  line `shall continue to be in force until the completion of the special revision so directed.`
  line
  line `Explanation:—In this section, the expression "qualifying date" means such date as the ^1[Election`
  line `Commission] may, by order, specify in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_e_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 12, for "Central Government" (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 12, ibid. for "a parliamentary constituency" (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_7_f:
  sectionId (27125)
  sectionNo 7F
  orderNo 15
  title `Correction of entries in electoral roll.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_f_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 13, ibid. for "Director of Municipal Elections" (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27125&sectionno=7F&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_7_f_content:
  string
  line `If the electoral registration officer, on an application`
  line `made to him or on his own motion, is satisfied after such inquiry as he thinks fit, that any entry in the`
  line `electoral roll for any ward—`
  line
  line `(a) is erroneous or defective in any particular; or`
  line
  line `(b) should be transposed to another place in the roll on the ground that the person concerned has`
  line `changed his place of ordinary residence within such ward; or`
  line
  line `(c) should be deleted on the ground that the person concerned is dead or has ceased to be`
  line `ordinarily resident within such ward or is otherwise not entitled to be registered in that the electoral`
  line `registration officer shall, subject to such general or special directions, if any, as may be given by the`
  line `^1[Election Commission] in this behalf, amend, transpose or delete the entry:`
  line
  line `Provided that before taking any action on the ground specified in clause (a) or clause (b) or any action`
  line `under clause (c) on the ground that the person concerned has ceased to be ordinarily resident within such`
  line `ward or that he is otherwise not entitled to be registered in the electoral roll of such ward, the electoral`
  line `registration officer shall give the person concerned a reasonable opportunity of being heard in respect of`
  line `the action proposed to be taken in relation to him.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_g:
  sectionId (27126)
  sectionNo 7G
  orderNo 16
  title `Inclusion of names in electoral roll.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_g_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_g_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27126&sectionno=7G&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_7_g_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person whose name is not included in the`
  line `electoral roll of a ward may apply to the electoral registration officer for the inclusion of his name in that`
  line roll.
  line
  line `(2) The electoral registration officer shall, if satisfied that the applicant is entitled to be registered in`
  line `the electoral roll, direct his name to be included therein:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the applicant is registered in the electoral roll of any other ward, the electoral`
  line `registration officer shall inform the electoral registration officer of that other ward and that Officer shall,`
  line `on receipt of the information, strike off the applicant's name from that roll.`
  line
  line `(3) No amendment, transposition or deletion of any entry shall be made under section 7F and no`
  line `direction for the inclusion of a name in the electoral roll of a ward shall be given under this section after`
  line `the last date for making nominations for an election in that ward and before the completion of that`
  line election.
obj_root_law_sections_7_g_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7_h:
  sectionId (27127)
  sectionNo 7H
  orderNo 17
  title Appeal.
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_h_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 14, for "Director of Municipal Elections" (w.e.f. 1-10-1993`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27127&sectionno=7H&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_7_h_content:
  string
  line `An appeal shall lie within such time and in such manner as may be prescribed by rules`
  line `to the ^1[Election Commission] from any order of the electoral registration officer under section 7F or`
  line `section 7G.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_i:
  sectionId (27128)
  sectionNo 7-I
  orderNo 18
  title `Jurisdiction of civil courts barred.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_i_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 15, ibid. for "Director of Municipal Elections" (w.e.f. 1-10-1993`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27128&sectionno=7-I&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_7_i_content:
  string
  line `No civil court shall have jurisdiction—`
  line
  line `(a) to entertain or adjudicate upon any question whether any person is or is not entitled to be`
  line `registered in an electoral roll for a ward; or`
  line
  line `(b) to question the legality of any action taken by or under the authority of an electoral`
  line `registration officer or of any decision given by the ^1[Election Commission].]`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (27129)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 19
  title `Qualifications for councillorship.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27129&sectionno=8&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `A person shall not be qualified to be chosen as a councillor`
  line `^1[unless he has attained the age of twenty-one years and his name] is registered as an elector in the`
  line `electoral roll for a ward:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of a seat reserved for the Scheduled Castes, a person shall not be so qualified`
  line `unless he is also a member of any of the said castes:`
  line
  line `^2[Provided further that in the case of a seat reserved for woman, no person other than a woman shall`
  line `be qualified to be chosen as a councillor.]`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 16, ibid. for "unless his name" (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `2. The proviso ins. by s. 16, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (27130)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 20
  title `Disqualifications for membership of Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27130&sectionno=9&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person shall be disqualified for being chosen as, and for being, a councillor, ^1***`
  line
  line `(a) if he is of unsound mind and stands so declared by a competent court;`
  line
  line `(b) if he is an undischarged insolvent;`
  line
  line `(c) if he is not a citizen of India, or has voluntarily acquired the citizenship of a foreign State, or is under any acknowledgment of allegiance or adherence to a foreign State;`
  line
  line `^2[(d) if he is so disqualified by or under any law for the time being in force for the purposes of elections to the Legislative Assembly of the National Capital Territory of Delhi;`
  line
  line `(e) if he is so disqualified by or under any law made by the Legislative Assembly of the National Capital Territory of Delhi;]`
  line
  line `(f) if he holds any office of profit under ^3[^4[the Corporation]];`
  line
  line `(g) if he holds any office of profit under the Government ^5[or Central Government];`
  line
  line `(h) if he is a licensed architect, draughtsman, engineer, plumber, surveyor or town planner or is a partner of a firm of which any such licensed person is also a partner;`
  line
  line `(i) if he is interested in any subsisting contract made with, or any work being done for, ^3[^4[the Corporation]] except as a shareholder (other than a director) in an incorporated company or as a member of a cooperative society;`
  line
  line `(j) if he is retained or employed in any professional capacity either personally or in the name of a firm of which he is a partner or with which he is engaged in a professional capacity, in connection with any cause or proceeding in which ^3[^4[the Corporation]] or any of the municipal authorities is interested or concerned;`
  line
  line `(k) if he, having held any office under the Government, ^3[^4[the Corporation]] or any other authority, has been dismissed for corruption or disloyalty to the State unless a period of four years has elapsed since his dismissal or the disqualification has been removed by the ^6[Election Commission];`
  line
  line `(l) if he fails to pay any arrears of any kind due by him, otherwise than as an agent, receiver, trustee or an executor, to ^3[^4[the Corporation]] within three months after a notice in this behalf has been served upon him.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1)`
  line
  line `^7* * * * *`
  line
  line `(b) a person shall not be deemed to have incurred any disqualification under clause (f) or clause (g) of that sub-section by reason only of his receiving`
  line
  line `(i) any pension; or`
  line
  line `(ii) any allowance or facility for serving as the Mayor or Deputy Mayor or as a councillor ^1***; or`
  line
  line `^8[(iii) any fee for attendance at meetings of any committee of ^3[^4[the Corporation]];]`
  line
  line `(c) a person shall not be deemed to have any interest in a contract or works such as is referred to in clause (i) of that sub-section by reason only of his having a share or interest in`
  line
  line `(i) any lease, sale, exchange or purchase of immovable property or any agreement for the same; or`
  line
  line `(ii) any agreement for the loan of money or any security for the payment of money only; or`
  line
  line `(iii) any newspaper in which any advertisement relating to the affairs of the Corporation is inserted; or`
  line
  line `(iv) the sale ^3[^4[the Corporation]] or to any municipal authority or any officer or other employee of ^3[^4[the Corporation]]on behalf of ^3[^4[the Corporation]], of any article in which he regularly trades or the purchase from ^3[^4[the Corporation]]or from any such authority, officer or other employee on behalf of ^3[^4[the Corporation]], of any article of a value in either case not exceeding five thousand rupees in the aggregate in any year during the period of the contract or work; or`
  line
  line `(v) the letting out on hire to ^3[^4[the Corporation]] or the hiring from ^3[^4[the Corporation]] of any article of a value not exceeding two thousand rupees in the aggregate in any year during the period of the contract or work; or`
  line
  line `^9[(vi) any agreement or contract with ^3[^4[the Corporation]] or any municipal authority for any goods or services which ^3[^4[the Corporation]] may generally supply.]`
  line
  line `(3) If a person sits or votes as a member of ^3[^4[the Corporation ]] when he knows that he is not qualified or that he is disqualified for such membership, he shall be liable in respect of each day on which he so sits or votes to a penalty of three hundred rupees to be recovered as an arrear of tax under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "or an alderman" omitted by Act 67 of 1993, s. 17 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 17, ibid., for clauses (d) and (e) (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `3.Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "a Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 17 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 17, ibid., for "Central Government" (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `7. Omitted by Act 67 of 1993, s. 17 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by s. 17, ibid., for sub-clause (iii) (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 17, for sub-clause (vi) (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (27131)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 21
  title `Right to vote.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes `1. Omitted by Act 42 of 1961, s. 4 (w.e.f. 12-9-1961).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27131&sectionno=10&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person whose name is, for the time being, entered in the electoral roll`
  line `for a ward shall be entitled to vote at the election of a councillor from that ward.`
  line
  line `^1* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (27132)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 22
  title `General elections of councillors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27132&sectionno=11&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) A general election of councillors shall be held for the`
  line `purpose of constituting ^1[^2[the Corporation]] under section 3.`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
  line
  line `(3) For the aforesaid purposes the ^4[Election Commission] shall, by one or more notifications`
  line `published in the Official Gazette; call upon all the wards to elect councillors in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of this Act and the rules and orders made thereunder before such date or dates as may be`
  line `specified in the notification or notifications:`
  line
  line `Provided that where in any ward a seat has been reserved for the Scheduled Castes, such notification`
  line `or notifications shall specify that the person to fill that seat shall belong to one of the said castes:`
  line
  line `^5[Provided further that where in any ward a seat has been reserved for woman, such notification or`
  line `notifications shall specify that the person to fill that seat shall be a woman.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for "a Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2.Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Omitted by Act 67 of 1993, s. 18 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 18, for "Director of Municipal Elections" (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by s. 18 ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (27133)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 23
  title `Filling of casual vacancies in councillorship.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27133&sectionno=12&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a casual vacancy occurs in the office`
  line `of a councillor the ^1[Election Commission] shall, soon as may be after the occurrence of such vacancy and`
  line `subject to the provisions of sub-section (2), by a notification in the Official Gazette, call upon the ward`
  line `concerned to elect a person for the purpose of filling the vacancy in accordance with the provisions of this`
  line `Act and the rules and orders made thereunder before such date as may be specified in the notification:`
  line
  line `Provided that no election shall be held to fill a casual vacancy occurring within ^2[six months] prior to`
  line `the holding of a general election under section 11.`
  line
  line `(2) If the vacancy be a vacancy in a seat reserved for the Scheduled Castes the notification issued`
  line `under sub-section (1) shall specify that the person to fill that seat shall belong to one of the Scheduled`
  line Castes.
  line
  line `^3[(3) If the vacancy be a vacancy in a seat reserved for women the notification issued under subsection`
  line `(1) shall specify that the person to fill that seat shall be a woman.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 19, ibid., for "Director of Municipal Elections" (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 19, ibid., for "four months" (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 19, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (27134)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 24
  title [Omitted.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27134&sectionno=13&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `[Election of aldermen].—Omitted by the Delhi Municipal Corporation Amendment`
  line `Act 1993 (67 of 1993), s. 20 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (27135)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 25
  title `Publication of result of election.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 21, ibid., for section 14 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27135&sectionno=14&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `^1[14. Publication of result of election.—The names of all persons elected as councillors shall, as far`
  line `as may be, after each election, be published by the Election Commission simultaneously in the Official`
  line Gazette.]
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (27136)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 26
  title `Election petitions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27136&sectionno=15&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) No election of a councillor ^1*** shall be called in question except by an`
  line `election petition presented to the court of the district judge of Delhi within fifteen days from the date of`
  line `the publication of the result of the election under section 14.`
  line
  line `^2[(2) An election petition calling in question any such election may be presented under any of the`
  line `grounds specified in section 17 by any candidate at such election, by any elector of the ward concerned or`
  line `by any councillor.]`
  line
  line `(3) A petitioner shall join as respondents to his petition all the candidates at the election.`
  line
  line `(4) An election petition—`
  line
  line `(a) shall contain a concise statement of the material facts on which the petitioner relies;`
  line
  line `(b) shall, with sufficient particulars, set forth the ground or grounds on which the election is`
  line `called in question; and`
  line
  line `(c) shall be signed by the petitioner and verified in the manner laid down in the Code of Civil`
  line `Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) for the verification of pleadings.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "or an alderman" omitted by s. 22, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 22, ibid., for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (27137)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 27
  title `Relief that may be claimed by the petitioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27137&sectionno=16&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) A petitioner may claim—`
  line
  line `(a) a declaration that the election of all or any of the returned candidates is void, and`
  line
  line `(b) in addition thereto, a further declaration that he himself or any other candidate has been duly`
  line elected.
  line
  line `(2) The expression "returned candidate" means a candidate whose name has been published in the`
  line `Official Gazette under section 14.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (27138)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 28
  title `Grounds for declaring elections to be void.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes `1. The words "or, as the case may be, as an alderman" omitted by Act 67 of 1993, s. 23 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27138&sectionno=17&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (2) if`
  line `the court of the district judge is of opinion--`
  line
  line `(a) that on the date of his election a returned candidate was not qualified or was disqualified, to`
  line `be chosen as a councillor ^1*** under this Act, or`
  line
  line `(b) that any corrupt practice has been committed by a returned candidate or his agent or by any`
  line `other person with the consent of a returned candidate or his agent, or`
  line
  line `(c) that any nomination paper has been improperly rejected, or`
  line
  line `(d) that the result of the election, in so far as it concerns a returned candidate, has been materially`
  line affected--
  line
  line `(i) by the improper acceptance of any nomination, or`
  line
  line `(ii) by any corrupt practice committed in the interests of the returned candidate by a person`
  line `other than that candidate or his agent or a person acting with the consent of such candidate or`
  line `agent, or`
  line
  line `(iii) by the improper acceptance or refusal of any vote or reception of any vote which is`
  line `void, or`
  line
  line `(iv) by the non-compliance with the provisions of this Act or of any rules or orders made`
  line thereunder,
  line
  line `the court shall declare the election of the returned candidate to be void.`
  line
  line `(2) If in the opinion of the court, a returned candidate has been guilty by an agent of any corrupt`
  line `practice, but the court is satisfied`
  line
  line `(a) that no such corrupt practice was committed at the election by the candidate, and every such`
  line `corrupt practice was committed contrary to the orders, and without the consent of the candidate;`
  line
  line `(b) that the candidate took all reasonable means for preventing the commission of corrupt`
  line `practices at the election; and`
  line
  line `(c) that in all other respects the election was free from any corrupt practice on the part of the`
  line `candidate or any of his agents;`
  line
  line `then the court may decide that the election of the returned candidate is not void.`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (27139)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 29
  title `Procedure to be followed by the district judge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27139&sectionno=18&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `The procedure provided in the Code of Civil`
  line `Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), in regard to suits shall be followed by the court of the district judge as far as`
  line `it can be made applicable, in the trial and disposal of an election petition under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (27140)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 30
  title `Decision of the district judge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27140&sectionno=19&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) At the conclusion of the trial of an election petition, the`
  line `court of the district judge shall make an order—`
  line
  line `(a) dismissing the election petition; or`
  line
  line `(b) declaring the election of all or any of the returned candidates to be void; or`
  line
  line `(c) declaring the election of all or any of the returned candidates to be void and the petitioner and`
  line `any other candidates to have been duly elected.`
  line
  line `(2) If any person who has filed an election petition has, in addition to calling in question the election`
  line `of the returned candidate, claimed declaration that he himself or any other candidate has been duly elected`
  line `and the court of the district judge is of opinion—`
  line
  line `(a) that in fact the petitioner or such other candidate received a majority of the valid votes, or`
  line
  line `(b) that but for the votes obtained by the returned candidate the petitioner or such other candidate`
  line `would have obtained a majority of the valid votes,`
  line
  line `the court shall, after declaring the election of the returned candidate to be void, declare the petitioner or`
  line `such other candidate, as the case may be, to have been duly elected.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (27141)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 31
  title `Procedure in case of equality of votes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27141&sectionno=20&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `If during the trial of an election petition it appears that`
  line `there is an equality of votes between any candidates at the election and that the addition of a vote would`
  line `entitle any of those candidates to be declared elected, then, the court of the district judge shall decide`
  line `between them by lot and proceed as if the one on whom the lot falls had received an additional vote.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (27142)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 32
  title `Finality of decisions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes `1. The words "or an alderman" omitted by Act 67 of 1993, s. 24 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27142&sectionno=21&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) An order of the court of the district judge on an election petition shall`
  line `be final and conclusive.`
  line
  line `(2) An election of a councillor ^1*** not called in question in accordance with the foregoing provisions`
  line `shall be deemed to be a good and valid election.`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (27143)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 33
  title `Corrupt practices.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27143&sectionno=22&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `The following shall be deemed to be corrupt practices for the purposes of`
  line `this Act:—`
  line
  line `(1) Bribery as defined in clause (1) of section 123 of the Representation of the People`
  line `Act, 1951 (43 of 1951).`
  line
  line `(2) Undue influence as defined in clause (2) of the said section.`
  line
  line `(3) The systematic appeal by a candidate or his agent or by any other person, to vote or refrain`
  line `from voting on grounds of caste, race, community or religion or the use of or appeal to, religious`
  line `symbols or, the use of or appeal to, national symbols such as the national flag or the national emblem,`
  line `for the furtherance of the prospects of that candidate's election.`
  line
  line `(4) The publication by a candidate or his agent or by any other person of any statement of fact`
  line `which is false, and which he either believes to be false or does not believe to be true in relation to the`
  line `personal character or conduct of any candidate, or in relation to the candidature, or withdrawal from`
  line `contest of any candidate being a statement reasonably calculated to prejudice the prospects of that`
  line `candidate's election.`
  line
  line `(5) The hiring or procuring whether on payment or otherwise of any vehicle or vessel by a`
  line `candidate or his agent or by any other person for the conveyance of any elector (other than the`
  line `candidate himself, and the members of his family or his agent) to or from any polling station provided`
  line `in accordance with the rules made under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that the hiring of a vehicle or vessel by an elector or by several electors at their joint`
  line `costs for the purpose of conveying him or them to or from any such polling station shall not be`
  line `deemed to be a corrupt practice under this clause if the vehicle or vessel so hired is a vehicle or vessel`
  line `not propelled by mechanical power:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the use of any public transport vehicle or vessel or any tram car or railway`
  line `carriage by an elector at his own cost for the purpose of going to or coming from any such polling`
  line `station shall not be deemed to be a corrupt practice under this clause.`
  line
  line `Explanation—In this clause the expression "vehicle" means any vehicle used or capable of being`
  line `used for the purpose of road transport whether propelled by mechanical power or otherwise and`
  line `whether used for drawing other vehicles or otherwise.`
  line
  line `6) The holding of any meeting in which intoxicating liquors are served.`
  line
  line `(7) The issuing of any circular, placard or poster having a reference to the election which does not`
  line `bear the name and address of the printer and publisher thereof.`
  line
  line `(8) Any other practice which the Central Government may by rules specify to be a corrupt`
  line practice.
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (27144)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 34
  title `Maintenance of secrecy of voting.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27144&sectionno=23&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every officer or clerk, agent or other person who`
  line `performs any duty in connection with the recording or counting of votes at an election shall maintain and`
  line `aid in maintaining the secrecy of the voting and shall not (except for some purpose authorised by or under`
  line `any law) communicate to any person any information calculated to violate such secrecy.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person who contravenes the provisions of sub-section (1) shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to three months or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (27145)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 35
  title `Officers, etc., at elections not to act for candidates or to influence voting.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27145&sectionno=24&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person who`
  line `is a returning officer, or an assistant returning officer or a presiding officer or polling officer at an`
  line `election, or an officer or clerk appointed by the returning officer or the presiding officer to perform any`
  line `duty in connection with an election or a member of a police force shall in the conduct or management of`
  line `the election do any act (other than the giving of votes) for the furtherance of the prospects of the election`
  line `of a candidate.`
  line
  line `(2) No such person as aforesaid shall endeavour—`
  line
  line `(a) to persuade any person to give his vote at an election; or`
  line
  line `(b) to dissuade any person from giving his vote at an election; or`
  line
  line `(c) to influence the voting of any person at an election in any manner.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person who contravenes the provisions of sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) shall be`
  line `punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (27146)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 36
  title `Prohibition of canvassing in or near polling station and of public meeting on election day.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27146&sectionno=25&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall, on the date or dates on which the poll is taken at any polling station, commit`
  line `any of the following acts within the polling station or in any public or private place within a distance of`
  line `one hundred yards of the polling station, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) canvassing for votes; or`
  line
  line `(b) soliciting the vote of any elector; or`
  line
  line `(c) persuading any elector not to vote for any particular candidate; or`
  line
  line `(d) persuading any elector not to vote at the election; or`
  line
  line `(e) exhibiting any notice or sign (other than an official notice) relating to the election.`
  line
  line `(2) No person shall convene, hold or attend any public meeting within any ward on the date or dates`
  line `on which a poll is taken for an election in that ward.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person who contravenes the provisions of sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) shall be`
  line `punishable with fine which may extend to two hundred and fifty rupees.`
  line
  line `(4) An offence punishable under this section shall be cognizable.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (27147)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 37
  title `Penalty for disorderly conduct in or near polling station.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27147&sectionno=26&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall, on the date or`
  line `dates on which a poll is taken at any polling station—`
  line
  line `(a) use or operate within or at the entrance of the polling station or in any public or private place`
  line `in the neighbourhood thereof any apparatus for amplifying or reproducing the human voice, such as a`
  line `megaphone or a loud-speaker; or`
  line
  line `(b) shout or otherwise act in a disorderly manner, within or at the entrance of the polling station`
  line `or in any public or private place in the neighbourhood thereof;`
  line
  line `so as to cause annoyance to any person visiting the polling station for the poll, or so as to interfere with`
  line `the work of the officer and other persons on duty at the polling station.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person who contravenes or wilfully aids or abets the contravention of the provisions of subsection (1), shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three months, or with`
  line `fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `(3) If the presiding officer of a polling station has reason to believe that any person is committing or`
  line `has committed an offence punishable under this section, he may direct any police officer to arrest such`
  line `person, and thereupon the police officer shall arrest him.`
  line
  line `(4) Any police officer may take such step and use such force, as may be reasonably necessary for`
  line `preventing any contravention of the provisions of sub-section (1), and may seize any apparatus used for`
  line `such contravention.`
  line
  line `(5) An offence punishable under this section shall be cognizable,`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (27148)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 38
  title `Penalty for misconduct at the polling station.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27148&sectionno=27&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person who during the hours fixed for`
  line `the poll at any polling station, misconducts himself or fails to obey the lawful directions of the presiding`
  line `officer, may be removed from the polling station by the presiding officer or by any police officer on duty`
  line `or by any person authorised in this behalf by such presiding officer.`
  line
  line `(2) The powers conferred by sub-section (1) shall not be exercised so as to prevent any elector who is`
  line `otherwise entitled to vote at a polling station from having an opportunity of voting at that station.`
  line
  line `(3) If any person who has been so removed from a polling station, re-enters the polling station`
  line `without the permission of the presiding officer, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend to three months, or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `(4) An offence punishable under sub-section (3) shall be cognizable.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (27149)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 39
  title `Breaches of official duty in connection with election.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27149&sectionno=28&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any person to whom this section`
  line `applies, is without reasonable cause guilty of any act or omission in breach of his official duty, he shall be`
  line `punishable with fine which may extend to five hundred rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) No suit or other legal proceeding shall lie against any such person for damages in respect of any`
  line `such act or omission as aforesaid.`
  line
  line `(3) The persons to whom this section applies are returning officers, assistant returning officers,`
  line `presiding officers, polling officers and any other person appointed to perform any duty in connection with`
  line `the election; and the expression official duty shall for the purposes of this section be construed`
  line accordingly.
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (27150)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 40
  title `Removal of ballot papers or ballot boxes or the voting machines from polling station to be an offence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27150&sectionno=29&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person who at an`
  line `election fraudulently takes or attempts to take a ballot paper out of a polling station, or wilfully aids or`
  line `abets the doing of any such act, shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to`
  line `one year, or with fine which may extend to five hundred rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `(2) If the presiding officer of a polling station has reason to believe that any person is committing or`
  line `has committed an offence punishable under sub-section (1), such officer may, before such person leaves`
  line `the polling station, arrest or direct a police officer to arrest such person and may search such person or`
  line `cause him to be searched by a police officer:`
  line
  line `Provided that when it is necessary to cause a women to be searched, the search shall be made by`
  line `another woman with strict regard to decency.`
  line
  line `(3) Any ballot paper found upon the person arrested on search1`
  line `or a ballot box or a voting machine or`
  line `part thereof found being carried away by a person outside the polling station shall be made over for safe`
  line `custody to a police officer by the presiding officer or when the search is made by a police officer, shall be`
  line `kept by such officer in safe custody.`
  line
  line `(4) An offence punishable under sub-section (1) shall be cognizable.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29_a:
  sectionId (67064)
  sectionNo 29A
  orderNo 41
  title `Prohibition of going armed to or near a polling station.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Delhi Act 10 of 2002, s. 3 (w.e.f. 18-2-2002).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=67064&sectionno=29A&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_29_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[29A. Prohibition of going armed to or near a polling station.-- (1) No person, other than the returning officer, the presiding officer, any police officer and any other person appointed to maintain peace and order at a polling station who is on duty at the polling station, shall, on a polling day, go armed with arms, as defined in the Arms Act, 1959 (54 of 1959), of any kind within the neighbourhood of a polling station.`
  line
  line `(2) If any person contravenes the provisions of sub-section (1), he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Arms Act, 1959 (54 of 1959), where a person is convicted of an offence, under this section, the arms as defined in the said Act found in his possession shall be liable to confiscation and the licence granted in relation to such arms shall be deemed to have revoked under section 17 of that Act. (4) An offence punishable under sub-section (2) shall be cognizable.]`
obj_root_law_sections_29_b:
  sectionId (67065)
  sectionNo 29B
  orderNo 42
  title `Offence of booth capturing.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Delhi Act 10 of 2002, s. 3 (w.e.f. 18-2-2002).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=67065&sectionno=29B&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_29_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[Whoever commits an offence of booth capturing shall be punishable with imprisonment for a terms which shall not be less than one year but which may extend to three years and with fine, and where such offence is committed by a person in the service of the Government, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than three years but which may extend to five years and with fine.`
  line
  line `Explanation:For the purposes of this section booth capturing includes, among other things, all or any of the following activities, namely :`
  line
  line `(a) Seizure of a polling station or a place fixed for the poll by any person or persons making polling authorities surrender the ballot papers, used ballot box or boxes or voting machines use and doing of any other act which affects the orderly conduct of elections;`
  line
  line `(b) taking possession of a polling station or a place fixed for the poll by, any person or persons and allowing only his or their own supporters to exercise their right to vote and prevent others from free exercise of their right to vote;`
  line
  line `(c) coercing or intimidating or threatening directly or indirectly any elector and preventing him from going to the polling station or a place fixed for the poll to cast his vote;`
  line
  line `(d) seizure of place for counting of votes by any person or persons making the counting authorities surrender the ballot papers or voting machines and the doing of anything which affects the orderly counting of votes;`
  line
  line `(e) doing by any person in the service of Government of all or any of the aforesaid activities or aiding or conniving at, any such activity in the furtherance of the prospects of the election of a candidate.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_c:
  sectionId (67066)
  sectionNo 29C
  orderNo 43
  title `Liquor not to be sold, given or distributed on polling day`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Delhi Act 10 of 2002, s. 3 (w.e.f. 18-2-2002).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=67066&sectionno=29C&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_29_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) No spirituous, fermented or intoxicating liquors or other substances of a like nature shall be sold, given or distributed at a hotel, eating house, lavern, shop or any other place, public or private, within a polling area during the period of forty-eight hours ending with the hour fixed for the conclusion of the poll for any election in that polling area.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person who contravenes the provisions of sub-section (1) shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term, which may extend to six months or with fine which may extend to two thousand rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a person, is convicted of an offence under this section, the spirituous, fermented or intoxication liquors or other substances of a like nature found in his possession shall be liable to confiscation and the same shall be disposed of in such manner as may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (27151)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 44
  title `Other offences and penalties therefor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 25, for "Director of Municipal Elections" (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27151&sectionno=30&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person shall be guilty of an electoral offence if at`
  line `any election he—`
  line
  line `(a) fraudulently defaces or destroys any nomination paper; or`
  line
  line `(b) fraudulently defaces, destroys or removes any list, notice or other document affixed by or`
  line `under the authority of the returning officer; or`
  line
  line `(c) fraudulently defaces or destroys any ballot paper or the official mark on any ballot paper; or`
  line
  line `(d) without due authority supplies any ballot paper to any person or receives any ballot paper`
  line `from any person or is in possession of any ballot paper; or`
  line
  line `(e) fraudulently puts into any ballot box anything other than the ballot paper which he is`
  line `authorised by law to put in; or`
  line
  line `(f) without due authority destroys, takes, opens or otherwise interferes with any ballot box or`
  line `ballot paper then in use for the purposes of the election; or`
  line
  line `(g) fraudulently or without due authority, as the case may be, attempts to do any of the foregoing`
  line `acts or wilfully aids or abets the doing of any such acts.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person guilty of an offence under this section shall—`
  line
  line `(a) if he is a returning officer or an assistant returning officer or a presiding officer or a polling`
  line `officer or any other officer or clerk employed on official duty in connection with the election, be`
  line `punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years, or with fine, or with both;`
  line
  line `(b) if he is any other person, be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six`
  line `months, or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purposes of this section, a person shall be deemed to be on official duty if his duty is to`
  line `take part in the conduct of any election or part of an election including the counting of votes or to be`
  line `responsible after an election for the used ballot papers and other documents in connection with such`
  line election.
  line
  line `(4) An offence punishable under clause (b) of sub-section (2) shall be cognizable.`
  line
  line `(5) No court shall take cognizance of any offence under section 24, or under section 28, or under`
  line `clause (a) of sub-section (2) of this section unless there is a complaint made by order of, or under`
  line `authority from, the ^1[Election Commission].`
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (27152)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 45
  title `Power to make rules regulating the election of councillors and aldermen.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27152&sectionno=31&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central`
  line `Government may make rules to provide for or regulate all or any of the following matters ^1[for the`
  line `purpose of preparation, revision, and maintenance of electoral rolls of wards and holding elections] of`
  line `councillors ^2*** under this Act, namely:--`
  line
  line `^3[(a) the particulars to be entered in the electoral rolls;`
  line
  line `(aa) the preliminary publication of electoral rolls;`
  line
  line `(ab) the manner in which and the time within which claims and objections as to entries in`
  line `electoral rolls may be preferred;`
  line
  line `(ac) the manner in which notices of claims or objections shall be published;`
  line
  line `(ad) the place, date and time at which claims or objections shall be heard and the manner in`
  line `which claims or objections shall be heard and disposed of;`
  line
  line `(ae) the final publication of electoral rolls;`
  line
  line `(af) the revision and correction of electoral rolls and inclusion of names therein;`
  line
  line `(ag) the manner in which and the purpose for which the electoral roll of ^4[an assembly`
  line `constituency] may be used;`
  line
  line `(ah) the correction of electoral rolls on change of extent or boundaries of wards;]`
  line
  line `(b) the appointment of returning officers, assistant returning officers, presiding officers and`
  line `polling officers for the conduct of elections;`
  line
  line `(c) the nomination of candidates, form of nomination papers, objections to nomination and`
  line `scrutiny of nominations;`
  line
  line `(d) the deposits to be made by candidates, time and manner of making such deposits and the`
  line `circumstances under which such deposits may be returned to candidates or forfeited to ^5[^6[the Corporation]];`
  line
  line `(e) the withdrawal of candidatures;`
  line
  line `(f) the appointment of agents of candidates;`
  line
  line `(g) the procedure in contested and uncontested elections and the special procedure at elections in`
  line `wards where any seat is reserved for the Scheduled Castes ^8[and women];`
  line
  line `(h) the date, time and place for poll and other matters relating to the conduct of elections`
  line including--
  line
  line `(i) the appointment of polling stations for each ward,`
  line
  line `(ii) the hours during which the polling station shall be kept open for the casting of votes,`
  line
  line `(iii) the printing and issue of ballot papers,`
  line
  line `(iv) the checking of voters by reference to the electoral roll,`
  line
  line `(v) the marking with indelible ink of the left forefinger or any other finger or limb of the voter`
  line `and prohibition of the delivery of any ballot paper to any person if at the time such person applies`
  line `for such paper he has already such mark so as to prevent personation of voters,`
  line
  line `(vi) the manner in which votes are to be given and in particular in the case of illiterate voters`
  line `or of voters under physical or other disability,`
  line
  line `(vii) the procedure to be followed in respect of challenged votes and tendered votes,`
  line
  line `(viii) the scrutiny of votes, counting of votes, the declaration of the results and the procedure`
  line `in case of equality of votes or in the event of a councillor being elected to represent more than`
  line `one ward,`
  line
  line `(ix) the custody and disposal of papers relating to elections,`
  line
  line `(x) the suspension of polls in case of any interruption by riot, violence or any other sufficient`
  line `cause and the holding of a fresh poll,`
  line
  line `(xi) the holding of a fresh poll in the case of destruction of or tampering with ballot boxes`
  line `before the count,`
  line
  line `(xii) the countermanding of the poll in the case of the death of a candidate before the poll;`
  line
  line `^9[(hh) the requisitioning of premises, vehicles, vessels or animals, payment of compensation in`
  line `connection with such requisitioning, eviction from requisitioned premises and release of premises`
  line `from requisition;]`
  line
  line `^10* * * * *`
  line
  line `(j) the fee to be paid on an election petition;`
  line
  line `(k) any other matter ^11[relating to electoral rolls or elections] or election disputes in respect of`
  line `which the Central Government deems it necessary to make rules under this section or in respect of`
  line `which this Act makes no provision or makes insufficient provision and provision is, in the opinion of`
  line `the Central Government necessary.`
  line
  line `(2) In making any rule under this section the Central Government may provide that any contravention`
  line `thereof shall be punishable with fine which may extend to one hundred rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 55 of 1974, s. 7, for "for the purpose of holding elections" (w.e.f. 10-1-1975).`
  line
  line `2. The words "and alderman" omitted by Act 67 of 1993, s. 26 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 55 of 1974, s. 7, for clause (a) (w.e.f. 10-1-1975).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 26, for “a parliamentary constituency” (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for "the Corporation"(w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "a Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 26, for "a parliamentary constituency" (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `8. Ins. by s. 26, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `9. Ins. by Act 42 of 1961, s. 5 (w.e.f. 12-9-1961).`
  line
  line `10. Omitted by Act 67 of 1993, s. 26 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `11. Subs. by Act 55 of 1974, s. 7, for "relating to elections" (w.e.f. 10-1-1975).`
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (27153)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 46
  title `Oath or affirmation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27153&sectionno=32&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `^1[32. Oath or affirmation.--(1) Every councillor and every person nominated under sub-clause (i) of`
  line `clause (b) of sub-section (3) of section 3, before taking his seat, make and subscribe at a meeting of ^2[^3the Corporation]] an oath or affirmation according to the following form, namely:--`
  line
  line `I, A. B. having been`
  line `nominated under sub-clause (i) of clause (b) of`
  line `nominated under sub-clause (i) of clause (b) of sub-section (3) of section 3 as representative in`
  line `the Municipal Corporation of Delhi, do swear in the name of God that I will bear true faith and allegiance to the solemnly affirm Constitution of India as by law established and I will faithfully discharge the duty upon which I am about to enter.`
  line
  line `(2) If a person sits or votes as a councillor or sits as a representative before he has complied with the`
  line `requirements of sub-section (1) he shall be liable in respect of each day on which he sits or votes as the`
  line `case may be, to a penalty of three hundred rupees to be recovered as arrears of tax under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 27, for section 32 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "a Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_32_a:
  sectionId (27154)
  sectionNo 32A
  orderNo 47
  title `Declaration of assets.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27154&sectionno=32A&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_32_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[32A. Declaration of assets.--(1) Every councillor shall, not later than thirty days after making and`
  line `subscribing the oath or affirmation under sub-section (1) of section 32 and before the last day of the same`
  line `month in each succeeding year, file with the Mayor a declaration in such form as may be prescribed by`
  line `rules by the ^2[^3[Central Government]], of all the assets owned by him and members of his family and. such declaration shall form part of the records of ^4[^5[the Corporation]].`
  line
  line `Explanation--For the purposes of this sub-section, family means the spouse and dependant children of the councillor.`
  line
  line `(2) A person shall be disqualified for being a councillor---`
  line
  line `(a) if he fails to file a declaration referred to in sub-section (1); or`
  line
  line `(b) if he files a declaration under that sub-section which is either false or which he knows or`
  line `believes to be false.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 28 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for "Central Government" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "Government"(w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `4.Subs. by Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "a Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_32_b:
  sectionId (27155)
  sectionNo 32B
  orderNo 48
  title `Vacation of seats in case of multiple membership.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27155&sectionno=32B&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_32_b_content:
  string
  line `No councillor shall be a member both of`
  line `^1[^2[the Corporation]] and Parliament or the Legislative Assembly and if a person is so chosen, then at the`
  line `expiration of fourteen days from the date of the publication in the Gazette of India, or as the case may be,`
  line `in the Official Gazette, whichever is later that he has been so chosen, that person's seat in Parliament or`
  line `the Legislative Assembly shall become vacant unless he has previously resigned his seat in ^1[^2[the`
  line Corporation]].]
obj_root_law_sections_32_b_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (27156)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 49
  title `Vacation of seats.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27156&sectionno=33&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) If a councillor ^1***--`
  line
  line `(a) becomes subject to any of the disqualifications mentioned in ^2[section 9 or sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 32A or],`
  line
  line `(b) resigns his seat by writing under his hand addressed to the Mayor and delivered to the`
  line `Commissioner, his seat shall thereupon become vacant.`
  line
  line `(2) If during three successive months, a councillor ^3*** is, without permission of ^4[^5[the Corporation]],`
  line `absent from all the meetings thereof, the Corporation may declare his seat vacant.`
  line
  line `^6[(3) If any question arises as to whether a councillor ^3*** has become subject to any of the`
  line `disqualifications mentioned in section 9 or sub-section (2) of section 32A, the question shall be referred`
  line `for the decision of the Administrator and his decision shall be final.]`
  line
  line `^7[(4) Before giving any decision on any such question the Administrator shall obtain the opinion of`
  line `the Election Commission and shall act according to such opinion.]`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "or an alderman" omitted by Act 67 of 1993, s. 29 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 29, ibid., for section 9 or (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `3. The words "or an alderman omitted" by Act 67 of 1993, s. 29 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `5.Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "a Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 29, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by s. 29, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_33_a:
  sectionId (27157)
  sectionNo 33A
  orderNo 50
  title `Powers of Election Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 30 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27157&sectionno=33A&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_33_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[33A. Powers of Election Commission.--(1) Where in connection with the tendering of any`
  line `opinion to the Administrator under sub-section (4) of section 33, the Election Commission considers it`
  line `necessary or proper to make an inquiry, and the Commission is satisfied that on the basis of the affidavits`
  line `filed and the documents produced in such inquiry by the parties concerned of their own accord, it cannot`
  line `come to a decisive opinion on the matter which is being inquired into, the Commission shall have, for the`
  line `purposes of such inquiry, the powers of a civil court, while trying a suit under the Code of Civil`
  line `Procedure, 1908, (5 of 1908) in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of any document or other material object producible as`
  line evidence;
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) requisitioning any public record or a copy thereof from any court or office;`
  line
  line `(e) issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses or documents.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission shall also have the power to require any person, subject to any privilege which`
  line `may be claimed by that person under any law for the time being in force, to furnish information on such`
  line `points or matters as in the opinion of the Commission may be useful for, or relevant to, the subject-matter`
  line `of the inquiry.`
  line
  line `(3) The Commission shall be deemed to be a civil court and when any such offence, as is described in`
  line `section 175, section 178, section 179, section 180 or section 228 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860), is`
  line `committed in the view or presence of the Commission, the Commission may, after recording the facts`
  line `constituting the offence and the statement of the accused as provided for in the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), forward the case to a magistrate having jurisdiction to try the same and the`
  line `magistrate to whom any such case is forwarded shall proceed to hear the complaint against the accused as`
  line `if the case had been forwarded to him under section 346 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973.`
  line
  line `(4) Any proceeding before the Commission shall be deemed to be a judicial proceeding within the`
  line `meaning of section 193 and section 228 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_33_b:
  sectionId (27158)
  sectionNo 33B
  orderNo 51
  title `Statements made by persons to the Election Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 30, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27158&sectionno=33B&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_33_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[33B. Statements made by persons to the Election Commission.-- No statement made by a person`
  line `in the course of giving evidence before the Election Commission shall subject him to, or be used against`
  line `him in, any civil or criminal proceeding except a prosecution for giving false evidence by such statement:`
  line
  line `Provided that the statement--`
  line
  line `(a) is made in reply to a question which he is required by the Commission to answer; or`
  line
  line `(b) is relevant to the subject-matter of the inquiry.]`
obj_root_law_sections_33_c:
  sectionId (27159)
  sectionNo 33C
  orderNo 52
  title `Procedure to be followed by the Election Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 30, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27159&sectionno=33C&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_33_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[33C. Procedure to be followed by the Election Commission.-- The Election Commission shall`
  line `have the power to regulate its own procedure (including the fixing of places and times of its sittings and`
  line `deciding whether to sit in public or in private).]`
obj_root_law_sections_33_d:
  sectionId (27160)
  sectionNo 33D
  orderNo 53
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_d_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 30, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27160&sectionno=33D&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_33_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[33D. Protection of action taken in good faith.-- No suit, prosecution or other legal proceedings`
  line `shall lie against the Commission or any person acting under the direction of the Commission in respect of`
  line `anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done in pursuance of the foregoing provisions of`
  line `sections 33A to 33C or of any order made thereunder or in respect of the tendering of any opinion by the`
  line `Commission to the Administrator or in respect of the publication, by or under the authority of the`
  line `Commission of any such opinion, paper or proceedings.]`
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (27161)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 54
  title `Payment of allowances to councillors and aldermen.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 31, for "the councillors and the alderman" (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27161&sectionno=34&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `^1[The councillors and the persons`
  line `referred to in clause (b) of sub-section (3) of section 3] shall be entitled to receive allowances for`
  line `attendance at meetings of the Corporation and of any of its committees at such rate as may be determined`
  line `by rules made in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (27162)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 55
  title `Annual election of Mayor and Deputy Mayor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27162&sectionno=35&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1)^1[^2[The Corporation]] shall at its first meeting in`
  line `each year elect one of its members to be ^3[the Chairperson to be known as] the Mayor and another`
  line `member to be the Deputy Mayor of the Corporation:`
  line
  line `^4[Provided that during the duration of ^5[^6[the Corporation]] the office of the Mayor shall be reserved in`
  line `favour of a member who is a woman for the first year of ^5[^6[the Corporation]] and in favour of a member`
  line `belonging to a Scheduled Caste for the third year of ^5[^6[the Corporation]].]`
  line
  line `(2) On the occurrence of any vacancy in the office of the Mayor or the Deputy Mayor, ^5[^6[the`
  line `Corporation]] shall within one month of the occurrence of such vacancy elect one of its members as Mayor`
  line `or Deputy Mayor, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `^4[(3) If the vacancy be a casual vacancy in the office of the Mayor and is reserved for woman or for`
  line `Scheduled Castes, the vacancy shall be filled by electing one of the councillors from amongst women or a`
  line `member of the Scheduled Castes as the case may be.]`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for "The Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "A Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Added by Act 67 of 1993, s. 32 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by s. 32, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "a Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (27163)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 56
  title `Term of office of the Mayor and Deputy Mayor and facilities and privileges of the Mayor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27163&sectionno=36&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Mayor or the Deputy Mayor shall hold office from the time of his election until the`
  line `election of his successor in office, unless in the meantime he resigns his office as Mayor or Deputy Mayor`
  line `^1*** or unless in the case of the Deputy Mayor he is elected as Mayor.`
  line
  line `(2) The Mayor or the Deputy Mayor may be given such facilities in respect of residential`
  line `accommodation, conveyance and the like as may be determined in each case by rules made in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(3) The Mayor shall have full access to all the records of ^2[^3[the Corporation]] and may obtain reports--`
  line
  line `^4*** from the Commissioner on any matter connected with the municipal government of ^5[^6]Delhi]];`
  line
  line `^7* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "or his term of office as a member of the Corporation terminates in any manner" omitted by Act 67 of 1993, s. 33 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "a Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `4. The brackets and letter (a) omitted by Act 67 of 1993, s. 33 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 3, for “Delhi” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “the area of the Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022)`
  line `7. Omitted by Act 67 of 1993, s. 33 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (27164)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 57
  title `Discharge of functions of the Mayor by the Deputy Mayor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27164&sectionno=37&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) When the office of the`
  line `Mayor is vacant, the Deputy Mayor shall act as Mayor until a new Mayor is elected.`
  line
  line `(2) When the Mayor is absent from his duty on account of illness or any other cause, the powers,`
  line `duties and functions of the Mayor shall be exercised and performed by the Deputy Mayor.`
  line
  line `(3) The Mayor may by order in writing delegate any of his powers, duties and functions to the Deputy`
  line Mayor.
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (27165)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 58
  title `Resignation of Mayor and Deputy Mayor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 42 of 1961, s. 6, for Secretary (w.e.f. 12-9-1961).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27165&sectionno=38&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Mayor may, by writing under his hand`
  line `addressed to the Deputy Mayor and delivered to the ^1[Municipal Secretary], resign his office.`
  line
  line `(2) The Deputy Mayor may, by writing under his hand addressed to the Mayor and delivered to the`
  line `^1[Municipal Secretary], resign his office.`
  line
  line `(3) A resignation under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) shall take effect from the date on which it is`
  line delivered.
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (27166)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 59
  title `Rural Areas Committee and Education Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27166&sectionno=39&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) In addition to the Standing`
  line `Committee, ^1[and the Wards Committee] referred to in section 44, there shall be a Rural Areas Committee`
  line `and an Education Committee of ^2[^3[the Corporation]],`
  line
  line `(2) The Rural Areas Committee shall consist of all the councillors elected from the wards situated`
  line `within the rural areas.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall be the duty of the Rural Areas Committee---`
  line
  line `(a) to make recommendations to ^2[^3[the Corporation]]---br`
  line
  line `(i) in relation to the functions of ^2[^3[the Corporation]] which may be discharged within the rural`
  line `areas and questions of policy and schemes relating to the development of such areas;`
  line
  line `(ii) in relation to taxes which ^2[^3[the Corporation]] proposes to levy in the rural areas; and`
  line
  line `(iii) generally in relation to the expenditure that may be incurred by ^2[^3[the Corporation]] for the`
  line `municipal government in those areas;`
  line
  line `(b) to review the progress of work of ^2[^3[the Corporation]] in the rural areas;`
  line
  line `(c) to bring to the notice of the appropriate municipal authorities deficiencies in the rural areas`
  line `and make proposals to those authorities for the removal of such deficiencies;`
  line
  line `(d) to discharge such other functions in relation to the rural areas as may be assigned to it by`
  line `resolution made by ^2[^3[the Corporation]] or by regulations made under this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) ^4[^5[The Corporation]] or any of the municipal authorities specified in section 44 shall not take any`
  line `action, in relation to any of the matters specified in sub-clauses (i), (ii) and (iii) of clause (a) of`
  line `sub-section (3) except in consultation with the Rural Areas Committee.`
  line
  line `(5) The Education Committee shall consist of seven members of whom such number not exceeding`
  line `three as may be determined by ^2[^3[the Corporation]], shall be nominated by the Corporation, from among`
  line `experts in education who are not members of ^2[^3[the Corporation]] and the rest shall be elected by the members`
  line `of the corporation from among themselves at the first meeting of ^2[^3[the Corporation]] after each general`
  line `election or as soon as possible at any other meeting subsequent thereto.`
  line
  line `(6) The Education Committee shall exercise and perform such powers, duties and functions in`
  line `relation to education in ^6[the area of the corporation] as may be determined by regulations made in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(7) The Rural Areas Committee as well as the Education Committee shall at its first meeting in each`
  line `year elect one of its members ^7[who is a councillor to be the Chairman and another member to be the`
  line `Deputy Chairman].`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 34, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "a Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for "The Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "A Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `6. Subs by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for “Delhi” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by s. 34, ibid., for "to be the Chairman and another member to be the Deputy Chairman" (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (27167)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 60
  title `Special and adhoc committies and ward committees, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27167&sectionno=40&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `(1) ^1[^2[The Corporation]] may`
  line `constitute as many special and ad hoc committees as it thinks fit for the exercise of any power or`
  line `discharge of any function which ^3[^4[the Corporation]] may by resolution delegate to them or for inquiring into,`
  line `reporting or advising upon any matter which ^3[^4[the Corporation]] may refer to them.`
  line
  line `(2) Any such committee shall consist of members of ^3[^4[the Corporation]] only:`
  line
  line `Provided that an ad hoc committee may with the sanction of ^3[^4[the Corporation]] co-opt not more than`
  line `three persons who are not members of ^3[^4[the Corporation]] but who in the opinion of ^3[^4[the Corporation]] possess`
  line `special qualifications for serving on such committee.`
  line
  line `^5* * * * *`
  line
  line `(6) Each committee constituted under this section shall elect one of its members ^6[who is a councillor]`
  line `as the Chairman and another member as the Vice-Chairman.`
  line
  line `(7) Any matter relating to each of the committees constituted under section 39 or this section, not`
  line `expressly provided in this Act may be provided by regulations made in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for "The Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "A Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "a Corporation"(w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `5. Omitted by Act 67 of 1993, s. 35 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by s. 35, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (27168)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 61
  title `General powers of the Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27168&sectionno=41&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `41. General powers of ^1[^2[the Corporation]].--(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act and the rules,`
  line `regulations and bye-laws made thereunder the municipal government of ^3[^4[Delhi]] shall vest in ^1[^2[the`
  line Corporation]].
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the provisions of sub-section (1), it shall be the duty of ^1[^2[the`
  line `Corporation]] to consider all periodical statements of the receipts and disbursements and all progress`
  line `reports and pass such resolutions thereon as it thinks fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "a Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for "Delhi" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "the area of the Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (27169)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 62
  title `Obligatory functions of the Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27169&sectionno=42&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `Obligatory functions of ^1[^2[the Corporation]]--^3[Subject to the provisions of this Act and any other`
  line `law for the time being in force, it shall be incumbent] on ^1[^2[the Corporation]] to make adequate provision by`
  line `any means or measures which it may lawfully use or take, for each of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the construction, maintenance and cleansing of drains and drainage works and of public`
  line `latrines, urinals and similar conveniences;`
  line
  line `^4* * * **`
  line
  line `(c) the scavenging, removal and disposal of filth, rubbish and other obnoxious or polluted`
  line matters;
  line
  line `^5* * * * *`
  line
  line `(e) the reclamation of unhealthy localities, the removal of noxious vegetation and generally the`
  line `abatement of all nuisances;`
  line
  line `(f) the regulation of places for the disposal of the dead and the provision and maintenance of`
  line `places for the said purpose;`
  line
  line `(g) the registration of births and deaths;`
  line
  line `(h) public vaccination and inoculation;`
  line
  line `(i) measures for preventing and checking the spread of dangerous diseases;`
  line
  line `(j) the establishment and maintenance of ^6*** dispensaries and maternity and child welfare`
  line `centres and the carrying out of other measures necessary for public medical relief;`
  line
  line `^7[(jj)) the maintenance including the expansion and upgradation of facilities of the hospitals`
  line `existing on the date of the commencement of the Delhi Municipal Corporation (Amendment) Act,`
  line `1993 (67 of 1993);]`
  line
  line `(k) the construction and maintenance of municipal markets and slaughter houses and the`
  line `regulation of all markets and slaughter houses;.`
  line
  line `(l) the regulation and abatement of offensive or dangerous trades or practices;`
  line
  line `(m) the securing or removal of dangerous buildings and places;`
  line
  line `(n) the construction, maintenance, alteration and improvements of public streets, bridges,`
  line `culverts, causeways and the like;`
  line
  line `(o) the lighting, watering and cleansing of public streets and other public places;`
  line
  line `(p) the removal of obstructions and projections in or upon streets, bridges and other public places;`
  line
  line `(q) the naming and numbering of streets and premises;`
  line
  line `(r) the establishment, maintenance of, and aid to, schools for primary education subject to such`
  line `grants as may be determined by the Central Government from time to time;`
  line
  line `(s) the maintenance of municipal offices;`
  line
  line `(t) the laying out or the maintenance of public parks, gardens or recreation grounds;`
  line
  line `^8* * * * *`
  line
  line `(v) the maintenance of monuments and memorials vested in any local authority in Delhi`
  line `immediately before the commencement of this Act or which may be vested in ^1[^2[the Corporation]] after`
  line `such commencement;`
  line
  line `(w) the maintenance and development of the value of all properties vested in or entrusted to the`
  line `management of ^1[^2[the Corporation]]; and`
  line
  line `^9[(wa) the preparation of plans for economic development and social justice.]`
  line
  line `^10[(wb) securing and establishment of e-governance system for citizens' services on an anytime-anywhere basis for better, speedy, accountable and transparent administration;]`
  line
  line `(x) the fulfilment of any other obligation imposed by or under this Act or any other law for the`
  line `time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 the Corporation (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for a Corporation (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 36, for It shall be incumbent (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `4. Omitted by s. 36, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `5. Omitted by s. 36, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `6. The word hospitals omitted by s. 36, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by s. 36, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `8. Omitted by Act 67 of 1993, s. 36 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `9. Ins. by s. 36, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `10. Ins. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 6 (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (27170)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 63
  title `Discretionary functions of the Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27170&sectionno=43&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `^1[Subject to any general or special order of the`
  line `Government, from time to time, ^2[^3[the Corporation]] may] provide either wholly or in part for all or any of the`
  line `following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the furtherance of education including cultural and physical education, by measures other than`
  line `the establishment and maintenance of and aid to, schools for primary education;`
  line
  line `(b) the establishment and maintenance of, and aid to, libraries, museums, art galleries, botanical`
  line `or zoological collections;`
  line
  line `(c) the establishment and maintenance of, and aid to, stadia, gymnasia, a kharas and places for`
  line `sports and games;`
  line
  line `(d) the planting and care of trees on roadsides and elsewhere;`
  line
  line `(e) the surveys of buildings and lands;`
  line
  line `(f) the registration of marriages;`
  line
  line `(g) the taking of a census of population;`
  line
  line `(h) the civic reception to persons of distinction;`
  line
  line `(i) the providing of music or other entertainments in public places or places of public resort and`
  line `the establishment of theatres and cinemas;`
  line
  line `(j) the organisation and management of fairs and exhibitions;`
  line
  line `(k) the acquisition of movable or immovable property for any of the purposes before mentioned,`
  line `including payment of the cost of investigations, surveys or examinations in relation thereto for the`
  line `construction or adaptation of buildings necessary for such purposes;`
  line
  line `(l) the construction and maintenance of--`
  line
  line `(i) rest-houses,`
  line
  line `(ii) poor houses,`
  line
  line `(iii) infirmaries,`
  line
  line `(iv) children's homes,`
  line
  line `(v) houses for the deaf and dumb and for disabled and handicapped children,`
  line
  line `(vi) shelters for destitute and disabled persons,`
  line
  line `(vii) asylums for persons of unsound mind;`
  line
  line `(m) the construction and maintenance of cattle pounds;`
  line
  line `(n) the building or purchase and maintenance of dwelling houses for municipal officers and other`
  line `municipal employees;`
  line
  line `(o) any measures for the welfare of the municipal officers and other municipal employees or any`
  line `class of them including the sanctioning of loans to such officers and employees or any class of them`
  line `for construction of houses and purchase of vehicles;`
  line
  line `(p) the organisation or management of chemical or bacteriological laboratories for the`
  line `examination or analysis of water, food and drugs for the detection of diseases or research connected`
  line `with public health or medical relief;`
  line
  line `(q) the provision for relief to destitute and disabled persons;`
  line
  line `(r) the establishment and maintenance of veterinary hospitals;`
  line
  line `(s) the organisation, construction, maintenance and management of swimming pool, public wash`
  line `houses, bathing places and other institutions designed for the improvement of public health;`
  line
  line `(t) the organisation and management of farms and dairies within or without Delhi for the supply,`
  line `distribution and processing of milk and milk products for the benefit of the residents of ^4[the area of the Corporation];`
  line
  line `(u) the organisation and management of cottage industries, handicraft centres and sales emporia;`
  line
  line `(v) the construction and maintenance of warehouses and godowns;`
  line
  line `(w) the construction and maintenance of garages, sheds and stands for vehicles and cattle biers;`
  line
  line `(x) the provision for unfiltered water supply;`
  line
  line `(y) the improvement of ^4[^5[Delhi]] in accordance with improvement schemes approved by ^2[^3[the`
  line Corporation]];
  line
  line `(z) the provision of housing accommodation for the inhabitants of any area or for any class of`
  line `inhabitants; and`
  line
  line `(za) any measure not hereinbefore specifically mentioned, likely to promote public safety, health,`
  line `convenience or general welfare.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 37, for "The Corporation may in its discretion" (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "a Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for "Delhi" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "the area of the Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (27171)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 64
  title `Enumeration of municipal authorities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27171&sectionno=44&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `^1[44. Enumeration of municipal authorities.---For the efficient performance of its functions, there`
  line `shall be the following municipal authorities under ^2[^3[the Corporation]], namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the Standing Committee;`
  line
  line `(b) the Wards Committee; and`
  line
  line `(c) the Commissioner.]`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 38, for section 44 (w.e.f 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “the area of the Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (27172)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 65
  title `Constitution of the Standing Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27172&sectionno=45&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) The Standing Committee shall consist off---`
  line
  line `(i) six members elected by the councillors from among themselves at the first meeting of ^2[^3[the Corporation]];`
  line
  line `(ii) one member each elected by the members of each Wards Committee from among themselves`
  line `at the first meeting of the Wards Committee;`
  line
  line `after each general election or as soon as possible at any other meeting subsequent thereto.]`
  line
  line `(2) On and ^4[from such date as may be determined by ^2[^3[the Corporation]] by resolution] the Standing`
  line `Committee shall be deemed to have been constituted.`
  line
  line `^5[(3) One-half of the members referred to in clause (i) of sub-section (1) and one-half of the members`
  line `referred to in clause (ii) of that sub-section shall retire on the expiration of one year from the date of the`
  line `constitution of the Standing Committee after the commencement of the Delhi Municipal Corporation`
  line `(Amendment) Act, 1993 (27 of 1993), and for that purpose they shall be selected by lot from amongst`
  line `their respective categories before the said expiration in such manner as the Chairman of the Standing`
  line `Committee may determine;]`
  line
  line `(4) During each succeeding year the members who have been longest in office shall retire therefrom:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of a member who has been re-elected the term of his office shall for the`
  line `purpose of this sub-section be computed from the date of his re-election.`
  line
  line `^6[(5) ^7[^8[The Corporation]] or the concerned Wards Committee as the case may be, shall in a meeting held`
  line `immediately before the occurrence of the vacancies caused by the retirement of the members under`
  line `sub-section (3) or sub-section (4), elect the requisite member or members from amongst the councillors or`
  line `from amongst members of the Wards Committee, as the case may be, to fill up those vacancies.]`
  line
  line `(6) Any councillor ^9*** who ceases to be a member of the Standing Committee shall be eligible for`
  line re-election.
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 39, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "the area of the Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line `3. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 39, for "from the date of such election" (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 39, ibid., for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line `6. Subs. by s. 39, ibid., for sub-section (5) (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line `7. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "A Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line `9. The words "or alderman" omitted by Act 67 of 1993, s. 39 w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (27173)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 66
  title `Casual vacancies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27173&sectionno=46&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a casual vacancy occurs in the office of a member of the Standing`
  line `Committee, ^1[Corporation or, as the case may be, Wards Committee shall] fill up the vacancy, as soon as`
  line `may be after, and in any case within one month of, the occurrence of the vacancy, by the election of`
  line `another councillor or ^2[persons referred to in sub-clause (i) of clause (b) of sub-section (3)] of section 3.]`
  line
  line `(2) A member elected to fill a casual vacancy shall be elected to serve for the remainder of his`
  line `predecessor's term of office`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 40, ibid., for "Corporation shall" (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 40, ibid., for "alderman" (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (27174)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 67
  title `Chairman and Deputy Chairman of the Standing Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 41 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27174&sectionno=47&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Standing Committee`
  line `shall at its first meeting in each year elect one of its members ^1[who is a councillor] to be the Chairman`
  line `and another member to be the Deputy Chairman.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairman or the Deputy Chairman of the Standing Committee shall hold office from the date`
  line `of his election until the election of his successor in office unless in the meantime he resigns his office as`
  line `Chairman or Deputy Chairman or his term of office as member of the Standing Committee is in any`
  line `manner determined or unless in the case of the Deputy Chairman he is elected as Chairman.`
  line
  line `(3) On the occurrence of any casual vacancy in the office of the Chairman or the Deputy Chairman,`
  line `the Standing Committee shall within one month of the occurrence of such vacancy elect one of its`
  line `members ^1[who is a councillor] as Chairman or Deputy Chairman, as the case may be, and the Chairman`
  line `or the Deputy Chairman so elected shall hold office for the remainder of his predecessor's term.`
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (27175)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 68
  title `Resignation of Chairman and members of the Standing Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27175&sectionno=48&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any member of the`
  line `Standing Committee may resign his office by writing under his hand addressed to the Chairman; and the`
  line `Chairman may resign his office by writing under his hand addressed to the Mayor.`
  line
  line `(2) A resignation under sub-section (1) shall take effect from the date specified for the purpose in the`
  line `writing referred to in that sub-section, or if no such date is specified, from the date of its receipt by the`
  line `Chairman or the Mayor, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (27176)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 69
  title `Functions of the Standing Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27176&sectionno=49&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `The Standing Committee shall exercise such powers`
  line `and perform such functions as are specifically conferred or imposed upon it by or under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (27177)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 70
  title `Constitution of the Wards Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 42, for the heading and sections 50 to 53 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27177&sectionno=50&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `^1[50. Constitution of the Wards Committee.-- (1) For each Zone shall be a Wards Committee which`
  line `shall consist of,--`
  line
  line `(a) all the councillors elected from the wards comprised in that Zone; and`
  line
  line `(b) the person, if any, nominated by the Administrator under sub-clause (i) of clause (b) of`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 3 if his name is registered as an elector within the territorial limits of the`
  line `Zone concerned.`
  line
  line `(2) The Wards Committee shall be deemed to have been constituted from the date on which the`
  line `Corporation is constituted after each general election.]`
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (27178)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 71
  title `Application of sections 47 and 48.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 42, for the heading and sections 50 to 53 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27178&sectionno=51&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `^1[51. Application of sections 47 and 48.-- The provisions of sections 47 and 48 shall apply in relation`
  line `to a Wards Committee as they apply in relation to the Standing Committee.]`
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (27179)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 72
  title `Powers and functions of the Wards Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27179&sectionno=52&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `^1[52. Powers and functions of the Wards Committee.-- (1) Subject to the provisions of this Act,`
  line `every Wards Committee shall exercise the powers and perform the functions as specified in the Fifteenth`
  line `Schedule on behalf of ^2[^3[the Corporation]] in relation to that Zone.`
  line
  line `(2) ^4[The Central Government may] , after consultation with the Government, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, amend the Fifteenth Schedule.`
  line
  line `(3) When any question arises as to whether any matter falls within the purview of a Wards Committee`
  line `or ^2[^3[the Corporation]], it shall be referred to the Government, and the decision of that Government thereon`
  line `shall be final.]`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 42, for the heading and sections 50 to 53 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "a Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 10, for “The Central Government may, after consultation with the Government” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (27180)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 73
  title `Appointment, etc., of the Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27180&sectionno=54&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, by notification in`
  line `the Official Gazette, appoint a suitable person as the Commissioner of ^1[^2[the Corporation]].`
  line
  line `(2) The Commissioner so appointed shall hold office for a term of five years in the first instance:`
  line
  line `Provided that his appointed may be renewed from time to time for a term not exceeding one year at a`
  line `time:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where the Commissioner holds a lien on any service under the Government, the`
  line `Central Government may at any time after reasonable notice to ^1[^2[the Corporation]] replace his services at the`
  line `disposal of that Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government`
  line
  line `(a) shall remove the Commissioner from office if at a special meeting of ^1[^2[the Corporation]] called`
  line `for the purpose a resolution for such removal has been passed by a majority of not less than threefifths`
  line `of the total number of members;`
  line
  line `(b) may remove the Commissioner from office at any time if it appears, to that Government that`
  line `he is incapable of performing the duties of his office or has been guilty of neglect or misconduct in`
  line `the discharge of such duties which renders his removal expedient.`
  line
  line `(4) The Commissioner shall not undertake any work unconnected with his office without the sanction`
  line `of the Central Government and of ^1[^2[the Corporation]].`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (27181)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 74
  title `Salary and allowances of the Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27181&sectionno=55&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `The Commissioner shall be paid out of the`
  line `Municipal Fund such monthly salary and such monthly allowances, if any, as may from time to time be`
  line `fixed by ^1[^2[the Central Government]] and may be given such facilities (if any) in relation to residential`
  line `accommodation, conveyance and the like as may from time to time be fixed by that Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that the salary of the Commissioner shall not be varied to his disadvantage after his`
  line appointment.
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for “Central Government” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “Government” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (27182)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 75
  title `Leave of absence of Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27182&sectionno=56&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `(1) Leave may be granted to the Commissioner by the`
  line `Standing Committee.`
  line
  line `(2) Whenever such leave is granted to the Commissioner ^1[^2[the Central Government]] shall appoint`
  line `another person to officiate as Commissioner in his place.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for "Central Government" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "Government" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (27183)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 76
  title `Appointment of officiating Commissioner in case of death, resignation or removal of Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27183&sectionno=57&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `If any vacancy occurs in the office of the Commissioner on account of death,`
  line `resignation or removal, ^1[^2[the Central Government]] may appoint another person to officiate as Commissioner`
  line `in his place for a term not exceeding two months, pending the appointment of a Commissioner under`
  line `section 54.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for “Central Government” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “Government” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (27184)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 77
  title `Service regulations of Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27184&sectionno=58&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Commissioner is an officer in the service of`
  line `the Government, ^1[^2[the Corporation]] shall make such contribution towards his leave allowances, pension and`
  line `provident fund as may be required by the conditions of his service under the Government, to be paid by`
  line `him or for him, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) If the Commissioner is not an officer in the service of the Government, his leave and leave`
  line `allowances, his superannuation or retirement, his gratuity or pension and the proportions of his`
  line `pensionary or provident fund contribution payable respectively from his salary and from the Municipal`
  line `Fund shall be governed by rules:`
  line
  line `Provided that--`
  line
  line `(a) the amount of any such leave and leave allowances, gratuity or pension shall in no case,`
  line `without the special sanction of the Central Government, exceed what would be admissible in the case`
  line `of Government servants of similar standing and status; and`
  line
  line `(b) the conditions under which such allowances, gratuity or pension are granted or any leave,`
  line `superannuation or retirement is sanctioned shall not without similar sanction be more favourable than`
  line `those for the time being prescribed for such Government servants.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (27185)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 78
  title `Functions of the Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27185&sectionno=59&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise provided in this Act, the entire executive`
  line `power for the purpose of carrying out the provisions of this Act ^1*** ^2*** and of any other Act for the`
  line `time being in force which confers any power or imposes any duty on the Corporation, shall vest in the`
  line `Commissioner who shall also—`
  line
  line `(a) exercise all the powers and perform all the duties specifically conferred or imposed upon him`
  line `by this Act or by any other law for the time being in force;`
  line
  line `(b) prescribe the duties of, and exercise supervision and control over the acts and proceedings of,`
  line `all municipal officers and other municipal employees other the Municipal Secretary and the`
  line `Municipal Chief Auditor and the municipal officers and other municipal employees immediately`
  line `subordinate to them and subject to any regulation that may be made in this behalf, dispose of all`
  line `questions relating to the service of the said officers and other employees and their pay, privileges,`
  line `allowances and other conditions of service;`
  line
  line `(c) on the occurrence or threatened occurrence of any sudden accident or any unforseen event or`
  line `natural calamity involving or likely to involve extensive damage to any property of the Corporation,`
  line `or danger to human life, take such immediate action as he considers necessary and make a report`
  line `forthwith to the Standing Committee and the Corporation of the action he has taken and the reasons`
  line `for the same as also of the amount of cost, if any, incurred or likely to be incurred in consequence of`
  line `such action, which is not covered by a budget grant;`
  line
  line `^3[(d) subject to any regulation that may be made in this behalf, be the disciplinary authority in`
  line `relation to all municipal officers and other municipal employees.]`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "other than those pertaining to the Delhi Electric Supply Undertaking" omitted by Act 67 of 1993,`
  line `s. 43 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `2. The words "on the Delhi Transport Undertaking" omitted by Act 71 of 1971, s. 7(b) and the Second`
  line `Schedule (w.e.f. 3-11-1971).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 43, for clause (d) (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
