  content `[Functions of the General Managers.] Omitted by s. 44, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27190&sectionno=64&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (27191)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 84
  title `Appointment of sub-committees by the various committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 45, ibid., for certain words (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27191&sectionno=65&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Standing`
  line `Committee, ^1[or the Wards Committee] may appoint from among its own members any sub-committee`
  line `consisting of such number as that committee may think fit for exercising any power or performing any`
  line `function of that committee under this Act or for inquiring into or reporting or advising upon any matter`
  line `which that committee may refer to such sub-committee.`
  line
  line `(2) Every such sub-committee shall conform to such instructions as may be given to it by the`
  line `committee by which it has been appointed.`
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (27192)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 85
  title `Commissioner and General Managers not to be interested in any contract, etc., with the Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27192&sectionno=66&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person shall be disqualified for being appointed as the Commissioner ^1*** who has,`
  line `directly or indirectly, by himself or by a partner, or any other person, any share or interest in any contract`
  line `made with, or any work being done for, ^2[^3[the Corporation]] other than as such Commissioner ^4***.`
  line
  line `(2) If the Commissioner, ^1`
  line `*** acquires directly or indirectly, by himself or by his partner, or any`
  line `other person, any share or interest in any such contract or work as is referred to in sub-section (1), he`
  line `shall, unless the Corporation in any particular case otherwise decides, be liable to be removed from his`
  line `office by the order of the authority competent to remove him under the provisions of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that before an order of removal is made, the Commissioner ^5*** shall be given a reasonable`
  line `opportunity of showing cause against the action proposed to be taken in regard to him.`
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words and brackets "or the General Manager (Electricity)" omitted by Act 67 of 1993, s. 122, s. 46 (w.e.f 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 "the Corporation"(w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "a Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `4. The words "or General Manager, as the case may be" omitted by Act 67 of 1993, s. 122, s. 46 (w.e.f 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `5. The words "or such General Manager" omitted by s. 46, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (27193)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 86
  title `Vacation of seats by members of committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27193&sectionno=67&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) A member of the Standing Committee or a`
  line `Wards Committee, if he ceases to be a councillor or ceases to represent any of the categories mentioned in`
  line `sub-clause (ii) of clause (b) of sub-section (3) of section 3 shall cease to be a member of that Committee`
  line `and his seat shall thereupon become vacant.]`
  line
  line `(2) If a member of the Standing Committee, ^2***, absents himself during three successive months`
  line `from the meetings of the committee except on account of illness or any other cause approved by the`
  line `committee, or absents himself during six successive months from the meetings of the committee on`
  line `account of any cause whatsoever, whether approved by the committee or not, he shall cease to be a`
  line `member of the committee and his seat shall thereupon become vacant.`
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 122, s. 47, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `2. The words "the Delhi Electric Supply Committee or the Delhi Water Supply and Sewage Disposal Committee" omitted`
  line `by s. 47, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (27194)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 87
  title `Committees to continue in office till new committees are constituted.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 48, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27194&sectionno=68&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `The Standing`
  line `Committee, ^1[or the Wards Committee] shall continue to function until a new committee is constituted in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of this Act notwithstanding that the members or some of the members of`
  line `such committee have ceased to be councillors or aldermen.`
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (27195)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 88
  title `Power of Corporation to call for extracts of proceedings from the Committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27195&sectionno=69&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line ^1[^2[The
  line `Corporation]] may at any time call for any extract of any proceedings of the Standing Committee, ^3[the`
  line `Wards Committee], the Delhi Rural Areas Committee, the Education Committee or of any other`
  line `committee or sub-committee constituted or appointed under this Act and for any return, statement,`
  line `account or report concerning or connected with any matter with which any such committee or subcommittee`
  line `is empowered by or under this Act to deal; and every such requisition shall be complied with`
  line `by any such Committee or sub-committee without any unreasonable delay.`
obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes:
  string
  line `1.Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “A Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 49, for certain words (w.e.f 1-10-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (27196)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 89
  title `Power of Corporation to require the Commissioner, etc., to produce documents and furnish returns, reports, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27196&sectionno=70&orderno=89&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `(1) ^1[^2[The Corporation]] may at any time require the Commissioner--`
  line
  line `(a) to produce any record, correspondence, plan or other document which is in his possession or`
  line `under his control as Commissioner or which is recorded or filed in his office or in the office of any`
  line `municipal officer or other municipal employee subordinate to him;`
  line
  line `(b) to furnish any return, plan, estimate, statement, account or statistics concerning or connected`
  line `with any matter pertaining to the administration of this Act or the municipal government of`
  line `^3[^4[Delhi]] ^5*** ^6***;`
  line
  line `(c) to furnish a report by himself or to obtain from the head of any department subordinate to him`
  line `and furnish with his own remarks thereon, a report, upon any subject concerning or connected with`
  line `the administration of this Act or the municipal government of ^3[^4[Delhi]] ^5*** ^7***.`
  line
  line `(2) Every such requisition shall be complied with by the Commissioner without any unreasonable`
  line `delay; and it shall be incumbent on every municipal officer and other municipal employee to obey any`
  line `order made by the Commissioner in pursuance of any such requisition:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Commissioner shall not be bound to comply with any such requisition if with the`
  line `previous approval of the Mayor he makes a statement that such compliance would be prejudicial to public`
  line `interest or to the interests of ^8[^9[the Corporation]].`
  line
  line `^10* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "A Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for "Delhi" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012)..`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "the area of the Corporation"(w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `5. The words "except in regard to the Delhi Electric Supply Undertaking" omitted by s. 50, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `6. The words ", or the Delhi Transport Undertaking" omitted by Act 71 of 1971, s. 7(b) and the Second`
  line `Schedule (w.e.f. 3-11-1971).`
  line
  line `7. The words "or the Delhi Transport Undertaking" omitted by Act 71 of 1971, s. 7(b) and the Second Schedule (w.e.f. 3-11-1971).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "a Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `10. Omitted by Act 67 of 1993, s. 50 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993)`
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (27197)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 90
  title `Exercise of powers to be subject to sanction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27197&sectionno=71&orderno=90&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise provided in this Act, the`
  line `exercise of any power or the performance of any duty conferred or imposed upon ^1[^2[the Corporation]] or any`
  line `municipal authority by or under this Act, which will involve expenditure, shall be subject to the following`
  line `conditions, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) that such expenditure, in so far as it is to be incurred in the year in which such power is`
  line `exercised or duty performed, shall be provided for under a current budget-grant; and`
  line
  line `(b) that if the exercise of such power or the performance of such duty involves or is likely to`
  line `involve expenditure for any period or at any time after the close of the said year, such expenditure`
  line `shall not be incurred without the sanction---`
  line
  line `(i) of the Standing Committee ^3***, if it is incurred in the year next following such year, or`
  line
  line `(ii) of ^4[^5[the Corporation]]`
  line `, if it is incurred at any time after the next following year.`
obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Certain words omitted by Act 67 of 1993, s s. 51 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (27198)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 91
  title Meetings.
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27198&sectionno=72&orderno=91&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `(1) ^1[^2[The Corporation]] shall ordinarily hold at least one meeting in every month for the`
  line `transaction of business.`
  line
  line `(2) The Mayor or in his absence the Deputy Mayor may, whenever he thinks fit, and shall, upon a`
  line `requisition in writing by not less than one-fourth of the total number of councillors ^3[and other persons`
  line `referred to in clause (b) of sub-section (3) of section 3], convene a special meeting of the Corporation.`
  line
  line `(3) Any meeting may be adjourned until the next or any subsequent date, and an adjourned meeting`
  line `may be further adjourned in like manner.`
obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for "The Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "A Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 52, for "and alderman" (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (27199)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 92
  title `First meeting of the Corporation after general election.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27199&sectionno=73&orderno=92&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `The first meeting of ^1[^2[the Corporation]]`
  line `after a general election shall be held as early as possible after the publication of the results of the election`
  line `^3*** under section 14 and shall be convened by the Administrator.`
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2 . Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "a Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. The words "of alderman" omitted by Act 67 of 1993, s. 53 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (27200)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 93
  title `Notice of meetings and business.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27200&sectionno=74&orderno=93&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `A list of the business to be transacted at every meeting`
  line `except at an adjourned meeting shall be sent to the address of each councillor ^1[and the persons referred to`
  line `in clause (b) of sub-section (3) of section 3] at least seventy-two hours before the time fixed for such`
  line `meeting; and no business shall be brought before, or transacted at, any meeting other than the business of`
  line `which a notice has been so given:`
  line
  line `Provided that any councillor ^2[or the persons referred to in clause (b) of sub-section (3) of section 3]`
  line `may send or deliver to of such meeting so as to reach him at least forty-eight hours before the date fixed`
  line `for the meeting and the Municipal Secretary shall with all possible despatch take steps to circulate such`
  line `resolution to every councillor ^1[and the persons referred to in clause (b) of sub-section (3) of section 3 in`
  line `such manner as he may think fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 54, for "and alderman" (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 54, ibid., for "or alderman" (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (27201)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 94
  title Quorum.
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27201&sectionno=75&orderno=94&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `(1) The quorum necessary for the transaction of business at a meeting of ^1[^2[the`
  line `Corporation]] shall be one-fifth of the total number of members ^3[and the persons referred to in sub-clauses`
  line `(ii), (iii) and (iv) of clause (b) of sub-section (3) of section 3.]`
  line
  line `(2) If at any time during a meeting of the Corporation there is no quorum, it shall be the duty of the`
  line `Mayor or the person presiding over such meeting either to adjourn the meeting or to suspend the meeting`
  line `until there is a quorum.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a meeting has been adjourned under sub-section (2), the business which would have been`
  line `brought before the original meeting if there had been a quorum present thereat, shall be brought before,`
  line `and may be transacted at an adjourned meeting, whether there is a quorum present or not.`
obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes:
  string
  line `1.Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "a Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 55 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (27202)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 95
  title `Presiding officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27202&sectionno=76&orderno=95&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Mayor or in his absence, the Deputy Mayor, shall preside at every`
  line `meeting of ^1[^2[the Corporation]].`
  line
  line `^3[(2) In the absence of both the Mayor and Deputy Mayor from the meeting, the members and the`
  line `persons referred to in sub-clauses (ii), (iii) and (iv) of clause (b) of sub-section (3) of section 3 shall elect`
  line `one from among the councillors to preside.]`
  line
  line `(3) The Mayor or the person presiding over a meeting shall have and exercise a second or a casting`
  line `vote in all cases of equality of votes.`
obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 56, ibid., for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (27203)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 96
  title `Presiding officer at meeting for the election of Mayor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes `1. The words "or an alderman" omitted by Act 67 of 1993, s. 57 (w.e.f 1-10-1993).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27203&sectionno=77&orderno=96&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained`
  line `in section 76`
  line
  line `(a) at a meeting for the election of a Mayor the Administrator shall nominate a councillor ^1`
  line ***
  line `who is not a candidate for such election to preside over the meeting;`
  line
  line `(b) if during the election of Mayor it appears that there is an equality of votes between any`
  line `candidates at such election and that the addition of a vote would entitle any of those candidates to be`
  line `elected as Mayor, then, the person presiding over the meeting shall decide between them by lot to be`
  line `drawn in the presence of the candidates and in such manner as he may determine, and the candidate`
  line `on whom the lot falls shall be deemed to have received an additional vote.`
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (27204)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 97
  title `Method of deciding questions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27204&sectionno=78&orderno=97&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise provided in this Act, all matters required`
  line `to be decided by ^1[^2[the Corporation]] shall be decided by the majority of the votes of the ^3[members and`
  line `persons referred to in sub-clauses (ii), (iii) and (iv) of clause (b) of sub-section (3) of section 3] present`
  line `and voting.`
  line
  line `(2) The voting shall be by show of hands, but ^1[^2[the Corporation]] may, subject to such regulations as may`
  line `be made by it, resolve that any question or class of questions shall be decided by ballot.`
  line
  line `(3) At any meeting, unless voting be demanded by at least four ^3[members and persons referred to in`
  line `sub-clauses (ii), (iii) and (iv) of clause (b) of sub-section (3)] of section 3, a declaration by the presiding`
  line `officer at such meeting that a resolution has been carried or lost, and an entry to that effect in the minutes`
  line `of the proceedings shall, for the purposes of this Act, be inclusive evidence of the fact without proof of`
  line `the number or proportion of the votes recorded in favour of or against such resolution.`
  line
  line `(4) If voting as aforesaid is demanded, the votes of all the ^3[members and persons referred to in`
  line `sub-clauses (ii), (iii) and (iv) of clause (b) of sub-section (3) of section 3] present who desire to vote shall`
  line `be taken under the direction of the presiding officer at the meeting and the result of the voting shall be`
  line `deemed to be the resolution of ^1[^2[the Corporation]] at such meeting.`
obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 58, for members (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (27205)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 98
  title `Maintenance of order at, and admission of public to, meetings; withdrawal and suspension of councillors and alderman.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27205&sectionno=79&orderno=98&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Mayor or the person presiding over a meeting shall preserve`
  line `order threat and shall have all powers necessary for the purpose of preserving such order.`
  line
  line `(2) The Mayor or the person presiding over a meeting may direct any councillor ^1[or persons referred`
  line `to in clause (b) of sub-section (3) of section 3] whose conduct is in his opinion grossly disorderly to`
  line `withdraw immediately from the meeting, and any councillor ^1[or persons referred to in clause (b) of`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 3] so directed to withdraw shall do so forthwith and shall absent himself during`
  line `the remainder of the meeting.`
  line
  line `(3) If any councillor ^1[or persons referred to in clause (b) of sub-section (3) of section 3] is ordered to`
  line `withdraw a second time within fifteen days, the Mayor or the person presiding may suspend such`
  line `councillor ^1[or persons referred to in clause (b) of sub-section (3) of section 3] from attending the`
  line `meetings of the Corporation for any period not exceeding fifteen days and the councillor ^1[or persons`
  line `referred to in clause (b) of sub-section (3) of section 3] so suspended shall absent himself accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Mayor may at any time decide that such suspension be terminated:`
  line
  line `Provided further that such suspension shall not debar the suspended councillor ^1[or persons referred to`
  line `in clause (b) of sub-section (3) of section 3] from serving on any committee of the Corporation of which`
  line `he is a member.`
  line
  line `(4) Subject to sub-section (5) every meeting shall be open to the public, unless a majority of the`
  line `^2[members and persons referred to in sub-clauses (ii), (iii) and (iv) of clause (b) of sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 3] present at the meeting decide that any inquiry or deliberation pending before ^3[^4[the Corporation]]`
  line `shall be held in private.`
  line
  line `(5) The Corporation may make regulations for the purpose of admission of the member of the public`
  line `to its meetings and for the removal by force, if necessary, of any member of the public admitted to a`
  line `meeting for interrupting or disturbing the proceedings of the meeting.`
  line
  line `(6) In the case of grave disorder arising in a meeting the Mayor or the person presiding may, if he`
  line `thinks it necessary to do so, adjourn the meeting to a date specified by him.`
obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 59, for "or alderman" (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 59, ibid., for "members" (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "a Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_80:
  sectionId (27206)
  sectionNo (80)
  orderNo 99
  title `Councillors or aldermen not to vote on matter in which they are interested.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_80_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27206&sectionno=80&orderno=99&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_80_content:
  string
  line `No councillor`
  line `or ^1[persons referred to in sub-clauses (ii), (iii) and (iv) of clause (b) of sub-section (3) of section 3] shall`
  line `vote at a meeting of ^2[^3[the Corporation]] or of any committee thereof on any question relating to his own`
  line `conduct or vote or take part in any discussion on any matter (other than a matter affecting generally the residents of Delhi or of any particular ward), which affects his pecuniary interest or any property in`
  line `respect of which he is directly or indirectly interested, or any property of or for which he is a manager or`
  line agent.
obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 60, ibid., for alderman (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_81:
  sectionId (27207)
  sectionNo (81)
  orderNo 100
  title `Right to attend meetings of the Corporation and its committees, etc., and right of councillors and aldermen to ask questions in relation to the municipal government of Delhi.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_81_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27207&sectionno=81&orderno=100&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_81_content:
  string
  line `81. Right to attend meetings of ^1[^2[the Corporation]] and its committees, etc., and right of`
  line `councillors and aldermen to ask questions in relation to the municipal government of Delhi.--^3[(1)`
  line `The Commissioner or any municipal officer authorised by him in this behalf may attend, speak in, or`
  line `otherwise take part in the proceedings of, any meeting of ^1[^2[the Corporation]] or any of its Committees, but`
  line `none of the persons specified herein shall by virtue of this sub-section be entitled to vote in any such`
  line meeting.]
  line
  line `(2) A councillor or ^4[person referred to in sub-clauses (ii), (iii) and (iv) of clause (b) of sub-section (3)`
  line `of section 3] may, subject to the provisions of sub-section (3), ask the Commissioner questions on any`
  line `matter relating to the municipal government of Delhi or the administration of this Act or the functions of`
  line `any of the municipal authorities.`
  line
  line `(3) The right to ask a question shall be governed by the following conditions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) not less than seven clear days' notice in writing specifying the question shall be given to the`
  line `Municipal Secretary;`
  line
  line `(b) no question shall---`
  line
  line `(i) bring in any name or statement not strictly necessary to make the question intelligible,`
  line
  line `(ii) contain arguments, ironical expressions, imputations, epithets or defamatory statements,`
  line
  line `(iii) ask for an expression of opinion or the solution of a hypothetical proposition,`
  line
  line `(iv) ask as to the character or conduct of any person except in his official or public capacity,`
  line
  line `(v) relate to a matter which is not primarily the concern of ^1[^2[the Corporation]] or of any of the`
  line `municipal authorities,`
  line
  line `(vi) make or imply a charge of a personal character,`
  line
  line `(vii) raise questions of policy too large to be dealt with within the limits of an answer to a`
  line question,
  line
  line `(viii) repeat in substance questions already answered or to which an answer has been refused.`
  line
  line `(ix) ask for information on trivial matters,`
  line
  line `(x) ordinarily ask for information on matters of past history,`
  line
  line `(xi) ask for information set forth in accessible documents or in ordinary works of reference,`
  line
  line `(xii) raise matters under the control of bodies or persons not primarily responsible to the`
  line Corporation,
  line
  line `(xiii) ask for any information on matter which is under adjudication by a court of law.`
  line
  line `(4) The Mayor shall disallow any question which is, in his opinion, in contravention of the provisions`
  line `of sub-section (3).`
  line
  line `(5) If any doubt arises whether any question is or is not in contravention of the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (3), the Mayor shall decide the point and his decision shall be final.`
  line
  line `(6) The Commissioner shall not be bound to answer a question if it asks for information which has`
  line `been communicated to him in confidence or if in the opinion of the Mayor it cannot be answered without`
  line `prejudice to public interest or the interest of the Corporation.`
  line
  line `(7) Unless otherwise directed by the Mayor or the presiding officer of the meeting, every question`
  line `shall be answered by the Commissioner at a meeting of ^1[^2[the Corporation]].`
  line
  line `^5* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "a Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022)/.br`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 61, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 61, ibid., for "alderman" (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `5. Omitted by Act 67 of 1993, s. 61 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993)`
