  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27211&sectionno=85&orderno=104&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_85_content:
  string
  line `Minutes, in which shall be recorded the names of the`
  line `^1[members and other persons referred to in clause (b) of sub-section (3) of section 3] present at, and the`
  line `proceedings of each meeting ^2*** of ^3[^49560the Corporation]] and of the Standing Committee and every other`
  line `committee of ^3[^49560the Corporation]], shall be drawn up and recorded in a book to be kept for that purpose, and`
  line `shall be laid before the next ensuing meeting of ^3[^49560the Corporation]] or of such committee, as the case may be,`
  line `and signed at such meeting by the presiding officer thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 63, for "members present" (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `2. The words "of the councillors for the election of any alderman and of each" omitted by s. 63, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `3.Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "a Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_86:
  sectionId (27212)
  sectionNo (86)
  orderNo 105
  title `Circulation of minutes and inspection of minutes and reports of proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_86_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27212&sectionno=86&orderno=105&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_86_content:
  string
  line `(1) Minutes`
  line `of the proceedings of each meeting of`
  line `^1[^2[the Corporation]] shall be circulated to`
  line `all the ^3[persons referred to in`
  line `clause (b) of sub-section (3) of section 3] and shall at all reasonable times be available at the municipal`
  line `office for inspection by any other person on payment of a fee of eight annas.`
  line
  line `(2) Full reports, if any, of such proceedings shall similarly be available for inspection by any`
  line `^3[persons referred to in clause (b) of sub-section (3) of section 3] without charge and by any other person`
  line `on payment of a fee of eight annas.`
obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes:
  string
  line `1.Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "a Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 64, for "members of the Corporation" (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_87:
  sectionId (27213)
  sectionNo (87)
  orderNo 106
  title `Forwarding minutes and reports of proceedings to the Administrator.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_87_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27213&sectionno=87&orderno=106&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_87_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Municipal`
  line `Secretary shall forward to the Administrator a copy of the minutes of the proceedings of each meeting of`
  line `^1[^2[the Corporation]], within ten days from the date on which the minutes of the proceedings of such meeting`
  line `were signed under section 85.`
  line
  line `(2) The Administrator may also in any case ask for a copy of any paper or all the papers which were`
  line `laid before ^1[^2[the Corporation]] or any committee thereof and the Municipal Secretary shall forward to the`
  line `Administrator a copy of such paper or papers.`
  line
  line `(3) The Municipal Secretary shall also forward to the Administrator as soon as may be after the date`
  line `referred to in sub-section (1), a full report of the proceedings of each meeting of ^1[^2[the Corporation]], if any`
  line `such report be prepared.`
obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_88:
  sectionId (27214)
  sectionNo (88)
  orderNo 107
  title `Validation of proceedings, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_88_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27214&sectionno=88&orderno=107&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_88_content:
  string
  line `(1) No act done or proceeding taken under this Act shall be`
  line `questioned on the ground merely of--`
  line
  line `(a) the seat of any councillor ^1*** remaining unfilled from any cause whatsoever;`
  line
  line `(b) the existence of any vacancy in, or any defect in the constitution of, ^2[^3[the Corporation]], or in any`
  line `committee thereof;`
  line
  line `(c) any ^4[councillor or any person referred to in sub-clauses (ii), (iii) and (iv) of clause (b) of`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 3] or taken part in any proceedings in contravention of section 80;`
  line
  line `(d) any defect or irregularity not affecting the merits of the case.`
  line
  line `(2) Every meeting ^5*** of ^2[^3[the Corporation]] or of any committee thereof, the minutes of the proceeding`
  line `of which have been duly drawn up and signed shall be deemed to have been duly convened and to be free`
  line `from all defects and irregularities.`
obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "or alderman" omitted by Act 67 of 1993, s. 65 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 "the Corporation"(w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "a Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 65, for "councillor having voted" (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `5. The words "of the councillors for the election of any alderman or" omitted by s. 65, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_89:
  sectionId (27215)
  sectionNo (89)
  orderNo 108
  title `Appointment of certain officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_89_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27215&sectionno=89&orderno=108&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_89_content:
  string
  line `(1) ^1[^2[The Corporation]] shall appoint suitable persons to be`
  line `respectively ^3***, the Municipal Engineer, the Municipal Health Officer, the Education Officer, the`
  line `Municipal Chief Accountant, the Municipal Secretary and the Municipal Chief Auditor and may appoint`
  line `one or more Deputy Commissioners and such other officer or officers of a status equivalent to or higher`
  line `than the status of any of the officers specified earlier in this sub-section as ^4[^5[the Corporation]] may deem fit`
  line `on such monthly salaries and such allowances, if any, as may be fixed by ^4[^5[the Corporation]].`
  line
  line `(2) The appointment of the Municipal Chief Auditor shall be made with the previous approval of`
  line `the ^6*** Government and every other appointment referred to in sub-section (1) except that of the`
  line `Municipal Chief Accountant and the Municipal Secretary shall be subject to confirmation by that`
  line `Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Municipal Chief Auditor shall not be eligible for any other office under ^4[^5[the`
  line `Corporation]] after he has ceased to hold his office.`
obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “A Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. The words and brackets the Chief Engineer (Water Supply) omitted by 67 of 1993,`
  line `s. 66 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `6. The word Central omitted by 67 of 1993, s. 66 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_90:
  sectionId (27216)
  sectionNo (90)
  orderNo 109
  title `Schedule of permanent posts and creation of temporary posts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_90_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27216&sectionno=90&orderno=109&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_90_content:
  string
  line `(1) The ^1[Commissioner] shall from time to time prepare and lay before ^2[the Standing Committee] two schedules of posts other than those specified in sub-section (1) of section 89 setting forth the designations and grades of municipal officers and other municipal employees who should be maintained permanently in the service of ^3[^4[the Corporation]] indicating therein the salaries, fees and allowances which are proposed to be paid to such officers and other employees.`
  line
  line `^5[(2) Of the two schedules referred to in sub-section (1), the first schedule shall deal with category A posts and second schedule with category B and category C posts.]`
  line
  line `(3) ^6[The Standing Committee] shall lay the first schedule with its comments thereon before ^3[^4[the Corporation]] for its consideration and approval and shall sanction the second either without modifications or with such modifications as it thinks fit and thereafter may amend it either on its own motion after ascertaining the views of the ^7[Commissioner or at his instance].`
  line
  line `(4) ^8[^9[The Corporation]] shall after considering the comments of ^2[the Standing Committee] sanction the first schedule either without modifications or with such modifications as it thinks fit and thereafter may amend it either on its own motion after ascertaining the views of the ^1[Commissioner] and ^2[the Standing Committee] or at the instance of ^10[the Commissioner] or committee.`
  line
  line `^11[(5) The ^1[Commissioner9563 may create for a period not exceeding six months any category C post:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such post shall be continued beyond the said period without the previous approval of ^2[the Standing Committee].`
  line
  line `(6) ^6[The Standing Committee] may, on the recommendation of the ^1[Commissioner] create for a period not exceeding six months any category A or category B post:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such post shall be continued beyond the said period without the previous approval of ^3[^4[the Corporationi]].]`
  line
  line `^12* * * * *`
  line
  line `^13[(8) In this section and in section 92--`
  line
  line `^14[(i) "category A post" means any post, which, having regard to its scale of pay or emoluments, would, if such post had been in the Central Government, be classified as a Group A post under the Central Government in accordance with the orders issued by that Government from time to time;`
  line
  line `(ii) "category B post" means any post which, having regard to its scale of pay or emoluments, would, if such post had been in the Central Government, be classified as a Group B post under the Central Government in accordance with the orders issued by that Government from time to time;]`
  line
  line `(iii) "category C post" means any post, other than a category A or category B post.]`
obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes:
  string
