  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27219&sectionno=92A&orderno=113&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_92_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[92A. Recruitment to category B and category C posts.—The direct recruitment to category B`
  line `and category C posts may be made by the Government through such agencies as may be prescribed by it.]`
obj_root_law_sections_93:
  sectionId (27220)
  sectionNo (93)
  orderNo 114
  title `Officers and other employees not to undertake any extraneous work.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_93_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27220&sectionno=93&orderno=114&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_93_content:
  string
  line `No municipal officer`
  line `or other municipal employee shall undertake any work unconnected with his duties under this Act except`
  line `with the permission of ^1[^2[the Corporation]].`
obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_94:
  sectionId (27221)
  sectionNo (94)
  orderNo 115
  title `Officers and other employees not to be interested in any contract, etc., with the Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_94_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27221&sectionno=94&orderno=115&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_94_content:
  string
  line `94. Officers and other employees not to be interested in any contract, etc., with ^2[^3[the`
  line `Corporatio]].--(1) A person shall be disqualified for being appointed as a municipal officer or employee`
  line `if he has, directly or indirectly, by himself or by a partner or any other person any share or interest in any`
  line `contract made with, or any work being done for, ^2[^3[the Corporation]] other than as such officer or employee.`
  line
  line `(2) If any such officer or other employee acquires, directly or indirectly, by himself or by a partner or`
  line `any other person, any share or interest in any such contract or work as is referred to in sub-section (1), he`
  line `shall unless the authority appointing him in any particular case otherwise decides, be liable to be removed`
  line `from his office by an order of such authority:`
  line
  line `Provided that before an order of removal is made, such officer or other employee shall be given a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of showing cause against the action proposed to be taken in regard to him.`
obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 the Corporation (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for a Corporation (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_95:
  sectionId (27222)
  sectionNo (95)
  orderNo 116
  title `Punishment for municipal officers and other employees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_95_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27222&sectionno=95&orderno=116&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_95_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every municipal officer or other`
  line `municipal employee shall be liable to have his increments or promotion withheld or to be censured,`
  line `reduced in rank, compulsorily retired, removed or dismissed for any breach of any departmental`
  line `regulations or of discipline or for carelessness, unfitness, neglect of duty or other misconduct by such`
  line `authority as may be prescribed by regulations:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such officer or other employee as aforesaid shall be reduced in rank, compulsorily`
  line `retired, removed or dismissed by any authority subordinate to that by which he was appointed:`
  line
  line `Provided further that ^1[^2[the Corporation]] may by regulations provide that municipal employees belonging`
  line `to such classes or categories as may be specified in the regulations shall be liable also to be fined by such`
  line `authority as may be specified therein.`
  line
  line `(2) No such officer or other employee shall be punished under sub-section (1) unless he has been`
  line `given a reasonable opportunity of showing cause against the action proposed to be taken in regard to him:`
  line
  line `Provided that this sub-section shall not apply`
  line
  line `(a) where an officer or other employee is removed or dismissed on the ground of conduct which`
  line `had led to his conviction on a criminal charge; or`
  line
  line `(b) where the authority empowered to remove or dismiss such officer or other employee is`
  line `satisfied that for some reason to be recorded by that authority, it is not reasonably practicable to give`
  line `that person an opportunity of showing cause.`
  line
  line `(3) If any question arises whether it is reasonably practicable to give to any officer or other employee`
  line `an opportunity of showing cause under sub-section (2), the decision thereon of the authority empowered`
  line `to remove or dismiss such officer or other employee shall be final.`
  line
  line `(4) An officer or other employee upon whom a punishment has been inflicted under this section may`
  line `appeal to such officer or authority as may be prescribed by regulations.`
  line
  line `^3[Provided that in the case of an officer or other employee appointed by the Commissioner an appeal`
  line `shall lie to the Administrator.]`
obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 70 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_96:
  sectionId (27223)
  sectionNo (96)
  orderNo 117
  title `Consultation with the Union Public Service Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_96_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27223&sectionno=96&orderno=117&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_96_content:
  string
  line `No appointment ^1*** ^2*** ^3[to any`
  line `category A post within the meaning of clause (i) of sub-section (8) of section 90 shall be made except`
  line `after consultation with the Commission]:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such consultation with the Commission shall be necessary in regard to the selection`
  line `for appointment`
  line
  line `(a) to any acting or temporary post for a period not exceeding one year; or`
  line
  line `(b) to such ministerial posts as may from time to time be specified by ^4[^5[the Corporation]] in`
  line `consultation with the Commission when such posts are to be filled by promotion; or`
  line
  line `(c) to a post when at the time of such appointment the person to be appointed thereto is in the`
  line `service of the Central Government or a State Government in a class I post; or`
  line
  line `(d) to a permanent or temporary post, if the officer or other employee to be appointed is not likely`
  line `to hold that post for more than one year; or if such officer or other employee is likely to hold the post`
  line `for more than one year but not more than three years and the Commission advises that the`
  line `appointment may be made without consulting the Commission; ^6[or]`
  line
  line `^6[(e) to such other posts, as may, from time to time, be specified by the Central Government in`
  line `consultation with the Commission.]`
obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words and brackets "to the post of the General Manager (Electricity)" omitted by Act 67 of 1993, s. 71 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `2.The words and brackets "or the General Manager (Transport)" omitted by Act 71 of 1971, s. 7(b) and the Second Schedule`
  line `(w.e.f. 3-11-1971).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 55 of 1974, s. 10, for certain words and brackets (w.e.f. 10-1-1975).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "a Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 55 of 1974, s. 10 (w.e.f. 10-1-1975).`
obj_root_law_sections_97:
  sectionId (27224)
  sectionNo (97)
  orderNo 118
  title `Power of Commission to make regulations and reference to the Central Government in case of difference between the Commission and the Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_97_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27224&sectionno=97&orderno=118&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_97_content:
  string
  line `97. Power of Commission to make regulations and reference to the Central Government in case`
  line `of difference between the Commission and ^1[^2[the Corporation]].---(1) The Commission may make`
  line `regulations for the following matters, namely:`
  line
  line `(a) the procedure to be followed by the Commission in advertising posts, inviting applications,`
  line `scrutinizing the same and selecting candidates for interview;`
  line
  line `(b) the procedure to be followed by the Commission for selecting candidates for appointment and`
  line `by ^1[^2[the Corporation]] for consultation with the Commission;`
  line
  line `(c) any other matter which is incidental to, or necessary for, the purpose of consultation with the`
  line Commission.
  line
  line `(2) In the case of any difference of opinion between the Commission and the Corporation on any`
  line `matter, ^1[^2[the Corporation]] shall refer the matter to the Central Government and the decision of that`
  line `Government thereon shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "a Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_98:
  sectionId (27225)
  sectionNo (98)
  orderNo 119
  title `Power of Corporation to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_98_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27225&sectionno=98&orderno=119&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_98_content:
  string
  line `(1) ^1[^2[The Corporation]] may make regulations to`
  line `provide for any one or more of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the tenure of office, salaries and allowances, provident funds, pensions, gratuities, leave of`
  line `absence and other conditions of service of officers and other employees appointed under this Chapter;`
  line
  line `(b) the powers, duties and functions of the Municipal Secretary;`
  line
  line `(c) the qualifications of candidates for appointment to posts specified in sub-section (1) of section`
  line `89 and to posts dealt with in the first schedule of post referred to in sub-section (2) of section 90 and`
  line `the manner of selection for appointments to posts dealt with in the second schedule of posts referred`
  line `to in that sub-section;`
  line
  line `(d) the procedure to be followed in imposing any penalty under sub-section (1) of section 95,`
  line `suspension pending departmental inquiries before the imposition of such penalty and the authority by`
  line `whom such suspension may be ordered; the officer or authority to whom an appeal shall lie under`
  line `sub-section (4) of that section;`
  line
  line `(e) any matter which is incidental to, or necessary for, the purpose of regulating the appointment`
  line `and conditions of service of persons appointed to services and posts under ^3[^4[the Corporation]] and any`
  line `other matter for which in the opinion of ^3[^4[the Corporation]] provisions should be made by regulations.`
  line
  line `(2) No regulation under clause (c) of sub-section (1) shall be made except after consultation with the`
  line Commission.
obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “The Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “A Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_99:
  sectionId (27226)
  sectionNo (99)
  orderNo 120
  title `Constitution of the Municipal Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_99_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27226&sectionno=99&orderno=120&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_99_content:
  string
  line `The Municipal Fund`
  line
  line `(1) Save as otherwise provided in this Act,`
  line
  line `(a) all funds which immediately before the establishment of ^1[^2[the Corporation]] vested in any body`
  line `or local authority specified in the Second Schedule;`
  line
  line `(b) all moneys received by or on behalf of ^1[^2[the Corporation]] under the provisions of this Act or of`
  line `any other law for the time being in force, or under any contract;`
  line
  line `(c) all proceeds of the disposal of property by, or on behalf of, ^1[^2[the Corporation]];`
  line
  line `(d) all rents accruing from any property of ^1[^2[the Corporation]];`
  line
  line `(e) all moneys raised by any tax, rate or cess levied for the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(f) all fees collected and all fines levied under this Act or under any rule, regulation or bye-law`
  line `made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(g) all moneys received by or on behalf of ^1[^2[the Corporation]] from the Government or any`
  line `individual or association of individuals by way of grant or gift or deposit;`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
  line
  line `(i) all interests and profits arising from any investment of, or from any transaction in connection`
  line `with, any money belonging to ^1[^2[the Corporation]], including loans advanced under this Act; and`
  line
  line `(j) all moneys received by or on behalf of ^1[^2[the Corporation]] from any other source whatsoever,`
  line
  line `shall form one Fund to be entitled the Municipal Fund of Delhi (hereinafter in this Act referred to as the`
  line `Municipal Fund).`
  line
  line `^4[(2) The Municipal Fund shall be held by ^1[^2[the Corporation]] in trust for the purposes of this Act subject`
  line `to the provisions herein contained and a General Account relating to all moneys received by or on behalf`
  line `of ^1[^2[the Corporation]] shall be maintained.]`
obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "a Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Omitted by Act 67 of 1993, s. 72 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 72, ibid., for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_100:
  sectionId (27227)
  sectionNo (100)
  orderNo 121
  title `Municipal Fund to be kept in the State Bank of India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_100_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 14, for section 100 (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27227&sectionno=100&orderno=121&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_100_content:
  string
  line `^1[100. Municipal Fund to be kept in the State Bank of India.—All moneys payable to the credit of`
  line `the Municipal Fund in the General Account shall be received by the Commissioner and shall be forthwith`
  line `paid into the State Bank of India to the credit of the said Account which shall be entitled The General`
  line `Account of the Municipal Fund of the Corporation.]`
obj_root_law_sections_101:
  sectionId (27228)
  sectionNo (101)
  orderNo 122
  title `Operation of the Accounts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_101_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27228&sectionno=101&orderno=122&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_101_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise provided in this Act no payment shall be`
  line `made by the State Bank of India out of the Municipal Fund except on a cheque signed by both--`
  line
  line `(a) the Chief Accountant or an officer subordinate to him authorised by the standing Committee`
  line `in this behalf; and`
  line
  line ^1
  line `(b) the Commissioner or a Deputy Commissioner or an officer subordinate to the Commissioner`
  line `authorised by the Standing Committee in this behalf.]`
  line
  line `(2) Payment of any sum due by ^2[^3[the Corporation]] in excess of one hundred rupees shall be made by`
  line `means of a cheque signed in accordance with sub-section (1) and not in any other way.`
  line
  line `(3) Payments hot covered by sub-section (2) may be made in cash.`
obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 74, ibid., for clause (b) (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "a Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_102:
  sectionId (27229)
  sectionNo (102)
  orderNo 123
  title `Payments not to be made unless covered by a budget-grant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_102_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27229&sectionno=102&orderno=123&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_102_content:
  string
  line `No payment of any sum out of`
  line `the Municipal Fund shall be made unless the expenditure of the same is covered by a current budget-grant`
  line `and a sufficient balance of such budget grant is still available notwithstanding any reduction or transfer`
  line `thereof which may have been made under the provisions of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that this section shall not apply to payments made in the following classes of cases`
  line `namely:`
  line
  line `(a) refund of taxes and other moneys which are authorised under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) repayment of moneys belonging to contractors or other persons and held in deposit and of`
  line `moneys collected or credited to the Municipal Fund by mistake;`
  line
  line `(c) sums payable in any of the following circumstances--`
  line
  line `(i) under orders of the Central Government on failure of ^1[^2[the Corporation]] to take any action as`
  line `required by that Government; or`
  line
  line `(ii) under any other enactment for the time being in force; or`
  line
  line `(iii) under the decree or order of a civil or criminal court passed against ^1[^2[the Corporation]] ; or`
  line
  line `(iv) under a compromise of any claim, suit or other legal proceedings; or`
  line
  line `(v) on account of cost incurred in taking immediate action by ^1[^2[the Corporation]] or any of the`
  line `municipal authorities to avert a sudden threat of danger to the property of ^1[^2[the Corporation]] or to`
  line `human life;`
  line
  line `(d) temporary payments for works urgently required by the Central Government in the public`
  line interest;
  line
  line `(e) sums payable as compensation under this Act or under any rules, regulations or bye-laws`
  line `made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(f) expenses incurred by ^1[^2[the Corporation]] on special measures taken on the outbreak of dangerous`
  line diseases.
obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_103:
  sectionId (27230)
  sectionNo (103)
  orderNo 124
  title `Duty of persons signing cheques.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_103_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27230&sectionno=103&orderno=124&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_103_content:
  string
  line `Before any person signs a cheque in accordance with`
  line `section 101, he shall satisfy himself that the sum for which the cheque is drawn is either—`
  line
  line `(a) required for a purpose or work specifically sanctioned by the proper authority and covered by`
  line `a current budget-grant, or`
  line
  line `(b) required for any payment referred to, or specified in section 102.`
obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_104:
  sectionId (27231)
  sectionNo (104)
  orderNo 125
  title `Procedure when money not covered by a budget-grant is expended.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_104_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27231&sectionno=104&orderno=125&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_104_content:
  string
  line `Whenever any sum is`
  line `expended under ^1`
  line `[clause (c), (e) or (f)] of the proviso to section 102 the Commissioner, ^2`
  line `[shall forthwith`
  line `communicate the circumstances to the Standing Committee] ^3`
  line `*** which may take, or recommend to the`
  line `Corporation to take, such action under the provisions of this Act as shall, in the circumstances appear`
  line `possible and expedient for covering the amount of the additional expenditure.`
obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 71 of 1971, s. 7(b) and the Second Schedule, for "clauses (c), (e) or (f)" (w.e.f. 3-11-1971).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 75, for certain words and brackets (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `3. The words "or the Delhi Transport Committee" omitted by Act 71 of 1971, s. 7(b) and the Second Schedule`
  line `(w.e.f. 3-11-1971).`
obj_root_law_sections_105:
  sectionId (27232)
  sectionNo (105)
  orderNo 126
  title `Application of Municipal Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_105_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27232&sectionno=105&orderno=126&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_105_content:
  string
  line `(1) The moneys from time to time credited to the Municipal`
  line `Fund shall be applied in payment of all sums, charges and costs necessary for carrying out the provisions`
  line `of this Act, and of the rules, regulations and bye-laws made thereunder, or of which payment is duly`
  line `directed, sanctioned or required by or under any of the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Such moneys shall likewise be applied in payment of all sums payable out of the Municipal Fund`
  line `under any other enactment for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_106:
  sectionId (27233)
  sectionNo (106)
  orderNo 127
  title `Temporary payments from the Municipal Fund for works urgently required for the public service.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_106_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27233&sectionno=106&orderno=127&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_106_content:
  string
  line `(1) On the written requisition of a Secretary to the Central Government, ^1`
  line `[the Commissioner],`
  line `may at any time undertake the execution of any work certified by such Secretary to be urgently required`
  line `in public interest, and for this purpose may temporarily make payments from the Municipal Fund so far as`
  line `the same can be met without unduly interfering with the regular work of the municipal government.`
  line
  line `(2) The cost of work so executed and of the establishment engaged in executing the same shall be`
  line `paid by the Central Government and credited to the Municipal Fund.`
  line
  line `(3) On the receipt of any requisition under sub-section (1) the Commissioner ^2`
  line `*** ^3`
  line `*** shall`
  line `forthwith forward a copy thereof to ^4[^5[the Corporation together with a report of the steps taken by him in`
  line `pursuance of the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 76, for certain words and brackets (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `2. The words and brackets "or as the case may be, the General Manager (Electricity)" omitted by s. 76,`
  line `ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `3. The words or the General Manager omitted by Act 71 of 1971, s. 7(b) and the Second Schedule (w.e.f. 3-11-1971).`
  line
  line `4Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `5Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "a Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_107:
  sectionId (27234)
  sectionNo (107)
  orderNo 128
  title `Investment of surplus moneys.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_107_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27234&sectionno=107&orderno=128&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_107_content:
  string
  line `^1[107. Investment of surplus moneys.--(1) Surplus money standing at the credit of General Account`
  line `of the Municipal Fund which cannot immediately be applied for the purposes specified in section 105`
  line `shall be deposited in the State Bank of India or in such scheduled bank or banks as ^2[^3[the Corporation]] may`
  line `select or be invested in public securities.`
  line
  line `(2) The loss, if any, arising from such deposit of investment shall be debited to the General Accounts`
  line `of the Municipal Fund.`
obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 77, for section 107 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_107_a:
  sectionId (27235)
  sectionNo 107A
  orderNo 129
  title `Constitution of Finance Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_107_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_107_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27235&sectionno=107A&orderno=129&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_107_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[107A. Constitution of Finance Commission.-- (1) The Administrator shall, as soon as may be,`
  line `within one year from the commencement of the Constitution (Seventy-third Amendment) Act, 1992 and`
  line `thereafter at the expiration of every fifth year constitute a Finance Commission to review the financial`
  line `position of ^2[^3[the Corporation]] and to make recommendations to the Administrator as to,--`
  line
  line `(a) the principles which should govern,--`
  line
  line `(i) the distribution between the National Capital Territory of Delhi and ^2[^3[the Corporation]] of the`
  line `net proceeds of the taxes, duties, tolls and fees leviable by the National Capital Territory of Delhi`
  line `which may be divided between them.`
  line
  line `(ii) the determination of the taxes, duties, tolls and fees which may be assigned to or`
  line `appropriated by ^2[^3[the Corporation]] ;`
  line
  line `(iii) the grants-in-aid to ^2[^3[the Corporation]] from the consolidated fund of the National Capital`
  line `Territory of Delhi;`
  line
  line `(b) the measures needed to improve the financial position of ^2[^3[the Corporation]];`
  line
  line `(c) any other matter referred to the Finance Commission by the Administrator in the interest of`
  line `sound finance of ^2[^3[the Corporation]].`
  line
  line `(2) The Legislature of the National Capital Territory of Delhi, may by law provide for the`
  line `composition of the Commission, the qualifications which shall be required for appointment of members`
  line `thereof, and the manner in which they shall be selected.`
  line
  line `(3) The Commission shall determine their procedure and shall have such powers in the performance`
  line `of their functions as the Legislature of the National Capital Territory of Delhi, may, by law, confer on`
  line them.
  line
  line `(4) The Administrator shall cause every recommendation made by the Commission under this section`
  line `together with an explanatory memorandum as to the action taken thereon to be laid before the Legislative`
  line `Assembly of the National Capital Territory of Delhi.]`
obj_root_law_sections_107_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 77, for section 107 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `2.Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `3.Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_108:
  sectionId (27236)
  sectionNo (108)
  orderNo 130
  title `Constitution of special funds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_108_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27236&sectionno=108&orderno=130&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_108_content:
  string
  line `(1) ^1[^2[The Corporation]] shall constitute such special fund or funds`
  line `as may be prescribed by regulations and such other funds necessary for the purposes of this Act as may be`
  line `so prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The constitution and disposal of such funds shall be effected in the manner laid down by`
  line regulations.
obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "Every Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_109:
  sectionId (27237)
  sectionNo (109)
  orderNo 131
  title `Adoption of budget estimates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_109_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27237&sectionno=109&orderno=131&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_109_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[(1) ^2[^3[The Corporation]] shall, on or before the 31st day of`
  line `March of every year, adopt for the ensuing year the budget estimate which shall be an estimate of the`
  line `income and expenditure of ^4[^5[the Corporation]] to be received and incurred on account of the municipal`
  line `government of ^6[^7[Delhi]].]`
  line
  line `(2) On or before the 15th day of February of each year ^4[^5[the Corporation]] shall determine the rates at`
  line `which various municipal taxes, rates and cesses shall be levied in the next following year and save as`
  line `otherwise provided in this Act the rates so fixed shall not be subsequently altered for the year for which`
  line `they have been fixed.`
  line
  line `(3) Budget estimates shall be prepared in such form as may be approved by the Standing Committee`
  line `and presented and adopted in such manner and shall provide for all such matters as are prescribed by`
  line `regulations made in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 78, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `3Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "Every Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "a Corporation"(w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `6.Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for "the area of the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 10 of 2011, s. 2, for "Delhi" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_110:
  sectionId (27238)
  sectionNo (110)
  orderNo 132
  title `Power of Corporation to alter budget estimates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_110_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_110_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27238&sectionno=110&orderno=132&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_110_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[(1) On the recommendation of the`
  line `Standing Committee in respect of the budget estimate, ^2[^3[the Corporation]] may from time to time, during the`
  line year,--
  line
  line `(i) increase the amount of budget grant under any head;`
  line
  line `(ii) make an additional budget grant for the purpose of meeting any special or unforeseen`
  line `requirement arising during the said year; or`
  line
  line `(iii) reduce the amount of the budget grant under any head:`
  line
  line `Provided that due regard shall be had to all the requirements of this act and in making any increase or`
  line `any additional budget grant the estimated cash balance at the close of the year shall not be reduced below`
  line `the sum of one lakh rupees or such higher sum as ^2[^3[the Corporation]] may determine in respect of the budget`
  line estimate.]
  line
  line `(2) Every increase in a budget-grant and every additional budget-grant made in any year under subsection`
  line `(1) shall be deemed to be included in the budget estimates finally adopted for that year.`
  line
  line `(3) The Standing Committee may from time to time during the year--`
  line
  line `(a) reduce the amount of a budget-grant; or`
  line
  line `(b) Sanction the transfer of any amount within a budget-grant:`
  line
  line `Provided that every reduction if it exceeds five hundred rupees shall be reported forthwith by`
  line `Standing Committee to ^2[^3[the Corporation]] and the Standing Committee and the Commissioner shall give`
  line `effect to any order that may be passed by ^2[^3[the Corporation]] in relation thereto.`
  line
  line `(4) The Commissioner may from time to time during the year, sanction the transfer of any amount not`
  line `exceeding five thousand rupees within a minor head if such transfer does not involve a recurring liability:`
  line
  line `Provided that every such transfer, if it exceeds five hundred rupees, shall be reported forthwith by the`
  line `Commissioner to the Standing Committee and the Commissioner shall give effect to any order that may`
  line `be passed by that Committee in relation thereto,`
  line
  line ^4
  line `* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_110_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 79, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "a Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `4. Omitted by Act 67 of 1993, s. 79 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_111:
  sectionId (27239)
  sectionNo (111)
  orderNo 133
  title `Power of Corporation to re-adjust income and expenditure during the year.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_111_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27239&sectionno=111&orderno=133&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_111_content:
  string
  line `(1) If at any`
  line `time during the year it appears to ^1[^2[the Corporationo]] that, notwithstanding any reduction of budget-grant that`
  line `has been made under section 110 the income of the Municipal Fund during the same year will not suffice`
  line `to meet the expenditure sanctioned in the budget estimates of that year and to leave at the close of the`
  line `year the cash balance specified in or determined under the proviso to sub-section (1) of section 110, then,`
  line `it shall be incumbent on ^1[^2[the Corporation]] to sanction forthwith any measures which it may consider`
  line `necessary for adjusting the year's income to the expenditure.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of sub-section (1), ^1[^2[the Corporation]] may either diminish the sanctioned`
  line `expenditure of the year so far as it may be possible so to do with regard to all the requirements of this Act,`
  line `or have recourse to supplementary taxation under section 151 or to an increase of the rates of cesses, fees,`
  line `fares and other charges leviable under this Act, or to adopt all or any of those methods.`
obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_112:
  sectionId (27240)
  sectionNo (112)
  orderNo 134
  title `Provisions as to unexpended budget-grant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_112_content
  footnotes `1. Certain words omitted by Act 67 of 1993, s. 80 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27240&sectionno=112&orderno=134&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_112_content:
  string
  line `If the whole or arty part of any budget-grant`
  line `included in the budget estimates for a year remains unexpended at the close of that year, and the amount`
  line `thereof has not been taken into account in the opening balance entered in the budget estimates of any`
  line `of the next two following years, the Standing Committee ^1`
  line `*** may sanction the expenditure of such`
  line `budget-grant or the unexpended portion thereof during the next two following years for the completion of`
  line `the purpose or object for which the budget-grant was originally made and not for any other purpose or`
  line object.
obj_root_law_sections_113:
  sectionId (27241)
  sectionNo (113)
  orderNo 135
  title `Taxes to be imposed by the Corporation under this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_113_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_113_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27241&sectionno=113&orderno=135&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_113_content:
  string
  line `(1) ^1[^2[The Corporation]] shall, for the`
  line `purposes of this Act, levy the following taxes, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) property taxes;`
  line
  line `(b) a tax on vehicles and animals;`
  line
  line `(c) a theatre-tax;`
  line
  line `(d) a tax on advertisements other than advertisements published in the newspapers;`
  line
  line `(e) a duty on the transfer of property; and`
  line
  line `(f) a tax on buildings payable along with the application for sanction of the building plan.`
  line
  line `(2) In addition to the taxes specified in sub-section (1), ^3[^4[the Corporation]] may, for the purposes of this`
  line `Act, levy any of the following taxes, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) an education cess;`
  line
  line `(b) a local rate on land revenues;`
  line
  line `(c) a tax on professions, trades, callings and employments;`
  line
  line `(d) a tax on the consumption, ^5`
  line `[sale or supply] of electricity;`
  line
  line `(e) a betterment tax on the increase in urban land values caused by the execution of any`
  line `development or improvement work;`
  line
  line `(f) a tax on boats; and`
  line
  line `(g) tolls.`
  line
  line `(3) The taxes specified in sub-section (1) sub-section (2) shall be levied, assessed and collected in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of this Act and the bye-laws made thereunder.`
  line
  line `^6[Explanation.In this Chapter, person shall, unless the context otherwise requires, include a`
  line `company, a society registered under any law for the time being in force, an association of individuals, a`
  line `partnership, and a Hindu undivided family.]`
obj_root_law_sections_113_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 "The Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "A Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "a Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 42 of 1961, s. 7, for "or sale" (w.e.f. 12-9-1961).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Delhi Act 6 of 2003, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-8-2003).`
obj_root_law_sections_114:
  sectionId (27242)
  sectionNo (114)
  orderNo 136
  title `Components of property tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_114_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 6 of 2003, s. 5, for section 114 (w.e.f. 1-8-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27242&sectionno=114&orderno=136&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_114_content:
  string
  line `^1[114. Components of property tax.Save as otherwise provided in this Act, the property taxes shall`
  line `be levied on lands and buildings in Delhi and shall consist of the following, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) a building tax, and`
  line
  line `(b) a vacant land tax.]`
obj_root_law_sections_114_a:
  sectionId (67068)
  sectionNo 114A
  orderNo 137
  title `Building tax.`
  content `^1114A. Building tax.—For any building, the building tax shall be equal to the rate of building tax as may be prescribed by ^2[^3[a Corporation]] under section 114D multiplied by the annual value of the covered space of building determined under sub-section (1) of section 116E or section 116F.]`
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 6 of 2003, s. 5, for section 114 (w.e.f. 1-8-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=67068&sectionno=114A&orderno=137&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_114_b:
  sectionId (67069)
  sectionNo 114B
  orderNo 138
  title `Rebate for senior citizens, women and physically challenged persons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_114_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_114_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=67069&sectionno=114B&orderno=138&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_114_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[114B. Rebate for senior citizens, women and physically challenged persons.---In the case of any`
  line `self-occupied residential building singly owned by a man who is sixty-five years or more in age or by a`
  line `woman irrespective of her age or a physically challenged person as may be defined in the bye-laws,`
  line `irrespective of age, or jointly owned by any of these categories, ^2[^3[the Corporation]] may specify a rebate`
  line `on the building tax not exceeding thirty per cent of the tax due on the covered space of such building up to`
  line `one hundred square metres of the covered space:`
  line
  line `Provided that such rebate shall not be available for more than one residential building within the`
  line `jurisdiction of the National Capital Territory of Delhi.]`
obj_root_law_sections_114_b_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 6 of 2003, s. 5, for section 114 (w.e.f. 1-8-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "a Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_114_c:
  sectionId (67070)
  sectionNo 114C
  orderNo 139
  title `Vacant land tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_114_c_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_114_c_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=67070&sectionno=114C&orderno=139&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_114_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[114C. Vacant land tax.—The vacant land tax in respect of any premises shall be equal to the rate of`
  line `vacant land tax as may be specified by ^2[^3[the Corporation]] under section 114E multiplied by the annual`
  line `value of the vacant land determined under sub-section (3) of section 116E;`
  line
  line `Provided that where there is any construction on the land and the area of plinth of such building is in`
  line `excess of such percentage of the area of the plot, as may be prescribed in the bye-laws, no vacant land tax`
  line `shall be levied.`
obj_root_law_sections_114_c_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 6 of 2003, s. 5, for section 114 (w.e.f. 1-8-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_114_d:
  sectionId (67071)
  sectionNo 114D
  orderNo 140
  title `Rate of building tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_114_d_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_114_d_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=67071&sectionno=114D&orderno=140&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_114_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[114D. Rate of building tax.--Save as otherwise provided in this Act, the base rate of property tax on`
  line `buildings in Delhi shall be between a minimum of six per cent, and a maximum of twenty per cent, of the`
  line `annual values of such buildings as may be specified by ^2[^3[the Corporation]] from time to time:`
  line `Provided that ^2[^3[the Corporation]] may, at any time, prescribe fixed rates between the minimum and`
  line `the maximum rates of tax as aforesaid for different colonies or for different groups of buildings in such`
  line `colonies:`
  line
  line `Provided further that ^2[^3[the Corporation]] may also introduce graduated rates of tax within the`
  line `minimum and the maximum rates of tax as aforesaid on the basis of straight line system or any other system`
  line `as may be specified by ^2[^3[the Corporation]].`
  line
  line `Explanation.---Straight line system shall mean the system in which the rate of tax is equivalent to the`
  line `annual value of a property (X) divided by the minimum annual value (X1) and Y being added to the quotient so arrived, Y being the difference between the maximum rate of tax and the quotient of maximum (X2) and`
  line `minimum (X1) annual values.`
obj_root_law_sections_114_d_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 6 of 2003, s. 5, for section 114 (w.e.f. 1-8-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "a Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_114_e:
  sectionId (67072)
  sectionNo 114E
  orderNo 141
  title `Rate of vacant land tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_114_e_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_114_e_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=67072&sectionno=114E&orderno=141&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_114_e_content:
  string
  line `[^1114E. Rate of vacant land tax.—Save as otherwise provided in this Act, the rate of tax on vacant lands`
  line `in Delhi shall be between a minimum of six per cent, and a maximum of twenty per cent, of the annual`
  line `value of such lands as may be specified by ^2[^3[the Corporation]] from time to time.`
  line
  line `Provided that ^2[^3[the Corporation]] may, at any time, specify fixed rates between the minimum and the`
  line `maximum rates of tax as aforesaid for different colonies or for different groups of vacant lands in such`
  line colonies.
  line
  line `Provided further that ^2[^3[the Corporation]] may also introduce graduated rates of tax within the`
  line `minimum and the maximum rates of tax as aforesaid on the basis of straight line system or any other system`
  line `as may be specified by ^2[^3[the Corporation]].`
  line
  line `Explanation.—Straight line system' shall have the same meaning as in the Explanation to the second`
  line `proviso to section 114D.]`
obj_root_law_sections_114_e_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 6 of 2003, s. 5, for section 114 (w.e.f. 1-8-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_115:
  sectionId (27243)
  sectionNo (115)
  orderNo 142
  title `Exemption of vacant lands and buildings from property tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_115_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_115_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27243&sectionno=115&orderno=142&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_115_content:
  string
  line `^1[115. Exemption of vacant lands and buildings from property tax.(1) Save as otherwise provided`
  line `in this Act, property tax shall be levied on all vacant lands and buildings in Delhi except`
  line
  line `(i) vacant lands and buildings (other than dwelling houses) exclusively used for agricultural`
  line `purposes in accordance with the guidelines prescribed in the bye-laws;`
  line
  line `(ii) any vacant land or building included in any village a badi, which is occupied for residential`
  line `purpose by any original owner or his legal heir, subject to a maximum of one hundred square metres of`
  line `covered space;`
  line
  line `(iii) vacant lands or buildings or portions thereof, exclusively used for the purpose of public`
  line worship;
  line
  line `(iv) vacant land or buildings or portions thereof, exclusively occupied and used, with the approval`
  line `of ^2[^3[the Corporation]], for the purpose of public charity as may be specified in the bye-laws or for the`
  line `purpose of medical relief to, or education of, the poor, free of charge;`
  line
  line `(v) vacant lands or buildings exclusively used for the purpose of public burial or as cremation`
  line `ground, or any other place used for the disposal of the dead, duly registered under this Act;`
  line
  line `(vi) such heritage lands or buildings as are specifically notified for exemption by ^2[^3[the Corporation]] as also such premises as are so specified by the Archeological Survey of India;`
  line
  line `(vii) vacant lands and buildings owned exclusively by war widows, gallantry award winners in`
  line `Defence Forces, Police and Paramilitary Forces as also civilians who have received bravery awards of`
  line `the highest order from the Government including Annual Bravery Awards given by the President:`
  line
  line `Provided that the exemption shall be subject to the condition that`
  line
  line `(a) The premises in question is in self-occupation for residential use and no portion thereof is`
  line `let out for any purpose, whatsoever;`
  line
  line `(b) In case the person concerned has more than one property in Delhi, the exemption shall be`
  line `applicable to only one property which is permanently used for self-residence;`
  line
  line `(c) The benefit of exemption shall be limited to the life time of the person concerned, except`
  line `where the award has been granted posthumously, in which case the exemption will be granted to`
  line `the widow of the gallantry award winner;`
  line
  line `(viii) vacant lands and buildings owned by, or vested in, ^2[^3[the Corporation]] but not leased out or`
  line `rented out, and in respect of which the property tax, if levied, would, under the provisions of this Act,`
  line `be leviable primarily on ^2[^3[the Corporation]].`
  line
  line `Explanation-- For the purpose of clause (iii), no portion of any vacant land or building where any trade`
  line `or business is carried on, or which is used for residential purpose, or in respect of which any rent or income`
  line `is derived, shall be deemed not to be exclusively used for public worship and such portion of such vacant`
  line `land or building shall be assessed as a separate unit of assessment.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commissioner shall cause to be maintained a register showing separately the vacant lands and`
  line `buildings exempted from the property tax under sub-section (1) in such form as may be specified by ^2[^3[theCorporation]], and such register shall be open to the public for inspection.`
  line
  line `(3) ^2[^3[the Corporation]] may levy on such vacant lands and covered space of buildings as are exempt`
  line `from the property tax, service charge on such scale, as may be provided under this Act or as prescribed by ^2[^3[the Corporation]]:`
  line
  line `Provided that the service charge so levied shall not be less than seventy five per cent of the amount that`
  line `would have been payable as property tax for the covered space of the building or the vacant land as referred`
  line `to in section 114D or section 114E.`
obj_root_law_sections_115_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 6 of 2002, s. 7, for section 115 (w.e.f. 1-8-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 the Corporation (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for a Corporation (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `4. Certain words omitted by s. 82, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_115_a:
  sectionId (67073)
  sectionNo 115A
  orderNo 143
  title `Unit of assessment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_115_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_115_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=67073&sectionno=115A&orderno=143&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_115_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[115A. Unit of assessment.—(1) Every building and every vacant land shall be assessed as a single`
  line `unit:`
  line
  line `Provided that where portions of any building or vacant land are separately owned so as to be entirely`
  line `independent and capable of separate enjoyment, notwithstanding the fact that access to such separate`
  line `portions is made through a common passage or a common stair case, as the case may be, such separately`
  line `owned portions may be assessed separately.`
  line
  line `(2) All buildings, to the extent they are contiguous or are within the same cartilage or are on the same`
  line `foundation and are owned by the same owner or co-owners as an undivided property, shall be treated as`
  line `one unit for the purpose of assessment under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that if any such building is sub-divided into separate shares which are not entirely independent`
  line `and capable of separate enjoyment, the Commissioner may, on application from the owners or the coowners, apportion the valuation and assessment of such building among the co-owners according to the`
  line `value of their respective shares, treating the entire building as a single unit.`
  line
  line `(3) Each residential unit with its percentage of the undivided interest in the common areas and facilities,`
  line `constructed or purchased and owned by, or under the control of, any housing co-operative society registered`
  line `under any law regulating co-operative housing for the time being in force, shall be assessed separately.`
  line
  line `(4) Each apartment and its percentage of the undivided interest in the common areas and facilities in a`
  line `building within the meaning of any law regulating apartment ownership for the time being in force, shall`
  line `be assessed separately.`
  line
  line `(5) If the ownership of any vacant land or building or any portion thereof is sub-divided into separate`
  line `shares, or if more than one adjoining vacant land or building or portion thereof comes under one ownership`
  line `by amalgamation, the Commissioner may, on an application from the owner or the co-owners, as the case`
  line `may be, separate, or amalgamate, as the case may be, such vacant land or building or portion thereof so as`
  line `to ensure conformity with the provisions of this section.`
  line
  line `(6) Notwithstanding any assessment made in respect of any vacant lands or buildings before the`
  line `commencement of the Delhi Municipal Corporation (Amendment) Act, 2003, the Commissioner may, on`
  line `his own or otherwise, amalgamate, or separate, or continue to assess, such vacant lands or buildings or`
  line `portions thereof so as to ensure conformity with the provisions of this section.`
  line
  line `(7) The Commissioner shall, upon an application made in this behalf by an owner, lessee, sub-lessee,`
  line `or occupier of any vacant land or building and upon payment of such fee as may be prescribed in the byelaws, furnish to such owner, lessee, sub-lessee, or occupier, as the case may be, information regarding the`
  line `apportionment of the property tax on such vacant land or building among the several occupiers of such`
  line `vacant land or building for the current period of assessment or for any preceding period of assessment:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall prevent ^2[^3[the Corporation]] from recovering the arrear`
  line `dues on account of property tax from any such person, jointly or severally.`
obj_root_law_sections_115_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1.Subs. by Delhi Act 6 of 2002, s. 7, for section 115 (w.e.f. 1-8-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_116:
  sectionId (27244)
  sectionNo (116)
  orderNo 144
  title `Constitution of Municipal Valuation Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_116_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_116_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27244&sectionno=116&orderno=144&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_116_content:
  string
  line `^1[116. Constitution of Municipal Valuation Committee.--(1) The Government shall as soon as may`
  line `be after the commencement of the Delhi Municipal Corporation (Amendment) Act, 2003, and thereafter at`
  line `the expiration of every third year, constitute by notification in the Official Gazette, a Municipal Valuation`
  line Committee.
  line
  line `(2) The Municipal Valuation Committee shall consist of--`
  line
  line `(a) a Chairperson, and`
  line
  line `(b) such other members, being not less than two and not more than six, as the Government may`
  line determine.
  line
  line `(3) The Chairperson and the other members of the Municipal Valuation Committee shall be appointed`
  line `by the Government and the qualifications and experience requisite for their appointment, the manner of`
  line `selection, and other terms and conditions of service including salaries and allowances, tenure of office shall`
  line `be such as the Government may by rules determine.`
  line
  line `(4) The salaries and allowances of the Chairperson and the other members of the Municipal Valuation`
  line `Committee shall be paid from the Municipal Fund.`
  line
  line `(5) The functions of the Municipal Valuation Committee shall be`
  line
  line `(a) to make recommendations to ^2[^3[the Corporation]] on matters relating to classification of vacant`
  line `lands and buildings in any ward of Delhi into colonies and groups of lands and buildings and fixation`
  line `of base value per unit area of vacant land or per unit area of covered space of building and factors for`
  line `increase or decrease, or for no increase or decrease, thereof;`
  line
  line `(b) to consider objections under section 116C, and to make recommendation thereon; and`
  line
  line `(c) to perform such other functions as the Government may require.]`
obj_root_law_sections_116_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 6 of 2003, s. 8, for section 116 (w.e.f. 1-8-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "a Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_116_a:
  sectionId (67074)
  sectionNo 116A
  orderNo 145
  title `Classification of vacant lands and buildings into colonies and groups and specification of base unit area values therefore.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_116_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_116_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=67074&sectionno=116A&orderno=145&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_116_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[116A. Classification of vacant lands and buildings into colonies and groups and specification of`
  line `base unit area values therefore.---(1) The Municipal Valuation Committee shall recommend the`
  line `classification of the vacant lands and buildings in any ward of Delhi, referred to in section 5, into colonies`
  line `and groups of lands and buildings after taking into account the following parameters:--`
  line
  line `(a) settlement pattern such as plotted housing, group housing, colony with flats only, urban village,`
  line `unauthorized colony, resettlement colony, rural village and non-residential areas;`
  line
  line `(b) availability of civic and social infrastructure;`
  line
  line `(c) access to roads;`
  line
  line `(d) access to district centres, local shopping centres, convenience shopping centres, and other`
  line markets;
  line
  line `(e) land prices as may, from time to time, be notified by ^2[the ^3[Government]] or the Delhi`
  line `Development Authority;`
  line
  line `(f) use-wise category of any building including residential building, business building, mercantile`
  line `building, building for recreation and sports purposes, industrial building, hazardous building and public`
  line `purpose building including educational, medical and such other institutional building and farmhouse,`
  line `as may be specified by ^4[^5[the Corporation]];`
  line
  line `(g) in the case of buildings used for business, mercantile, recreation and sports, industrial,`
  line `hazardous, storage or farmhouse purposes, the location of such buildings adjacent to such categories of`
  line `streets, as may, subject to the provisions of sub-section (2), be specified by ^4[^5[the Corporation]];`
  line
  line `(h) the types of buildings which may be classified as pucca, semi-pucca or katcha, as may be`
  line `specified by 1`
  line `^4[^5[the Corporation]];`
  line
  line `(i) the age-wise grouping of buildings as may be specified by ^4[^5[the Corporation]]; and`
  line
  line `(j) such other parameters as may be considered relevant by the Municipal Valuation Committee.`
  line
  line `(2) The Municipal Valuation Committee shall recommend, group wise,--`
  line
  line `(a) the base unit area value of any owner-occupied vacant land, or any wholly owner-occupied`
  line `building of pucca structure, constructed in the year 2000 or thereafter, and put to exclusive residential`
  line `use, and`
  line
  line `(b) the factor for increasing or decreasing, or for not increasing or decreasing, the base unit area`
  line `values specified in clause (a), separately in respect of each of the parameters of type of colony, use,`
  line `age, type of structure and occupancy status of the vacant land or building, as the case may be, subject`
  line `to a lower limit of zero point five and upper limit of ten point zero.`
obj_root_law_sections_116_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Delhi Act 6 of 2003, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-8-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 "the Government" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "Government" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "a Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_116_b:
  sectionId (67075)
  sectionNo 116B
  orderNo 146
  title `Notification of classification of vacant lands and buildings into colonies and groups and specification of base unit area values therefore and factors for increase or decrease.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_116_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_116_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=67075&sectionno=116B&orderno=146&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_116_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[116B. Notification of classification of vacant lands and buildings into colonies and groups and specification of base unit area values therefore and factors for increase or decrease.--(1) ^2[^3[The Corporation[[ shall, having regard to the recommendations of the Municipal Valuation Committee, declare its intention to classify vacant lands and buildings in each ward into such colonies and groups of lands and buildings as ^4[^5[the Corporation]] may, by public notice, specify, and shall also specify in such public notice the base value it proposes to specify per unit area of vacant land and per unit area of covered space of building within each such group and also the factors for increasing or decreasing, or for not increasing or decreasing, the base unit area values of vacant lands and buildings referred to in clause (b) of sub-section (2) of section 116A.`
  line
  line `(2) ^2[^3[The Corporation]] shall, on receipt of any representation from any group in any colony affected by such classification of lands or buildings into any group or specification of the base unit area values of vacant lands or covered space of buildings within such groups, and the factors for increasing or decreasing, or for not increasing or decreasing, such unit area values of vacant lands or covered space of buildings, refer such representation to the Municipal Valuation Committee for reconsideration, and the decision of the Municipal Valuation Committee thereon shall, subject to the provisions of section 116K, be binding on ^4[^5[the Corporation]].`
obj_root_law_sections_116_b_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Delhi Act 6 of 2003, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-8-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "A Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "a Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_116_c:
  sectionId (67076)
  sectionNo 116C
  orderNo 147
  title `Objection to classification of vacant lands and buildings into colonies and groups and fixation of base unit area values and factors for increasing or decreasing such base unit area values`
  content obj_root_law_sections_116_c_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_116_c_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=67076&sectionno=116C&orderno=147&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_116_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[116C. Objection to classification of vacant lands and buildings into colonies and groups and fixation of base unit area values and factors for increasing or decreasing such base unit area values.—(1) If any owner or occupier of any vacant land or building in any ward in respect of which a public notice has been issued under section 116B, has any objection to the manner of classification of any group or groups, or the base value per unit area of vacant land or the base value per unit area of covered space of building in any group, or the factors as specified in clause (b) of sub-section (2) of section 116A, he may submit to such officer of ^2[^3[the Corporation]] as may be authorized by ^2[^3[the Corporation]] in this behalf his objection in such form, and containing such particulars, as may be prescribed, within thirty days from the date of publication of such public notice, and such objection shall be considered by the Municipal Valuation Committee, after giving the person submitting the objection an opportunity of being heard.`
  line
  line `(2) The procedure for hearing and disposal of objections shall be such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) On the expiry of thirty days from the date of publication of the public notice under section 116B and after considering the recommendation of the Municipal Valuation Committee on the objections, if any, in accordance with the provisions of this section ^2[^3[the Corporation]] shall, by public notice, specify group wise the base unit area value of vacant land and the base unit area value of covered space of building and the factors referred to in clause (b) of sub-section (2) of section 116A:`
  line
  line `Provided that ^2[^3[the Corporation]] shall not alter the unit area values recommended by the Municipal valuation committee without the approval of the government.`
obj_root_law_sections_116_c_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Delhi Act 6 of 2003, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-8-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_116_d:
  sectionId (67077)
  sectionNo 116D
  orderNo 148
  title `Final base unit area values of vacant land and of covered space of building.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_116_d_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_116_d_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=67077&sectionno=116D&orderno=148&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_116_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[116D. final base unit area values of vacant land and of covered space of building.—(1) subject to`
  line `the provisions of section 169, the base unit area value of vacant land and the base unit area value of covered`
  line `space of building in any group, as may be specified under sub-section (3) of section 116c, shall be final.`
  line
  line `(2) ^2[^3[the corporation]] shall publish the final base unit area value of vacant land and the final base unit`
  line `area value of covered space of building as aforesaid and the factors used for increasing or decreasing, or`
  line `for not increasing or decreasing, the final base unit area values as aforesaid and shall make them available`
  line `for inspection by any person free of charge. copies thereof shall also be made available to any person on`
  line `payment of cost.`
obj_root_law_sections_116_d_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Delhi Act 6 of 2003, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-8-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “A Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_116_e:
  sectionId (67078)
  sectionNo 116E
  orderNo 149
  title `Determination of annual value of covered space of building and of vacant land.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_116_e_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_116_e_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=67078&sectionno=116E&orderno=149&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_116_e_content:
  string
  line `^1[116E. determination of annual value of covered space of building and of vacant land.(1) the`
  line `annual value of any covered space of building in any ward shall be the amount arrived at by multiplying`
  line `the total area bf such covered space of building by the final base unit area value of such covered space and`
  line `the relevant factors as referred to in clause (b) of sub-section (2) of section 116 a.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- covered space, in relation to a building, shall mean the total floor area in all the floor`
  line `thereof, including the thickness of walls, and shall include the spaces of covered verandah and courtyard,`
  line `gangway, garage, common service area, staircase, and balcony including any area projected beyond the plot`
  line `boundary and such other space as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) ^2[^3[the corporation]] may require the total area of the covered space of building as aforesaid to be`
  line `certified by an architect registered under the architects act, 1972 (20 of 1972), or any licensed`
  line `architect,116a. classification of vacant lands and buildings into colonies and groups and specification of`
  line `base unit area values therefor subject to such conditions as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) the annual value of any vacant land in any ward shall be the amount arrived at by multiplying the`
  line `total area of such vacant land by the final base unit area value of such land and the relevant factors as`
  line `referred to in clause (b) of subsection (2) of section 116a.`
  line
  line `(4) if, in the case of any vacant land or covered space of building, any portion thereof is subject to`
  line `different final base unit area values or is not self-occupied, the annual value of each such portion shall be`
  line `computed separately, and the sum of such annual values shall be the annual value for such vacant land or`
  line `covered space of building, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_116_e_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Delhi Act 6 of 2003, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-8-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 the Corporation (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for a Corporation (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_116_f:
  sectionId (67733)
  sectionNo 116F
  orderNo 150
  title `Determination of annual value of building where land is exempted from property tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_116_f_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Delhi Act 6 of 2003, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-8-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=67733&sectionno=116F&orderno=150&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_116_f_content:
  string
  line `^1116F. determination of annual value of building where land is exempted from property tax.—`
  line `where any vacant land is exempted from property tax under any law for the time being in force, the annual`
  line `value of any building erected on such land, which is in existence for more than one year and is not entitled`
  line `to any exemption from such tax under this act or any other law for the time being in force, shall be`
  line `determined in accordance with the provisions of this chapter.`
obj_root_law_sections_116_g:
  sectionId (67079)
  sectionNo 116G
  orderNo 151
  title `Transitory provisions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_116_g_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Delhi Act 6 of 2003, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-8-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=67079&sectionno=116G&orderno=151&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_116_g_content:
  string
  line `[^1116G.Transitory provisions.—(1) notwithstanding anything contained in this act, as amended by the`
  line `delhi municipal corporation (Amendment) Act, 2003, a tax on vacant land or covered space of building or`
  line `both, levied under this Act immediately before the date of coming into force of the Delhi Municipal`
  line `Corporation (Amendment) Act, 2003, shall, on the coming into force of the Delhi Municipal Corporation`
  line `(Amendment) Act, 2003, be deemed to be the tax on such vacant land or covered space of building or both,`
  line `levied under this Act as amended by the Delhi Municipal Corporation (Amendment) Act, 2003, and shall`
  line `continue to be in force until such tax is revised in accordance with the provisions of this Act, as amended`
  line `by the Delhi Municipal Corporation (Amendment) Act, 2003.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where assessment has not been finalized in`
  line `respect of a vacant land or covered space of a building or both, on the date of the commencement of the`
  line `Delhi Municipal Corporation (Amendment) Act, 2003, the assessee may have such land or building or both,`
  line `as the case may be, assessed on the basis of the annual value.`
obj_root_law_sections_116_h:
  sectionId (67080)
  sectionNo 116H
  orderNo 152
  title `One-time tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_116_h_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Delhi Act 6 of 2003, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-8-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=67080&sectionno=116H&orderno=152&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_116_h_content:
  string
  line `^1[116H. One-time taxic.--Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, in those cases where the owner`
  line `has already paid one-time tax under some scheme in the past, the extent of the rate able value on the basis`
  line `of which the one-time tax was paid shall be set off against the annual value calculated under the provisions`
  line `of the Delhi Municipal Corporation (Amendment) Act, 2003 and the tax liability shall be worked out on`
  line `the basis of net annual value.`
obj_root_law_sections_116_i:
  sectionId (67081)
  sectionNo 116I
  orderNo 153
  title `Validity of base unit area values of vacant land and covered space of building.—`
  content obj_root_law_sections_116_i_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Delhi Act 6 of 2003, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-8-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=67081&sectionno=116I&orderno=153&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_116_i_content:
  string
  line `^1[116I. Validity of base unit area values of vacant land and covered space of building.---The base unit area value of vacant land and the base unit area value of covered space of building in respect of a specified group in a ward shall remain in force for a period of three years:`
  line
  line `Provided that till the revision of such base unit area values is completed, the existing base unit area values shall continue to be in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_116_j:
  sectionId (67082)
  sectionNo 116J
  orderNo 154
  title `Indexation of unit area value`
  content obj_root_law_sections_116_j_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Delhi Act 6 of 2003, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-8-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=67082&sectionno=116J&orderno=154&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_116_j_content:
  string
  line `^1[116J. Indexation of unit area value.—If, for any reason, the base unit area value of any vacant land,`
  line `or the base unit area value of any covered space of building, in any group in any ward has not been revised`
  line `on the completion of a period of three years from the date on which such base unit area values were last`
  line `determined, it shall be lawful to increase or decrease the base unit area values according to the changes in`
  line `the consumer price index of urban non-manual workers or such other suitable index as the Government`
  line `may determine till such revision is made by the Municipal Valuation Committee, and to realize the amount`
  line `of property tax for such covered space of building or vacant land on the basis of the revised base unit area`
  line values.
obj_root_law_sections_116_k:
  sectionId (67083)
  sectionNo 116K
  orderNo 155
  title `Hardship and Anomaly Committee`
  content obj_root_law_sections_116_k_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_116_k_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=67083&sectionno=116K&orderno=155&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_116_k_content:
  string
  line `^1[116K. Hardship and Anomaly Committee.—(1) ^2[^3[The Corporation]] shall, on the coming into force`
  line `of the Delhi Municipal Corporation (Amendment) Act, 2003, appoint, for such period, not exceeding one`
  line `year, as ^4[^5[the Corporation]] may think fit, a Hardship and Anomaly Committee with a view to considering`
  line `the cases of hardships or anomalies, if any, in respect of property tax imposed under the provisions of this`
  line `Act as amended by the Delhi Municipal Corporation (Amendment) Act, 2003.`
  line
  line `(2) The Hardship and Anomaly Committee shall consist of a professional from areas of finance,`
  line `taxation, law or municipal management, as the Chairperson and four other members of whom one shall be`
  line `a Councillor to be nominated by ^4[^5[the Corporation]], one shall be the chairperson of the Municipal`
  line `Valuation Committee and one member shall be nominated from among the members of the Municipal`
  line `Valuation Committee and one shall be the Additional Commissioner (Revenue) of ^4[^5[the Corporation]].`
  line
  line `(3) The Hardship and Anomaly Committee shall make recommendations to ^4[^5[the Corporation]] on`
  line `the petitions received from any group of affected persons regarding any hardship or anomaly arising out of`
  line `the property tax imposed, and the decision of ^4[^5[the Corporation]] on such recommendation shall be final.`
  line
  line `(4) The procedure for the functioning of the Hardship and Anomaly Committee shall be such as may`
  line `be specified by ^4[^5[the Corporation]].]`
obj_root_law_sections_116_k_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Delhi Act 6 of 2003, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-8-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “A Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `5Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
