  sectionNo (119)
  orderNo 158
  title `Taxation of Union properties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_119_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_119_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27247&sectionno=119&orderno=158&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_119_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[(1)] Notwithstanding anything contained in the foregoing`
  line `provisions of this Chapter, lands and buildings being properties of the Union shall be exempt from the`
  line `property taxes specified in section 114:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing ^2`
  line `[in this sub-section] shall prevent ^3[^4[the Corporation]] from levying any of the said`
  line `taxes on such lands and buildings to which immediately before the 26th January, 1950, they were liable or`
  line `treated as liable, so long as that tax continues to be levied by ^3[^4[the Corporation]] on other lands and`
  line buildings.
  line
  line `^5[Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, property owned by a Government company or a`
  line `statutory corporation, which has a corporate personality of its own, shall not be deemed to be the property`
  line `of the Union.]`
  line
  line ^6****
obj_root_law_sections_119_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 119 re-numbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 42 of 1961, s. 8 (w.e.f. 12-9-1961).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for in this section (w.e.f. 12-9-1961).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "a Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Delhi Act 6 of 2003, s. 9 (w.e.f. 1-8-2003).`
  line
  line `6. Sub-section (2) omitted by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-8-2003).`
obj_root_law_sections_120:
  sectionId (27248)
  sectionNo (120)
  orderNo 159
  title `Incidence of property taxes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_120_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_120_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27248&sectionno=120&orderno=159&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_120_content:
  string
  line `^1[120. Incidence of property taxes.--(1) (a) The property tax on any land or building shall be`
  line `primarily leviable upon the owner thereof.`
  line
  line `(b) The liability of the several owners of any land or building constituting a single unit of assessment,`
  line `which is, or purports to be, severally owned in parts including flats or rooms, for payment of property tax`
  line `or any instalment thereof, payable during the period of such ownership, shall be joint and several:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Commissioner may apportion the amount of property tax on such land or building`
  line `among several co-owners:`
  line
  line `Provided further that in any case where the Commissioner is, for reasons to be recorded in writing,`
  line `satisfied that the owner is not traceable, the occupier of such land or building for the time being shall be`
  line `liable for payment of the property tax and shall also be entitled to the rebate, if admissible.`
  line
  line `(c) In the case of any land or building which is not self-occupied and where the owner is constrained`
  line `by any law, order of the Government, or order of a court from recovering the tax due, such tax shall be`
  line `recovered from the occupier or occupiers, as the case may be:`
  line
  line `Provided that the owner shall continue to pay such amount of tax as he was liable to pay before the`
  line `coming into force of the Delhi Municipal Corporation (Amendment) Act, 2003 and only the balance`
  line `amount, if any, shall be recovered from the occupier.`
  line
  line `(d) The property tax on any land or building, which is the property of ^2[^3`
  line `[the Corporationic956] and the`
  line `possession of which has been delivered under any agreement or licensing arrangement, shall be leviable`
  line `upon the transferee or the licensee, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(e) The property tax in respect of any land or building, being the property of the Union, the possession`
  line `of which has been delivered in pursuance of section 20 of the Displaced Persons (Compensation and`
  line `Rehabilitation) Act, 1954 (44 of 1954), shall be leviable upon the transferee.`
  line
  line `(2) If any land has been let to a tenant for a term exceeding one year and such tenant has built upon`
  line `such land, the property tax assessed in respect of such land and the building erected thereon shall be payable`
  line `by such tenant, whether the land and the building are in the occupation of such tenant or a sub-tenant of`
  line `such tenant.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, tenant' shall include any person deriving title to the`
  line `land or the building erected upon such land, from the tenant, whether by operation of law or by transfer`
  line `inter vivos.`
obj_root_law_sections_120_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 6 of 2003, s. 10, for section 120 (w.e.f. 1-8-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "a Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
