  line
obj_root_law_sections_122:
  sectionId (27250)
  sectionNo (122)
  orderNo 161
  title `Recovery of property taxes from occupiers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_122_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_122_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27250&sectionno=122&orderno=161&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_122_content:
  string
  line `(1) On the failure to recover any sum due on`
  line `account of property taxes in respect of any land or building from the person primarily liable therefor`
  line `under section 120, the Commissioner shall recover from every occupier of such land or building by`
  line `attachment, in accordance with section 162 of the rent payable by such occupier, a portion of the total`
  line `sum due which bears, as nearly as may be, the same proportion to that sum as the rent annually payable`
  line `by such occupier bears to the total amount of rent annually payable in respect of the whole of the land or`
  line building.
  line
  line `(2) An occupier from whom any sum is recovered under sub-section (1) shall be entitled to be`
  line `reimbursed by the person primarily liable for the payment, and may in addition to having recourse to`
  line `other remedies that may be open to him, deduct the amount so recovered from the amount of any rent`
  line `from time to time becoming due from him to such person.`
obj_root_law_sections_122_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_123:
  sectionId (27251)
  sectionNo (123)
  orderNo 162
  title `Property taxes a first charge on premises on which they are assessed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_123_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 85, for the Explanation (w.e.f. 1-10-1993)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27251&sectionno=123&orderno=162&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_123_content:
  string
  line `Property taxes due`
  line `under this Act in respect of any land or building shall, subject to the prior payment of the land revenue, if`
  line `any, due to the Government thereon, be a first charge—`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of any land or building held immediately from the Government, upon the interest`
  line `in such land or building of the person liable for such taxes and upon the goods and other movable`
  line `properties, if any, found within or upon such land or building and belonging to such person; and`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of any other land or building, upon such land or building and upon the goods and`
  line `other movable properties, if any, found within or upon such land or building and belonging to the`
  line `person liable for such taxes.`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[Explanation—The term "property taxes" in this section shall be deemed to include the costs on`
  line `recovery of property taxes and the penalty, if any, payable as specified in the bye-laws.]`
obj_root_law_sections_123_a:
  sectionId (67084)
  sectionNo 123A
  orderNo 163
  title `Submission of returns.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_123_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Delhi Act 6 of 2003, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1-8-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=67084&sectionno=123A&orderno=163&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_123_a_content:
  string
  line `^2[123A. Submission of returns.--(1) The Commissioner shall, with a view to determining the annual`
  line `values of vacant land and covered space of building in any ward and the person primarily liable for the`
  line `payment of property tax, by public notice, or by notice, in writing, require the owner and the occupier of`
  line `such vacant land or covered space of building or any portion thereof, including such owner or the person`
  line `computing the tax due under the provisions of section 123B, to furnish a return in such form as may be`
  line `prescribed by bye-laws and within such time, not being less than thirty days from the date of publication of`
  line `such notice, as may be specified therein, containing the following particulars, namely:`
  line
  line `(a) the name of the owner and the occupier;`
  line
  line `(b) the number of the ward, the name of the colony, and the number and the sub-number of the`
  line `premises of such vacant land or covered space of building, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(c) whether the building is pucca, semi-pucca or katcha;`
  line
  line `(d) year of completion of construction of the building, or year or years of part construction thereof,`
  line `as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(e) the use with reference to the provisions of clause (f) of sub-section (1) of section 116A to which`
  line `such vacant land or covered space of building is put or intended to be put;`
  line
  line `(f) the area of the vacant land and the covered space of the building with break-up of the area under`
  line `various uses;`
  line
  line `(g) whether wholly owner-occupied or wholly tenanted, or partly owner-occupied and partly`
  line `tenanted, and the areas thereof; and`
  line
  line `(h) such other particulars as may be prescribed by bye-laws.`
  line
  line `(2) (a) Every owner and every occupier as aforesaid shall be bound to comply with such notice and`
  line `to furnish a return with a declaration that the statement made therein is correct to the best of knowledge and`
  line `belief of such owner and occupier.`
  line
  line `(b) Whoever omits to comply with such requisition, shall in addition to any penalty to which he may`
  line `be liable, be precluded from objecting to any assessment made by the Commissioner in respect of such land`
  line `or building.`
  line
  line `(3) The Commissioner or any person subordinate to him and duly authorized by him in this behalf, in`
  line `writing, or any licensed architect, may, with or without giving any previous notice to the owner or the`
  line `occupier of any land or building, enter upon, and make any inspection or survey, and take measurement of`
  line `such land or building with a view to verifying the statement made in the return for such land or building or`
  line `for collecting the particulars referred to in sub-section (1) in respect of such land or building:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such entry shall be made except between the hours of sunrise and sunset.`
obj_root_law_sections_123_b:
  sectionId (67085)
  sectionNo 123B
  orderNo 164
  title `Self assessment and submission of return.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_123_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_123_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=67085&sectionno=123B&orderno=164&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_123_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[123B. Self assessment and submission of return.--(1) After the coming into force of the Delhi`
  line `Municipal Corporation (Amendment) Act, 2003, any owner of any vacant land or covered space of building`
  line `or any other person liable to pay the property tax or any occupier in the absence of such owner or person,`
  line `shall file a return of self assessment within sixty days of the coming into force of the aforesaid Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Such owner or other person or occupier, as the case may be, shall, thereafter, file the annual return`
  line `only in those cases where there is a change in the position as compared to the previous return, within three`
  line `months after the end of the financial year in which the change in position has occurred.`
  line
  line `(3) Any owner of any covered space of building or vacant land or any other person liable to pay the`
  line `property tax, or any occupier in the absence of such owner or person shall compute the tax due under section`
  line `114A or section 114C, as the case may be, and pay the same in equated quarterly installment by the 30th`
  line `day of June, 30th day of September, 31st day of December and 31st day of March of the financial year for`
  line `which tax is to be paid. In the event of tax being paid in one lump sum for the financial year by the 30th`
  line `day of June of the financial year, rebate of such percentage not exceeding fifteen percent, as may be notified`
  line `by ^2[^3[the Corporation]], of the total tax amount due shall be allowed.`
  line
  line `(4) Any owner of any vacant land or covered space of building or any other person liable to pay the`
  line `property tax or any occupier in the absence of such owner or person, who computes such property tax under`
  line `this section, shall, on such computation pay the property tax on such vacant land or covered space of`
  line `building, as the case may be, together with interest, if any, payable under the provisions of this Act on`
  line
  line `(a) any new building or existing building which has not been assessed; or`
  line
  line `(b) any existing building which has been redeveloped or substantially altered or improved after the`
  line `last assessment, but has not been subjected to revision of assessment consequent upon such`
  line `redevelopment or alteration or improvement) as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(5) Such owner or person, as the case may be, shall furnish to the Commissioner a return of selfassessment in such form, and in such manner, as may be specified in the bye-laws and every such return`
  line `shall be accompanied by proof of payment of property tax and interest, if any.`
  line
  line `(6) In the case of any new building for which an occupancy certificate has been granted, or which has`
  line `been occupied, after the coming into force of the Delhi Municipal Corporation (Amendment) Act, 2003,`
  line `such payment shall be made, and such return shall be furnished, within thirty days of the expiry of the`
  line `quarter in which such occupancy certificate is granted or such building is occupied, whichever- is earlier.`
  line
  line `Explanation.For the removal of doubt, it is hereby declared that occupancy certificate may be`
  line `provisional or final and may be for the whole or any part of the building and occupancy may be of the whole`
  line `or any part of the building.`
  line
  line `(7) After the determination of the annual value of vacant land or covered space of building under section`
  line `116E or section 116F or revision thereof under section123C has been made, any amount paid on selfassessment under this section shall be deemed to have been paid on account of such determination under`
  line `this Act as amended by the Delhi Municipal Corporation (Amendment) Act, 2003.`
  line
  line `(8) If any owner or other person as aforesaid, liable to pay the property tax under this Act, fails to pay`
  line `the same together with interest thereon, if any, in accordance with the provisions of this section, he shall,`
  line `without prejudice to any other action to which he may be subject, be deemed to be a defaulter in respect of`
  line `such property tax, or interest, or both, remaining unpaid, and all the provisions of this Act applicable to`
  line `such defaulter shall apply to him accordingly.`
  line
  line `(9) If, after the assessment of the annual value of any land or covered space, of building is finally made`
  line `under this Act, the payment on self-assessment under this section is found to be less than that of the amount`
  line `payable by the assessee, the assessee shall pay the difference within two months from the date of final`
  line `assessment, failing which recovery shall be made in accordance with the provisions of this Act, but, after the final assessment, if it is found that the assessee has paid excess amount, such excess amount shall be`
  line `refunded:`
  line
  line `Provided that in any case where the amount of tax determined in the final assessment is more than the`
  line `amount of tax paid under self assessment, and the difference in the amount of tax is, in the opinion of the`
  line `Commissioner, the result of wilful suppression of facts as defined in the bye-laws, the Commissioner may`
  line `levy a penalty not exceeding thirty per cent of such difference in the tax besides the interest thereon:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the levy of such penalty shall be in addition to any other punishment provided for`
  line `under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided also that the procedure for sending of notice, hearing of objection and determination of tax`
  line `and penalties shall be such as may be specified in the bye-laws.`
  line
  line `(10) Where no notice is sent by the Commissioner under section 123C within twelvemonths after the`
  line `year to which such self-assessment relates, such self assessment shall be regarded as assessment made under`
  line `this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that in any case, where there has been wilful suppression of facts, penalty upto thirty per cent`
  line `of the tax due may be imposed:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the procedure for sending of notice, hearing of objection and determination of tax`
  line `and penalties shall be such as may be specified in the bye-laws.`
obj_root_law_sections_123_b_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Delhi Act 6 of 2003, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1-8-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_123_c:
  sectionId (67086)
  sectionNo 123C
  orderNo 165
  title `Revision of assessment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_123_c_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_123_c_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=67086&sectionno=123C&orderno=165&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_123_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[123C. Revision of assessment.—(1) The Commissioner may cause any revision to be made at any`
  line `time in the annual value of any vacant land or covered space of building or any portion thereof in the`
  line `following cases, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) where the nature of use changes; or`
  line
  line `(ii) where the nature of occupancy changes; or`
  line
  line `(iii) where a new building is erected or an existing building is redeveloped or substantially altered`
  line `or improved during the period the annual value remains in force; or`
  line
  line `(iv) where, on an application made, in writing, by the owner or the person liable to pay the property`
  line `tax, it is established that during the period the annual value is in force, such value has been reduced by`
  line `reason of any substantial demolition or has suffered depreciation on account of any accident or any`
  line `calamity proved to the satisfaction of the Commissioner to have been beyond the control of such owner`
  line `or person; or`
  line
  line `(v) where any vacant land or covered space of building or portion thereof is acquired by purchase`
  line `or otherwise by the ^2[^3[Government]] or the Government or ^4[^5[the Corporation]]; or`
  line
  line `(vi) where any vacant land or covered space of building or portion thereof is sold or otherwise`
  line `transferred to the ^2[^3[Government]] or the Government or the Corporation; or`
  line
  line `(vii) where, upon the acquisition or transfer of a part of any vacant land or covered space of`
  line `building, a residual portion remains; or`
  line
  line `(viii) where it becomes necessary so to do for any other reason to be recorded in writing.`
  line
  line `(2) Before making any revision of the annual value under sub-section (1), the Commissioner shall give`
  line `any owner, person or occupier as a case may be, affected by such revision, notice of not less than 30 days`
  line `that he proposes to make the revision and consider any objections which may be made by such owner,`
  line `person or occupier.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where the annual value of any vacant land`
  line `or covered space of building—`
  line
  line `(i) has not, for any reason, been determined under this Act, the annual value of such vacant land or`
  line `covered space of building, as the case may be, may be determined by the Commissioner at any time`
  line `during the currency of the period of assessment in respect of such vacant land or covered space of`
  line `building under section 116E or section 116F, as the case may be; or`
  line
  line `(ii) has been cancelled on the ground of irregularity, the annual value of such vacant land or covered`
  line `space of building, as the case may be, may be determined by the Commissioner at any time after such`
  line `cancellation; and such annual value of such vacant land or covered space of building, as the case may`
  line `be, shall remain in force until a fresh valuation or revision is made.`
  line
  line `(4) Any revision of annual value of any vacant land or covered space of building or any portion thereof`
  line `under this section shall be made with reference to the group into which such vacant land or covered space`
  line `of building or part thereof is classified under section 116A, and the annual value fixed per unit area of such`
  line `vacant land or covered space of building for that group shall be applicable.`
  line
  line `(5) Notwithstanding anything contained in the foregoing provisions of this section, no revision of the`
  line `annual value of any vacant land or covered space of building under this section shall be made without giving`
  line `the owner or the occupier of such vacant land or covered space of building a reasonable opportunity of`
  line `being heard.`
  line
  line `(6) Where any revision of annual value of any vacant land or covered space of building is made under`
  line `this section, the order of such revision shall be communicated to the owner or the occupier of such vacant`
  line `land or covered space of building within ten days from the date of the order.`
  line
  line `(7) An appeal shall lie against an order under sub-section (6) to an officer appointed by the Government,`
  line `if preferred by the owner, person or the occupier of such vacant land or covered space of building within`
  line `forty-five days from the date of the receipt of the order.`
obj_root_law_sections_123_c_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Delhi Act 6 of 2003, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1-8-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “Central Government” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “Government” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “ a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_123_d:
  sectionId (67087)
  sectionNo 123D
  orderNo 166
  title `Power of Commissioner regarding assessment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_123_d_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Delhi Act 6 of 2003, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1-8-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=67087&sectionno=123D&orderno=166&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_123_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[123D. Power of Commissioner regarding assessment.The Commissioner may, at any time`
  line
  line `(a) make, suo motu, an assessment in any case where a return on the basis of self assessment has`
  line `not been filed;`
  line
  line `(b) revise any assessment where the information furnished in the return of self assessment is found`
  line `to be incorrect;`
  line
  line `(c) reopen any assessment even after the period of one year in any case where it has been detected`
  line `that there is wilful suppression of information; and`
  line
  line `(d) impose a penalty not exceeding thirty per cent of the difference in tax arising from non-filing`
  line `of a return in time, giving wrong information or wilful suppression of facts].`
obj_root_law_sections_124:
  sectionId (27252)
  sectionNo (124)
  orderNo 167
  title `Assessment list.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_124_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_124_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27252&sectionno=124&orderno=167&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_124_content:
  string
  line `^1[124. Assessment list.—(1) ^2[^3[The Corporation]] shall maintain a Municipal Assessment Book in`
  line `such form, and in such manner, as may be specified in the bye-laws and shall make it available for`
  line `inspection, free of charge, through electronic media or otherwise:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Municipal Assessment Book shall not be kept pending for any case for which any`
  line `objection or appeal has been filed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commissioner may, at any time, amend the Municipal Assessment Book for such reasons as`
  line `may be specified in the bye-laws:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such amendment shall be made without giving any person affected a reasonable`
  line `opportunity of being heard..`
obj_root_law_sections_124_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 6 of 2003, s. 13, for section 124 (w.e.f. 1-8-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “ A Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_125:
  sectionId (27253)
  sectionNo (125)
  orderNo 168
  title `Evidential value of assessment list.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_125_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_125_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27253&sectionno=125&orderno=168&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_125_content:
  string
  line `^1[125. Assignment of property identification code.—(1) ^2[^3[The Corporation]] shall cause to be`
  line `maintained a register wherein the property identification code numbers by which any premises or part`
  line `thereof shall be known, shall be recorded in respect of each such premises in the municipal area and such`
  line `numbers shall be fixed in such manner as may be specified in the bye-laws.`
  line
  line `(2) When the property identification code numbers in respect of premises in any ward of ^4[^5[the Corporation]] have been determined, the Commissioner shall notify the same in such manner as may be`
  line `prescribed in the bye-laws.`
  line
  line `(3) After the property identification code numbers in respect of premises in any ward have been notified`
  line `under sub-section (2), any person required under this Act or any other law to make any application to ^4[^5[the Corporation]] for permission, licence or for payment of any tax or for payment of any dues for any service`
  line `and for such other purposes as may be prescribed, shall at the time of making such application mentioned`
  line `in the application, the property identification code number determined under sub-section (1).]`
obj_root_law_sections_125_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 6 of 2003, s. 15, for section 15 (w.e.f. 1-8-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “A Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “ a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
