obj_root_law_sections_128:
  sectionId (27256)
  sectionNo (128)
  orderNo 171
  title `Notice of transfers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_128_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_128_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27256&sectionno=128&orderno=171&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_128_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever the title of any person primarily liable for the payment of`
  line `property taxes on any land or building is transferred, the person whose title is transferred and the person`
  line `to whom the same is transferred shall within three months after the execution of the instrument of transfer`
  line `or after its registration, if it is registered, or after the transfer is effected, if no instrument is executed, give`
  line `notice of such transfer in writing to the Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(2) In the event of the death of any person primarily liable as aforesaid, the person on whom the title`
  line `of the deceased devolves, shall give notice of such devolution to the Commissioner within six months`
  line `from the date of the death of the deceased.`
  line
  line `(3) The notice to be given under this section shall be in such form as may be determined by bye-laws`
  line `made under this Act, and the transferee or the other person on whom the title devolves shall, if so`
  line `required, be bound to produce before the Commissioner any documents evidencing the transfer or`
  line devolution.
  line
  line `(4) Every person who makes a transfer as aforesaid without giving such notice to the Commissioner`
  line `shall, in addition to any penalty to which he may be subjected under the provisions of this Act, continue`
  line `liable for the payment of all property taxes from time to time payable in respect of the land or building`
  line `transferred until he gives such notice or until the transfer has been recorded in the Commissioners book,`
  line `but nothing in this section shall be held to affect the liability of the transferee for the payment of the said`
  line tax.
  line
  line `(5) The Commissioner shall record every transfer or devolution of title notified to him under this`
  line `section in his books and in the assessment list.`
  line
  line `(6) On a written request by the Commissioner, the registrar or sub-registrar of Delhi appointed under`
  line `the Indian Registration Act, 1908 (16 of 1908), shall furnish such particulars regarding the registration of`
  line `instrument of transfer of immovable properties in Delhi, as the Commissioner may from time to time`
  line require.
  line
  line `(7) Such information shall be furnished as soon as may be after the registration of an instrument of`
  line `transfer is effected, or, if the Commissioner so requests, by periodical returns at such intervals as the`
  line `Commissioner may fix.`
obj_root_law_sections_128_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_129:
  sectionId (27257)
  sectionNo (129)
  orderNo 172
  title `Notice of erection of building, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_129_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_129_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27257&sectionno=129&orderno=172&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_129_content:
  string
  line `When any new building is erected or when any building is`
  line `rebuilt or enlarged or when any building which has been vacant is re-occupied, the person primarily liable`
  line `for the property taxes assessed on the building shall give notice thereof in writing to the Commissioner`
  line `within fifteen days from the date of its completion or occupation whichever first occurs, or as the case`
  line `may be, from the date of its enlargement or re-occupation; and property taxes shall be assessable on the`
  line `building from the said date.`
obj_root_law_sections_129_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_130:
  sectionId (27258)
  sectionNo (130)
  orderNo 173
  title `Notice of demolition or removal of building.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_130_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_130_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27258&sectionno=130&orderno=173&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_130_content:
  string
  line `(1) When any building or any portion of a`
  line `building, which is liable to the payment of property taxes is demolished or removed, otherwise than by`
  line `order of the Commissioner, the person primarily liable for the payment of the said taxes shall give notice`
  line `thereof in writing to the Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(2) Until such notice is given, the person aforesaid shall continue liable to the payment of such`
  line `property taxes as he would have been liable to pay in respect of such building if the same or any portion`
  line `thereof had not been demolished or removed.`
obj_root_law_sections_130_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_131:
  sectionId (27259)
