obj_root_law_sections_135:
  sectionId (27263)
  sectionNo (135)
  orderNo 178
  title `Power of Commissioner to employ valuers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_135_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_135_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27263&sectionno=135&orderno=178&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_135_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commissioner may, if he thinks fit,`
  line `employ one or more competent persons to give advice or assistance in connection with the valuation of`
  line `any land or building, and any person so employed shall have power, at all reasonable times and after`
  line `giving due notice, and on production, if so required, of authorisation in writing in that behalf from the`
  line `Commissioner, to enter on, survey and value any land or building which the Commissioner may direct`
  line `him to survey and value.`
  line
  line `(2) No person shall wilfully delay or obstruct and such person in the exercise of any of his powers`
  line `under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_135_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_136:
  sectionId (27264)
  sectionNo (136)
  orderNo 179
  title `Tax on certain vehicles and animals and rates thereof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_136_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_136_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27264&sectionno=136&orderno=179&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_136_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise provided in this`
  line `Act, a tax at the rates not exceeding those specified in the Third Schedule shall be levied on vehicles and`
  line `animals of the descriptions specified in that Schedule which are kept within Delhi.`
obj_root_law_sections_136_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_137:
  sectionId (27265)
  sectionNo (137)
  orderNo 180
  title `The tax on whom leviable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_137_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_137_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27265&sectionno=137&orderno=180&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_137_content:
  string
  line `The tax on vehicles or animals shall be leviable upon the owner`
  line `of, or the person having possession or control of, such vehicles or animals in respect of which the tax is`
  line `leviable:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of an animal generally used or employed in drawing any vehicle, the tax in`
  line `respect of such animal shall be leviable upon the owner of, or the person having possession or control of,`
  line `such vehicle, whether or not such animal is owned by such owner or person:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the tax under this section shall not be levied in respect of---`
  line
  line `(a) vehicles and animals belonging to ^1[the Central ^2[Government]] or to ^3[^4[the Corporation]] used or`
  line `intended to be used solely for public purposes;`
  line
  line `(b) vehicles intended exclusively for the conveyance free of charge, of the injured, the sick or the`
  line dead;
  line
  line `(c) childrens perambulators or tricycles;`
  line
  line ^5
  line `[(d) a cow or a she-buffalo kept for milking for domestic use if the cow or the she-buffalo is the`
  line `only cow or she-buffalo kept by the owner or the person having possession or control thereof for such`
  line `milking and is registered in accordance with bye-laws made in this behalf, so, however, that`
  line
  line `(i) where more cows or, as the case may be, more she-buffaloes than one are kept by several`
  line `such owners or person constituting a family, the tax under this section shall be levied in respect of`
  line `all such cows or all such she-buffaloes;`
  line
  line `(ii) where a cow and also a she-buffalo are kept by the owner or the person having the`
  line `possession or control thereof or by several such owners or persons constituting a family, the tax`
  line `under this section shall be levied in respect of the cow and the she-buffalo.]`
obj_root_law_sections_137_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 "Central Government" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "Government" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "a Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 42 of 1961, s. 14 (w.e.f. 12-9-1961).`
obj_root_law_sections_138:
  sectionId (27266)
  sectionNo (138)
  orderNo 181
  title `Tax when payable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_138_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_138_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27266&sectionno=138&orderno=181&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_138_content:
  string
  line `The tax on vehicles or animals shall be payable in advance in such`
  line `number of instalments and in such manner as may be determined by bye-laws made in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_138_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_139:
  sectionId (27267)
  sectionNo (139)
  orderNo 182
  title `Power of Commissioner to compound with livery stable keeper, etc., for tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_139_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_139_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27267&sectionno=139&orderno=182&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_139_content:
  string
  line The
  line `Commissioner may, with the approval of the Standing Committee, compound for any period not`
  line `exceeding one year at a time, with any livery stable keeper or other person keeping vehicles for hire or`
  line `animals for sale or hire, for a lump sum to be paid in respect of the vehicles or animals so kept in lieu of`
  line `the taxes leviable under section 136 which such livery stable keeper or other person would otherwise be`
  line `liable to pay.`
obj_root_law_sections_139_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_140:
  sectionId (27268)
  sectionNo (140)
  orderNo 183
  title Theatre-tax.
  content obj_root_law_sections_140_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_140_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27268&sectionno=140&orderno=183&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_140_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise provided in the Act, there shall be levied a tax (referred to in`
  line `this Act as theatre-tax) in respect of every cinema, theatre, circus, carnival and other place of`
  line `entertainment to which persons are ordinarily admitted on payment for performances or shows held or`
  line `conducted thereat, at such rates not exceeding those specified in the Fourth Schedule as ^1[^2[the Corporation]]`
  line `may determine:`
  line
  line `Provided that the theatre-tax shall not be levied in respect of any performance or show if the`
  line `Commissioner is satisfied`
  line
  line `(a) that the entire receipts from such performance or show will be devoted to philanthropic,`
  line `religious or charitable purposes; or`
  line
  line `(b) that the performance or show is of a wholly educational character; or`
  line
  line `(c) that the performance or show is provided for partly educational or partly scientific purposes`
  line `by a society not conducted or established for profit.`
obj_root_law_sections_140_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_141:
  sectionId (27269)
  sectionNo (141)
  orderNo 184
  title `Liability to pay theatre-tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_141_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_141_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27269&sectionno=141&orderno=184&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_141_content:
  string
  line `Every proprietor, manager, or person incharge of a theatre,`
  line `cinema, circus, carnival or other place of entertainment shall be liable to pay the theatre-tax and shall pay`
  line `the same in advance before the commencement of the performances or shows:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Commissioner may, with the approval of the Standing Committee, compound for`
  line `any series of performances or shows or for any period not exceeding one month, with such proprietor,`
  line `manager, or person for a lump sum to be paid for such series of performances or shows or for the`
  line `performances or shows held or conducted during such period.`
obj_root_law_sections_141_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_142:
  sectionId (27270)
  sectionNo (142)
  orderNo 185
  title Omitted..
  content `142. [Tax on advertisements.] Omitted by Delhi Act 3 of 2017, s. 173 (i) (w.e.f. 1-7-2017).`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_142_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27270&sectionno=142&orderno=185&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_142_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_143:
  sectionId (27271)
  sectionNo (143)
  orderNo 186
  title `Prohibition of advertisements without written permission of the Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_143_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_143_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27271&sectionno=143&orderno=186&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_143_content:
  string
  line `(1) No`
  line `advertisement shall be erected, exhibited, fixed or retained upon or over any land, building, wall,`
  line `hoarding, frame, post or structure or upon or in any vehicle or shall be displayed in any manner`
  line `whatsoever in any place within Delhi without the written permission of the Commissioner granted in`
  line `accordance with bye-laws made under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commissioner shall not grant such permission if—`
  line
  line `(a) the advertisement contravenes any bye-law made under this Act; or`
  line
  line `(b) the tax, if any, due in respect of the advertisement has not been paid.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (2), in the case of an advertisement liable to the`
  line `advertisement tax, the Commissioner shall grant permission for the period to which the payment of the`
  line `tax relates and no fee shall be charged in respect of such permission.`
obj_root_law_sections_143_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_144:
  sectionId (27272)
  sectionNo (144)
  orderNo 187
  title `Permission of the Commissioner to become void in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_144_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_144_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27272&sectionno=144&orderno=187&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_144_content:
  string
  line `The permission granted`
  line `under section 143 shall become void in the following cases, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) if the advertisement contravenes any bye-law made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) if any material change is made in the advertisement or any part thereof without the previous`
  line `permission of the Commissioner;`
  line
  line `(c) if the advertisement or any part thereof falls otherwise than through accident;`
  line
  line `(d) if any addition or alteration is made to, or in the building, wall, hoarding, frame, post or`
  line `structure upon or over which the advertisement is erected, exhibited, fixed or retained if such addition`
  line `or alteration involves the disturbance of the advertisement or any part thereof; and`
  line
  line `(e) if the building, wall, hoarding, frame, post or structure over which the advertisement is`
  line `erected, exhibited, fixed or retained is demolished or destroyed.`
obj_root_law_sections_144_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_145:
  sectionId (27273)
  sectionNo (145)
  orderNo 188
  title `Presumption in case of contravention.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_145_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_145_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27273&sectionno=145&orderno=188&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_145_content:
  string
  line `Where any advertisement has been erected, exhibited,`
  line `fixed or retained upon or over any land, building, wall, hoarding, frame, post or structure or upon or in`
  line `any vehicle or displayed to public view from a public street or public place in contravention of the provisions of this Act or any bye-laws made thereunder, it shall be presumed, unless and until contrary is`
  line `proved, that the contravention has been committed by the person or the persons on whose behalf the`
  line `advertisement purports to be or the agents of such person or persons.`
obj_root_law_sections_145_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_146:
  sectionId (27274)
  sectionNo (146)
  orderNo 189
  title `Power of Commissioner in case of contravention.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_146_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_146_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27274&sectionno=146&orderno=189&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_146_content:
  string
  line `If any advertisement is erected, exhibited,`
  line `fixed or retained in contravention of the provisions of section 143, the Commissioner may require the`
  line `owner or occupier of the land, building, wall, hoarding, frame, post or structure or vehicle upon, or over`
  line `or in which the same is erected, exhibited, fixed or retained, to take down or remove such advertisement`
  line `or may enter any land, building, property or vehicle and have the advertisement dismantled taken down or`
  line `removed or spoiled, defaced or screened.`
obj_root_law_sections_146_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_147:
  sectionId (27275)
  sectionNo (147)
  orderNo 190
  title `Duty on transfer of property and method of assessment thereof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_147_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_147_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27275&sectionno=147&orderno=190&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_147_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise`
  line `provided in this Act, ^1[^2[the Corporation]] shall levy a duty on transfers of immovable property situated within`
  line `the limits of ^3[^4[Delhi]] in accordance with the provisions hereafter in this section contained.`
  line
  line `(2) The said duty shall be levied--`
  line
  line `(a) in the form of a surcharge on the duty imposed by the Indian Stamp Act, 1899 (2 of 1899) as`
  line `in force for the time being in the Union territory of Delhi, on every instrument of the description`
  line `specified below, and`
  line
  line `(b) at such rate as may be determined by ^1[^2[the Corporation]] not exceeding five per cent, on the`
  line `amount specified below against such instruments:---`
  line
  line `Description of instrument Amount on which duty should be levied`
  line
  line `(i) Sale of immovable property. The amount or value of the consideration for the`
  line `sale, as set forth in the instrument.`
  line
  line `(ii) Exchange of immovable property. The value of the property of the greater value, as`
  line `set forth in the instrument.`
  line
  line `(iii) Gift of immovable property. The value of the property, as set forth in the`
  line instrument.
  line
  line `(iv) Mortgage with possession of`
  line `immovable property.`
  line `The amount secured by the mortgage as set forth`
  line `in the instrument.`
  line
  line `(v) Lease in perpetuity of immovable`
  line property.
  line `The amount equal to one-sixth of the whole`
  line `amount or value of the rent which would be`
  line `paid or delivered in respect of the first fifty`
  line `years of the lease as set forth in the instrument.`
  line
  line `^5[(vi) Contract for transfer of`
  line `immovable property`
  line `Ninety percent of the value of the consideration for`
  line `the transfer as set out in the contract.]`
obj_root_law_sections_147_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for “Delhi” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “the area of the Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Delhi Act 6 of 2003, s. 23 (w.e.f. 1-8-2003).`
obj_root_law_sections_148:
  sectionId (27276)
  sectionNo (148)
  orderNo 191
  title `Provisions applicable on the introduction of transfer duty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_148_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_148_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27276&sectionno=148&orderno=191&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_148_content:
  string
  line `On the introduction of the duty`
  line `on transfers of property---`
  line
  line `(a) section 27 of the Indian Stamp Act, 1899 (2 of 1899), as in force in Delhi shall be read as if it`
  line `specifically required the particulars to be set forth separately in respect of property situated within`
  line `and without Delhi;`
  line
  line `(b) section 64 of the said Act shall be read as if it referred to ^1[^2[the Corporation]] as well as the`
  line Government.
obj_root_law_sections_148_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_149:
  sectionId (27277)
  sectionNo (149)
  orderNo 192
  title `Tax on building applications.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_149_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_149_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27277&sectionno=149&orderno=192&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_149_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise provided in this Act, ^1[^2[the Corporation]]`
  line `shall levy a tax on buildings at such rates not exceeding those specified in the Sixth Schedule, as ^1[^2[the`
  line `Corporation]] shall determine.`
  line
  line `(2) The tax shall be leviable on every person who makes an application to the Commissioner for the`
  line `sanction of building plan and shall be payable along with the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_149_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_150:
  sectionId (27278)
  sectionNo (150)
  orderNo 193
  title `Imposition of other taxes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_150_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_150_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27278&sectionno=150&orderno=193&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_150_content:
  string
  line `(1) ^1[^2[The Corporation]] may, at a meeting, pass a resolution for the`
  line `levy of any of the taxes specified in sub-section (2) of section 113, defining the maximum rate of the tax`
  line `to be levied, the class or classes of persons or the description or descriptions of articles and properties to`
  line `be taxed, the system of assessment to be adopted and the exemptions, if any, to be granted.`
  line
  line `(2) Any resolution passed under sub-section (1) shall be submitted to the ^3`
  line `*** Government for its`
  line `sanction, and if sanctioned by that Government, shall come into force on and from such date as may be`
  line `specified in the order of sanction.`
  line
  line `(3) After a resolution has come into force under sub-section (2), ^4[^5[the Corporation]] may, subject to the`
  line `maximum rate, pass a second resolution determining the actual rates at which the tax shall be leviable;`
  line `and the tax shall come into force on the first day of the quarter of the year next following the date on`
  line `which second resolution is passed.`
  line
  line `(4) After a tax has been levied in accordance with the foregoing provisions of this section, the`
  line `provisions of sub-section (2) of section 109, shall apply in relation to such tax as they apply in relation to`
  line `any tax imposed under sub-section (1) of section 113.`
obj_root_law_sections_150_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “A Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. The word Central omitted by Act 67 of 1993, s. 86 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_151:
  sectionId (27279)
  sectionNo (151)
  orderNo 194
  title `Supplementary taxation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_151_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_151_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27279&sectionno=151&orderno=194&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_151_content:
  string
  line `Whenever ^1[^2[the Corporation]] decides to have recourse to`
  line `supplementary taxation under sub-section (2) of section 111 in any year, it shall do so by increasing from`
  line `such date as ^1[^2[the Corporation]] may determine, the rates at which any tax leviable under this Act is being`
  line `levied, but every such increase shall be made subject to the maximum rate and any other limitation`
  line `specified in respect of such tax.`
obj_root_law_sections_151_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_152:
  sectionId (27280)
  sectionNo (152)
  orderNo 195
  title `Time and manner of payment of taxes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_152_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 6 of 2003, s. 24, for section 152 (w.e.f. 1-8-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27280&sectionno=152&orderno=195&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_152_content:
  string
  line `^1[152. Time and manner of payment of taxes.—(1) Save as otherwise provided in this Act, any tax`
  line `levied under this Act shall be payable on such dates, in such number of installments and in such manner as`
  line `may be determined by bye-laws made in this behalf:`
  line
  line `Provided that if, on the coming into force of the Delhi Municipal Corporation (Amendment) Act, 2003,`
  line `there is any increase in the amount of property tax which was being paid or was payable immediately before`
  line `the coming into force of the Delhi Municipal Corporation (Amendment) Act, 2003, the difference in the`
  line `amount of property tax in excess of fifty per cent above the tax being paid or being payable, shall be given`
  line `effect to by stages covering a period of three years by dividing the amount of such increase in the property`
  line `tax by three, the quotient being added to the amount of property tax which was payable immediately before`
  line `the coming into force of the Delhi Municipal Corporation (Amendment) Act, 2003, and to the amount of`
  line `property tax which shall be payable respectively in each of the remaining two successive years after such`
  line addition.
  line
  line `(2) Where any person liable for the payment of property tax under this Act has failed to pay--`
  line
  line `(a) such tax by the date as specified in sub-section (3) of section 123 B; or`
  line
  line `(b) the arrear of tax, interest and penalty, if any, and any other sum in the nature of tax up to the`
  line `31st March of the preceding financial year;`
  line
  line `he shall be liable to pay simple interest at the rate of one per cent for every month or part of the month`
  line `comprising the period from the expiry of the due date, till the amount is actually paid.]`
obj_root_law_sections_152_a:
  sectionId (67088)
  sectionNo 152A
  orderNo 196
  title `Punishment for wilful default in payment of property tax, furnishing wrong information in return of assessment, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_152_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Delhi Act 6 of 2003, s. 24, for section 152 (w.e.f. 1-8-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=67088&sectionno=152A&orderno=196&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_152_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[152A. Punishment for wilful default in payment of property tax, furnishing wrong information`
  line `in return of assessment, etc.—Whoever wilfully makes default in the payment of, or wilfully attempts in`
  line `any manner whatsoever to evade, any tax, including amount of interest due and penalty levied under this`
  line `Act, or furnishes any wrong information in the return of assessment, or wilfully fails to furnish in due time`
  line `the return of property tax, or does not furnish information as asked for under any provision of this Act, he`
  line `shall, without prejudice to any other penal provision under this Act to which he may be subject, be`
  line `punishable, —`
  line
  line `(a) in the case where the amount of tax sought to be evaded exceeds ten lakh rupees, with rigorous`
  line `imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than three months but which may extend up to seven`
  line `years, and with fine of not less than fifty percent of the amount of tax evaded; and`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, with rigorous imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than one month`
  line `but which may extend up to three years, and with fine of not less than fifty percent of the amount of tax`
  line `evaded:`
  line
  line `Provided that the penalties so imposed shall be in addition to, and not in derogation of, any liability`
  line `in respect of the payment of tax which the defaulter may have incurred.]`
obj_root_law_sections_153:
  sectionId (27281)
  sectionNo (153)
  orderNo 197
  title `Presentation of bill.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_153_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_153_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27281&sectionno=153&orderno=197&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_153_content:
  string
  line `(1) When any tax has become due, the Commissioner shall cause to be`
  line `presented to the person liable for the payment thereof, a bill for the amount due:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such bill shall be necessary in the case of---`
  line
  line `^1[(a) property tax payable on self-assessment of vacant land or covered space in any building;]`
  line
  line `^2[(aa)] a tax on vehicles and animals;`
  line
  line `(b) a theatre-tax; and`
  line
  line `(c) ^3[****]`
  line
  line `(2) Every such bill shall specify the particulars of the tax and the period for which the charge is made.`
obj_root_law_sections_153_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Delhi Act 6 of 2003, s. 25 (w.e.f. 1-8-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Clause (a) re-numbered as clause (aa) by s. 25, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-8-2003).`
  line
  line `3. Clause (c) omitted by Delhi Act 3 of 2017, s. 173 (w.e.f. 1-7-2017).`
obj_root_law_sections_154:
  sectionId (27282)
  sectionNo (154)
  orderNo 198
  title `Notice of demand and notice-fee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_154_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_154_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27282&sectionno=154&orderno=198&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_154_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the amount of the tax for which a bill has been`
  line `presented under section 153, is not paid within fifteen days from the presentation thereof, or if the tax on`
  line `vehicles and animals or the theatre-tax or the tax on advertisements is not paid after it has become due,`
  line `the Commissioner may cause to be served upon the person liable for the payment of the same a notice of`
  line `demand in the form set forth in the Seventh Schedule.`
  line
  line `(2) For every notice of demand which the Commissioner causes to be served on any person under this`
  line `section, a fee of such amount not exceeding five rupees as may be determined by bye-laws made in this`
  line `behalf, shall be payable by the said person and shall be included in this cost of recovery.`
obj_root_law_sections_154_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_155:
  sectionId (27283)
  sectionNo (155)
  orderNo 199
  title `Penalty in case of default of payment of taxes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_155_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_155_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27283&sectionno=155&orderno=199&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_155_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the person liable for the payment of any`
  line `tax does not, within thirty days of the service of the notice of demand under section 154, pay the sum due`
  line `and if no appeal is preferred against such tax, he shall be deemed to be in default.`
  line
  line `(2) When the person liable for the payment of any tax is deemed to be in default under`
  line `sub-section (1), such sum not exceeding twenty per cent, of the amount of the tax as may be determined`
  line `by the Commissioner may be recovered from him by way of penalty, in addition to the amount of the tax`
  line `and the notice fee, payable under sub-section (2) of section 154.`
  line
  line `(3) The amount due as penalty under sub-section (2) shall be recoverable as an arrear of tax under this`
  line Act.
obj_root_law_sections_155_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_156:
  sectionId (27284)
  sectionNo (156)
  orderNo 200
  title `Recovery of tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_156_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_156_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27284&sectionno=156&orderno=200&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_156_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the person liable for the payment of the tax does not, within thirty days`
  line `from the service of the notice of demand, pay the amount due, such sum together with all costs and the`
  line `penalty provided for in section 155, may be recovered under a warrant, issued in the form set forth in the`
  line `Eighth Schedule, by distress and sale of the movable property or the attachment and sale of the`
  line `immovable property, of the defaulter:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Commissioner shall not recovery any sum the liability for which has been remitted`
  line `on appeal under the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every warrant issued under this section shall be signed by the Commissioner.`
obj_root_law_sections_156_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_156_a:
  sectionId (67089)
  sectionNo 156A
  orderNo 201
  title `Recovery of property tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_156_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Delhi Act 6 of 2003, s. 26 (w.e.f. 1-8-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=67089&sectionno=156A&orderno=201&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_156_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[156A. Recovery of property tax.—If, after the coming into force of the Delhi Municipal Corporation`
  line `(Amendment) Act, 2003, any owner of any vacant land or covered space of building or any other person`
  line `liable to pay the property tax or any occupier, in the absence of any such owner or person, does not file a`
  line `return of self-assessment within sixty days of the coming into force of the Delhi Municipal Corporation`
  line `(Amendment) Act, 2003, or if the person liable for the payment of property tax does not pay the amount`
  line `due within the due date, such sum together with all costs and penalty may be recovered under a warrant,`
  line `issued in the form set forth in the Eighth Schedule, by distress and sale of the movable property, or the`
  line `attachment and sale of the immovable property, of the defaulter:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Commissioner shall not recover any sum the liability for which has been remitted on`
  line `appeal under the provisions of this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_157:
  sectionId (27285)
  sectionNo (157)
  orderNo 202
  title Distress.
  content obj_root_law_sections_157_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_157_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27285&sectionno=157&orderno=202&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_157_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall be lawful for any officer or other employee of ^1[^2[the Corporation]] to whom a`
  line `warrant issued under section 156 is addressed to distrain, wherever it may be found in any place in Delhi,`
  line `any movable property or any standing timber, growing crops or grass belonging to the person therein`
  line `named as defaulter, subject to the following conditions, exceptions and exemptions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the following property shall not be distrained:---`
  line
  line `(i) the necessary wearing apparel and bedding of the defaulter, his wife and children and their`
  line `cooking and eating utensils;`
  line
  line `(ii) tools of artisans;`
  line
  line `(iii) books of account; or`
  line
  line `(iv) when the defaulter is an agriculturist, his implements of husbandry, seed, grain and such`
  line `cattle as may be necessary to enable the defaulter to earn his livelihood;`
  line
  line `(b) the distress shall not be excessive, that is to say, the property distrained shall be as nearly as`
  line `possible equal in value to the amount recoverable under the warrant, and if any property has been`
  line `distrained which, in the opinion of the Commissioner, should not have been distrained, it shall`
  line `forthwith be released.`
  line
  line `(2) The person charged with the execution of a warrant of distress shall forthwith make an inventory`
  line `of the property which he seizes under such warrant, and shall, at the same time, give a written notice in`
  line `the form set forth in the Ninth Schedule, to the person in possession thereof at the time of seizure that the`
  line `said property will be sold as therein mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_157_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_158:
  sectionId (27286)
  sectionNo (158)
  orderNo 203
  title `Disposal of distrained property and attachment and sale of immovable property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_158_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_158_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27286&sectionno=158&orderno=203&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_158_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `When the property seized is subject to speedy and natural decay or when the expense of keeping it in`
  line `custody is, when added to the amount to be recovered, likely to exceed its value, the Commissioner shall`
  line `give notice to the person in whose possession the property was at the time of seizure that it will be sold at`
  line `once, and shall sell it accordingly by public auction unless the amount mentioned in the warrant is`
  line `forthwith paid.`
  line
  line `(2) If the warrant is not in the meantime suspended by the Commissioner, or discharged, the property`
  line `seized shall, after the expiry of the period named in the notice served under sub-section (2) of section 157,`
  line `be sold by public auction by order of the Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(3) When a warrant is issued for the attachment and sale of immovable property, the attachment shall`
  line `be made by an order prohibiting the defaulter from transferring or charging the property in any way, and all persons from taking any benefit from such transfer or charge, and declaring that such property would`
  line `be sold unless the amount of tax due with all costs of recovery is paid into the municipal office within`
  line `fifteen days from the date of the attachment.`
  line
  line `(4) Such order shall be proclaimed at some place on or adjacent to such property by beat of drum or`
  line `other customary mode and a copy of the order shall be affixed on a conspicuous part of the property and`
  line `upon a conspicuous part of the municipal office and also, when the property is land paying revenue to the`
  line `Government, in the office of the collector.`
  line
  line `(5) Any transfer of or charge on the property attached or any interest therein made without written`
  line `permission of the Commissioner shall be void as against all claims of ^1[^2[the Corporation]] enforceable under`
  line `the attachment.`
  line
  line `(6) The surplus of the sale-proceeds, if any shall, immediately after the sale of the property, be`
  line `credited to the Municipal Fund, and notice of such credit shall be given at the same time to the person`
  line `whose property has been sold or his legal representative and if the same is claimed by written application`
  line `to the Commissioner within one year from the date of the notice, a refund thereof shall be made to such`
  line `person or representative.`
  line
  line `(7) Any surplus not claimed within one year as aforesaid shall be the property of ^1[^2[the Corporation]].`
  line
  line `(8) For every distraint and attachment made in accordance with the foregoing provisions, a fee of`
  line `such amount not exceeding two-and-a-half per cent. of the amount of the tax due as shall in each case be`
  line `fixed by the Commissioner, shall be charged, and the said fee shall be included in the costs of recovery.`
obj_root_law_sections_158_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_159:
  sectionId (27287)
  sectionNo (159)
  orderNo 204
  title `Recovery from a person about to leave Delhi.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_159_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_159_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27287&sectionno=159&orderno=204&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_159_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Commissioner has reason to believe`
  line `that any person from whom any sum is due or is about to become due on account of any tax is about to`
  line `move from Delhi, he may direct the immediate payment by such person of the sum so due or about to`
  line `become due and cause a notice of demand for the same to be served on such person.`
  line
  line `(2) If, on the service of such notice, such person does not forthwith pay the sum so due or about to`
  line `become due, the amount shall be leviable by distress or attachment and sale in the manner hereinbefore`
  line `provided, and the warrant of distress or attachment and sale may be issued and executed without any`
  line delay.
obj_root_law_sections_159_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_160:
  sectionId (27288)
  sectionNo (160)
  orderNo 205
  title `Power to institute suit for recovery.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_160_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_160_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27288&sectionno=160&orderno=205&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_160_content:
  string
  line `Instead of proceeding against a defaulter by distress and`
  line `sale as hereinbefore provided, or after a defaulter has been so proceeded against unsuccessfully or with`
  line `partial success, any sum due or the balance of any sum due, as the case may be, from such defaulter on`
  line `account of a tax may be recovered from him by a suit in any court of competent jurisdiction.`
obj_root_law_sections_160_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_161:
  sectionId (27289)
  sectionNo (161)
  orderNo 206
  title `Power of seizure of vehicles and animals in case of non-payment of tax thereon.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_161_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_161_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27289&sectionno=161&orderno=206&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_161_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the`
  line `tax on any vehicle or animal is not paid, then, instead of proceeding against the defaulter by distress and`
  line `sale of his other movable property as hereinbefore provided, the Commissioner may, at any time after the`
  line `tax has become due, seize and detain the vehicle or animal or both and, if the owner or other person`
  line `entitled thereto does not within seven days in respect of a vehicle and two days in respect of an animal`
  line `from the date of such seizure and detention, claim the same and pay the tax due together with the charges`
  line `incurred in connection with the seizure and detention, the Commissioner may cause the same to be sold`
  line `and apply the proceeds of sale or such part thereof as is required in discharge of the sum due and the`
  line `charges incurred as aforesaid.`
  line
  line `(2) The surplus, if any, remaining after the application of the sale-proceeds under sub-section (1) shall`
  line `be disposed of in the manner laid down in sub-sections (6) and (7) of section 158.`
obj_root_law_sections_161_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_162:
  sectionId (27290)
  sectionNo (162)
  orderNo 207
  title `Occupiers may be required to pay rent towards satisfaction of property taxes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_162_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_162_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27290&sectionno=162&orderno=207&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_162_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the`
  line `purposes of recovering the amount of any property tax from any occupier under section 122, the`
  line `Commissioner shall cause to be served on such occupier a notice requiring him to pay to ^1[^2[the Corporation]]`
  line `any rent due or falling due from him in respect of the land or building to the extent necessary to satisfy`
  line `the portion of the sum due for which he is liable under the said section.`
  line
  line `(2) Such notice shall operate as an attachment of the said rent unless the portion of the sum due shall`
  line `have been paid and satisfied and the occupier shall be entitled to credit in account with the person to`
  line `whom such rent is due for any sum paid by him to ^1[^2[the Corporation]] in pursuance of such notice:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the person to whom such rent is due is not the person primarily liable for payment of`
  line `the property tax, he shall be entitled to recover from the person primarily liable for the payment of such`
  line `tax any amount for which credit is claimed as aforesaid.`
  line
  line `(3) If any occupier fails to pay to ^1[^2[the Corporation]] any rent due or falling due which he has been`
  line `required to pay in pursuance of a notice served upon him as aforesaid, the amount of such rent may be`
  line `recovered from him by ^1[^2[the Corporation]] as an arrear of tax under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_162_footnotes:
