obj_root_law_sections_169:
  sectionId (27297)
  sectionNo (169)
  orderNo 214
  title `Appeal against assessment, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_169_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_169_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27297&sectionno=169&orderno=214&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_169_content:
  string
  line `^1[169. Appeal against assessment, etc.—(1) An appeal against the levy or assessment or revision of`
  line `assessment of any tax under this Act shall lie to the Municipal Taxation Tribunal constituted under this`
  line `section:`
  line `Provided that the full amount of the property tax shall be paid before filing any appeal:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Municipal Taxation Tribunal may, with the approval of the District Judge of`
  line `Delhi, also take up any case for which any appeal may be pending before the court of such District Judge.`
  line `Provided also that any appeal pending before the court of such District Judge shall be transferred to the`
  line `Municipal Taxation Tribunal for disposal, if requested by the applicant for the settlement thereof on the`
  line `basis of annual value.`
  line
  line `(2) (a) The Government shall constitute a Municipal Taxation Tribunal consisting of a Chairperson`
  line `,and such other members as the Government may determine:`
  line
  line `Provided that on the recommendation of the Government the Chairperson may constitute one or more`
  line `separate Benches, each Bench comprising two members, one of whom shall be a member of the Higher`
  line `Judicial Service of a State or a Union territory and the other member from the higher administrative service, and may transfer to any such Bench any appeal for disposal or may withdraw from any Bench any appeal`
  line `before it is finally disposed of.`
  line
  line `(b) The Chairperson, and not less than half of the other members, of the Municipal Taxation Tribunal`
  line `shall be persons who are or have been the members of the Higher Judicial Service of a State or a Union`
  line `territory for a period of not less than five years, and the remaining members, if any, shall have such`
  line `qualifications and experience as the Government may by rules determine.`
  line
  line `(c) The Chairperson and the other members of the Municipal Taxation Tribunal shall be appointed by`
  line `the Government for a period of five years or till they attain the age of sixty-five years, whichever is earlier.`
  line
  line `(d) The other terms and conditions of service of the Chairperson and the other members of the`
  line `Municipal Taxation Tribunal, including salaries and allowances, shall be such as may be determined by`
  line `rules by the Government.`
  line
  line `(e) The salaries and allowances of the Chairperson and the other members of the Municipal Taxation`
  line `Tribunal shall be paid from the Municipal Fund.`
  line
  line `(3) In every appeal, the costs shall be in the discretion of the Municipal Taxation Tribunal or the bench`
  line `thereof, if any.`
  line
  line `(4) Costs awarded under this section to ^2[^3[the Corporation]] shall be recoverable by ^2[^3[the Corporation]] as an arrear of tax due from the appellant.`
  line
  line `(5) If ^2[^3[the Corporation]] fails to pay any costs awarded to an appellant within ten days from the date`
  line `of the order for payment thereof, the Municipal Taxation Tribunal may order the Commissioner to pay the`
  line `costs to the appellant.]`
obj_root_law_sections_169_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 6 of 2003, s. 32, for section 169 (w.e.f. 1-8-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_170:
  sectionId (27298)
  sectionNo (170)
  orderNo 215
  title `Conditions of right to appeal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_170_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_170_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27298&sectionno=170&orderno=215&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_170_content:
  string
  line `No Appeal shall be heard or determined under section 169`
  line unless
  line
  line `(a) the appeal is, in the case of a property tax, brought within thirty days next after the date of`
  line `authentication of the assessment list under section 124 (exclusive of the time requisite for obtaining a`
  line `Copy of the relevant entries therein) or, as the case may be, within thirty days of the date on which an`
  line `amendment is finally made under section 126, and, in the case of any other tax, within thirty days`
  line `next after the date of the receipt of the notice of assessment or of alteration of assessment or, if no`
  line `notice has been given, within thirty days after the date of the presentation of the first bill or, as the`
  line `case may be, the first notice of demand in respect thereof:`
  line
  line `Provided that an appeal may be admitted after the expiration of the period prescribed therefor by`
  line `this section if the appellant satisfies the court that he had sufficient cause for not preferring the appeal`
  line `within that period;`
  line
  line `(b) the amount, if any, in dispute in the appeal has been deposited by the appellant in the office of`
  line `^1[^2[the Corporation]].`
obj_root_law_sections_170_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_171:
  sectionId (27299)
  sectionNo (171)
  orderNo 216
  title `Finality of appellate orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_171_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 6 of 2003, s. 33, for “court” (w.e.f. 1-8-2003).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27299&sectionno=171&orderno=216&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_171_content:
  string
  line `The order of the court confirming, setting aside or modifying an`
  line `order in respect of any rateable value or assessment or liability to assessment or taxation shall be final:`
  line
  line `Provided that it shall be lawful for the ^1[Municipal Taxation Tribunal], upon application or on its own motion, to review any`
  line `order passed by it in appeal within three months from the date of the order.`
obj_root_law_sections_172:
  sectionId (27300)
  sectionNo (172)
  orderNo 217
  title `Power to inspect for purposes of determining rateable value or tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_172_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 6 of 2003, s. 2, for "rateable value".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27300&sectionno=172&orderno=217&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_172_content:
  string
  line `172. Power to inspect for purposes of determining ^1[annual value] or tax.---(1) The Commissioner`
  line `may, without giving any previous notice, enter upon and make an inspection of`
  line
  line `(a) any land or building for the purpose of determining the ^1[annual value] of such land or`
  line building;
  line
  line `(b) any stable, garage, or coach house or any place wherein he may have reason to believe that`
  line `there is any vehicle or animal liable to a tax under this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) any place or premises which he has reason to believe are being used or are about to be used`
  line `for any performance or show in respect of which the theatre tax is payable or would be payable;`
  line
  line `(d) any land, building or vehicle in or upon which any advertisement liable to tax under this Act`
  line `is exhibited or displayed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commissioner may, by written summons, require the attendance before him of any person`
  line `whom he has reason to believe to be liable to the payment of a tax in respect of a vehicle or animal, or of`
  line `any servant of any such person and may examine such person or servant as to the number and description`
  line `of vehicles and animals owned by or in the possession or under the control of such person; and every`
  line `person or servant of such person so summoned shall be bound to attend before the Commissioner and to`
  line `give information to the best of his knowledge and belief as to the said matters.`
obj_root_law_sections_172_a:
  sectionId (67090)
  sectionNo 172A
  orderNo 218
  title `Power to appoint an agency for administration of property tax`
  content obj_root_law_sections_172_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_172_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=67090&sectionno=172A&orderno=218&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_172_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[172A. Power to appoint an agency for administration of property tax.--(1) The Commissioner`
  line `may, subject to such bye-laws as specified by ^2[^3[the Corporation]] in this behalf, appoint any citizens`
  line `welfare association recognized by ^2[^3[the Corporation]] , or any Scheduled bank, or any person or other`
  line `agency to--`
  line
  line `(a) maintain the assessment book under section 124;`
  line
  line `(b) collect tax and deposit the same with ^2[^3[the Corporation]]; and`
  line
  line `(c) carry out such other tasks as may be assigned to them by a resolution of the Standing Committee.`
  line
  line `(2) Such citizens welfare association, bank or person, or other agency shall be paid such collection`
  line `charges as may be authorized by such bye-laws as may be specified by ^2[^3[the Corporation]].]`
obj_root_law_sections_172_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Delhi Act 6 of 2003, s. 35 (w.e.f. 1-8-2003).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "a Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_173:
  sectionId (27301)
  sectionNo (173)
  orderNo 219
  title Composition.
  content obj_root_law_sections_173_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_173_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27301&sectionno=173&orderno=219&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_173_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commissioner may, with the previous sanction of the Standing`
  line `Committee, allow any person to compound for any tax.`
  line
  line `(2) Every sum due by reason of the composition of a tax under sub-section (1) shall be recovered as`
  line `an arrear of tax under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_173_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_174:
  sectionId (27302)
  sectionNo (174)
  orderNo 220
  title `Irrecoverable debts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_174_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_174_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27302&sectionno=174&orderno=220&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_174_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commissioner may write off any sum due on account of any tax`
  line `or of the costs of recovering any tax if such sum is, in his opinion irrecoverable:`
  line
  line `Provided that, where the sum written off in favour of any one person exceeds one hundred rupees, the`
  line `previous sanction of the Standing Committee shall be first obtained.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commissioner shall report to the Standing Committee every case in which any sum has been`
  line `written off under sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_174_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_175:
  sectionId (27303)
  sectionNo (175)
  orderNo 221
  title `Obligation to disclose liability.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_175_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_175_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27303&sectionno=175&orderno=221&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_175_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commissioner may, by written notice, call upon any`
  line `inhabitant of Delhi to furnish such information as may be necessary for the purpose of ascertaining--`
  line
  line `(a) whether such inhabitant is liable to pay any tax imposed by ^1[^2[the Corporation]] under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) at what amount he should be assessed; or`
  line
  line `(c) the rateable value of the land or building which he occupies and the name and address of the`
  line `owner or lessee thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) If any person when called upon under sub-section (1) to furnish information neglects to furnish it`
  line `within the period specified in this behalf by the Commissioner or furnishes information which is not true`
  line `to the best of his knowledge or belief, he shall be liable, in addition to any penalty which may be imposed`
  line `under this Act, to be assessed at such amount on account of tax as the Commissioner may deem proper,`
  line `and the assessment so made shall, subject to the provisions of this Act, be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_175_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_176:
  sectionId (27304)
  sectionNo (176)
  orderNo 222
  title `Immaterial error not to affect liability.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_176_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_176_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27304&sectionno=176&orderno=222&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_176_content:
  string
  line `No assessment and no charge or demand on account`
  line `of any tax shall be impeached or affected by reason only of any mistake in the name, residence, place of`
  line `business or occupation of any person liable to pay the tax or in the description of any property or thing, or`
  line `of any mistake in the amount of the assessment, charge or demand, or by reason only of clerical error or`
  line `other defect of form, if the directions contained in this Act and the bye-laws made thereunder have in`
  line `substance and effect been complied with; and it shall be enough in the case of any such tax on property or`
  line `any assessment of value for the purpose of any such tax, if the property taxed or assessed is so described`
  line `as to be generally known; and it shall not be necessary to name the owner or occupier thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_176_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_177:
  sectionId (27305)
  sectionNo (177)
  orderNo 223
  title `General power of exemption.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_177_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_177_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27305&sectionno=177&orderno=223&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_177_content:
  string
  line `^1[^2[The Corporation]] may, by resolution passed in this behalf,`
  line `exempt either wholly or in part from the payment of any tax levied under this Act, any class of persons or`
  line `any class of property or goods.`
