obj_root_law_sections_185:
  sectionId (27313)
  sectionNo (185)
  orderNo 231
  title `Power of Corporation to borrow.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_185_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_185_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27313&sectionno=185&orderno=231&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_185_content:
  string
  line `(1) ^1[^2[The Corporation]] may, in pursuance of any resolution`
  line `passed by it, borrow by way of debenture or otherwise on the security of all or any of the taxes, rates,`
  line `cesses, fees and charges authorised by or under this Act, any sums of money which may be required--`
  line
  line `(a) for acquiring any land which it has power to acquire;`
  line
  line `(b) for erecting any building which it has power to erect;`
  line
  line `(c) for the execution of any permanent work, the provision of any plant, or the doing of any other`
  line `thing which it has power to execute, provide or do, if the cost of carrying out the purpose in question`
  line `ought to be spread over a term of years;`
  line
  line ^3
  line `[(d) to pay off any debt due to the Central Government or the Government;]`
  line
  line `(e) to repay a loan previously raised under this Act or any other Act previously in force; or`
  line
  line `(f) for any other purpose for which ^4[^5[the Corporation]] is, by virtue of this Act or any other law for`
  line `the time being in force, authorised to borrow:`
  line
  line `Provided that--`
  line
  line `(i) no loan shall be raised without the previous sanction of the Central Government or without`
  line `previous publication of the application for sanction under the Local Authorities Loans Act, 1914, (9`
  line `of 1914) and the rules made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(ii) the amount of loan, the rate of interest and the terms including the date of floatation, the time`
  line `and method of the repayment and the like shall be subject to the approval of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) When any sum of money has been borrowed under sub-section (1), no portion of any sum of`
  line `money borrowed for any of the purposes referred to in clause (c) of sub-section (1) shall be applied to the`
  line `payment of salaries and allowances to any municipal officers or other municipal employees other than`
  line `those exclusively employed in connection with the carrying out of that purpose.`
obj_root_law_sections_185_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “A Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022)`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 89, for clause (d) (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_186:
  sectionId (27314)
  sectionNo (186)
  orderNo 232
  title `Time for repayment of money borrowed under section 185.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_186_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_186_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27314&sectionno=186&orderno=232&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_186_content:
  string
  line `The time for the repayment of`
  line `any money borrowed under section 185 shall in no case exceed sixty years and the time for repayment of`
  line `any money borrowed for the purpose of discharging any previous loan shall not, except with the express`
  line `sanction of the Central Government, extend beyond the unexpired portion of the period for which such`
  line `previous loan was sanctioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_186_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_187:
  sectionId (27315)
  sectionNo (187)
  orderNo 233
  title `Form and effect of debentures.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_187_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_187_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27315&sectionno=187&orderno=233&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_187_content:
  string
  line `All debentures issued under this Chapter shall be in such`
  line `form as ^1[^2[Corporation]] may, with the previous sanction of ^3[the Central ^4[Government]], determine and shall be`
  line `transferable in such manner as shall be therein expressed; and the right to sue in respect of the moneys`
  line `secured by any of such debentures shall vest in the holders thereof for the time being without any`
  line `preference by reason of some such debentures being prior in date to others.`
obj_root_law_sections_187_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "a Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for "Central Government" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "Government" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
obj_root_law_sections_188:
  sectionId (27316)
  sectionNo (188)
  orderNo 234
  title `Payment to survivors of joint payees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_188_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_188_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27316&sectionno=188&orderno=234&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_188_content:
  string
  line `When any debenture or security issued under this Act`
  line `is payable to two or more persons jointly, and either or any of them dies, then notwithstanding anything in`
  line `section 45 of the Indian Contract Act, 1872 (9 of 1872), the debenture or security shall be payable to the`
  line `survivor or survivors of such person :`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall affect any claim by the legal representative of a deceased`
  line `person against such survivor or survivors.`
obj_root_law_sections_188_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_189:
  sectionId (27317)
  sectionNo (189)
  orderNo 235
  title `Receipt by joint holders for interest or dividend.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_189_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_189_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27317&sectionno=189&orderno=235&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_189_content:
  string
  line `When two or more persons are joint`
  line `holders of any debenture or security issued under this Act, any one of such persons may give an effectual`
  line `receipt for any interest or dividend payable in respect of such debenture or security, unless notice to the`
  line `contrary has been given to ^1[^2[the Corporation]] by the other of such persons.`
obj_root_law_sections_189_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_190:
  sectionId (27318)
  sectionNo (190)
  orderNo 236
  title `Maintenance and investment of sinking funds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_190_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_190_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27318&sectionno=190&orderno=236&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_190_content:
  string
  line `(1) ^1[^2[The Corporation]] shall maintain sinking`
  line `funds for the repayment of money borrowed on debentures issued and shall pay every year into such`
  line `sinking funds such sum as will be sufficient for the repayment within the period fixed for the loan of all`
  line `moneys borrowed on the debentures issued.`
  line
  line `(2) All money paid into the sinking funds shall, as soon as possible, be invested by the Commissioner`
  line `in public securities and every such investment shall be reported by the Commissioner to ^3[^4[the Corporation]] within fifteen days.`
  line
  line `(3) All dividends and other sums received in respect of any such investment shall, as soon as possible`
  line `after receipt, be paid into the sinking funds and invested in the manner laid down in sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(4) When any part of a sinking fund is invested in Delhi municipal debentures, or is applied in paying`
  line `off any part of a loan before the period fixed for repayment, the interest which would otherwise have been`
  line `payable on such debentures or on such part of the loan shall be paid into the sinking fund and invested in`
  line `the manner laid down in sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(5) Any investment made under this section may, subject to the provisions of sub-section (2), be`
  line `varied or transposed.`
obj_root_law_sections_190_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “A Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_191:
  sectionId (27319)
  sectionNo (191)
  orderNo 237
  title `Application of sinking funds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_191_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_191_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27319&sectionno=191&orderno=237&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_191_content:
  string
  line `A sinking fund or any part thereof shall be applied in or`
  line `towards the discharge of the loan or a part of the loan for which such fund was created, and until such`
  line `loan or part is wholly discharged shall not be applied for any other purpose:`
  line
  line `Provided that when any loan or part thereof has been consolidated under section 193, the`
  line `Commissioner shall transfer to the sinking fund of the consolidated loan such part of the sinking funds of`
  line `the original loans as may be proportionate to the amount of the original loans incorporated in the`
  line `consolidated loan.`
obj_root_law_sections_191_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_192:
  sectionId (27320)
  sectionNo (192)
  orderNo 238
  title `Annual statement by Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_192_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_192_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27320&sectionno=192&orderno=238&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_192_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commissioner shall, at the end of every year,`
  line `submit to Corporation a statement showing—`
  line
  line `(a) the amount which has been invested during the year under section 190;`
  line
  line `(b) the date of the last investment made previous to the submission of the statement;`
  line
  line `(c) the aggregate amount of the securities then in his hands; and`
  line
  line `(d) the aggregate amount which has up to the date of the statement been applied under section`
  line `191, in or towards discharging loans.`
  line
  line `(2) Every such statement shall be published in the Official Gazette.`
obj_root_law_sections_192_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_193:
  sectionId (27321)
  sectionNo (193)
  orderNo 239
  title `Power of Corporation to consolidate loans.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_193_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_193_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27321&sectionno=193&orderno=239&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_193_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary`
  line `contained in this Chapter, ^1[^2[the Corporation]] may consolidate all or any of its loans and for that purpose may`
  line `invite tenders for a new loan (to be called the Delhi Municipal consolidated loan, 19----------) and invite`
  line `holders of the municipal debentures to exchange their debentures for scrips of such loan.`
  line
  line `(2) The terms of any such consolidated loan and the form of its scrip and the rates at which exchange`
  line `into such consolidated loan shall be permitted shall be subject to the prior approval of the ^3[^4[Central`
  line Government]].
  line
  line `(3) The period for the exchanging of any such consolidated loan shall not, without the sanction of the`
  line `Central Government, extend beyond the farthest date within which any of the loans to be consolidated`
  line `would otherwise be repayable.`
  line
  line `(4) ^5[^6[The Corporation]] shall provide for the repayment of any such consolidated loan by a sinking fund`
  line `in the manner laid down in section 190, having regard to the amount transferred to such sinking fund`
  line `under section 191.`
obj_root_law_sections_193_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "a Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3.Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for “Central Government” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “Government” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "A Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_194:
  sectionId (27322)
  sectionNo (194)
  orderNo 240
  title `Priority of payments for interest and repayment of loans over other payments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_194_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_194_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27322&sectionno=194&orderno=240&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_194_content:
  string
  line All
  line `payments due from ^1[^2[the Corporation]] for interest on and repayment of loans shall be made in priority to all`
  line `other payments due from ^1[^2[the Corporation]].`
obj_root_law_sections_194_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_195:
  sectionId (27323)
  sectionNo (195)
  orderNo 241
  title `Attachment of Municipal Fund for recovery of money borrowed from Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_195_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 90, for "Government" (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27323&sectionno=195&orderno=241&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_195_content:
  string
  line `(1) If`
  line `any money borrowed or deemed to have been borrowed by the Corporation from the ^1`
  line [Central
  line `Government or the Government] or any interest or costs due in respect thereof be not repaid according to`
  line `the conditions of the loan, the ^1`
  line `[Central Government or the Government] may attach the Municipal Fund`
  line `or any part thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) After such attachment no person except an officer appointed in this behalf by the Central`
  line `Government shall in any way deal with the attached fund; but such officer may do all acts in respect`
  line `thereof which any municipal authority, officer or other employee might have done if such attachment had`
  line `not taken place, and may apply the proceeds in satisfaction of the arrears and of all interests and costs due`
  line `in respect thereof and of all expenses caused by the attachment and subsequent proceedings:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such attachment shall defeat or prejudice any debt for which the fund was previously`
  line `charged in accordance with law; and all such prior charges shall be paid out of the proceeds of the fund`
  line `before any part of the proceeds is applied to the satisfaction of the debt due to the ^1`
  line `[Central Government].`
obj_root_law_sections_196:
  sectionId (27324)
  sectionNo (196)
  orderNo 242
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_196_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_196_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27324&sectionno=196&orderno=242&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_196_content:
  string
  line `^1[^2[The Corporation]] may make regulations to carry out the purpose`
  line `of this Chapter including, in particular, the issue of duplicates in case of loss of debentures by theft,`
  line `destruction or otherwise, and renewal of debentures on payment of fees prescribed in this behalf by such`
  line regulations.
obj_root_law_sections_196_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “A Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_197:
  sectionId (27325)
  sectionNo (197)
  orderNo 243
  title `Acquisition of property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_197_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_197_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27325&sectionno=197&orderno=243&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_197_content:
  string
  line `^1[^2[The Corporation]] shall, for the purpose of this Act, have power to`
  line `acquire and hold movable and immovable property, or any interest therein.`
obj_root_law_sections_197_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “A Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_198:
  sectionId (27326)
  sectionNo (198)
  orderNo 244
  title `Acquisition of immovable property by agreement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_198_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_198_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27326&sectionno=198&orderno=244&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_198_content:
  string
  line `Whenever ^1[^2[the Corporation]] decides to`
  line `acquire any immovable property for the purpose of this Act, the Commissioner shall acquire such`
  line `property on behalf of ^1[^2[the Corporation]] by agreement on such terms and at such price as may be approved`
  line `by the Standing Committee.`
obj_root_law_sections_198_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_199:
  sectionId (27327)
  sectionNo (199)
  orderNo 245
  title `Procedure when immovable property cannot be acquired by agreement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_199_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_199_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27327&sectionno=199&orderno=245&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_199_content:
  string
  line `Whenever the`
  line `Commissioner is unable to acquire any immovable property under section 198 by agreement, ^1[Government] may at the request of the Commissioner procure the acquisition thereof under the provisions`
  line `of the Land Acquisition Act, 1894 (1 of 1894), and on payment by ^2[^3[the Corporation]] of the compensation`
  line `awarded under that Act and of the charges incurred by the Government in connection with the`
  line `proceedings, the land shall vest in ^2[^3[the Corporation]].`
obj_root_law_sections_199_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 90, for "Government" (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).br`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).br`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "a Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_200:
  sectionId (27328)
  sectionNo (200)
  orderNo 246
  title `Disposal of property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_200_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_200_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27328&sectionno=200&orderno=246&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_200_content:
  string
  line `With respect to the disposal of property belonging to ^1[^2[the Corporation]],`
  line `the following provisions shall have effect, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) the Commissioner may, in his discretion, dispose of, by sale or otherwise, any movable`
  line `property belonging to ^1[^2[the Corporation]] not exceeding in value in each instance one thousand rupees, or`
  line `such higher amount as ^1[^2[the Corporation]] may prescribe, or let out or hire any movable property or grant`
  line `a lease of any immovable property belonging to ^1[^2[the Corporation]], including any right of gathering and`
  line `taking fruits and the like, for a period not exceeding one year at a time;`
  line
  line `(b) the Commissioner may, with the sanction of the Standing Committee,---`
  line
  line `(i) dispose of, by sale or otherwise, any movable property belonging to ^1[^2[the Corporation]] the`
  line `value of which does not exceed five thousand rupees;`
  line
  line `(ii) grant a lease (other than a lease in perpetuity) of any immovable property belonging to ^1[^2[the`
  line `Corporation]]; or`
  line
  line `(iii) sell or grant a lease in perpetuity of any immovable property belonging to ^1[^2[the`
  line `Corporation]] the value of which does not exceed fifty thousand rupees or the annual rent of which`
  line `does not exceed three thousand rupees;`
  line
  line `(c) in cases not covered by clause (a) or clause (b), the Commissioner may, with the sanction of`
  line `^1[^2[the Corporation]], lease, sell, let out on hire or otherwise transfer any property, movable or immovable,`
  line `belonging to ^1[^2[the Corporation]];`
  line
  line `(d) the consideration for which any immovable property may be sold, leased or otherwise`
  line `transferred shall not be less than the value at which such immovable property could be sold, leased or`
  line `otherwise transferred in normal and fair competition;`
  line
  line `(e) the sanction of the Standing Committee or of ^1[^2[the Corporation]] under the aforesaid clauses may`
  line `be given either generally for any class of cases or specially for any particular case;`
  line
  line `(f) subject to any conditions or limitations that may be specified in any other provisions of this`
  line `Act, the foregoing provisions of this section shall apply to every disposal of property belonging to ^1[^2[the`
  line `Corporation]] made under, or for any purpose of, this Act;`
  line
  line `(g) every case of disposal of property under clause (a) and clause (b) shall be reported by the`
  line `Commissioner without delay to the Standing Committee and ^1[^2[the Corporation]] respectively.`
obj_root_law_sections_200_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_201:
  sectionId (27329)
  sectionNo (201)
  orderNo 247
  title `Contracts by the Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_201_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_201_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27329&sectionno=201&orderno=247&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_201_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of sections 202 and 203, ^1[^2[the`
  line `Corporation]] shall be competent to enter into and perform any contract necessary for the purposes of this`
  line Act.
obj_root_law_sections_201_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_202:
  sectionId (27330)
  sectionNo (202)
  orderNo 248
  title `Procedure for making contracts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_202_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_202_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27330&sectionno=202&orderno=248&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_202_content:
  string
  line `With respect to the making of contracts, the following`
  line `provisions shall have effect, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) every such contract shall be made on behalf of ^1[^2[the Corporation]] by the Commissioner;`
  line
  line `(b) no such contract, for any purpose which in accordance with any provision of this Act the`
  line `Commissioner may not carry out without the approval or sanction of ^1[^2[the Corporation]] or some other`
  line `municipal authority shall be made by him until and unless such approval or sanction has been duly`
  line obtained;
  line
  line ^3
  line `[(c) no contract which will involve an expenditure exceeding ten lakh rupees or such higher`
  line `amount as ^4[the Central ^5[Government]] may from time to time, fix, shall be made by the Commissioner`
  line `unless the same is previously approved by the Standing Committee; and`
  line
  line `(d) every contract made by the Commissioner involving an expenditure exceeding one lakh`
  line `rupees but not exceeding ten lakh rupees or such higher amount as may be fixed under clause (c) shall`
  line `be reported by him, within one month after the same has been made to the Standing Committee.]`
  line
  line ^6
  line `* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_202_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 91, for clauses (c) and (d) (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “Central Government” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “Government” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `6. Omitted by s. 91, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_203:
  sectionId (27331)
  sectionNo (203)
  orderNo 249
  title `Mode of executing contracts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_203_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_203_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27331&sectionno=203&orderno=249&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_203_content:
  string
  line `(1) The mode of executing contracts under this Act shall be`
  line `prescribed by bye-laws made in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) No contract which is not made in accordance with the provisions of this Act and the bye-laws`
  line `made thereunder shall be binding on ^1[^2[the Corporation]].`
  line
  line `^3[^4[(3) The contracts already made in accordance with the provisions of the bye-laws made under this`
  line `Act prior to the commencement of the Delhi Municipal Corporation (Amendment) Act, 2022 shall be`
  line `deemed to have been executed by the Commissioner on behalf of the Corporation constituted under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 3 and shall continue until the expiry of the validity period of such contracts.]]`
obj_root_law_sections_203_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3 Ins. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 15 (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 8, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_204:
  sectionId (27332)
  sectionNo (204)
  orderNo 250
  title `Accounts to be kept.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_204_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_204_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27332&sectionno=204&orderno=250&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_204_content:
  string
  line `^1[There shall be kept in such manner and in such form as may be`
  line `prescribed by regulations the General Account of all receipts and expenditures of ^1[^2[the Corporation]].]`
obj_root_law_sections_204_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022 s. 92, for section 204 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_205:
  sectionId (27333)
  sectionNo (205)
  orderNo 251
  title `Scrutiny of accounts by Municipal Chief Auditor and by the Standing Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_205_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_205_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27333&sectionno=205&orderno=251&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_205_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `The Municipal Chief Auditor shall conduct a monthly examination and audit of the municipal accounts`
  line `and shall report thereon to the Standing Committee who shall publish monthly an abstract of the receipt`
  line `and expenditure of the month last preceding, signed by not less than two members of that Committee and`
  line `by the Municipal Chief Auditor.`
  line
  line `(2) The Standing Committee may also from time to time and for such period as it thinks fit conduct`
  line `independently any examination and audit of the municipal accounts.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purpose of examination and audit of the municipal accounts the Standing Committee and`
  line `the Municipal Chief Auditor shall have access to all the municipal accounts and to all records and`
  line `correspondence relating thereto and the Commissioner shall forthwith furnish to the Standing Committee`
  line `or the Municipal Chief Auditor any explanation concerning any receipts or expenditure which they may`
  line `call for.`
obj_root_law_sections_205_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_206:
  sectionId (27334)
  sectionNo (206)
  orderNo 252
  title `Report by the Municipal Chief Auditor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_206_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_206_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27334&sectionno=206&orderno=252&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_206_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Municipal Chief Auditor shall---`
  line
  line `(a) report to the Standing Committee any material impropriety or irregularity which he may at`
  line `any time observe in the expenditure or in the recovery of moneys due to ^1[^2[the Corporation]] or in the`
  line `municipal accounts;`
  line
  line `(b) furnish to the Standing Committee such information as that Committee may from time to time`
  line `require concerning the progress of the audit.`
  line
  line `(2) The Standing Committee shall cause to be laid before ^1[^2[the Corporation]] every report made by the`
  line `Municipal Chief Auditor to the Standing Committee and every statement of the views of the Municipal`
  line `Chief Auditor on any matter affecting the exercise and performance of the powers and duties assigned to`
  line `him under this Act which the Municipal Chief Auditor may require the Standing Committee to place`
  line `before ^1[^2[the Corporation]] together with a report stating what orders have been passed by the Standing`
  line `Committee upon such report or statement, and ^1[^2[the Corporation]] may take such action in regard to any of`
  line `the matters aforesaid as ^1[^2[the Corporation]] may deem necessary.`
  line
  line `(3) As soon as may be after the commencement of each year the Municipal Chief Auditor shall`
  line `deliver to the Standing Committee a report of the entire municipal accounts for the previous year.`
  line
  line `(4) The Commissioner shall cause the said report to be printed and shall forward as soon as may be a`
  line `printed copy thereof to each councillor and alderman.`
  line
  line `(5) The Commissioner shall also forward without delay to the ^3`
  line `*** Government so many copies of`
  line `the said report as may be required by that Government with a brief statement of the action, if any taken or`
  line `proposed to be taken thereon.`
obj_root_law_sections_206_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012)`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. The word Central omitted by Act 67 of 1993, s. 93 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_207:
  sectionId (27335)
  sectionNo (207)
  orderNo 253
  title `Special audit at the direction of the Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_207_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_207_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27335&sectionno=207&orderno=253&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_207_content:
  string
  line `(1) The ^1*** Government may at`
  line `any time appoint an auditor for the purpose of making a special audit ^2[of the General Account] of the`
  line `Municipal Fund and of reporting thereon to the ^1*** Government and the costs of such audit as`
  line `determined by the ^1*** Government shall be chargeable to the Municipal Fund.`
  line
  line `(2) An auditor so appointed may exercise any power which the Municipal Chief Auditor may`
  line exercise.
obj_root_law_sections_207_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The word "Central" omitted by Act 67 of 1993, s. 94 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 94, ibid., for "of any of the Accounts" (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_208:
  sectionId (27336)
  sectionNo (208)
  orderNo 254
  title `Procedure to be followed by the Municipal Chief Auditor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_208_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_208_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27336&sectionno=208&orderno=254&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_208_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Municipal Chief Auditor`
  line `shall audit the accounts of ^1[^2[the Corporation]] with the assistance of officers and other employees`
  line `subordinate to him.`
  line
  line `(2) In the discharge of his functions under this section the Municipal Chief Auditor shall`
  line
  line `(a) audit the accounts of expenditure from the revenue of ^1[^2[the Corporation]], expenditure on account`
  line `of loan works and expenditure incurred out of special funds shall ascertain whether moneys shown`
  line `therein as having been disbursed were legally available for, and applicable to, the service or purpose`
  line `to which they have been applied or charged, and whether the expenditure conforms to the authority`
  line `which governs it;`
  line
  line `(b) audit the accounts of debts, deposits sinking funds, advances, suspense and remittance`
  line `transactions of the Corporation and report upon those accounts and upon the results of verification of`
  line `the balances relating thereto.`
  line
  line `(3) The Municipal Chief Auditor shall examine and audit the statement of accounts relating to the`
  line `commercial services conducted in any department of ^1[^2[the Corporation]], including the trading,`
  line `manufacturing and profit and loss accounts, and the balance-sheets where such accounts are maintained`
  line `under the orders of ^1[^2[the Corporation]], ^3`
  line `[or the Standing Committee,] and shall certify and report upon these`
  line accounts.
  line
  line `(4) The Municipal Chief Auditor shall, in consultation with ^4`
  line `*** the Standing Committee and subject`
  line `to any directions given by the Corporation, determine the form and manner in which his reports on the`
  line `accounts of ^1[^2[the Corporation]] shall be prepared and shall have authority to call upon any officer of the`
  line `Corporation to provide any information necessary for the preparation of these reports.`
obj_root_law_sections_208_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "a Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 95, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `4. Certain words omitted by s. 95, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_209:
  sectionId (27337)
  sectionNo (209)
  orderNo 255
  title `Power of Municipal Chief Auditor to make queries, etc., and call for returns, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_209_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_209_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=27337&sectionno=209&orderno=255&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_209_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `Municipal Chief Auditor may make such queries and observations in relation to any of the accounts of ^1[^2[the`
  line `Corporation]] which he is required to audit and call for such vouchers, statements, returns and explanations`
  line `in relation to such accounts as he may think fit.`
  line
  line `(2) Every such query or observation as aforesaid shall be promptly taken into consideration by the`
  line `officer or authority to whom it may be addressed and returned without delay with the necessary vouchers,`
  line `documents or explanations to the Municipal Chief Auditor.`
  line
  line `(3) The powers of the Municipal Chief Auditor with regard to the disapproval of, and the procedure`
  line `with regard to the settlement of objections to, expenditure from the revenues of ^1[^2[the Corporation]] shall be`
  line `such as may be prescribed by the Standing Committee in consultation with the Municipal Chief Auditor`
  line `and with the approval of ^1[^2[the Corporation]].`
  line
  line `(4) If the Municipal Chief Auditor considers it desirable that the whole or any part of the audit`
  line `applied to any accounts which he is required to audit shall be conducted in the offices in which those`
  line `accounts originate he may require that those accounts, together with all books and documents having`
  line `relation there to, shall at all convenient times be made available in the said offices for inspection.`
  line
  line `(5) The Municipal Chief Auditor shall have the power to require that any books or other documents`
  line `relating to the accounts he is required to audit shall be sent for inspection by him:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the documents are confidential he shall be responsible for preventing disclosure of`
  line `their contents.`
  line
  line `(6) The Municipal Chief Auditor shall have authority to frame standing orders and to give directions`
  line `on all matters relating to audit, and particularly in respect of the method and the extent of audit to be`
  line `applied and the raising and pursuing of objections.`
  line
  line `(7) Expenditure sanctioned by the Municipal Chief Auditor shall be audited by an officer to be`
  line `nominated by ^1[^2[the Corporation]].`
obj_root_law_sections_209_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "a Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
