obj_root_law_sections_298:
  sectionId (31207)
  sectionNo (298)
  orderNo 346
  title `Vesting of public streets in the Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_298_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_298_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31207&sectionno=298&orderno=346&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_298_content:
  string
  line `(1) ^1[(1) All streets within the jurisdiction of ^2[^3[the Corporation]] constituted under sub-section (1) of section 3 of the this Act which are or at any time become`
  line `public streets, and the pavements, stones and other materials thereof shall vest in such Corporation:`
  line
  line `Provided that no public street which immediately before the commencement of the Delhi Municipal`
  line `Corporation (Amendment) Act, 2011 vested in the Union, shall, unless the ^4[Government] with the consent`
  line `of the concerned Corporation so directs, vest in such Corporation by virtue of this sub-section.]`
  line
  line `(2) All public streets vesting in ^2[^3[the Corporation]] shall be under the control of the Commissioner and`
  line `shall be maintained; controlled and regulated by him in accordance with the bye-laws made in this behalf.`
  line
  line ^5
  line `[(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-sections (1) and (2), the ^4[Government] may,`
  line `by notification, direct that all or any of the functions of ^2[^3[the Corporation]] or the Commissioner, in respect`
  line `of public streets under this Act shall be performed by such authority as may be specified therein.]`
obj_root_law_sections_298_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 16, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "a Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for "Central Government" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 97 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_299:
  sectionId (31208)
  sectionNo (299)
  orderNo 347
  title `Functions of Commissioner in respect of public streets.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_299_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_299_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31208&sectionno=299&orderno=347&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_299_content:
  string
  line `(1)The Commissioner shall, from`
  line `time to time, cause all public streets vested in ^1[^2[the Corporation]] to be levelled, metalled or paved,`
  line `channelled, altered or repaired, and may widen, extend or otherwise improve any such street or cause the`
  line `soil thereof to be raised, lowered or altered or may place and keep in repair fences and posts for the safety`
  line `of foot-passengers:`
  line
  line `Provided that no widening, extension or other improvement of a public street, the aggregate cost of`
  line `which will exceed five thousand rupees, shall be undertaken by the Commissioner except with the`
  line `previous sanction of ^1[^2[the Corporation]].`
  line
  line `(2) With the previous sanction of ^1[^2[the Corporation]] the Commissioner may permanently close the`
  line `whole or any part of a public street:`
  line
  line `Provided that before according such sanction ^1[^2[the Corporation]] shall by notice publish in the manner`
  line `specified by bye-laws give reasonable opportunity to the residents likely to be affected by such closure to`
  line `make suggestions or objections with respect to such closure and shall consider all such suggestions or`
  line `objections which may be made within one month from the date of the publication of the said notice.`
obj_root_law_sections_299_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_300:
  sectionId (31209)
  sectionNo (300)
  orderNo 348
  title `Disposal of land forming site of public streets permanently closed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_300_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_300_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31209&sectionno=300&orderno=348&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_300_content:
  string
  line `Whenever any public`
  line `street or a part thereof is permanently closed under sub-section (2) of section 299 the site of such street or`
  line `of the portion thereof may be disposed of as land vesting in ^1[^2[the Corporation]].`
obj_root_law_sections_300_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_301:
  sectionId (31210)
  sectionNo (301)
  orderNo 349
  title `Power to make new public streets.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_301_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_301_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31210&sectionno=301&orderno=349&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_301_content:
  string
  line `The Commissioner may at any time with the previous`
  line `sanction of ^1[^2[the Corporation]]:---`
  line
  line `(a) lay out and make new public streets;`
  line
  line `(b) construct bridges and sub-ways;`
  line
  line `(c) turn or divert any existing public street; and`
  line
  line `(d) lay down and determine the position and direction of a street or streets in any part of ^3[^4[Delhi]]`
  line `notwithstanding that no proposal for the erection of any building in the vicinity has been received.`
obj_root_law_sections_301_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for “Delhi” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “the area of the Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_302:
  sectionId (31211)
  sectionNo (302)
  orderNo 350
  title `Minimum width of new public streets.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_302_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_302_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31211&sectionno=302&orderno=350&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_302_content:
  string
  line `The Commissioner shall, from time to time, with the`
  line `sanction of the Standing Committee, specify the minimum width of different classes of new public streets`
  line `according to the nature of the traffic likely to be carried thereon, and the streets with which they join at`
  line `one or both ends, the localities in which they are situated, the heights up to which buildings abutting`
  line `thereon may be erected and other similar considerations.`
obj_root_law_sections_302_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_303:
  sectionId (31212)
  sectionNo (303)
  orderNo 351
  title `Power to prohibit use of public streets for certain kind of traffic`
  content obj_root_law_sections_303_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_303_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31212&sectionno=303&orderno=351&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_303_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commissioner`
  line may
  line
  line `(a) prohibit vehicular traffic in any public street or any portion thereof so as to prevent danger,`
  line `obstruction or inconvenience to the public or to ensure quietness in any locality;`
  line
  line `(b) prohibit in respect of all public streets, or any particular public street, the transit of any vehicle`
  line `of such form, construction, weight or size or laden with such heavy or unwiledy objects as may be`
  line `likely to cause injury to the roadways or any construction thereon, except under such conditions as to`
  line `time, mode of traction or locomotion, use of appliances for the protection of roadways, number of`
  line `lights and assistants and other general precautions and upon the payment of such charges as may be`
  line `specified by the Commissioner generally or specially in each case;`
  line
  line `(c) prohibit access to premises from any particular public street carrying high speed vehicular`
  line `traffic :`
  line
  line `Provided that the Commissioner shall not take action without the sanction of ^1[^2[the Corporation]] in cases`
  line `under clause (a) and without the sanction of the Standing Committee in cases under clause (c).`
  line
  line `(2) Notices of such prohibition as are imposed under sub-section (1) shall be posted in conspicuous`
  line `places at or near both ends of public streets or portions thereof to which they relate, unless such`
  line `prohibition applies generally to all public streets.`
obj_root_law_sections_303_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_304:
  sectionId (31213)
  sectionNo (304)
  orderNo 352
  title `Power to acquire lands and buildings for public streets and for public parking places.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_304_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_304_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31213&sectionno=304&orderno=352&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_304_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions contained in Chapter X, the Commissioner may`
  line
  line `(a) acquire any land required for the purpose of opening, widening, extending or otherwise`
  line `improving any public street or of making any new public street, and any building standing upon such`
  line land;
  line
  line `(b) acquire in relation to any such land or building, all such land with buildings, if any, thereon as ^1[^2[`
  line `the Corporation]] may think expedient to acquire outside of the regular line, or of the intended regular`
  line `line, of such street;`
  line
  line `(c) acquire any land for the purpose of laying out or making a public parking place.`
obj_root_law_sections_304_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_305:
  sectionId (31214)
  sectionNo (305)
  orderNo 353
  title `Defining the regular line of streets`
  content obj_root_law_sections_305_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_305_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31214&sectionno=305&orderno=353&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_305_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commissioner may define a line on one or both`
  line `sides of any public street in accordance with the bye-laws made in this behalf and may, with the previous`
  line `sanction of ^1[^2[the Corporation]], redefine at any time any such regular line :`
  line
  line `Provided that, before according sanction ^1[^2[the Corporation]] shall by public notice afford reasonable`
  line `opportunity to the residents of premises abutting on such public street to make suggestions or objections`
  line `with respect to the proposed redefined line of the street and shall consider all such suggestions or`
  line `objections which may be made within one month from the date of the publication of the said notice:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the regular line of any public street operative under any law in force in any part`
  line `of Delhi immediately before the commencement of this Act shall be deemed to be a line defined by the`
  line `Commissioner under this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(2) The line for the time being defined or redefined shall be called the regular line of street.`
  line
  line `(3) No person shall construct or reconstruct any building or a portion thereof or any boundary wall or`
  line `other structure whatsoever within the regular line of a street except with the written permission of the`
  line `Commissioner:`
  line
  line `Provided that if within sixty days after the receipt of application from any person for permission to`
  line `construct or reconstruct a boundary wall or a portion thereof, the Commissioner fails to take steps to`
  line `acquire the land within the regular line of the street in accordance with section 308, then, that person may,`
  line `subject to any other provisions of this Act and the bye-laws made thereunder, proceed with the work of`
  line `construction or reconstruction of such boundary wall or portion thereof.`
  line
  line `(4) When the Commissioner grants permission for the construction or reconstruction of any building`
  line `or any boundary wall or other structure within the regular line of a street, he may require the owner of the building to execute an agreement binding himself and his successors-in-interest not to claim`
  line `compensation in the event of the Commissioner at any time thereafter calling upon him or any of his`
  line `successors by written notice to remove any work carried out in pursuance of such permission and to pay`
  line `the expenses of such removal if, in default, such removal is carried out by the Commissioner and may for`
  line `that purpose require such owner to deposit in the Municipal Fund such sum as may be determined by him.`
  line
  line `(5) The Commissioner shall maintain`
  line
  line `(a) a register containing such particulars as may be specified by him in this behalf with plans`
  line `attached thereto showing all public streets in respect of which the regular line of the street has been`
  line `defined or redefined and containing any other particulars which the Commissioner may deem`
  line necessary;
  line
  line `(b) a register of all agreements executed under sub-section (4) and of all deposits made`
  line thereunder.
  line
  line `(6) All such registers shall be open to inspection by any person on payment of such fee as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Commissioner with the sanction of the Standing Committee.`
  line
  line `(7) Any agreement entered into in pursuance of sub-section (4) shall be in writing, shall be registered`
  line `under the Indian Registration Act, 1908 (16 of 1908), and shall be deemed to be an agreement in respect`
  line `of the land to which it relates and any condition contained in such agreement shall be deemed to be an`
  line `obligation annexed to the ownership of the said land and enforceable against the successors-in-interest of`
  line `the owner of such land.`
obj_root_law_sections_305_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "a Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_306:
  sectionId (31215)
  sectionNo (306)
  orderNo 354
  title `Setting back building to regular line of street.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_306_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_306_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31215&sectionno=306&orderno=354&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_306_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any part of a building abutting on a`
  line `public street is within the regular line of that street, the Commissioner may, whenever it is proposed--`
  line
  line `(a) to repair, rebuild or construct such building or to take down such building to an extent`
  line `exceeding one-half thereof above the ground level, such half to be measured in cubic feet; or`
  line
  line `(b) to repair, remove, construct or reconstruct or make any additions to, or structural alterations`
  line `of, any portion of such building which is within the regular line of the street,`
  line
  line `by any order which he issues concerning the additions to, rebuilding, construction, repair or alterations of,`
  line `such building, require such building to be set back to the regular line of the street.`
  line
  line `(2) When any building or any part thereof within the regular line of a public street falls down or is`
  line `burnt down or is, whether by the order of the Commissioner or otherwise, taken down, the Commissioner`
  line `may forthwith take possession on behalf of ^1[^2[the Corporation]] of the portion of the land within the regular`
  line `line of the street therefore occupied by the said building and, if necessary, clear the same.`
  line
  line `(3) Land acquired under this section shall be deemed to be a part of the public street and shall vest in`
  line `^1[^2[the Corporation]] .`
obj_root_law_sections_306_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_307:
  sectionId (31216)
  sectionNo (307)
  orderNo 355
  title `Compulsory setting back of building to regular line of street.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_307_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_307_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31216&sectionno=307&orderno=355&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_307_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any building or`
  line `any part thereof is within the regular line of a public street and in the opinion of the Commissioner it is`
  line `necessary to set back the building or part thereof to the regular line of the street he may, by notice served`
  line `on the owner in accordance with the provisions of this Act, require him to show cause within such period`
  line `as may be specified in the notice as to why such building or part thereof which is within the regular line`
  line `of the street should not be pulled down and the land within the regular line acquired by the Commissioner`
  line `on behalf of ^1[^2[the Corporation]].`
  line
  line `(2) If such owner fails to show cause as required by sub-section (1) the Commissioner may, with the`
  line `approval of the Standing Committee, require the owner by another notice to be served on him in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of this Act, to pull down the building or part thereof which is within the`
  line `regular line of the street within such period as is specified in the notice.`
  line
  line `(3) If within such period the owner of the building fails to pull down the building or part thereof as`
  line `required by the Commissioner, the Commissioner may pull down the same and all the expenses incurred`
  line `in so doing shall be paid by the owner and recoverable from him as an arrear of tax under this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) The Commissioner shall at once take possession on behalf of ^1[^2[the Corporation]] of the portion of the`
  line `land within the regular line of the street occupied by the said building or part thereof and such land shall`
  line `thereupon be deemed to be a part of the public street and shall vest in ^1[^2[the Corporation]].`
obj_root_law_sections_307_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_308:
  sectionId (31217)
  sectionNo (308)
  orderNo 356
  title `Acquisition of open land and land occupied by platforms, etc., within the regular line of street.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_308_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_308_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31217&sectionno=308&orderno=356&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_308_content:
  string
  line `If any land, whether open or enclosed, not vesting in ^1[^2[the Corporation]] and not occupied by any`
  line `building is within the regular line of a public street or if a platform, verandah, step, compound wall, hedge`
  line `or fence or some other structure external to a building abutting on a public street or a portion of such`
  line `platform, verandah, step, compound wall, hedge, fence or other structure is within the regular line of such`
  line `street the Commissioner may, after giving to the owner of the land or building not less than seven clear`
  line `days' notice of his intention so to do, take possession on behalf of ^1[^2[the Corporation]] of the said land with its`
  line `enclosing wall, hedge or fence, if any, or of the said platform, verandah, step, compound wall, hedge,`
  line `fence or other structure or of any portion thereof which is within the regular line of the public street and,`
  line `if necessary, clear the same and the land so acquired shall thereupon be deemed to be a part of the public`
  line `street and shall vest in ^1[^2[the Corporation]]:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the land or building is vested in the Union or a State the Commissioner shall not`
  line `take posession thereof without the previous sanction of the Central ^3[Government].`
obj_root_law_sections_308_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “ Central Government” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
obj_root_law_sections_309:
  sectionId (31218)
  sectionNo (309)
  orderNo 357
  title `Acquisition of the remaining part of a building and land after their portions within a regular line of street have been acquired.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_309_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_309_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31218&sectionno=309&orderno=357&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_309_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a land or building is partly within the regular line`
  line `of a public street and the Commissioner is satisfied that the land remaining after the excision of the`
  line `portion within the said line will not be suitable or fit for any beneficial use, he may, at the request of the`
  line `owner, acquire such land in addition to the land within the said line and such surplus land shall be deemed`
  line `to be a part of the public street and shall vest in ^1[^2[the Corporation ]].`
  line
  line `(2) Such surplus land may thereafter be utilised for the purpose of setting forward a building under`
  line `section 310.`
obj_root_law_sections_309_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_310:
  sectionId (31219)
  sectionNo (310)
  orderNo 358
  title `Setting forward of buildings to the regular line of street.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_310_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_310_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31219&sectionno=310&orderno=358&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_310_content:
  string
  line `The Commissioner may, upon`
  line `such terms as he thinks fit, allow any building to be set forward for the purpose of improving the regular`
  line `line of a public street and may, with the sanction of the Standing Committee, by notice required any`
  line `building to be so set forward in the case of reconstruction thereof or of a new construction.`
  line
  line `Explanation:—For the purpose of this section a wall separating any premises from a public street`
  line `shall be deemed to be a building; and it shall be deemed a sufficient compliance with permission or`
  line `requisition to set forward a building to the regular line of a street if a wall of such material and`
  line `dimensions as are approved by the Commissioner is erected along the said line.`
obj_root_law_sections_310_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_311:
  sectionId (31220)
  sectionNo (311)
  orderNo 359
  title `Compensation to be paid in certain cases of setting back or setting forward of buildings, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_311_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_311_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31220&sectionno=311&orderno=359&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_311_content:
  string
  line `(1) Compensation shall be paid by the Commissioner to the owner of any building or land acquired`
  line `for a public street under the provisions of sections 306, 307 and 308 for any loss which such owner may`
  line `sustain in consequence of his building or land being so acquired and for any expense incurred by such`
  line `owner in consequence of any order made by the Commissioner:`
  line
  line `Provided that:--`
  line
  line `(a) any increase or decrease in the value of the remainder of the property of which the building or`
  line `land so acquired formed part, likely to accrue from the setting back to the regular line of the street`
  line `shall be taken into consideration and allowed for in determining the amount of such compensation;`
  line
  line `(b) if any such increase in the value exceeds the amount of loss sustained or expenses incurred by`
  line `the owner, the Commissioner may recover from him half the amount of such excess as a betterment`
  line charge.
  line
  line `(2) If in consequence of any order to set forward a building made by the Commissioner, the owner of`
  line `such building sustains any loss or damage, compensation shall be paid to him by the Commissioner for`
  line `such loss or damage after taking into account any increase in value likely to accrue from the setting`
  line forward.
  line
  line `(3) If the additional land which will be included in the premises of any person required or permitted`
  line `under sub-section (2) to set forward a building belongs to ^1[^2[ the Corporation]], the order or permission of the`
  line `Commissioner to set forward the building shall be a sufficient conveyance to the said owner of the said`
  line `land; and the price to be paid to ^1[^2[the Corporation]] by the owner for such additional land and the other terms`
  line `and conditions of the conveyance shall be set forth in the order or permission.`
  line
  line `(4) If, when the Commissioner requires any building to be set forward, the owner of the building is`
  line `dissatisfied with the price fixed to be paid to ^1[^2[the Corporation]] or with any of the terms or conditions of`
  line `conveyance, the Commissioner shall, upon the application of the owner at any time within fifteen days`
  line `after the said terms and conditions are communicated to him, refer the case for the determination of the`
  line `court or the district judge of Delhi whose decision thereon shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_311_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_312:
  sectionId (31221)
  sectionNo (312)
  orderNo 360
  title `Owner’s obligation when dealing with land as building sites.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_312_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_312_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31221&sectionno=312&orderno=360&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_312_content:
  string
  line `If the owner of any land`
  line `utilises, sells, leases out or otherwise disposes of such land for the construction of buildings thereon he`
  line `shall lay down and make a street or streets giving access to the plots into which the land may be divided`
  line `and connecting with an existing public or private street.`
obj_root_law_sections_312_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_313:
  sectionId (31222)
  sectionNo (313)
  orderNo 361
  title `Lay-out plans.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_313_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_313_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31222&sectionno=313&orderno=361&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_313_content:
  string
  line `(1) Before utilising, selling or otherwise dealing with any land under section`
  line `312, the owner thereof shall send to the Commissioner a written application with a lay-out plan of the`
  line `land showing the following particulars, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the plots into which the land is proposed to be divided for the erection of buildings thereon`
  line `and the purpose or purposes for which such buildings are to be used;`
  line
  line `(b) the reservation or allotment of any site for any street, open space, park, recreation ground,`
  line `school, market or any other public purpose;`
  line
  line `(c) the intended level, direction and width of street or streets;`
  line
  line `(d) the regular line of street or streets;`
  line
  line `(e) the arrangements to be made for leveling, paving, metalling, flagging, channelling, severing,`
  line `draining, conserving and lighting street or streets.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of this Act and the bye-laws made thereunder as to width of the public streets and`
  line `the height of buildings abutting thereon, shall apply in the case of streets referred to in sub-section (1) and`
  line `all the particulars referred to in that sub-section shall be subject to the sanction of the Standing`
  line Committee.
  line
  line `(3) Within sixty days after the receipt of any application under sub-section (1) the Standing`
  line `Committee shall either accord sanction to the lay-out plan on such conditions as it may think fit or`
  line `disallow it or ask for further information with respect to it.`
  line
  line `(4) Such sanction shall be refused:—`
  line
  line `(a) if the particulars shown in the lay-out plan would conflict with any arrangements which have`
  line `been made or which are in the opinion of the Standing Committee likely to be made for carrying out`
  line `any general scheme of development of Delhi whether contained in the master plan or a zonal`
  line `development plan prepared for Delhi or not; or`
  line
  line `(b) if the said lay-out plan does not conform to the provisions of this Act and bye-laws made`
  line `thereunder; or`
  line
  line `(c) if any street proposed in the plan is not designed so as to connect at one end with a street`
  line `which is already open.`
  line
  line `(5) No person shall utilise, sell or otherwise deal with any land or lay-out or make any new street`
  line `without or otherwise than in conformity with the orders of the Standing Committee and if further`
  line `information is asked for, no step shall be taken to utilise, sell or otherwise deal with the land or to lay-out`
  line `or make the street until orders have been passed upon receipt of such information:`
  line
  line `Provided that the passing of such orders shall not be in any case delayed for more than sixty days`
  line `after the Standing Committee has received the information which it considers necessary to enable it to`
  line `deal with the said application.`
  line
  line `(6) The lay-out plan referred to earlier in this section shall, if so required by the Standing Committee,`
  line `be prepared by a licensed town planner.`
obj_root_law_sections_313_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_314:
  sectionId (31223)
  sectionNo (314)
  orderNo 362
  title `Alteration or demolition of street made in breach of section 313.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_314_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_314_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31223&sectionno=314&orderno=362&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_314_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any person lays-out`
  line `or makes any street referred to in section 313, without or otherwise than in conformity with the orders of`
  line `the Standing Committee, the Commissioner may, whether or not the offender be prosecuted under this`
  line `Act, by notice:—`
  line
  line `(a) require the offender to show cause by a written statement signed by him and sent to the`
  line `Commissioner on or before such date as may be specified in the notice, why such street should not be`
  line `altered to the satisfaction of the Commissioner or if such alteration be impracticable, why such street`
  line `should not be demolished; or`
  line
  line `(b) require the offender to appear before the Commissioner either personally or by a duly`
  line `authorised agent on such day and at such time and place as may be specified in the notice and show`
  line `cause as aforesaid.`
  line
  line `(2) If any person on whom such notice is served fails to show cause to the satisfaction of the`
  line `Commissioner why such street should not be so altered or demolished, the Commissioner may pass an`
  line `order directing the alteration or demolition of such street.`
obj_root_law_sections_314_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_315:
  sectionId (31224)
  sectionNo (315)
  orderNo 363
  title `Power of Commissioner to order work to be carried out or to carry it out himself in default.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_315_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_315_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31224&sectionno=315&orderno=363&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_315_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any private street or part thereof is not levelled, paved, metalled, flagged, channelled,`
  line `severed, drained, conserved or lighted to the satisfaction of the Commissioner, he may by notice require`
  line `the owners of such street or part and the owners of the lands and buildings fronting or abutting on such`
  line `street or part to carry out any work which in his opinion may be necessary, and within such time as may`
  line `be specified in such notice.`
  line
  line `(2) If such work is not carried out within the time specified in the notice, the Commissioner may, if`
  line `he thinks fit, execute it and the expenses incurred shall be paid by the owners referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) in such proportion as may be determined by the Commissioner and shall be recoverable`
  line `from them as an arrear of tax under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_315_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_316:
  sectionId (31225)
  sectionNo (316)
  orderNo 364
  title `Right of owners to require streets to be declared public.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_316_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_316_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31225&sectionno=316&orderno=364&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_316_content:
  string
  line `If any street has been levelled,`
  line `paved, metalled, flagged, channelled, severed, drained, conserved and lighted under the provisions of`
  line `section 315, the Commissioner may, and on the requisition of a majority of the owners referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) of that section shall, declare such a street to be a public street and thereupon the street`
  line `shall vest in ^1[^2[the Corporation]].`
obj_root_law_sections_316_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_317:
  sectionId (31226)
  sectionNo (317)
  orderNo 365
  title `Prohibition of projections upon streets, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_317_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_317_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31226&sectionno=317&orderno=365&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_317_content:
  string
  line `(1) Except as provided in section 318, no person`
  line `shall erect, set up, add to, or place against or in front of any premises any structure or fixture which will—`
  line
  line `(a) overhang, jut or project into, or in any way encroach upon, and obstruct in any way the safe or`
  line `convenient passage of the public along, any street, or`
  line
  line `(b) jut or project into or encroach upon any drain or open channel in any street so as in any way to`
  line `interfere with the use or proper working of such drain or channel or to impede the inspection or`
  line `cleansing thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commissioner may by notice require the owner or occupier of any premises to remove, or to`
  line `take such other action as he may direct in relation to, any structure or fixture which has been erected, set`
  line `up, added to, or placed against, or in front of, the said premises in contravention of this section.`
  line
  line `(3) If the occupier of the said premises removes or alters any structure or fixture in accordance with`
  line `such notice, he shall be entitled, unless the structure or fixture was erected, set up or placed by himself, to credit into account with the owner of the premises for all reasonable expenses incurred by him in`
  line `complying with the notice.`
obj_root_law_sections_317_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_318:
  sectionId (31227)
  sectionNo (318)
  orderNo 366
  title `Projections over streets may be permitted in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_318_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_318_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31227&sectionno=318&orderno=366&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_318_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commissioner may give`
  line `a written permission, on such terms and on payment of such fee as he in each case thinks fit, to the owner`
  line `or occupier of the building abutting on any street--`
  line
  line `(a) to erect an arcade over such street or any portion thereof; or`
  line
  line `(b) to put up a verandah, balcony, arch, connecting passage, sun-shade, weather frame, canopy,`
  line `awning or other such structure or thing projecting from any storey over or across any street or portion`
  line `thereof:`
  line
  line `Provided that no permission shall be given by the Commissioner for the erection of an arcade in any`
  line `public street in which construction of an arcade has not been generally sanctioned by ^1[^2[the Corporation]].`
  line
  line `(2) The Commissioner may at any time by notice require the owner or occupier of any building to`
  line `remove a verandah, balcony, sun-shade, weather frame or the like put up in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of any law and such owner or occupier shall be bound to take action accordingly but shall be`
  line `entitled to compensation for the loss caused to him by such removal and the cost incurred thereon.`
obj_root_law_sections_318_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_319:
  sectionId (31228)
  sectionNo (319)
  orderNo 367
  title `Ground floor doors, etc., not to open outwards on streets.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_319_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_319_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31228&sectionno=319&orderno=367&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_319_content:
  string
  line `The Commissioner may at any`
  line `time by notice require the owner of any premises on the ground floor of which any door, gate, bar, or`
  line `window opens outwards upon a street or upon any land required for the improvement of a street in such`
  line `manner, as in the opinion of the Commissioner, to obstruct the safe or convenient passage of the public`
  line `along such street, to have the said door, gate, bar or window altered so as not to open outwards.`
obj_root_law_sections_319_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_320:
  sectionId (31229)
  sectionNo (320)
  orderNo 368
  title `Prohibition of structures or fixtures which cause obstruction in streets.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_320_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_320_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31229&sectionno=320&orderno=368&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_320_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person`
  line `shall, except with the permission of the Commissioner granted in this behalf, erect or set up any wall,`
  line `fence, rail, post, step, booth or other structure whether fixed or movable or whether of a permanent or`
  line `temporary nature, or any fixture in or upon any street or upon or over any open channel, drain, well or`
  line `tank in any street so as to form an obstruction to, or an encroachment upon, or a projection over, or to`
  line `occupy any portion of such street, channel, drain, well or tank.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in this section shall apply to any erection or thing to which clause (c) sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 325 applies.`
obj_root_law_sections_320_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_321:
  sectionId (31230)
  sectionNo (321)
  orderNo 369
  title `Prohibition of deposit, etc., of things in streets.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_321_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_321_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31230&sectionno=321&orderno=369&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_321_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall, except with the`
  line `permission of the Commissioner and on payment of such fee as he in each case thinks fit, place or deposit`
  line `upon any street, or upon any open channel, drain or well in any street or upon any public place any stall,`
  line `chair, bench, box, ladder, bale or other thing whatsoever so as to form an obstruction thereto or`
  line `encroachment thereon.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in sub-section (1) applies to building materials.`
obj_root_law_sections_321_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_322:
  sectionId (31231)
  sectionNo (322)
  orderNo 370
  title `Power to remove anything deposited or exposed for sale in contravention of this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_322_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_322_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31231&sectionno=322&orderno=370&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_322_content:
  string
  line The
  line `Commissioner may, without notice, cause to be removed—`
  line
  line `(a) any stall, chair, bench, box, ladder, bale or other thing whatsoever, placed, deposited,`
  line `projected, attached or suspended in, upon from or to any place in contravention of this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) any article whatsoever hawked or exposed for sale on any public street or in other public place`
  line `in contravention of this Act and vehicle, package, box or any other thing in or on which such article is`
  line placed.
obj_root_law_sections_322_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_323:
  sectionId (31232)
  sectionNo (323)
  orderNo 371
  title `Prohibition of the tethering of animals and milking of cattle.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_323_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_323_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31232&sectionno=323&orderno=371&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_323_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall tether any`
  line `animal or cause or permit the same to be tethered in any public street.`
  line
  line `(2) No person shall milk or cause or permit to be milked any cow or buffalo in any street.`
  line
  line `(3) Any animal tethered or any cow or buffalo found being milked as aforesaid in any street may be`
  line `removed by the Commissioner or any municipal officer or employee and be impounded and dealt with`
  line `under the provisions of the Cattle-Trespass Act, 1871 (1 of 1871).`
obj_root_law_sections_323_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_324:
  sectionId (31233)
  sectionNo (324)
  orderNo 372
  title `Precautions during repair of streets.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_324_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_324_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31233&sectionno=324&orderno=372&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_324_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commissioner shall, so far as is practicable`
  line `during the construction or repair of any public street, or any municipal drain or any premises vested in ^1[^2[the`
  line Corporation]]--
  line
  line `(a) cause the same to be fenced and guarded;`
  line
  line `(b) take proper precautions against accident by shoring up and protecting the adjoining buildings;`
  line
  line `(c) cause such bars, chains or posts to be fixed across or in any street in which any such work of`
  line `construction or repair is under execution as are necessary in order to prevent the passage of vehicles`
  line `or animals and avert danger.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commissioner shall cause such street, drain or premises to be sufficiently lighted or guarded`
  line `during night while under construction or repair.`
  line
  line `(3) The Commissioner shall, with all reasonable speed, cause the said work to be completed, the`
  line `ground to be filled in, the said street, drain or premises to be repaired and the rubbish occasioned thereby`
  line `to be removed.`
  line
  line `(4) No person shall, without the permission of the Commissioner or other lawful authority, remove`
  line `any bar, chain, post or shoring, timber, or remove or extinguish any light set up under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_324_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_325:
  sectionId (31234)
  sectionNo (325)
  orderNo 373
  title `Streets not to be opened or broken up and building materials not to be deposited thereon without permission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_325_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_325_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31234&sectionno=325&orderno=373&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_325_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person other than the Commissioner or a municipal officer or other`
  line `municipal employee shall, without the written permission of the Commissioner—`
  line
  line `(a) open, break up, displace, take up or make any alteration in, or cause any injury to the soil or`
  line `pavement or any wall, fence, post, chain or other material or thing forming part of any street; or`
  line
  line `(b) deposit any building materials in any street; or`
  line
  line `(c) set up in any street any scaffold or any temporary erection for the purpose of any work`
  line `whatever, or any posts, bars, rails, boards or other things by way of an enclosure, for the purpose of`
  line `making mortar or depositing bricks, lime, rubbish or other materials.`
  line
  line `(2) Any permission granted under clause (b) or clause (c) of sub-section (1) shall be terminable at the`
  line `discretion of the Commissioner on his giving not less than twenty-four hours notice of such termination to`
  line `the person to whom such permission was granted.`
  line
  line `(3) The Commissioner may, without notice, cause to be removed any of the things referred to in`
  line `clause (b) or clause (c) of sub-section (1) which has been deposited or set up in any street without the`
  line `permission specified in that sub-section, on which having been deposited or set up with such permission`
  line `has not been removed within the period specified in the notice issued under sub-section (2):`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall apply to cases under clause (b) or clause (c) of`
  line `sub-section (1) in which an application for permission has been made with such fee as may be prescribed`
  line `by the Commissioner in this behalf but not reply has been sent to the applicant within seven days from the`
  line `date of the application.`
obj_root_law_sections_325_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_326:
  sectionId (31235)
  sectionNo (326)
  orderNo 374
  title `Disposal of things removed under this Chapter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_326_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_326_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31235&sectionno=326&orderno=374&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_326_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any of the things caused to be removed`
  line `by the Commissioner under this Chapter shall, unless the owner thereof turns up to take back such thing`
  line `and pays to the Commissioner the charges for the removal and storage of such thing, be disposed of by`
  line `the Commissioner by public auction or in such other manner and within such time as the Commissioner`
  line `thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(2) The charges for removal and storage of the thing sold under sub-section (1) shall be paid out of`
  line `the proceeds of the sale thereof and the balance, if any, shall be paid to the owner of the thing sold on a`
  line `claim being made therefor within a period of one year from the date of sale, and if no such claim is made`
  line `within the said period, shall be credited to the Municipal Fund.`
obj_root_law_sections_326_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_327:
  sectionId (31236)
  sectionNo (327)
  orderNo 375
  title `Naming and numbering of streets.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_327_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_327_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31236&sectionno=327&orderno=375&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_327_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commissioner may---`
  line
  line `(a) with the sanction of ^1[^2[the Corporation]], determine the name or number by which any street or`
  line `public place vested in ^1[^2[the Corporation]] shall be known;`
  line
  line `(b) cause to be put up or painted at a conspicuous part of any building, wall or place at or near`
  line `each end, corner or entrance of such street or on some convenient part of such street the name or`
  line `number by which it is to be known;`
  line
  line `(c) cause to be put up or painted on boards of suitable size the name of any public place vested in`
  line `the Corporation;`
  line
  line `(d) determine the number or sub-number by which any premises or part of such premises shall be`
  line `known and cause such number or sub-number to be fixed to the side or outer door of such premises or`
  line `to some place at the entrance of the enclosure thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) No person shall destroy, remove, deface or in any way injure or alter any such name or number or`
  line `sub-number or put up or paint any name or number or sub-number different from that put up or painted by`
  line `order of the Commissioner.`
obj_root_law_sections_327_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_328:
  sectionId (31237)
  sectionNo (328)
  orderNo 376
  title `Commissioner to take steps for repairing or enclosing dangerous places.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_328_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_328_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31237&sectionno=328&orderno=376&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_328_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any place`
  line `is, in the opinion of the Commissioner, for want of sufficient repair or protection or enclosure, or owing`
  line `to some work being carried on thereupon, dangerous or causing inconvenience to passengers along a`
  line `street or to other persons including the owner or occupier of the said place, who have legal access thereto`
  line `or to the neighbourhood thereof, the commissioner may by notice in writing require the owner or occupier`
  line `of such place to repair, protect or enclose the same or take such other step as shall appear to the`
  line `Commissioner necessary in order to prevent the danger or inconvenience arising therefrom.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commissioner may before giving any such notice or before the period of any such notice has`
  line `expired, take such temporary measures as he thinks fit to prevent the danger or inconvenience arising`
  line `therefrom; and any expense incurred by the Commissioner in taking such temporary measures shall be`
  line `recoverable from the owner or occupier of the place as an arrear of tax under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_328_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_329:
  sectionId (31238)
  sectionNo (329)
  orderNo 377
  title `Measures for lighting.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_329_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_329_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31238&sectionno=329&orderno=377&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_329_content:
  string
  line `The Commissioner shall—`
  line
  line `(a) take measures for lighting in a suitable manner all such public streets and public places as`
  line `may be specified by the Standing Committee;`
  line
  line `(b) procure, erect and maintain such number of lamps, lamp posts and other appurtenances as`
  line `may be necessary for the said purpose;`
  line
  line `(c) cause such lamps to be lighted by means of oil, electricity or such other light as the Standing`
  line `Committee may determine.`
obj_root_law_sections_329_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_330:
  sectionId (31239)
  sectionNo (330)
  orderNo 378
  title `Prohibition of removal, etc., of lamps.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_330_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_330_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31239&sectionno=330&orderno=378&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_330_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall, without lawful authority, take`
  line `away or wilfully or negligently break or throw down or damage—`
  line
  line `(a) any lamp or any appurtenance of any lamp or lamp post or lamp iron set up in any public`
  line `street or any public place;`
  line
  line `(b) any electric wire for lighting such lamp;`
  line
  line `(c) any post, pole, standard, stay, strut, bracket or other contrivance for carrying, suspending or`
  line `supporting any electric wire or lamp.`
  line
  line `(2) No person shall wilfully or negligently extinguish the light of any lamp set up in any public street`
  line `or any public place.`
  line
  line `(3) If any person wilfully or through negligence or accident breaks, or causes any damage to, any of`
  line `the things described in sub-section (1), he shall in addition to any penalty to which he may be subjected`
  line `under this Act, pay the expenses of repairing the damage so done by him.`
obj_root_law_sections_330_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_330_a:
  sectionId (31240)
  sectionNo 330A
  orderNo 379
  title `General superintendence etc., of the Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_330_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_330_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31240&sectionno=330A&orderno=379&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_330_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[330A. General superintendence, etc., of the ^2[^3[Central Government]].--Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in any other provision of this Act, the Commissioner shall exercise his powers and discharge`
  line `his functions under this Chapter, under the general superintendence, direction and control of the ^2[^3[Central`
  line Government]].]
obj_root_law_sections_330_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 98 (w.e.f 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 "Central Government" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "Government" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_331:
  sectionId (31241)
  sectionNo (331)
  orderNo 380
  title Definition.
  content obj_root_law_sections_331_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_331_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31241&sectionno=331&orderno=380&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_331_content:
  string
  line `In this Chapter, unless the context otherwise requires, the expression “to erect a`
  line `building” means—`
  line
  line `(a) to erect a new building on any site whether previously built upon or not;`
  line
  line `(b) tore-erect.—`
  line
  line `(i) any building of which more than one-half of the cubical contents above the level of the`
  line `plinth have been pulled down, burnt or destroyed, or`
  line
  line `(ii) any building of which more than one-half of the superficial area of the external walls`
  line `above the level of the plinth has been pulled down, or`
  line
  line `(iii) any frame building of which more than half of the number of the posts or beams in the`
  line `external walls have been pulled down;`
  line
  line `(c) to convert into a dwelling house any building or any part of a building not originally`
  line `constructed for human habitation or, if originally so constructed, subsequently appropriated for any`
  line `other purpose;`
  line
  line `(d) to convert into more than one dwelling house a building originally constructed as one`
  line `dwelling house only;`
  line
  line `(e) to convert into a place of religious worship or into a sacred building any place or building not`
  line `originally constructed for such purpose;`
  line
  line `(f) to roof or cover an open space between walls or buildings to the extent of the structure which`
  line `is formed by the roofing or covering of such space;`
  line
  line `(g) to convert two or more tenements in a building into a greater or lesser number;`
  line
  line `(h) to convert into a stall, shop, warehouse or godown, stable, factory or garage any building not`
  line `originally constructed for use as such or which was not so used before the change;`
  line
  line `(i) to convert a building which when originally constructed was legally exempt from the`
  line `operations of any building regulations contained in this Act or in any bye-laws made thereunder or in`
  line `any other law, into a building which had it been originally erected in its converted form, would have`
  line `been subject to such building regulations;`
  line
  line `(j) to convert into or use as dwelling house any building which has been discontinued as or`
  line `appropriated for any purpose other than a dwelling house.`
obj_root_law_sections_331_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_332:
  sectionId (31242)
  sectionNo (332)
  orderNo 381
  title `Prohibition of building without sanction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_332_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_332_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31242&sectionno=332&orderno=381&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_332_content:
  string
  line `No person shall erect or commence to erect any`
  line `building, or execute any of the works specified in section 334 except with the previous sanction of the`
  line `Commissioner, not otherwise than in accordance with the provisions of this Chapter and of the bye-laws`
  line `made under this Act in relation to the erection of buildings or execution of works.`
obj_root_law_sections_332_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_333:
  sectionId (31243)
  sectionNo (333)
  orderNo 382
  title `Erection of building.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_333_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_333_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31243&sectionno=333&orderno=382&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_333_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person who intends to erect a building shall apply for sanction`
  line `by giving notice in writing of his intention to the Commissioner in such form and containing such`
  line `information as may be prescribed by bye-laws made in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) Every such notice shall be accompanied by such documents and plans as may be so prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_333_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_334:
  sectionId (31244)
  sectionNo (334)
  orderNo 383
  title `Applications for additions to, or repairs of, buildings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_334_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_334_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31244&sectionno=334&orderno=383&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_334_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person who intends to`
  line `execute any of the following works, that is to say—`
  line
  line `(a) to make any addition to a building;`
  line
  line `(b) to make any alteration or repairs to a building involving the removal or re-erection of any`
  line `external or partly wall thereof or of any wall which supports the roof thereof to an extent exceeding`
  line `one-half of such wall above the plinth level, such half to be measured in superficial feet;`
  line
  line `(c) to make any alteration or repairs to a frame building involving the removal or re-erection of`
  line `more than one-half of the posts in any such wall thereof as aforesaid; or involving the removal or reerection of any such wall thereof as aforesaid to an extent exceeding one-half of such wall above`
  line `plinth level, such half to be measured in superficial feet;`
  line
  line `(d) to make any alteration in a building involving—`
  line
  line `(i) the sub-division of any room in such building so as to convert the same into two or more`
  line `separate rooms, or`
  line
  line `(ii) the conversion of any passage or space in such building into a room or rooms;`
  line
  line `(e) to repair, remove, construct, reconstruct or make any addition to or structural alteration in any`
  line `portion of a building abutting on a street which stands within the regular line of such street;`
  line
  line `(f) to close permanently any door or window in an external wall;`
  line
  line `(g) to remove or reconstruct the principal staircase or to alter its position;`
  line
  line `shall apply for sanction by giving notice in writing of his intention to the Commissioner in such form and`
  line `containing such information as may be prescribed by bye-laws made in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) Every such notice shall be accompanied by such documents and plans as may be so prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_334_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_335:
  sectionId (31245)
  sectionNo (335)
  orderNo 384
  title `Conditions of valid notice.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_335_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_335_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31245&sectionno=335&orderno=384&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_335_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person giving the notice required by section 333 shall`
  line `specify the purpose for which it is intended to use the building to which such notice relates; and a person`
  line `giving the notice required by section 334 shall specify whether the purpose for which the building is`
  line `being used is proposed or likely to be changed by the execution of the proposed work.`
  line
  line `(2) No notice shall be valid until the information required under sub-section (1) and any further`
  line `information and plans which may be required by bye-laws made in this behalf have been furnished to the`
  line `satisfaction of the Commissioner along with the notice.`
obj_root_law_sections_335_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_336:
  sectionId (31246)
  sectionNo (336)
  orderNo 385
  title `Sanction or refusal of building or work.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_336_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_336_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31246&sectionno=336&orderno=385&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_336_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commissioner shall sanction the erection`
  line `of a building or the execution of a work unless such building or work would contravene any of the`
  line `provisions of sub-section (2) of this section or the provisions of section 340.`
  line
  line `(2) The grounds on which the sanction of a building or work may be refused shall be the following,`
  line `namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) that the building or work or the use of the site for the building or work or any of the`
  line `particulars comprised in the site plan, ground plan, elevation, section or specification would`
  line `contravene the provisions of any bye-law made in this behalf or of any other law or rule, bye-law or`
  line `order made under such other law;`
  line
  line `(b) that the notice for sanction does not contain the particulars or is not prepared in the manner`
  line `required under the bye-laws made in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(c) that any information or documents required by the Commissioner under this Act or any byelaws made thereunder has or have not been duly furnished;`
  line
  line `(d) that in cases falling under section 312, lay-out plans have not been sanctioned in accordance`
  line `with section 313;`
  line
  line `(e) that the building or work would be an encroachment on Government land or land vested in the`
  line Corporation;
  line
  line `(f) that the site of the building or work does not about on a street or projected street and that there`
  line `is no access to such building or work from any such street by a passage or path-way appertaining to`
  line `such site.`
  line
  line `(3) The Commissioner shall communicate the sanction to the person who has given the notice; and`
  line `where he refuses sanction on any of the grounds specified in sub-section (2) or under section 340 he shall`
  line `record a brief statement of his reasons for such refusal and communicate the refusal along with the`
  line `reasons therefor to the person who has given the notice.`
  line
  line `(4) The sanction or refusal as aforesaid shall be communicated in such manner as may be specified in`
  line `the bye-laws made in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_336_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_337:
  sectionId (31247)
  sectionNo (337)
  orderNo 386
  title `When building or work may be proceeded with.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_337_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_337_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31247&sectionno=337&orderno=386&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_337_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where within a period of sixty days, or`
  line `in cases falling under clause (b) of section 331 within a period of thirty days, after the receipts of any`
  line `notice under section 333 or section 334 or of the further information, if any, required under section 335`
  line `the Commissioner does not refuse to sanction the building or work or upon refusal, does not communicate`
  line `the refusal to the person who has given the notice, the Commissioner shall be deemed to have accorded`
  line `sanction to the building or work and the person by whom the notice has been given shall be free to`
  line `commence and proceed with the building or work in accordance with his intention as expressed in the`
  line `notice and the documents and plans accompanying the same:`
  line
  line `Provided that if it appears to the Commissioner that the site of the proposed building or work is likely`
  line `to be affected by any scheme of acquisition of land for any public purpose or by any proposed regular line`
  line `of a public street or extension, improvement, widening or alteration of any street, the Commissioner may`
  line `withhold sanction of the building or work for such period not exceeding three months as he deems fit and`
  line `the period of sixty days or as the case may be, the period of thirty days specified in this sub-section shall`
  line `be deemed to commence from the date of the expiry of the period for which the sanction has been`
  line withheld.
  line
  line `(2) Where a building or work is sanctioned or is deemed to have been sanctioned by the`
  line `Commissioner under sub-section (1), the person who has given the notice shall be bound to erect the`
  line `building or execute the work in accordance with such sanction but not so as to contravene any of the`
  line `provisions of this Act or any other law or of any bye-law made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(3) If the person or anyone lawfully claiming under him does not commence the erection of the`
  line `building or the execution of the work within one year of the date on which the building or work is`
  line `sanctioned or is deemed to have been sanctioned, he shall have to give notice under section 333 or, as the`
  line `case may, be under section 334 for fresh sanction of the building or the work and the provisions of this`
  line `section shall apply in relation to such notice as they apply in relation to the original notice.`
  line
  line `(4) Before commencing the erection of a building or execution of a work within the period specified`
  line `in sub-section (3), the person concerned shall give notice to the Commissioner of the proposed date of the`
  line `commencement of the erection of the building or the execution of the work:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the commencement does not take place within seven days of the date so notified, the`
  line `notice shall be deemed not to have been given and a fresh notice shall be necessary in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_337_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_338:
  sectionId (31248)
  sectionNo (338)
  orderNo 387
  title `Sanction accorded under misrepresentation`
  content obj_root_law_sections_338_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_338_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31248&sectionno=338&orderno=387&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_338_content:
  string
  line `If at any time after the sanction of any building`
  line `or work has been accorded, the Commissioner is satisfied that such sanction was accorded in consequence`
  line `of any material misrepresentation or fraudulent statement contained in the notice given or information`
  line `further under sections 333, 334 and 335, he may be order in writing cancel for reasons to be recorded`
  line `such sanction and any building or work commenced, erected or done shall be deemed to have been`
  line `commenced, erected or done without such sanction:`
  line
  line `Provided that before making any such order the Commissioner shall give reasonable opportunity to`
  line `the person affected as to why such order should not be made.`
obj_root_law_sections_338_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_339:
  sectionId (31249)
  sectionNo (339)
  orderNo 388
  title `Buildings at corners of streets.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_339_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_339_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31249&sectionno=339&orderno=388&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_339_content:
  string
  line `The Commissioner may require any building intended to be`
  line `erected at the corner of two streets to be rounded off or splayed or cut off to such height and to such`
  line `extent as he may determine, and may acquire such portion of the site at the corner as he may consider`
  line `necessary for public convenience or amenity.`
obj_root_law_sections_339_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_340:
  sectionId (31250)
  sectionNo (340)
  orderNo 389
  title `Provisions as to buildings and works on either side of new streets.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_340_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_340_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31250&sectionno=340&orderno=389&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_340_content:
  string
  line `(1) The erection of any`
  line `building on either side of a new street may be refused by the Commissioner unless and until such new`
  line `street has been levelled, and wherever in the opinion of the Commissioner practicable, metalled or paved,`
  line `drained, lighted and laid with a water main to his satisfaction.`
  line
  line `(2) The erection of any such building or the execution of any such work may be refused by the`
  line `Commissioner if such building or any portion thereof or such work comes within the regular line of any`
  line `street, the position and direction of which has been laid down by the Commissioner but which has not`
  line `been actually constructed or if such building or any portion thereof or such work is in contravention of`
  line `any building or any other scheme or plan prepared under this Act or any other law for the time being in`
  line force.
obj_root_law_sections_340_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_341:
  sectionId (31251)
  sectionNo (341)
  orderNo 390
  title `Period for completion of building or work.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_341_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_341_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31251&sectionno=341&orderno=390&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_341_content:
  string
  line `The Commissioner, when sanctioning the`
  line `erection of a building or execution of a work, shall specify a reasonable period after the commencement`
  line `of the building or work within which the building or work is to be completed and if the building or work`
  line `is not completed within the period so specified, it shall not be continued thereafter without fresh sanction`
  line `obtained in the manner hereinbefore provided, unless the Commissioner on application made therefor has`
  line `allowed an extension of that period.`
obj_root_law_sections_341_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_342:
  sectionId (31252)
  sectionNo (342)
  orderNo 391
  title `Prohibition against use of inflammable materials for building, etc., without permission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_342_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_342_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31252&sectionno=342&orderno=391&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_342_content:
  string
  line In
  line `such areas as may be specified by bye-laws made in this behalf, no roof, verandah, pandal or wall of a`
  line `building or no shed or fence shall be constructed or reconstructed or cloth, grass leaves, mats or other`
  line `inflammable materials except with the written permission of the Commissioner, nor shall any such roof,`
  line `verandah, pandal, wall, shed or fence constructed or reconstructed in any year be retained in a subsequent`
  line `year except with fresh permission obtained in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_342_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_343:
  sectionId (31253)
  sectionNo (343)
  orderNo 392
  title `Order of demolition and stoppage of buildings and works in certain cases and appeal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_343_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_343_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31253&sectionno=343&orderno=392&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_343_content:
  string
  line `^1[343. Order of demolition and stoppage of buildings and works in certain cases and`
  line `appeal.—(1) Where the erection of any building or execution of any work has been commenced, or is`
  line `being carried on, or has been completed without or contrary to the sanction referred to in section 336 or in`
  line `contravention of any condition subject to which such sanction has been accorded or in contravention of`
  line `any of the provisions of this Act or bye-laws made thereunder, the Commissioner may, in addition to any`
  line `other action that may be taken under this Act, make an order directing that such erection or work shall be`
  line `demolished by the person at whose instance the erection or work has been commenced or is being carried`
  line `on or has been completed, within such period, (not being less than five days and more than fifteen days`
  line `from the date on which a copy of the order of demolition with a brief statement of the reasons therefor has`
  line `been delivered to that person), as may be, specified in the order of demolition:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order of demolition shall be made unless the person has been given by means of a`
  line `notice served in such manner as the Commissioner may think fit, a reasonable opportunity of showing`
  line `cause why such order shall not be made:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where the erection or work has not been completed, the Commissioner may by`
  line `the same order or by a separate order, whether made at the time of the issue of the notice under the first`
  line `proviso or at any other time, direct the person to stop the erection or work until the expiry of the period`
  line `within which any appeal against the order of demolition, if made, may be preferred under sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(2) Any person aggrieved by an order of the Commissioner made under sub-section (1) may prefer an`
  line `appeal against the order to ^2`
  line `[the Appellate Tribunal] within the period specified in the order for the`
  line `demolition of the erection or work to which it relates.`
  line
  line `(3) Where an appeal is preferred under sub-section (2) against an order of demolition, ^3`
  line `[the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal may, subject to the provisions of sub-section (3) of section 347C,] stay the enforcement of that`
  line `order on such terms, if any, and for such period, as it may think fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the erection of any building or execution of any work has not been completed at`
  line `the time of the making of the order of demolition, no order staying the enforcement of the order of`
  line `demolition shall be made by ^4`
  line `[the Appellate Tribunal, unless security, sufficient in the opinion of the said`
  line `Tribunal], has been given by the appellant for not proceeding, with such erection or work pending the`
  line `disposal of the appeal.`
  line
  line `(4)`
  line ^5
  line `[No court] shall entertain any suit, application or other proceeding for injunction or other relief`
  line `against the Commissioner to restrain him from taking any action or making any order in pursuance of the`
  line `provisions of this section.`
  line
  line `(5)`
  line ^6
  line `[Subject to an order made by the Administrator on appeal under section 347D, every order made`
  line `by the Appellate Tribunal on appeal under this section, and subject to the orders of the Administrator and`
  line `the Appellate Tribunal on appeal] the order of demolition made by the Commissioner shall be final and`
  line conclusive.
  line
  line `(6) Where no appeal has been preferred against an order of demolition made by the Commissioner`
  line `under sub-section (1) or where an order of demolition made by the Commissioner under that subsection ^7`
  line `[has been confirmed on appeal, whether with or without variation, by the Appellate Tribunal in a`
  line `case where no appeal has been preferred against the order of the Appellate Tribunal, and by the`
  line `Administrator in a case where an appeal has been preferred against the order of the Appellate Tribunal]`
  line `the person against whom the order has been made shall comply with the order within the period specified`
  line `therein, or as the case may be, within the period, if any, fixed by ^8`
  line `[the Appellate Tribunal or the`
  line `Administrator] on appeal and on the failure of the person to comply with the order within such period, the`
  line `Commissioner may himself cause the erection or the work to which the order relates to be demolished and`
  line `the expenses of such demolition shall be recoverable from such person as an arrear of tax under this Act].`
obj_root_law_sections_343_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 42 of 1961, s. 16, for section 343 (w.e.f. 12-9-1961).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 42 of 1984, s. 3, for "the court of the district judge of Delhi" (w.e.f. 10-2-1986).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "the court of the district judge may" (w.e.f. 10-2-1986).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 42 of 1984, s. 3, for "the court of the district judge unless security, sufficient in the opinion of the court"`
  line `(w.e.f. 10-2-1986).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "Save as provided in this section, no court" (w.e.f. 10-2-1986).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for certain words (w.e.f. 10-2-1986).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "has been confirmed on appeal, whether with or without variation" (w.e.f. 10-2-1986).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "the court of the district judge" (w.e.f. 10-2-1986).`
obj_root_law_sections_344:
  sectionId (31254)
  sectionNo (344)
  orderNo 393
  title `Order of stoppage of buildings or works in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_344_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_344_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31254&sectionno=344&orderno=393&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_344_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the erection of any`
  line `building or execution of any work has been commenced or is being carried on (but has not been`
  line `completed) without or contrary to the sanction referred to in section 336 or in contravention of any`
  line `condition subject to which such sanction has been accorded or in contravention of any provisions of this`
  line `Act or bye-laws made thereunder, the Commissioner may in addition to any other action that may be`
  line `taken under this Act, by order require the person at whose instance the building or the work has been`
  line `commenced or is being carried on to stop the same forthwith.`
  line
  line `(2)`
  line ^1
  line `[If an order made by the Commissioner under section 343 or under sub-section (1) of this section`
  line `directing any person to stop the erection of any building or execution of any work is not complied with,]`
  line `the Commissioner may require any police officer to remove such person and all his assistants and`
  line `workmen from the premises ^2`
  line `[or to seize any construction material, tool, machinery, scaffolding or other`
  line `things used in the erection of any building or execution of any work] within such time as may be specified`
  line `in the requisition and such police officer shall comply with the requisition accordingly.`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(2A) Any of the things caused to be seized by the Commissioner under subsection (2) shall be`
  line `disposed of by him in the manner specified in section 326.]`
  line
  line `(3) After the requisition under sub-section (2) has been complied with, the Commissioner may, if he`
  line `thinks fit, depute by a written order a police officer or a municipal officer or other municipal employee to`
  line `watch the premises in order to ensure that the erection of the building or the execution of the work is not`
  line continued.
  line
  line `(4) Where a police officer or a municipal officer or other municipal employee has been deputed under`
  line `sub-section (3) to watch the premises, the cost of such deputation shall be paid by the person at whose`
  line `instance such erection or execution is being continued or to whom notice under sub-section (1) was given`
  line `and shall be recoverable from such person as an arrear of tax under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_344_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 42 of 1961, s. 17, for "If such order is not complied with forthwith" (w.e.f. 12-9-1961).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 42 of 1984, s. 4 (w.e.f. 10-2-1986).`
obj_root_law_sections_345:
  sectionId (31255)
  sectionNo (345)
  orderNo 394
  title `Power of Commissioner to require alteration of work.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_345_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_345_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31255&sectionno=345&orderno=394&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_345_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commissioner may at any`
  line `time during the erection of any building or execution of any work or at any time ^1`
  line `[after the completion`
  line `thereof, by a written notice of not less than seven days], specify any matter in respect of which such`
  line `erection or execution is without or contrary to the sanction referred to in section 336 or is in contravention`
  line `of any condition of such sanction or any of the provisions of this Act or any bye-laws made thereunder`
  line `and require the person who give the notice under section 333 or section 334 or the owner of such building`
  line `or work either—`
  line
  line `(a) to make such alterations as may be specified in the said notice with the object of bringing the`
  line `building or work in conformity with the said sanction, condition or provisions, or`
  line
  line `(b) to show cause why such alterations should not be made, within a period stated in the notice.`
  line
  line `(2) If the person or the owner does not show cause as aforesaid, he shall be bound to make the`
  line `alterations specified in the notice.`
  line
  line `(3) If the person or the owner shows cause as aforesaid, the Commissioner shall by an order either`
  line `cancel the notice issued under sub-section (1) or confirm the same subject to such modifications as he`
  line `thinks fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_345_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 42 of 1984, s. 5, for "within three months after the completion thereof, by a written`
  line `notice" (w.e.f. 10-12-1985).`
obj_root_law_sections_345_a:
  sectionId (31256)
  sectionNo 345A
  orderNo 395
  title `Power to seal unauthorised constructions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_345_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 42 of 1984, s. 6 (w.e.f. 10-2-1986).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31256&sectionno=345A&orderno=395&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_345_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[345A. Power to seal unauthorised constructions.(1) It shall be lawful for the Commissioner, at`
  line `any time, before or after making an order of demolition under section 343 or of the stoppage of the`
  line `erection of any building or execution of any work under section 343 or under section 344, to make an`
  line `order directing the sealing of such erection or work or of the premises in which such erection or work is`
  line `being carried on or has been completed in the manner prescribed by rules, for the purpose of carrying out`
  line `the provisions of this Act, or for preventing any dispute as to the nature and extent of such erection or`
  line work.
  line
  line `(2) Where any erection or work or any premises in which any erection or work is being carried on,`
  line `has or have been sealed, the Commissioner may, for the purpose of demolishing such erection or work in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of this Act, order such seal to be removed.`
  line
  line `(3) No person shall remove such seal except`
  line
  line `(a) under an order made by the Commissioner under sub-section (2); or`
  line
  line `(b) under an order of an Appellate Tribunal or the Administrator, made in an appeal under this`
  line Act.]
obj_root_law_sections_346:
  sectionId (31257)
  sectionNo (346)
  orderNo 396
  title `Completion certificates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_346_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_346_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31257&sectionno=346&orderno=396&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_346_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person who employs a licensed architect or engineer or a`
  line `person approved by the Commissioner to design or erect a building or execute any work shall, within one`
  line `month after the completion of the erection of the building or execution of the work, deliver or send or`
  line `cause to be delivered or sent to the Commissioner a notice in writing of such completion accompanied by`
  line `a certificate in the form prescribed by bye-laws made in this behalf and shall give to the Commissioner all`
  line `necessary facilities for the inspection of such building or work.`
  line
  line `(2) No person shall occupy or permit to be occupied any such building or use or permit to be used any`
  line `building or a part thereof effected by any such work until permission has been granted by the`
  line `Commissioner in this behalf in accordance with bye-laws made under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the Commissioner fails within a period of thirty days after the receipt of the notice of`
  line `completion to communicate his refusal to grant such permission, such permission shall be deemed to have`
  line `been granted.`
obj_root_law_sections_346_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_347:
  sectionId (31258)
  sectionNo (347)
  orderNo 397
  title `Restrictions on user of buildings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_347_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_347_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31258&sectionno=347&orderno=397&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_347_content:
  string
  line `No person shall, without the written permission of the`
  line `Commissioner, or otherwise than in conformity with the conditions, if any, of such permission—`
  line
  line `(a) use or permit to be used for human habitation any part of a building not originally erected or`
  line `authorised to be used for that purpose or not used for that purpose before any alteration has been`
  line `made therein by any work executed in accordance with the provisions of this Act and of the bye-laws`
  line `made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(b) change or allow the change of the use of any land or building;`
  line
  line `(c) convert or allow the conversion of one kind of tenement into another kind.`
obj_root_law_sections_347_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_347_a:
  sectionId (31259)
  sectionNo 347A
  orderNo 398
  title `Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_347_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_347_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31259&sectionno=347A&orderno=398&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_347_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[347A. Appellate Tribunal.--(1) The Central Government shall, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, constitute one or more Appellate Tribunals with headquarters at Delhi, for deciding appeals`
  line `preferred under section 343 or section 347B.`
  line
  line `(2) An Appellate Tribunal shall consist of one person to be appointed by the Central Government on`
  line `such terms and conditions of service as may be prescribed by rules.`
  line
  line `(3) A person shall not be qualified for appointment as the presiding officer of an Appellate Tribunal`
  line `unless he is, or has been, a district judge or an additional district judge or has, for at least ten years, held a`
  line `judicial office in India.`
  line
  line `(4) The ^2[Government] may, if it so thinks fit, appoint one or more persons having special`
  line `knowledge of, or experience in, the matters involved in such appeals, to act as assessors to advise the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal in the proceedings before it, but no advice of the assessors shall be binding on the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(5) The ^2[Government] shall, by notification in the Official Gazette, define the territorial limits`
  line `within which an Appellate Tribunal shall exercise its jurisdiction, and where different Appellate Tribunals`
  line `have jurisdiction over the same territorial limits, the Central Government shall also provide for the`
  line `distribution and allocation of work to be performed by such Tribunals.`
  line
  line `(6) For the purpose of enabling it to discharge its functions under this Act, every Appellate Tribunal`
  line `shall have a Registrar and such other staff on such terms and conditions of service as may be prescribed`
  line `by rules:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Registrar and staff may be employed jointly for all or any number of such Tribunals`
  line `in accordance with the rules.]`
obj_root_law_sections_347_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 42 of 1984, s. 7 (w.e.f. 10-2-1986).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for "Central Government" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
obj_root_law_sections_347_b:
  sectionId (31260)
  sectionNo 347B
  orderNo 399
  title `Appeals against certain orders or notices issued under the Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_347_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 42 of 1984, s. 7 (w.e.f. 10-2-1986)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31260&sectionno=347B&orderno=399&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_347_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[347B. Appeals against certain orders or notices issued under the Act.-- (1) Any person aggrieved`
  line `by any of the following orders made or notices issued under this Act, may prefer an appeal against such`
  line `order or notice to the Appellate Tribunal, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) an order according or disallowing sanction to a lay-out plan under section 313;`
  line
  line `(b) an order directing the alteration or demolition of any street under section 314;`
  line
  line `(c) a notice under sub-section (1) of section 315;`
  line
  line `(d) a notice under sub-section (2) of section 317;`
  line
  line `(e) an order directing the disposal of things removed under Chapter XV or seized under section`
  line `344, or an order rejecting the claim of any person for the balance of the proceeds of sale of the things`
  line `so disposed of;`
  line
  line `(f) an order sanctioning or refusing to sanction the erection of any building or the execution of`
  line `any work under section 336;`
  line
  line `(g) an order with holding sanction under the proviso to sub-section (1) of section 337;`
  line
  line `(h) an order cancelling a sanction under section 338;`
  line
  line `(i) an order requiring the rounding off, splaying or cutting off the height of a building intended to`
  line `be erected, or for the acquisition of any portion of a site, under section 339;`
  line
  line `(j) an order disallowing the erection of any building or the execution of any work under`
  line `section 340;`
  line
  line `(k) an order requiring the stoppage of any erection or work under section 344;`
  line
  line `(l) an order requiring the alteration of any building or work under section 345;`
  line
  line `(m) an order directing the sealing of unauthorised constructions under section 345A;`
  line
  line `(n) an order refusing to grant permission under sub-section (2) of section 346;`
  line
  line `(o) an order granting or refusing permission under section 347;`
  line
  line `(p) any such other order or notice relating to or arising out of planned development under the`
  line `provisions of this Act as may be prescribed by rules.`
  line
  line `(2) An appeal under this section shall be filed within thirty days from the date of the order or notice`
  line `appealed against:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Appellate Tribunal may entertain an appeal after the expiry of the said period of`
  line `thirty days if it is satisfied that there was sufficient cause for not filing it within that period.`
  line
  line `(3) An Appeal to the Appellate Tribunal shall be made in such form and shall be accompanied by a`
  line `copy of the order or notice appealed against and by such fees as may be prescribed by rules.]`
obj_root_law_sections_347_c:
  sectionId (31261)
  sectionNo 347C
  orderNo 400
  title `Procedure of the Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_347_c_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_347_c_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31261&sectionno=347C&orderno=400&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_347_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[347C. Procedure of the Appellate Tribunal.-- (1) The Appellate Tribunal may, after giving the`
  line `parties to the appeal, an opportunity of being heard, pass such orders thereon as it thinks fit, confirming,`
  line `modifying or annulling the order or notice appealed against or may refer the case back to the authority or`
  line `officer against whose order or notice the appeal is filed, for a fresh order or notice, after taking additional`
  line `evidence, if necessary, or such other action as the Appellate Tribunal may specify.`
  line
  line `(2) The Appellate Tribunal shall send a copy of every order passed by it to the parties to the appeal.`
  line
  line `(3) No Appellate Tribunal shall, in any appeal pending before it in respect of any order or notice`
  line `under this Act, make an interim order (whether by way of injunction or stay) against the Corporation or`
  line `against any officer or servant of ^2[^3[the Corporation]] acting or purporting to act in his official capacity, unless`
  line `an opportunity is given to ^2[^3[the Corporation]] or its officer or servant to be heard in the matter:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Appellate Tribunal may without giving an opportunity as aforesaid make an interim`
  line `order as an exceptional measure if it is satisfied for reasons to be recorded by it in writing that it is`
  line `necessary so to do for preventing any loss being caused to the person filing the appeal which cannot be`
  line `adequately compensated in money:`
  line
  line `Provided further that every such interim order shall, if it is not vacated earlier, cease to have effect on`
  line `the expiry of a period of fourteen days from the date on which it is made unless before the expiry of that`
  line `period, the Appellate Tribunal confirms or modifies that order after giving to ^2[^3[the Corporation]] or its officer`
  line `or servant an opportunity of being heard.`
  line
  line `(4) Subject to rules that may be made by the ^4[Government] in this behalf, the awarding of`
  line `damages in and the costs of, and incidental to, any appeal before an Appellate Tribunal, shall be in its`
  line `discretion and it shall have full power to determine by and to whom and to what extent and subject to`
  line `what conditions, if any, such damages or costs are to be paid and to give, in its order disposing of an`
  line `appeal, necessary directions for the purposes aforesaid.`
  line
  line `(5) An order of the Appellate Tribunal made under this section may be executed or caused to be`
  line `executed by it on the application of the person in whose favour the order has been made.`
  line
  line `(6) In hearing and deciding an appeal or in the execution of an order, an Appellate Tribunal shall`
  line `follow such procedure as may be prescribed by rules.`
  line
  line `(7) Every Appellate Tribunal, shall, in addition to the powers conferred on it under this Act, have`
  line `the same powers as are vested in a Civil Court while trying a suit under the Code of Civil`
  line `Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), in respect of the following matters, namely:`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of persons and examining them on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and inspection of documents;`
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) requisitioning any public record or copies thereof from any court or office;`
  line
  line `(e) issuing commisisons for the examination of witnesses or documents; and`
  line
  line `(f) any other matter which may be prescribed by rules, and every proceeding of an Appellate`
  line `Tribunal in hearing or deciding an appeal or in connection with the execution of its order, shall be`
  line `deemed to be a judicial proceeding within the meaning of sections 193 and 228, and for the purpose`
  line `of section 196, of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860), and every Appellate Tribunal shall be deemed`
  line `to a Civil Court for the purposes of section 195 and Chapter XXVI of the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).]`
obj_root_law_sections_347_c_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 42 of 1984, s. 7 (w.e.f. 10-2-1986).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2 "the Corporation"(w.e.f. 13-1-2012).br`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "a Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).br`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for "Central Government" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).br`
obj_root_law_sections_347_d:
  sectionId (31262)
  sectionNo 347D
  orderNo 401
  title `Appeal against orders of Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_347_d_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 42 of 1984, s. 7 (w.e.f. 10-2-1986)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31262&sectionno=347D&orderno=401&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_347_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[347D. Appeal against orders of Appellate Tribunal.-- (1) An appeal shall lie to the Administrator`
  line `against an order of the Appellate Tribunal, made in an appeal under section 343 or section 347B,`
  line `confirming, modifying or annulling an order made or notice issued under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of sub-sections (2) and (3) of section 347B and section 347C and the rules made`
  line `thereunder, shall, so far as may be, apply to the filing and disposal of an appeal under this section as they`
  line `apply to the filing and disposal of an appeal under those sections.`
  line
  line `(3) An order of the Administrator on an appeal under this section, and subject only to such order, an`
  line `order of the Appellate Tribunal under section 347B, and subject to such orders of the Administrator or an`
  line `Appellate Tribunal, an order or notice referred to in sub-section (1) of that section, shall be final.]`
obj_root_law_sections_347_e:
  sectionId (31263)
  sectionNo 347E
  orderNo 402
  title `Bar of jurisdiction of courts`
  content obj_root_law_sections_347_e_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 42 of 1984, s. 7 (w.e.f. 10-2-1986)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31263&sectionno=347E&orderno=402&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_347_e_content:
  string
  line `^1[347E. Bar of jurisdiction of courts.-- (1) After the commencement of section 7 of the Delhi`
  line `Municipal Corporation (Amendment) Act, 1984 (42 of 1984), no court shall entertain any suit, application`
  line `or other proceedings in respect of any order or notice appealable under section 343 or section 347B and`
  line `no such order or notice shall be called in question otherwise than by preferring an appeal under those`
  line sections.
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), every suit, application or other proceeding`
  line `pending in any court immediately before the commencement of section 7 of the Delhi Municipal`
  line `Corporation (Amendment) Act, 1984 (42 of 1984), in respect of any order or notice appealable under`
  line `section 343 or section 347B, shall continue to be dealt with and disposed of by that court as if the said`
  line `section had not been brought into force.]`
obj_root_law_sections_348:
  sectionId (31264)
  sectionNo (348)
  orderNo 403
  title `Removal of dangerous buildings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_348_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_348_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31264&sectionno=348&orderno=403&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_348_content:
  string
  line `(1) If it appears to the Commissioner at any time that any`
  line `building is in a ruinous condition, or likely to fall, or in any way dangerous to any person occupying,`
  line `resorting to or passing by such building or any other building or place in the neighbourhood of such`
  line `building, the Commissioner may, by order in writing, require the owner or occupier of such building to`
  line `demolish, secure or repair such building or do one or more of such things within such period as may be`
  line `specified in the order, so as to prevent all cause of danger therefrom.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commissioner may also, if he thinks fit, require such owner or occupier by the said order`
  line `either forthwith or before proceeding to demolish, secure or repair the building, to set up a proper and`
  line `sufficient hoard or fence for the protection of passers-by and other persons, with a convenient platform`
  line `and hand-rail wherever practicable to serve as a foot-way for passengers outside of such hoard or fence.`
  line
  line `(3) If it appears to the Commissioner that danger from a building which is in a ruinous condition or`
  line `likely to fall is imminent, he may, before making the order aforesaid, fence off, demolish, secure or repair`
  line `the said building or take such steps as may be necessary to prevent the danger.`
  line
  line `(4) If the owner or occupier of the building does not comply with the order within the period specified`
  line `therein, the Commissioner shall take such steps in relation to the building as to prevent all cause of danger`
  line therefrom.
  line
  line `(5) All expenses incurred by the Commissioner in relation to any building under this section shall be`
  line `recoverable from the owner or occupier thereof as an arrear of tax under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_348_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_349:
  sectionId (31265)
  sectionNo (349)
  orderNo 404
  title `Power to order building to be vacated in certain circumstances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_349_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_349_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31265&sectionno=349&orderno=404&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_349_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commissioner`
  line `may by order in writing direct that any building which in his opinion is in a dangerous condition or is not`
  line `provided with sufficient means of egress in case of fire or is occupied in contravention of section 346 be`
  line `vacated forthwith or within such period as may be specified in the order:`
  line
  line `Provided that at the time of making such order the Commissioner shall record a brief statement of the`
  line `reasons therefor.`
  line
  line `(2) If any person fails to vacate the building in pursuance of such order the Commissioner may direct`
  line `any police officer to remove such person from the building and the police officer shall comply with such`
  line `direction accordingly.`
  line
  line `(3) The Commissioner shall, on the application of any person who has vacated, or been removed from`
  line `any building in pursuance of an order made by him, reinstate such person in the building on the expiry of`
  line `the period for which the order has been in force according as the circumstances prevailing at that time`
  line permit.
obj_root_law_sections_349_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_349_a:
  sectionId (31266)
  sectionNo 349A
  orderNo 405
  title `Power of Central Government to make bye-laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_349_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_349_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31266&sectionno=349A&orderno=405&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_349_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[349A. Power of Central Government to make bye-laws.--(1) The ^2[Government] may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, make bye-laws for carrying out the provisions of this Chapter:`
  line
  line `Provided that all bye-laws made by ^3[^4[the Corporation]] under paragraph F of sub-section (1) of section`
  line `481 of this Act as it stood immediately before the commencement of the Delhi Municipal`
  line `Corporation(Amendment) Act, 1993 and in force immediately before such commencement, shall be`
  line `deemed to have been made under the provisions of this section and shall continue to have the same force`
  line `and effect after such commencement until it is amended, varied, rescinded or superseded under the`
  line `provisions of this section.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such bye-laws may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:`
  line
  line `(a) the regulation or restriction of the use of sites for buildings for different areas;`
  line
  line `(b) the regulation or restriction of buildings in different areas;`
  line
  line `(c) the form of notice of erection of any building or execution of any work and the fee in respect`
  line `of the same;`
  line
  line `(d) the plans and documents to be submitted together with such notice and the information and`
  line `further information to be furnished;`
  line
  line `(e) the level and width of foundation, level of lowest floor and stability of structure;`
  line
  line `(f) the construction of buildings and the materials to be used in the construction of buildings;`
  line
  line `(g) the height of buildings whether absolute or relative to the width of streets or to different area;`
  line
  line `(h) the number and height of storeys composing a building and the height of rooms and the`
  line `dimensions of room intended for human habitation;`
  line
  line `(i) the provision of open spaces, external and internal, and adequate means of light and`
  line ventilation;
  line
  line `(j) the provision of means of egress in case of fire, fire-escapes and water lifting devices;`
  line
  line `(k) the provision of secondary means of access for the removal of house refuse;`
  line
  line `(l) the materials and methods of construction of external and party walls, roofs and floors;`
  line
  line `(m) the position, materials and methods of construction of hearths, smoke-escapes, chimneys,`
  line `stair-cases, latrines, drains and cesspools;`
  line
  line `(n) the provision of lifts;`
  line
  line `(o) the paving of yards;`
  line
  line `(p) the restriction on the use of inflammable materials in buildings;`
  line
  line `(q) the restriction on construction of foundation on certain sites;`
  line
  line `(r) the measures to be taken to protect buildings from damp arising from sub-soil;`
  line
  line `(s) the wells, tanks and cisterns and pumps for the supply of water for human consumption in`
  line `connection with buildings;`
  line
  line `(t) in the case of wells, the dimensions of the well, the manner of enclosing it and if the well is`
  line `intended for drinking purposes, the means which shall be used to prevent pollution of the water;`
  line
  line `(u) the supervision of buildings;`
  line
  line `(v) the setting back of garages and shops from the regular line of a street;`
  line
  line `(w) the construction of portable structures and permission for such construction.`
  line
  line `(3) The draft of the bye-laws referred to in sub-section (1) shall be forwarded to the Commissioner,`
  line `who shall cause the same to be published in the Official Gazette for inviting objections and suggestions`
  line `from the public within thirty days from the date of such publication.`
  line
  line `(4) The Commissioner shall forward the draft bye-laws to the Central Government along with his`
  line `recommendations and the objections and suggestions received from the public, within three months of`
  line `their publication in the Official Gazette.`
  line
  line `(5) The Central Government may issue such directions to the Commissioner as it thinks fit, for`
  line `ensuring proper implementation of the bye-laws made under this section.]`
obj_root_law_sections_349_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 99 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for “Central Government” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_350:
  sectionId (31267)
  sectionNo (350)
  orderNo 406
  title `Provision for daily cleansing of streets and removal of rubbish and filth.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_350_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_350_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31267&sectionno=350&orderno=406&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_350_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the`
  line `purpose of securing the efficient scavenging and cleansing of all streets and premises, the Commissioner`
  line `shall provide—`
  line
  line `(a) for the daily surface-cleansing of all streets and the removal of the sweepings therefrom, and`
  line
  line `(b) for the removal of the contents of all receptacles and depots and of the accumulations at all`
  line `places provided or appointed by him under the provisions of this Act for the temporary deposit of`
  line `rubbish, filth and other polluted and obnoxious matter.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commissioner may, by public notice, issue directions as to the time at which, the manner in`
  line `which, and the conditions subject to which, any matter referred to in sub-section (1) may be removed`
  line `along a street or may be deposited or otherwise disposed of.`
obj_root_law_sections_350_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_351:
  sectionId (31268)
  sectionNo (351)
  orderNo 407
  title `Rubbish, etc., to be the property of the Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_351_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_351_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31268&sectionno=351&orderno=407&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_351_content:
  string
  line `All matters deposited in public`
  line `receptacles, depots and places provided or appointed under section 352 and all matters collected by`
  line `municipal employees or contractors in pursuance of section 350 and section 355 shall be the property of`
  line `^1[^2[the Corporation]].`
obj_root_law_sections_351_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "a Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_352:
  sectionId (31269)
  sectionNo (352)
  orderNo 408
  title `Provision or appointment of receptacles, depots and places for rubbish, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_352_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_352_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31269&sectionno=352&orderno=408&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_352_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `Commissioner shall—`
  line
  line `(a) provide or appoint in proper and convenient situations public receptacles, depots or places for`
  line `the temporary deposit of rubbish, filth and other polluted and obnoxious matter and for the final`
  line `disposal of rubbish, filth and other polluted and obnoxious matter;`
  line
  line `(b) provide dustbins for the temporary deposit of rubbish;`
  line
  line `(c) provide vehicles or other suitable means for the removal of rubbish and offensive matter; and`
  line
  line `(d) provide covered vehicles or vessels for the removal of filth and other polluted and obnoxious`
  line matter.
  line
  line `(2) Different receptacles, depots or places may be provided or appointed for the temporary deposit or`
  line `final disposal of any of the matter specified in sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) The Commissioner shall make adequate provision for preventing receptacles, depots, places,`
  line `dustbins, vehicles and vessels referred to in sub-section (1) from becoming sources of nuisance.`
obj_root_law_sections_352_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_353:
  sectionId (31270)
  sectionNo (353)
  orderNo 409
  title `Duty of owners and occupiers to collect and deposit rubbish, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_353_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_353_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31270&sectionno=353&orderno=409&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_353_content:
  string
  line `It shall be the duty of the`
  line `owners and occupiers of all premises—`
  line
  line `(a) to have the premises swept and cleaned;`
  line
  line `(b) to cause all filth, rubbish and other polluted and obnoxious matter to be collected from their`
  line `respective premises and to be deposited at such times as the Commissioner, by public notices`
  line `prescribes, in public receptacles, depots or places provided or appointed under section 352 for the`
  line `temporary deposit or final disposal thereof;`
  line
  line `(c) to provide receptacles of the type and in the manner prescribed by the Commissioner for the`
  line `collection therein of all filth, rubbish and other polluted and obnoxious matter from such premises`
  line `and to keep such receptacles in good condition and repair.`
obj_root_law_sections_353_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_354:
  sectionId (31271)
  sectionNo (354)
  orderNo 410
  title `Collection and removal of filth and polluted matter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_354_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_354_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31271&sectionno=354&orderno=410&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_354_content:
  string
  line `It shall be the duty of the owner and`
  line `occupier of every premises situate in any portion of Delhi ^1`
  line `*** in which there is not a latrine, or urinal`
  line `connected by a drain with a municipal drain, to cause all filth and polluted and obnoxious matter`
  line `accumulating upon such premises to be collected and removed to the nearest receptacle or depot provided`
  line `for this purpose under section 352 at such times, in such vehicle or vessel by such route and with such`
  line `precautions as the Commissioner may by public notice prescribe.`
obj_root_law_sections_354_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words, brackets, letters and figures “in respect of which the Commissioner has not given public notice under`
  line `clause (b) of sub-section (2) of section 115 or” omitted by Act 67 of 1993, s. 100 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_355:
  sectionId (31272)
  sectionNo (355)
  orderNo 411
  title `Collection and removal of filth and polluted matter through municipal agency.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_355_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_355_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31272&sectionno=355&orderno=411&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_355_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[(1) It`
  line `shall be lawful for the Commissioner to take or cause to be taken measures for the daily collection,`
  line `removal and disposal of all filth and polluted and obnoxious matter from latrines, urinals and cesspools`
  line `not connected by a drain with a municipal drain from all premises situate in any portion of ^2[^3[Delhi]].]`
  line
  line `(2) In such portion of ^2[^3[Delhi]] and in any premises wherever situate in which there is a latrine, or urinal`
  line `connected with a municipal drain, it shall not be lawful, except with the written permission of the`
  line `Commissioner, for any person who is not employed by or on behalf of the Commissioner, to discharge`
  line `any of the duties of scavengers.`
obj_root_law_sections_355_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 101, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Delhi Act 13 of 2011, s. 2, for "Delhi" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "the area of the Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_356:
  sectionId (31273)
  sectionNo (356)
  orderNo 412
  title `Removal of rubbish, etc., accumulated on premises used as factories, workshops, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_356_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_356_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31273&sectionno=356&orderno=412&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_356_content:
  string
  line The
  line `Commissioner may, if he thinks fit—`
  line
  line `(a) by written notice require the owner or occupier of any premises used for carrying on any`
  line `manufacture, trade or business or used as a factory, workshop, trade premises or market or in any way`
  line `so that rubbish, filth and other polluted and obnoxious matter are accumulated in large quantities, to`
  line `collect all such rubbish, filth and other polluted and obnoxious matter accumulating thereon and to`
  line `remove the same at such times and in such carts or receptacles and by such routes as may be specified`
  line `in the notice to a depot or place provided or appointed under section 352, or`
  line
  line `(b) after giving such owner or occupier notice of his intention, cause all rubbish, filth and other`
  line `polluted and obnoxious matter accumulated in such premises to be removed, and charge the said`
  line `owner or occupier for such removal such fee as may, with the sanction of the Standing Committee, be`
  line `specified in the notice issued under clause (a).`
obj_root_law_sections_356_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_357:
  sectionId (31274)
  sectionNo (357)
  orderNo 413
  title `Prohibition against accumulation of rubbish, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_357_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_357_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31274&sectionno=357&orderno=413&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_357_content:
  string
  line `(1) No owner or occupier of any premises`
  line `shall keep or allow to be kept for more than twenty-four hours or otherwise than in a receptacle approved`
  line `by the Commissioner, any rubbish, filth and other polluted and obnoxious matter on such premises or any`
  line `place belonging thereto or neglect to employ proper means to remove such rubbish, filth and other`
  line `polluted and obnoxious matter from, or to cleanse, such receptacle and to dispose of such rubbish, filth`
  line `and other polluted and obnoxious matter in the manner directed by the Commissioner, or fail to comply`
  line `with any requisition of the Commissioner as to the construction, repair, pavement or cleansing of any`
  line `latrine, or urinal on or belonging to the premises.`
  line
  line `(2) No owner or occupier shall allow the water of any sink, drain, latrine or urinal or any rubbish, filth`
  line `and other polluted and obnoxious matter to run down on or to, or be thrown or put upon, any street or into`
  line `any drain in or along the side of any street except in such manner as shall prevent any avoidable nuisance`
  line `from any such water, rubbish, filth or other polluted and obnoxious matter.`
  line
  line `(3) No person shall, after due provision has been made in this respect under the foregoing provisions`
  line `of this Chapter for the deposit and removal of the same—`
  line
  line `(a) deposit any rubbish, filth and other polluted and obnoxious matter in any street or on the`
  line `verandah of any building or on any unoccupied ground alongside any street or on the bank of a water`
  line `course; or`
  line
  line `(b) deposit any filth or other polluted and obnoxious matter in any dustbin or in any vehicle not`
  line `intended for the removal of the same; or`
  line
  line `(c) deposit rubbish in any vehicle or vessel intended for the removal of filth and other polluted`
  line `and obnoxious matter.`
obj_root_law_sections_357_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_358:
  sectionId (31275)
  sectionNo (358)
  orderNo 414
  title `Commissioner’s power to get premises scavenged and cleansed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_358_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_358_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31275&sectionno=358&orderno=414&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_358_content:
  string
  line `If any premises are not`
  line `properly and regularly scavenged or cleansed or are in a filthy and unwholesome condition, the`
  line `Commissioner may cause them to be scavenged and cleansed and recover the expenses from the owner`
  line `or, as the case may be, occupier as an arrear of tax under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_358_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_359:
  sectionId (31276)
  sectionNo (359)
  orderNo 415
  title `Public latrines, urinals, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_359_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_359_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31276&sectionno=359&orderno=415&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_359_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commissioner shall provide and maintain in proper and`
  line `convenient places a sufficient number of public latrines and urinals.`
  line
  line `(2) Such public latrines and urinals shall be so constructed as to provide separate compartments for`
  line `each sex and not to be a nuisance, and shall be provided with all necessary conservancy establishments,`
  line `and shall regularly be cleansed and kept in proper order.`
obj_root_law_sections_359_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_360:
  sectionId (31277)
  sectionNo (360)
  orderNo 416
  title `Construction of latrines and urinals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_360_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_360_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31277&sectionno=360&orderno=416&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_360_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall not be lawful to construct any latrine or`
  line `urinal for any premises except with the written permission of the Commissioner and in accordance with`
  line `such terms not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act or any bye-laws made thereunder as he may`
  line prescribe.
  line
  line `(2) In prescribing any such terms the Commissioner may determine in each case—`
  line
  line `(a) whether the premises shall be served by the service system or by the flush system or partly by`
  line `the one and partly by the other; and`
  line
  line `(b) what shall be the site or position of each latrine or urinal.`
  line
  line `(3) If any latrine or urinal is constructed on any premises in contravention of the foregoing`
  line `provisions, the Commissioner may, after giving not less than ten days notice to the owner or occupier of`
  line `such premises, alter, reconstruct, close or demolish such latrine or urinal and the expenditure incurred by`
  line `the Commissioner in so doing shall be recoverable from the owner or occupier as an arrear of tax under`
  line `this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_360_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_361:
  sectionId (31278)
  sectionNo (361)
  orderNo 417
  title `Latrines and urinals, etc., in new buildings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_361_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_361_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31278&sectionno=361&orderno=417&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_361_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall not be lawful to erect any building or`
  line `execute any work on or in relation to such building without providing such latrine accommodation and`
  line `urinal accommodation and accommodation for bathing or for washing clothes and utensils on each floor`
  line `of such building as the Commissioner may prescribe.`
  line
  line `(2) In prescribing any such accommodation the Commissioner may determine in each case--`
  line
  line `(a) whether such building shall be served by the service system or by the flush system or partly`
  line `by the one and partly by the other;`
  line
  line `(b) what shall be the site or position of each latrine, urinal, bathing or washing place or site and`
  line `their number of each floor and their clear internal dimensions.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall not be lawful to erect a residential building composed of separate tenements on the flat`
  line `system without providing at least one latrine and one bathing or washing place for servants on the ground`
  line `floor of such building or at any other suitable place in the same premises.`
  line
  line `(4) In this section the expression to erect a building has the same meaning as in section 331.`
obj_root_law_sections_361_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_362:
  sectionId (31279)
  sectionNo (362)
  orderNo 418
  title `Latrines and urinals for labourers, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_362_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_362_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31279&sectionno=362&orderno=418&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_362_content:
  string
  line `Every person employing workmen, labourers or`
  line `other persons exceeding twenty in number shall provide and maintain for the separate use of persons of`
  line `each sex so employed, latrines and urinals of such description and number as the Commissioner may by`
  line `notice require and within such time as may be fixed in the notice and shall keep the same in clean and`
  line `proper order.`
obj_root_law_sections_362_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_363:
  sectionId (31280)
  sectionNo (363)
  orderNo 419
  title `Provision of latrines and urinals for markets, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_363_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_363_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31280&sectionno=363&orderno=419&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_363_content:
  string
  line `The Commissioner may by notice require`
  line `any owner or manager of a market, cart stand, cattle shed, theatre, railway station and other place of`
  line `public resort within such time as may be specified in such notice to provide and maintain for the separate`
  line `use of persons of each sex, latrines of such description and number and in such position as may be`
  line `specified and to keep the same in clean and proper order.`
obj_root_law_sections_363_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_364:
  sectionId (31281)
  sectionNo (364)
  orderNo 420
  title `Other provisions as to private latrines.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_364_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_364_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31281&sectionno=364&orderno=420&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_364_content:
  string
  line `The Commissioner may, by written notice—`
  line
  line `(a) require the owner or other person having the control of any private latrine or urinal not to put`
  line `the same to public use; or`
  line
  line `(b) require the owner or other person having the control of such private latrine or urinal which in`
  line `the opinion of the Commissioner constitutes a nuisance, to remove the latrine or the urinal; or`
  line
  line `(c) require any person having the control whether as owner, lessee or occupier of any land or`
  line building—
  line
  line `(i) to have any latrines provided for the same shut out by a sufficient roof, wall or fence from`
  line `the view of persons passing by or dwelling in the neighbourhood; or`
  line
  line `(ii) to cleans in such manner as the Commissioner may prescribe in the notice any latrine or`
  line `urinal belonging to the land or building; or`
  line
  line `(d) where any premises intended or used for human habitation are without any latrine or urinal`
  line `accommodation or are provided with insufficient latrine or urinal accommodation, require the owner,`
  line `lessee or occupier of such premises to provide such or such additional latrine or urinal`
  line `accommodation as he may prescribe, if necessary by causing any part of such premises to be vacated`
  line `and demolished in accordance with bye-laws made in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_364_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_365:
  sectionId (31282)
  sectionNo (365)
  orderNo 421
  title `Removal of congested buildings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_365_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_365_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31282&sectionno=365&orderno=421&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_365_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where it appears to the Commissioner that any block of`
  line `buildings is in an unhealthy condition by reason of the manner in which the buildings are crowded`
  line `together, or of the narrowness, closeness, or faulty arrangement of streets, or of the want of proper`
  line `drainage and ventilation, or of the impracticability of cleansing the buildings or other similar cause, he`
  line `shall cause the block to be inspected to by the Municipal Health Officer and the Municipal Engineer who`
  line `shall make a report in writing to him regarding the sanitary condition of the block.`
  line
  line `(2) If upon receipt of such report the Commissioner considers that the sanitary condition of the block`
  line `is likely to cause risk of disease to the inhabitants of the buildings or of the neighbourhood or otherwise to`
  line `endanger the public health, he shall with the approval of the Standing Committee select the buildings`
  line `which in his opinion should wholly or in part be removed in order to abate the unhealthy condition of the block and may thereupon by notice in writing require the owners of such buildings to remove them within`
  line `such period as may be specified in the notice:`
  line
  line `Provided that before issuing the notice reasonable opportunity should be afforded to the owners to`
  line `show cause why the building should not be removed:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Commissioner shall make compensation to the owners for any buildings so`
  line `removed which may have been erected under proper authority.`
  line
  line `(3) If a notice under sub-section (2) requiring any owner of a building to remove it is not complied`
  line `with, then, after the expiration of the time specified in the notice the Commissioner may himself remove`
  line `the building required to be removed by the notice and recover from the owner of the building the`
  line `expenses of such removal as an arrear of tax under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_365_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_366:
  sectionId (31283)
  sectionNo (366)
  orderNo 422
  title `Power of Commissioner to require improvement of buildings unfit for human habitation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_366_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_366_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31283&sectionno=366&orderno=422&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_366_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Commissioner upon information in his possession is satisfied that any`
  line `building is in any respect unfit for human habitation, he may, unless in his opinion the building is not`
  line `capable at a reasonable expense of being rendered fit, serve upon the owner of the building a notice`
  line `requiring him within such time not being less than thirty days as may be specified in the notice to execute`
  line `the works of improvement specified therein and stating that in his opinion those works will render the`
  line `building fit for human habitation.`
  line
  line `(2) In addition to serving a notice under this section on the owner the Commissioner may serve a`
  line `copy of the notice on any other person having an interest in the building whether as a lessee, mortgagee or`
  line otherwise.
  line
  line `(3) In determining whether a building can be rendered fit for human habitation at a reasonable`
  line `expense regard shall be had to the estimated cost of the work necessary to render it so fit and the value`
  line `which it is estimated that the building will have when the works are completed.`
obj_root_law_sections_366_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_367:
  sectionId (31284)
  sectionNo (367)
  orderNo 423
  title `Enforcement of notice requiring execution of works of improvement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_367_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_367_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31284&sectionno=367&orderno=423&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_367_content:
  string
  line `If a notice under`
  line `section 366 requiring the owner of the building to execute works of improvement is not complied with,`
  line `then, after the expiration of the time specified in the notice the Commissioner may himself do the works`
  line `required to be done by the notice and recover the expenses incurred in connection therewith as an arrear`
  line `of tax under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_367_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_368:
  sectionId (31285)
  sectionNo (368)
  orderNo 424
  title `Power of Commissioner to order demolition of buildings unfit for human habitation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_368_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_368_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31285&sectionno=368&orderno=424&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_368_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `Where the Commissioner upon any information in his possession is satisfied that any building is unfit for`
  line `human habitation and is not capable at a reasonable expense of being rendered so fit he shall serve upon`
  line `the owner of the building, and upon any other person having an interest in the building, whether as a`
  line `lessee, mortgagee or otherwise a notice to show cause within such time as maybe specified in the notice`
  line `as to why an order of demolition of the building should not be made.`
  line
  line `(2) If any of the person upon whom a notice has been served under sub-section (1), appears in`
  line `pursuance thereof before the Commissioner and gives an undertaking to him that such person shall,`
  line `within a period specified by the Commissioner, execute such works of improvement in relation to the`
  line `building as will, in the opinion of the Commissioner, render the building fit for human habitation or an`
  line `undertaking that the building shall not be used for human habitation until the Commissioner on being`
  line `satisfied that it has been rendered fit for that purpose, cancels the undertaking, the Commissioner shall not`
  line `make an order of demolition of the building.`
  line
  line `(3) If no such undertaking as is mentioned in sub-section (2) is given, or if in a case where any such`
  line `undertaking has been given, any work of improvement to which the undertaking relates is not carried out`
  line `within the specified period, or the building is at any time used in contravention of the terms of the`
  line `undertaking, the Commissioner shall forthwith make an order of demolition of the building requiring that`
  line `the building shall be vacated within a period to be specified in the order not being less than thirty days`
  line `from the date of the order, and that it shall be demolished within six weeks after the expiration of that`
  line period.
  line
  line `(4) Where an order of demolition of a building under this section has been made, the owner of the`
  line `building or any other person having an interest therein, shall demolish that building within the time`
  line `specified in that behalf by the order, and if the building is not demolished within that time, the`
  line `Commissioner shall demolish the building and sell the materials thereof.`
  line
  line `(5) Any expenses incurred by the Commissioner under sub-section (4) if not satisfied out of the`
  line `proceeds of the sale of materials of the building shall be recovered from the owner of the building or any`
  line `other person having an interest therein as an arrear of tax under this Act.`
  line
  line `(6) In determining for the purposes of section 366 and this section whether a building is unfit for`
  line `human habitation, regard shall be had to its condition in respect of the following matters, that is to say,—`
  line
  line `(a) repair;`
  line
  line `(b) stability;`
  line
  line `(c) freedom from damp;`
  line
  line `(d) natural light and air;`
  line
  line `(e) water supply;`
  line
  line `(f) drainage and sanitary conveniences;`
  line
  line `(g) facilities for storage, preparation and cooking of food and for the disposal of rubbish, filth and`
  line `other polluted matter;`
  line
  line `and the building shall be deemed to be unfit as aforesaid if it is so far defective in one or more of the said`
  line `matters that it is not reasonably suitable for occupation in that condition.`
  line
  line `(7) For the purposes of section 366, section 367 and this section, "work of improvement" in relation`
  line `to a building includes any one or more of the following works, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) necessary repairs;`
  line
  line `(b) structural alterations;`
  line
  line `(c) provision of light points and water taps;`
  line
  line `(d) construction of drains, open or covered;`
  line
  line `(e) provision of latrines and urinals;`
  line
  line `(f) provision of additional or improved fixtures and fittings;`
  line
  line `(g) opening up or paving of courtyard;`
  line
  line `(h) removal of rubbish, filth and other polluted and obnoxious matter;`
  line
  line `(i) any other work including the demolition of any building or any part thereof which, in the`
  line `opinion of the Commissioner, is necessary for executing any of the works specified above.`
  line
  line `(8) The provisions of section 365, section 366, section 367 and this section shall not apply in relation`
  line `to any building in any area which has been declared to be a slum area under the Slum Area (Improvement`
  line `and Clearance) Act, 1956 (96 of 1956).`
obj_root_law_sections_368_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_369:
  sectionId (31286)
  sectionNo (369)
  orderNo 425
  title `Insanitary huts and sheds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_369_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_369_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31286&sectionno=369&orderno=425&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_369_content:
  string
  line `Where the Commissioner upon any information in his possession`
  line `is satisfied that any hut or shed used as a dwelling house or as a stable or for any other purpose, is likely,`
  line `by reason of its being constructed without a plinth or upon a plinth of insufficient height or without`
  line `proper means of drainage or on account of the impracticability of scavenging and cleansing it or owing to`
  line `the manner in which it and other huts of sheds are crowded together, to cause risk of disease to the`
  line `inmates thereof or to the inhabitants of the neighbourhood, or is for any reason likely to endanger public`
  line `health or safety, he may by notice in writing require the owner or occupier of the hut of shed or the owner`
  line `or occupier of the land on which the hut or shed stands to remove or alter the hut or shed or carry out such`
  line `improvement thereof as the Commissioner may deem necessary within such time as may be specified in`
  line `the notice.`
obj_root_law_sections_369_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_370:
  sectionId (31287)
  sectionNo (370)
  orderNo 426
  title `Prohibition against washing by washermen.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_370_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_370_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31287&sectionno=370&orderno=426&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_370_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commissioner may by public notice`
  line `prohibit the washing of clothes by washermen in the exercise of their callings except at such places as he`
  line `may appoint for the purpose.`
  line
  line `(2) When any such prohibition has been made, no person who is by calling a washerman shall in`
  line `contravention of such prohibition wash clothes except for himself or for personal and family service or`
  line `for hire on or within the premises of the hirer, at any place other than a place appointed under sub-section`
  line `(1).`
obj_root_law_sections_370_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_371:
  sectionId (31288)
  sectionNo (371)
  orderNo 427
  title `Obligation to give information of dangerous disease.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_371_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_371_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31288&sectionno=371&orderno=427&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_371_content:
  string
  line `Any person being in charge of, or in`
  line `attendance, whether as a medical practitioner or otherwise, upon any person whom he knows or has`
  line `reason to believe to be suffering from a dangerous disease, or being the owner, lessee, or occupier of any`
  line `building in which he knows that any such person is so suffering shall forthwith give information`
  line `respecting the existence of such disease to the Municipal Health Officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_371_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_372:
  sectionId (31289)
  sectionNo (372)
  orderNo 428
  title `Removal to hospital of patients suffering from dangerous disease.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_372_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_372_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31289&sectionno=372&orderno=428&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_372_content:
  string
  line `(1) When any person`
  line `suffering from any dangerous disease is found to be--`
  line
  line `(a) without proper lodging or accommodation, or`
  line
  line `(b) living in a room or house which the neither owns or pays rent for nor occupies as the guest or`
  line `relative of any person who owns, or pays rent for it, or`
  line
  line `(c) living in a sarai, hotel, boarding house or other public hotel, or`
  line
  line `(d) lodged in premises occupied by members of two or more families,`
  line
  line `the Commissioner or any person authorised by him in this behalf, may on the advice of any medical`
  line `officer of the rank not inferior to that of an assistant surgeon remove the patient to any hospital or place at`
  line `which persons suffering from such disease are received for medical treatment and may anything`
  line `necessary for such removal.`
  line
  line `(2) ^1[^2[The Corporation]] shall if required by the ^3[Government] erect an infectious diseases hospital`
  line `of such type and dimension as that Government may direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_372_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for “Central Government” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
obj_root_law_sections_373:
  sectionId (31290)
  sectionNo (373)
  orderNo 429
  title `Disinfection of buildings and articles.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_373_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_373_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31290&sectionno=373&orderno=429&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_373_content:
  string
  line `Where the Commissioner is of opinion that the`
  line `cleansing and disinfection of any building or part of a building or of any articles in such building or part`
  line `which are likely to retain infection, or the renewal of flooring of any building or part of such building, and`
  line `the renewal of plastering of the walls thereof, would tend to prevent or check the spread of any dangerous`
  line `disease; he may, by notice in writing, require the owner or occupier to cleanse and disinfect the said`
  line `building, part or articles, as the case may be, or to renew the said flooring and if necessary, the said`
  line `plastering also within such time as may be specified in the notice:`
  line
  line `Provided that where in the opinion of the Commissioner the owner or occupier is from poverty or any`
  line `other cause unable effectually, to carry out any such requisition, the Commissioner may at the expense of`
  line `the Municipal Fund cleanse and disinfect the building, part or articles, or, as the case may be, renew the`
  line `flooring and if necessary, the plastering also.`
obj_root_law_sections_373_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_374:
  sectionId (31291)
  sectionNo (374)
  orderNo 430
  title `Destruction of infectious huts or sheds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_374_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_374_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31291&sectionno=374&orderno=430&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_374_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the destruction of any hut or shed is in the`
  line `opinion of the Commissioner necessary to prevent the spread of any dangerous disease, the Commissioner`
  line `may by notice in writing require the owner to destroy the hut or shed and the materials thereof within`
  line `such time as may be specified in the notice.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the Commissioner is satisfied that the destruction of any hut or shed is immediately`
  line `necessary for the purpose of preventing the spread of any dangerous disease, he may order the owner or`
  line `occupier of the hut or shed to destroy the same forthwith or may himself cause it to be destroyed after`
  line `giving not less than six hours' notice to the owner or occupier.`
  line `(3) Compensation may be paid by the Commissioner, in any case which he thinks fit, to any person`
  line `who sustains substantial loss by the destruction of any such hut or shed, but, except as so allowed by the`
  line `Commissioner, no claim for compensation shall lie for any loss or damage caused by any exercise of the`
  line `power conferred by this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_374_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_375:
  sectionId (31292)
  sectionNo (375)
  orderNo 431
  title `Means of disinfection.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_375_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_375_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31292&sectionno=375&orderno=431&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_375_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commissioner shall—`
  line
  line `(a) provide proper places with necessary attendants and apparatus for the disinfection of`
  line `conveyances, clothing, bedding and other articles which have been exposed to infection;`
  line
  line `(b) cause conveyances, clothing and other articles brought for disinfection to be disinfected either`
  line `free of charge or on payment of such charges as he may fix.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commissioner may notify places at which articles of clothing, bedding and conveyances or`
  line `other articles which have been exposed to infection shall be washed and if he does so, no person shall`
  line `wash any such thing at any place not so notified without having previously disinfected such thing.`
  line
  line `(3) The Commissioner may direct the destruction of any clothing, bedding or other article likely to`
  line `retain infection and may give such compensation as he thinks fit for any article so destroyed.`
obj_root_law_sections_375_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_376:
  sectionId (31293)
  sectionNo (376)
  orderNo 432
  title `Special measures in case of outbreak of dangerous or epidemic diseases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_376_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_376_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31293&sectionno=376&orderno=432&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_376_content:
  string
  line `(1) In the event of`
  line `Delhi or any part thereof being visited or threatened by an outbreak of any dangerous disease among the`
  line `inhabitants thereof or of any epidemic disease among any animals therein, the Commissioner, if he thinks`
  line `that the other provisions of this Act and the provisions of any other law for the time being in force are`
  line `insufficient for the purpose, may, with the previous sanction of ^1[^2[the Corporation]],--`
  line
  line `(a) take such special measures, and`
  line
  line `(b) by public notice, give such directions to be observed by the public or by any class or section`
  line `of the public,`
  line
  line `as he thinks necessary to prevent the outbreak or spread of the disease:`
  line
  line `Provided that where in the opinion of the Commissioner immediate measures are necessary, he may`
  line `take action without such sanction as aforesaid and if he does so, shall forthwith report such action to ^1[^2[the`
  line Corporation]].
  line
  line `(2) No person shall commit a breach of any direction given under sub-section (1) and if he does so he`
  line `shall be deemed to have committed an offence under section 188 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_376_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “A Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_377:
  sectionId (31294)
  sectionNo (377)
  orderNo 433
  title `Infected clothes not to be sent to washerman or to laundry.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_377_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_377_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31294&sectionno=377&orderno=433&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_377_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person shall not send or`
  line `take to any washerman or to any laundry or place set a part for the exercise by washermen of their calling,`
  line `for the purpose of being washed or to anyplace for the purpose of being cleansed, any cloth or other`
  line `article which he knows to have been exposed to infection from a dangerous disease unless that cloth or`
  line `article has been disinfected by or to the satisfaction of the Municipal Health Officer.`
  line
  line `(2) The occupier of any building in which a person is suffering from a dangerous disease shall, if`
  line `required by the Municipal Health Officer, furnish to him the address of any washerman to whom or any`
  line `laundry or other place to which clothes and other articles from the building have been, or will be, sent`
  line `during the continuance of the disease, for the purpose of being washed or cleaned.`
obj_root_law_sections_377_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_378:
  sectionId (31295)
  sectionNo (378)
  orderNo 434
  title `Contamination and disinfection of public conveyance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_378_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_378_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31295&sectionno=378&orderno=434&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_378_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever—`
  line
  line `(a) uses a public conveyance while suffering from a dangerous disease, or`
  line
  line `(b) uses a public conveyance for the carriage of a person who is suffering from any disease, or`
  line
  line `(c) uses a public conveyance for the carriage of the corpse of a person who has died from any`
  line `such disease,`
  line
  line `shall be bound to take proper precautions against the communication of the disease to other persons using`
  line `or who may thereafter use the conveyance and to notify such use of the owner, driver or person incharge`
  line `of the conveyance, and further report without delay to the Commissioner the number of the conveyance`
  line `and the name of the person so notified.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any person suffering from, or the corpse of any person who has died from, a dangerous`
  line `disease has been carried in public conveyance which ordinarily plies in Delhi or any part thereof, the`
  line `driver thereof shall forthwith report the fact to the Commissioner who shall forthwith cause the`
  line `conveyance to be disinfected if that has not already been done.`
  line
  line `(3) No such conveyance shall be again brought into use until the Municipal Health Officer has`
  line `granted a certificate stating that it can be used without causing risk of infection.`
  line
  line `(4) Whoever fails to make to the Commissioner any report which he is required to make under this`
  line `section shall be guilty of an offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_378_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_379:
  sectionId (31296)
  sectionNo (379)
  orderNo 435
  title `Driver of conveyance not bound to carry persons suffering from dangerous disease.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_379_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_379_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31296&sectionno=379&orderno=435&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_379_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in any law for the time being in force no owner, driver or`
  line `person in charge of a public conveyance shall be bound to convey or to allow to be conveyed in such`
  line `conveyance in or in the vicinity of Delhi any person suffering from a dangerous disease or the corpse of`
  line `any person who has died from such disease unless and until such person pays or tenders a sum sufficient`
  line `to cover any loss and expense which would ordinarily be incurred in disinfecting the conveyance.`
obj_root_law_sections_379_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_380:
  sectionId (31297)
  sectionNo (380)
  orderNo 436
  title `Disinfection of buildings before letting the same.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_380_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_380_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31297&sectionno=380&orderno=436&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_380_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any building or part of a`
  line `building is intended to be let in which any person has, within six weeks immediately preceding, been`
  line `suffering from a dangerous disease, the person letting the building or part shall, before doing so, disinfect`
  line `the same in such manner as the Commissioner may by general or special notice direct together with all`
  line `articles therein liable to retain infection.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of this section the keeper of a hostel, lodging house or sarai shall be deemed to`
  line `let to any person who is admitted as a guest therein that part of the building in which such person is`
  line `permitted to reside.`
obj_root_law_sections_380_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_381:
  sectionId (31298)
  sectionNo (381)
  orderNo 437
  title `Disposal of infected articles without disinfection.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_381_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_381_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31298&sectionno=381&orderno=437&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_381_content:
  string
  line `No person shall, without previous`
  line `disinfection of the same, give, lend, sell, transmit or otherwise dispose of to another person any article or`
  line `thing which he knows or has reason to believe has been exposed to contamination by any dangerous`
  line `disease and is likely to be used in or taken into Delhi or any part thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_381_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_382:
  sectionId (31299)
  sectionNo (382)
  orderNo 438
  title `Prohibition of making or selling of food, etc., or washing of clothes by infected persons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_382_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_382_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31299&sectionno=382&orderno=438&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_382_content:
  string
  line `No person while suffering from or in circumstances in which he is likely to spread, any`
  line `dangerous disease, shall—`
  line
  line `(a) make, carry or offer for sale or take any part in the business of making, carrying or offering`
  line `for sale, any article of food or drink or any medicine or drug for human consumption, or any article of`
  line `clothing or bedding for personal use or wear, or`
  line
  line `(b) take any part in the business of the washing or carrying of clothes.`
obj_root_law_sections_382_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_383:
  sectionId (31300)
  sectionNo (383)
  orderNo 439
  title `Power to restrict or prohibit sale of food or drink.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_383_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_383_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31300&sectionno=383&orderno=439&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_383_content:
  string
  line `When Delhi or any part thereof is visited`
  line `or threatened by an outbreak of any dangerous disease the Commissioner may, by public notice, restrict in`
  line `such manner or prohibit for such period as may be specified in the notice, the sale or preparation of any`
  line `article of food or drink for human consumption specified in the notice or the sale of any flesh of any`
  line `description of animal so specified.`
obj_root_law_sections_383_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_384:
  sectionId (31301)
  sectionNo (384)
  orderNo 440
  title `Control over wells and tanks, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_384_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_384_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31301&sectionno=384&orderno=440&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_384_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Commissioner is of opinion that the water in any`
  line `well, tank or other place, is likely, if used for drinking, to endanger, or cause the spread of, any disease,`
  line `he may—`
  line
  line `(a) by public notice, prohibit the removal or use of such water for drinking; or`
  line
  line `(b) by notice in writing require the owner or person having control of such well, tank or place to`
  line `take such steps as may be directed by the notice to prevent the public from having access to or using`
  line `such water; or`
  line
  line `(c) take such other steps as he may consider expedient to prevent the outbreak or spread of any`
  line `such disease.`
  line
  line `(2) In the event of Delhi or any part thereof being visited or threatened by an outbreak of a dangerous`
  line `disease the Municipal Health Officer or any person authorised by him in this behalf may, without notice`
  line `and at any time, inspect and disinfect any well, tank or other place from which water is, or is likely to be,`
  line `taken for the purposes of drinking and may further take such steps as he may think fit to ensure the purity`
  line `of the water or to prevent the use of the same for drinking purposes.`
obj_root_law_sections_384_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_385:
  sectionId (31302)
  sectionNo (385)
  orderNo 441
  title `Duty of persons suffering from dangerous disease.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_385_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_385_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31302&sectionno=385&orderno=441&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_385_content:
  string
  line `No person shall,—`
  line
  line `(a) knowing that he is suffering from a dangerous disease, expose other persons to the risk of`
  line `infection by his presence or conduct in any public street or public place;`
  line
  line `(b) having the care of a person whom he knows to be suffering from a dangerous disease, cause`
  line `or permit that person to expose other persons to the risk of infection by his presence or conduct in any`
  line `such street or place as aforesaid;`
  line
  line `(c) place or cause to be placed in a dustbin or other receptacle for the deposit of rubbish, any`
  line `matter which he knows to have been exposed to infection from a dangerous disease and which has not`
  line `been disinfected properly;`
  line
  line `(d) throw or cause to be thrown into any latrine or urinal any matter which he knows to have been`
  line `exposed to infection from a dangerous disease and which has not been disinfected properly.`
obj_root_law_sections_385_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_386:
  sectionId (31303)
  sectionNo (386)
  orderNo 442
  title `Disposal of infectious corpses where any person has died from any dangerous disease.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_386_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_386_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31303&sectionno=386&orderno=442&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_386_content:
  string
  line `Where any person has died from any dangerous disease the Commissioner may, by notice in`
  line writing—
  line
  line `(a) require any person having charge of the corpse to convey the same to a mortuary thereafter to`
  line `be disposed of in accordance with law, or`
  line
  line `(b) prohibit the removal of corpses from the place where death occurred except for the purpose of`
  line `being burnt, buried or for being conveyed to a mortuary.`
obj_root_law_sections_386_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_387:
  sectionId (31304)
  sectionNo (387)
  orderNo 443
  title `Conditions of service of sweepers and certain other class of persons employed in municipal service.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_387_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_387_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31304&sectionno=387&orderno=443&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_387_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person being a sweeper employed by ^1[^2[the Corporation ]] shall in the absence of any`
  line `contract authorising him so to do and without reasonable cause, resign his employment or absent himself`
  line `from his duty without having given one month's notice to the Commissioner or shall neglect or without`
  line `reasonable cause refuse to perform his duties.`
  line
  line `(2) ^3[^4[The Corporation ]] may by resolution direct that on or from such date as may be specified in the`
  line `resolution, the provisions of this section shall apply in the case of any specified class of persons employed`
  line `by ^1[^2[the Corporation]] whose functions are intimately concerned with public health or safety.`
obj_root_law_sections_387_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “A Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_388:
  sectionId (31305)
  sectionNo (388)
  orderNo 444
  title Omitted..
  content obj_root_law_sections_388_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_388_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31305&sectionno=388&orderno=444&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_388_content:
  string
  line `388. [Conditions of service of sweepers employed for doing house scavenging.] Omitted by the Delhi`
  line `Municipal Corporation (Amendment) Act, 2022 (10 of 2022), s. 9 (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_388_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_389:
  sectionId (31306)
  sectionNo (389)
  orderNo 445
  title `Power to call for information regarding burning and burial grounds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_389_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_389_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31306&sectionno=389&orderno=445&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_389_content:
  string
  line `The Commissioner`
  line `may, by notice in writing, require the owner or person in charge of any burning or burial ground to supply`
  line `such information as may be specified in the notice concerning the condition, management, or position of`
  line `such ground.`
obj_root_law_sections_389_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_390:
  sectionId (31307)
  sectionNo (390)
  orderNo 446
  title `Permission for use of new burning or burial ground.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_390_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_390_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31307&sectionno=390&orderno=446&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_390_content:
  string
  line `(1) No place which has not been used`
  line `as a burning or burial ground before the commencement of this Act shall be so used without the`
  line `permission in writing of the Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(2) Such permission may be granted subject to any conditions which the Commissioner may think fit`
  line `to impose for the purpose of preventing any annoyance to, or danger to the health of, any persons residing`
  line `in the neighbourhood.`
obj_root_law_sections_390_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_391:
  sectionId (31308)
  sectionNo (391)
  orderNo 447
  title `Power to require closing of burning and burial grounds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_391_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_391_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31308&sectionno=391&orderno=447&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_391_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Commissioner, after`
  line `making or causing to be made local enquiry is of opinion that any burning or burial ground has become`
  line `offensive to, or dangerous to the health of, persons residing in the neighbourhood, he may, with the`
  line `previous sanction of the Standing Committee, by notice in writing, require the owner or person in charge`
  line `of such ground to close the same from such date as may be specified in the notice.`
  line
  line `(2) No corpse shall be burnt or buried at the burning or burial ground in respect of which a notice has`
  line `been issued under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_391_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_392:
  sectionId (31309)
  sectionNo (392)
  orderNo 448
  title `Removal of corpses.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_392_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_392_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31309&sectionno=392&orderno=448&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_392_content:
  string
  line `The Commissioner may by public notice prescribe routes by which alone`
  line `corpses may be removed to burning or burial ground.`
obj_root_law_sections_392_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_393:
  sectionId (31310)
  sectionNo (393)
  orderNo 449
  title `Disposal of dead animals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_393_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_393_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31310&sectionno=393&orderno=449&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_393_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever any animal in charge of any person dies, the person`
  line `in charge thereof shall within twenty-four hours either—`
  line
  line `(a) convey the carcass to a place provided or appointed under section 352 for the final disposal of`
  line `the carcasses of dead animals, or`
  line
  line `(b) give notice of the death to the Commissioner whereupon he shall cause the carcass to be`
  line `disposed of.`
  line
  line `(2) In respect of the disposal of the carcass of a dead animal under clause (b) of sub-section (1) the`
  line `Commissioner may charge such fee as he may by public notice prescribe.`
obj_root_law_sections_393_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_394:
  sectionId (31311)
  sectionNo (394)
  orderNo 450
  title `Appointment of Chief Registrar and registrars.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_394_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_394_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31311&sectionno=394&orderno=450&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_394_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Municipal Health Officer shall be`
  line `the Chief Registrar of births and deaths for ^1[^2[Delhi]] and shall keep in such form as may be prescribed by`
  line `bye-laws a register of all births and deaths occurring in ^1[^2[Delhi]].`
  line
  line `(2) The Commissioner shall for the purposes of this Chapter appoint such number of persons to be`
  line `registrars of births and deaths as he deems necessary and define the respective areas which shall be under`
  line `the charge of such registrars.`
obj_root_law_sections_394_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for “Delhi” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “the area of the Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_395:
  sectionId (31312)
  sectionNo (395)
  orderNo 451
  title `Duties of registrar.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_395_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_395_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31312&sectionno=395&orderno=451&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_395_content:
  string
  line `The registrar shall keep himself informed of every birth or death`
  line `occurring within the area under his charge and shall ascertain and register as soon as conveniently may be`
  line `after the event, and without fee or reward such particulars in respect of every birth or death as may be`
  line `prescribed by bye-laws made in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_395_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_396:
  sectionId (31313)
  sectionNo (396)
  orderNo 452
  title `Information of births and deaths.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_396_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_396_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31313&sectionno=396&orderno=452&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_396_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall be the duty of the father or mother of every`
  line `child born in Delhi and in default of the father or mother, of any relation of the child living in the same`
  line `premises, and in default of such relation, of the person having charge of the child, to give to the best of`
  line `his knowledge and belief to the registrar of the area concerned within eight days after such birth,`
  line `information containing such particulars as may be prescribed by bye-laws made in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall be the duty of the nearest relation present at the time of the death or in attendance during`
  line `the last illness of any person dying in Delhi and in default of such relation, of any person present or in`
  line `attendance at the time of the death, and of the occupier of the premises in which to his knowledge the`
  line `death took place and in default of the person hereinbefore mentioned, of each inmate of such premises`
  line `and of the undertaker or other person causing the corpse of the deceased person to be disposed of, to give`
  line `to the best of his knowledge and belief to the registrar of the area within which the death took place`
  line `information containing such particulars as may be prescribed by bye-laws made in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(3) If a birth or death occurs in the hospital, none of the persons mentioned in sub-section (1) or, as`
  line `the case may be, in sub-section (2) shall be bound to give information required by that sub-section, but it`
  line `shall be the duty of the medical officer in charge of the hospital within twenty-four hours after the birth or`
  line `death, to send to the Municipal Health Officer a notice containing such particulars as may be prescribed`
  line `by bye-laws made in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_396_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_397:
  sectionId (31314)
  sectionNo (397)
  orderNo 453
  title `Prohibition of nuisances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_397_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_397_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31314&sectionno=397&orderno=453&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_397_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall--`
  line
  line `(a) in any public street or public place---`
  line
  line `(i) ease himself; or`
  line
  line ^1
  line `* * * * *`
  line
  line `(iv) carry meat exposed to public view; or`
  line
  line `(v) picket animals, or collect carts; or`
  line
  line `(vi) being engaged in the removal of rubbish, filth or other polluted and obnoxious matter`
  line `wilfully or negligently permit any portion thereof to spill or fail, or neglect to sweep away or`
  line `otherwise effectually to remove any portion thereof which may spill or fall in such street or place;`
  line or
  line
  line `(vii) without proper authority affix, upon any building monument, post, wall, fence, tree or`
  line `other thing, any bill, notice or other document; or`
  line
  line `(viii) without proper authority deface or write upon or otherwise mark any building,`
  line `monument, port, wall, fence, tree or other thing; or`
  line
  line `(ix) without proper authority remove, destroy, deface or write upon or otherwise obliterate`
  line `any notice or other document put up or exhibited under this Act or the rules or bye-laws made`
  line `thereunder; or`
  line
  line `(x) without proper authority displace, damage, make any alteration in, or otherwise interfere`
  line `with, the pavement, gutter, storm water-drain, flags or other materials of any such street, or any`
  line `lamp bracket, direction-post, hydrant or water-pipe maintained by ^2[^3[the Corporation]] in any such`
  line `street or place, or extinguish a public light; or`
  line
  line `(xi) carry rubbish, filth or other polluted and obnoxious matter at any hour prohibited by the`
  line `Commissioner by public notice, or in any pattern of cart or receptacle which has not been`
  line `approved for the purpose by the Commissioner, or fail to close such cart or receptacle when in`
  line `use; or`
  line
  line `(b) carry rubbish, filth or other polluted and obnoxious matter along any route in contravention of`
  line `any prohibition made in this behalf by the Commissioner by public notice; or`
  line
  line `(c) deposit or cause or permit to be deposited, earth or materials of any description or any rubbish`
  line `or polluted and obnoxious matter in any place not intended for the purpose in any public street or`
  line `public place or waste or unoccupied land under the management of ^2[^3[the Corporation]]; or`
  line
  line `(d) make any grave or burn or bury any corpse at any place not set apart for such purpose; or`
  line
  line `(e) at any time or place at which the same has been prohibited by the Commissioner by public or`
  line `special notice, beat a drum or tom-tom, or blow a horn or trumpet, or beat any utensil, or sound any`
  line `brass or other instrument, or play any music; or`
  line
  line `(f) disturb the public peace or order by singing, screaming or shouting, or by using any apparatus`
  line `for amplifying or reproducing the human voice, such as a megaphone or a loudspeaker; or`
  line
  line `(g) let loose any animal so as to cause, or negligently allow any animal to cause, injury, danger,`
  line `alarm or annoyance to any person; or`
  line
  line `(h) save with the written permission of the Commissioner and in such manner as he may`
  line `authorise, store or use night-soil, cow dung, manure, rubbish or any other substance emitting an`
  line `offensive smell; or`
  line
  line `(i) use or permit to be used as a latrine any place not intended for that purpose.`
  line
  line `(2) Every person shall take all reasonable means to prevent every child under the age of twelve years`
  line `being in his charge from easing himself in any public street or public place.`
  line
  line `(3) The owner or keeper of any animal shall not allow it straying in a public street or public place`
  line `without a keeper.`
  line
  line `(4) Any animal found straying as aforesaid may be removed by an officer or employee of the`
  line `Corporation or by any police officer to a pound.`
  line
  line `(5)`
  line ^4
  line `[Swine] found straying in a public street or public place shall be liable to be destroyed by any`
  line `officer or other employee of ^2[^3[the Corporation]] appointed in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_397_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Omitted by Act 52 of 1964, s. 3 and the Second Schedule (w.e.f. 29-12-1964).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "a Corporation" (w.e.f.22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 58 of 1960, s. 3 and the Second Schedule, for "Swines" (w.e.f. 26-12-1960).`
obj_root_law_sections_398:
  sectionId (31315)
  sectionNo (398)
  orderNo 454
  title `Power of Commissioner to require removal or abetment of nuisance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_398_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_398_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31315&sectionno=398&orderno=454&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_398_content:
  string
  line `Where the`
  line `Commissioner is of opinion that there is a nuisance on any land or building, he may, by notice in writing,`
  line `require the person by whose act, default or sufferance the nuisance arises or continues or the owner,`
  line `lessee or occupier of the land or building, or any one or more of these persons, to remove or abate the`
  line `nuisance by taking such measures in such manner and within such period as may be specified in the`
  line notice.
obj_root_law_sections_398_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_399:
  sectionId (31316)
  sectionNo (399)
  orderNo 455
  title `Registration and control of dogs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_399_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_399_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31316&sectionno=399&orderno=455&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_399_content:
  string
  line `(1) ^1[^2[The Corporation ]] may, by bye-laws made in this`
  line behalf,--
  line
  line `(a) require the registration, by the registration authority appointed by the Commissioner in this`
  line `behalf of all dogs kept within Delhi;`
  line
  line `(b) require that every registered dog shall wear a collar to which shall be attached a metal token to`
  line `be issued by the registration authority, and fix the fee payable for the issue thereof;`
  line
  line `(c) require that any dog which has not been registered or which is not wearing such token shall, if`
  line `found in any public place, be detained at a place set apart for the purpose; and`
  line
  line `(d) fixed the fee which shall be charged for such detention and provide that any such dog shall be`
  line `liable to be destroyed or otherwise disposed of unless it is claimed and the fee in respect thereof is`
  line `paid within one week.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commissioner may--`
  line
  line `(a) cause to be destroyed, or to be confined for such period as he may direct, any dog or other`
  line `animal which is, or is reasonably suspected to be, suffering from rabies, or which has been bitten by`
  line `any dog or other animal suffering or suspected to be suffering from rabies;`
  line
  line `(b) by public notice direct that, after such date as may be specified in the notice, dogs which are`
  line `without collars or without marks distinguishing them as private property and are found straying on`
  line `the streets or beyond the enclosures of the houses of their owners, if any, may be destroyed and cause`
  line `them to be destroyed accordingly.`
  line
  line `(3) No damages shall be payable in respect of any dog or other animal destroyed or otherwise`
  line `disposed of under this section.`
  line
  line `(4) No one, being the owner or person in charge of any dog, shall allow it to be at large in any public`
  line `street or public place without being muzzled and without being secured by a chain lead in any case in`
  line which---
  line
  line `(a) he knows that the dog is likely to annoy or intimidate any person, or`
  line
  line `(b) the Commissioner has, by public notice during the prevalence of rabies, directed that dogs`
  line `shall not be at large without muzzles and chain leads.`
  line
  line `(5) No one shall--`
  line
  line `(a) allow any ferocious dog which belongs to him or is in his charge to be at large without being`
  line `muzzled, or`
  line
  line `(b) set on or urge any dog or other animal to attack, worry or intimidate any person, or`
  line
  line `(c) knowing or having reason to believe that any dog or animal belonging to him or in his charge`
  line `has been bitten by an animal suffering or reasonably suspected to be suffering from rabies, fail or`
  line `neglect to give immediate information of the fact to the Commissioner or give information which is`
  line false.
obj_root_law_sections_399_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “A Corporation” (w.e.f.22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_400:
  sectionId (31317)
  sectionNo (400)
  orderNo 456
  title `Stacking or collecting inflammable materials.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_400_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_400_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31317&sectionno=400&orderno=456&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_400_content:
  string
  line `The Commissioner may, by public notice,`
  line `prohibit in any case where such prohibition appears to him to be necessary for the prevention of danger to`
  line `life or property, the stacking or collecting of wood, dry grass, straw or other inflammable materials, or the`
  line `placing of mats or thatched huts or the lighting of fires in any place which may be specified in the notice.`
obj_root_law_sections_400_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_401:
  sectionId (31318)
  sectionNo (401)
  orderNo 457
  title `Care of naked lights.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_401_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_401_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31318&sectionno=401&orderno=457&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_401_content:
  string
  line `No person shall set a naked light on or near any building in any public`
  line `street or other public place in such manner as to cause danger of fire:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall be deemed to prohibit the use of lights for the purposes of`
  line `illumination on the occasion of a festival or public or private entertainment.`
obj_root_law_sections_401_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_402:
  sectionId (31319)
  sectionNo (402)
  orderNo 458
  title `Discharging fireworks, fire-arms, etc`
  content obj_root_law_sections_402_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_402_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31319&sectionno=402&orderno=458&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_402_content:
  string
  line `No one shall discharge any fire-arm or let of fireworks or fire-baloons, or engage in any game in such manner as to cause or to be likely to cause danger to`
  line `persons passing by or dwelling or working in the neighbourhood or risk of injury to property.`
obj_root_law_sections_402_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_403:
  sectionId (31320)
  sectionNo (403)
  orderNo 459
  title `Power to require buildings, wells, etc., to be rendered safe.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_403_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_403_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31320&sectionno=403&orderno=459&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_403_content:
  string
  line `Where any building, or wall, or`
  line `anything affixed thereto, or any well, tank, reservoir, pool, depression, or excavation, or any bank or tree,`
  line `is in the opinion of the Commissioner, in a ruinous state, for want of sufficient repairs, protection or`
  line `enclosure, a nuisance or dangerous to persons passing by or dwelling or working in the neighbourhood,`
  line `the Commissioner may by notice in writing require the owner or part-owner or person claiming to be the`
  line `owner or part-owner thereof or failing any of them the occupier thereof to remove the same or may`
  line `require him to repair, protect or enclose the same in such manner as he thinks necessary; and if the danger`
  line `is, in the opinion of the Commissioner, imminent, he shall forthwith take such steps as he thinks`
  line `necessary to avert the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_403_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_404:
  sectionId (31321)
  sectionNo (404)
  orderNo 460
  title `Enclosure of waste land used for improper purposes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_404_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_404_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31321&sectionno=404&orderno=460&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_404_content:
  string
  line `The Commissioner may, by notice in`
  line `writing, require the owner or part-owner, or person claiming to be the owner or part-owner of any land or`
  line `building, or the lessee or the person claiming to be the lessee of any such land which, by reason of disuse`
  line `or disputed ownership or other cause, has remained unoccupied and has become the resort of idle and`
  line `disorderly persons or of persons who have no ostensible means of subsistence or cannot give a`
  line `satisfactory account of themselves or is used for gaming or immoral purposes or otherwise occasions or is`
  line `likely to occasion a nuisance, to secure and enclose the same within such time as may be specified in the`
  line notice.
obj_root_law_sections_404_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_405:
  sectionId (31322)
  sectionNo (405)
  orderNo 461
  title `Provisions of municipal markets and slaughter houses.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_405_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_405_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31322&sectionno=405&orderno=461&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_405_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commissioner, when`
  line `authorised by^1[^2[the Corporation]] in this behalf, may provide and maintain municipal markets and slaughter`
  line `houses in such number as he thinks fit together with stalls, shops, sheds, pens and other buildings and`
  line `conveniences for the use of persons carrying on trade or business in, or frequenting such markets or`
  line `slaughter houses and may provide and maintain in any such markets, buildings and places machines,`
  line `weights, scales and measures for the weighment or measurement of goods sold therein.`
  line
  line `(2) Municipal markets and slaughter houses shall be under the control of the Commissioner who may,`
  line `at any time, by public notice, close any municipal market or slaughter house or any part thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_405_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “A Corporation” (w.e.f.22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_406:
  sectionId (31323)
  sectionNo (406)
  orderNo 462
  title `Use of municipal markets.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_406_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_406_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31323&sectionno=406&orderno=462&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_406_content:
  string
  line `(1) No persons shall, without the general or special permission in`
  line `writing of the Commissioner, sell or expose for sale any animal or article in any municipal market.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person contravening the provisions of sub-section (1), and any animal or article exposed for`
  line `sale by such person, may be summarily removed from the market by or under the orders of the`
  line `Commissioner or any officer or employee of ^1[^2[the Corporation ]] authorised by the Commissioner in this`
  line behalf.
obj_root_law_sections_406_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “A Corporation” (w.e.f.22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_407:
  sectionId (31324)
  sectionNo (407)
  orderNo 463
  title `Private markets and slaughter houses.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_407_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_407_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31324&sectionno=407&orderno=463&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_407_content:
  string
  line `(1) No place other than a municipal market shall be`
  line `used as a market unless such place has been licensed as a market by the Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(2) No place other than a municipal slaughter house shall be used as a slaughter house:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall be deemed--`
  line
  line `(a) to restrict the slaughter of any animal in any place on the occasion of any religious festival or`
  line `ceremony, subject to such conditions (non-compliance with which shall be punishable under this Act)`
  line `as the Commissioner may, by public or special notice, impose in this behalf, or`
  line
  line `(b) to prevent the Commissioner, with the sanction of ^1[^2[the Corporation]], from setting apart places`
  line `for the slaughter of animals in accordance with religious custom.`
obj_root_law_sections_407_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “A Corporation” (w.e.f.22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_408:
  sectionId (31325)
  sectionNo (408)
  orderNo 464
  title `Conditions of grant of licence for private market.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_408_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_408_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31325&sectionno=408&orderno=464&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_408_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commissioner may charge such`
  line `fees as he thinks fit to impose for the grant of a licence to any person to open a private market and may`
  line `grant such licence subject to such conditions, consistent with this Act and any bye-laws made thereunder,`
  line `as he thinks fit to impose.`
  line
  line `(2) When the Commissioner refuses to grant any licence, he shall record a brief statement of the`
  line `reasons for such refusal.`
  line
  line `(3) The Commissioner may, with the previous approval of the Standing Committee and for reasons to`
  line `be recorded, suspend a licence in respect of a private market for such period as he thinks fit or cancel such`
  line licence.
  line
  line `(4) A private market of which the licence has been suspended or cancelled as aforesaid shall be closed`
  line `with effect from such date as may be specified in the order of suspension or cancellation.`
obj_root_law_sections_408_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_409:
  sectionId (31326)
  sectionNo (409)
  orderNo 465
  title `Prohibition of keeping market open without licence, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_409_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_409_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31326&sectionno=409&orderno=465&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_409_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall keep open for`
  line `public use any market in respect of which a licence is required by or under this Act without obtaining a`
  line `licence therefor, or while the licence therefor is suspended or after the same has been cancelled.`
  line
  line `(2) When a licence to open a private market is granted or refused or is suspended or cancelled the`
  line `Commissioner shall cause a notice of the grant, refusal, suspension or cancellation to be posted in such`
  line `language or languages as he thinks necessary in some conspicuous place by or near the entrance to the`
  line `place to which the notice relates.`
obj_root_law_sections_409_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_410:
  sectionId (31327)
  sectionNo (410)
  orderNo 466
  title `Prohibition of use of un licenced markets.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_410_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_410_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31327&sectionno=410&orderno=466&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_410_content:
  string
  line `No person knowing that any market has been`
  line `opened to the public without a licence having been obtained therefor when such licence is required by or`
  line `under this Act or that the licence granted therefor is for the time being suspended or that it has been`
  line `cancelled, shall sell or expose for sale any animal or article in such market.`
obj_root_law_sections_410_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_411:
  sectionId (31328)
  sectionNo (411)
  orderNo 467
  title `Prohibition of business and trade near a market.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_411_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_411_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31328&sectionno=411&orderno=467&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_411_content:
  string
  line `(1) No animal or article shall be sold or`
  line `exposed for sale within a distance of one hundred yards of any municipal market or licensed private`
  line `market without the permission of the Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person contravening the provisions of sub-section (1) and any animal or article exposed for`
  line `sale by such person may be summarily removed by or under the orders of the Commissioner or any`
  line `officer or employee of ^1[^2[the Corporation]] appointed by him in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_411_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012)..`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “A Corporation” (w.e.f.22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_412:
  sectionId (31329)
  sectionNo (412)
  orderNo 468
  title `Levy of stallages, rents and fees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_412_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_412_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31329&sectionno=412&orderno=468&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_412_content:
  string
  line `The Commissioner, with the previous approval of the`
  line `Standing Committee, may—`
  line
  line `(a) charge such stallages, rents or fees as may from time to time be fixed by him in this behalf—`
  line
  line `(i) for the occupation or use of any stall, shop, stand, shed or pen in a municipal market or`
  line `municipal slaughter house;`
  line
  line `(ii) for the right to expose articles for sale in a municipal market;`
  line
  line `(iii) for the use of machines, weights, scales and measures provided for in any municipal market; and`
  line
  line `(iv) for the right to slaughter animals in any municipal slaughter house, and for the feed of such`
  line `animals before they are ready for slaughter; or`
  line
  line `(b) farm the stallages, rents and fees chargeable as aforesaid or any portion thereof for such`
  line `period as he may think fit; or`
  line
  line `(c) put up to public auction or dispose of by private sale, the privilege of occupying or using any`
  line `stall, shop, stand, shed or pen in a municipal market or municipal slaughter house for such period and`
  line `on such conditions as he may think fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_412_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_413:
  sectionId (31330)
  sectionNo (413)
  orderNo 469
  title `Stallages, rents, etc., to be published`
  content obj_root_law_sections_413_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_413_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31330&sectionno=413&orderno=469&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_413_content:
  string
  line `A copy of the table of stallages, rents and fees, if any,`
  line `chargeable in any municipal market or municipal slaughter house, and of the bye-laws made under this`
  line `Act for the purpose of regulating the use of such market or slaughter house printed in such language or`
  line `languages as the Commissioner may direct, shall be affixed in same conspicuous place in the market or`
  line `slaughter house.`
obj_root_law_sections_413_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_414:
  sectionId (31331)
  sectionNo (414)
  orderNo 470
  title `Power to expel lepers and disturbers, etc. from markets.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_414_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_414_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31331&sectionno=414&orderno=470&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_414_content:
  string
  line `The person in charge of a market`
  line `shall prevent the entry therein of, and shall expel therefrom, any person suffering from leprosy in whom`
  line `the process of ulceration has commenced or from any dangerous disease, who sells or exposes for sale`
  line `therein any article or who, not having purchased the same handles any articles exposed for sale therein;`
  line `and he may expel therefrom any person whom is creating a disturbance therein.`
obj_root_law_sections_414_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_415:
  sectionId (31332)
  sectionNo (415)
  orderNo 471
  title `Butcher's, fish-monger's and poulter's licence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_415_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_415_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31332&sectionno=415&orderno=471&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_415_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall without or otherwise`
  line `than in conformity with a licence from the Commissioner carry on the trade of a butcher, fish-monger,`
  line `poulterer or importer of flesh intended for human food or use any place for the sale of flesh, fish or`
  line `poultry intended for human food:`
  line
  line `Provided that no licence shall be required for any place used for the sale or storage for sale of`
  line `preserved flesh or fish contained in airtight or hermetically sealed receptacles.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commissioner may by order and subject to such conditions as to supervision and inspection`
  line `as he thinks fit to impose grant a licence or may by order refuse for reasons to be recorded, to grant the`
  line same.
  line
  line `(3) Every such licence shall expire at the end of the year for which it is granted or at such earlier date`
  line `as the Commissioner may, for special reasons, specify in the licence.`
  line
  line `(4) If any place is used for the sale of flesh, fish or poultry in contravention of the provisions of this`
  line `section, the Commissioner may stop the use thereof by such means as he may consider necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_415_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_416:
  sectionId (31333)
  sectionNo (416)
  orderNo 472
  title `Factory, etc., not to be established without permission of the Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_416_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_416_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31333&sectionno=416&orderno=472&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_416_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person`
  line `shall, without the previous permission in writing of the Commissioner, establish in any premises, or`
  line `materially alter, enlarge or extend, any factory, workshop or trade premises in which it is intended to`
  line `employ steam, electricity, water or other mechanical power.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commissioner may refuse to give such permission, if he is of the opinion that the`
  line `establishment, alteration, enlargement or extension of such factory, workshop or trade premises, in the`
  line `proposed position would be objectionable by reason of the density of the population in the neighbourhood`
  line `thereof, or would be a nuisance to the inhabitants of the neighbourhood.`
obj_root_law_sections_416_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_417:
  sectionId (31334)
  sectionNo (417)
  orderNo 473
  title `Premises not to be used for certain purposes without licence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_417_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_417_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31334&sectionno=417&orderno=473&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_417_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall use or`
  line `permit to be used any premises for any of the following purposes without or otherwise than in conformity`
  line `with the terms of a licence granted by the Commissioner in this behalf, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) any of the purposes specified in Part I of the Eleventh Schedule;`
  line
  line `(b) any purpose which is, in the opinion of the Commissioner dangerous to life, health or property`
  line `or likely to create a nuisance;`
  line
  line `(c) keeping horses, cattle or other quardruped animals or birds for transportation, sale or hire or`
  line `for sale of the produce thereof; or`
  line
  line `(d) storing any of the articles specified in Part II of the Eleventh Schedule except for domestic use`
  line `of any those article's:`
  line
  line `Provided that ^1[^2[the Corporation]] may declare that premises in which the aggregate quantity of articles`
  line `stored for sale does not exceed such quantity as may be prescribed by bye-laws in respect of any such`
  line `articles shall be exempted from the operation of clause (d).`
  line
  line `(2) In prescribing the terms of a licence granted under this section for the use of premises as mills or`
  line `iron yards or for similar purposes the Commissioner may, when he thinks fit, require the licensee to`
  line `provide a space or passage within the premises for carts for loading and unloading purposes.`
  line
  line `(3) ^3[^4[The Corporation]] shall fix a scale of fees to be paid in respect of premises licensed under subsection (1):`
  line
  line ^5****.
obj_root_law_sections_417_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f.22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “A Corporation” (w.e.f.22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `5. Proviso omitted by Act 7 of 2004, s. 5 (w.e.f. 7-12-2004).`
obj_root_law_sections_418:
  sectionId (31335)
  sectionNo (418)
  orderNo 474
  title `Seizure of certain animals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_418_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_418_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31335&sectionno=418&orderno=474&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_418_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any horses, cattle or other quadruped animals or birds are`
  line `kept on any premises in contravention of the provisions of section 417, or are found abandoned and`
  line `roaming or tethered on any street or public place or on any land belonging to the Corporation, the`
  line `Commissioner or any officer empowered by him may seize them and may cause them to be impounded or`
  line `removed to such place as may be appointed by the Government or the Corporation for this purpose and`
  line `the cost of seizure of these animals or birds and of impounding or removing them and of feeding and`
  line `watering them shall be recoverable by sale by auction of these animals or birds:`
  line
  line `Provided that anyone claiming such animal or bird may, within seven days of the seizure get them`
  line `released on his paying all expenses incurred by the Commissioner in seizing, impounding or removing`
  line `and in feeding and watering such animal or bird, and on his producing a licence for keeping these animals`
  line `and birds issued under the provisions of section 417.`
  line
  line `(2) Whenever the Commissioner is of opinion that the user of any premises for any of the purposes`
  line `referred to in sub-section (1) of section 417 is causing a nuisance and such nuisance should be`
  line `immediately stopped, the Commissioner may order the owner or the occupier of the premises to stop such`
  line `nuisance within such time as may be specified in the order and in the event of the failure of the owner or`
  line `occupier to comply with such order, the Commissioner may himself or by an officer subordinate to him`
  line `cause such user to be stopped.`
  line
  line `(3) Without prejudice to the foregoing provisions of this section any person by whom or at whose`
  line `instance any horses, cattle or other quadruped animals or birds are so kept, abandoned or tethered, shall`
  line `also be punishable under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_418_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_419:
  sectionId (31336)
  sectionNo (419)
  orderNo 475
  title `Power of Commissioner to prevent use of premises in particular areas for purposes referred to in section 417.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_419_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_419_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31336&sectionno=419&orderno=475&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_419_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commissioner may give public notice of his intention to declare`
  line `that in any area specified in the notice no person shall use any premises for any of the purposes referred to`
  line `in sub-section (1) of section 417, which may be specified in such notice.`
  line
  line `(2) No objections to any such declarations shall be received after a period of one month from the`
  line `publication of the notice.`
  line
  line `(3) The Commissioner shall consider all objections received within the said period, giving any person`
  line `affected by the notice an opportunity of being heard during such consideration, and may thereupon make`
  line `a declaration in accordance with the notice published under sub-section (1), with such modifications, if`
  line `any, as he may think fit but not so as to extend its application.`
  line
  line `(4) Every such declaration shall be published in the Official Gazette and in such other manner as the`
  line `Commissioner may determine, and shall take effect from the date of its publication in the Official`
  line Gazette.
  line
  line `(5) No person shall, in any area specified in any declaration published under sub-section (4), use any`
  line `premises for any of the purposes referred to in section 417 specified in the declaration and the`
  line `Commissioner shall have the power to stop the use of any such premises by such means as he considers`
  line necessary.
obj_root_law_sections_419_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_420:
  sectionId (31337)
  sectionNo (420)
  orderNo 476
  title `Licences for hawking articles, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_420_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_420_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31337&sectionno=420&orderno=476&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_420_content:
  string
  line `No person shall, without or otherwise than in conformity`
  line `with the terms of a licence granted by the Commissioner in this behalf,—`
  line
  line `(a) hawk or expose for sale in any place any article whatsoever whether it be for human`
  line `consumption or not;`
  line
  line `(b) use in any place his skill in any handicraft or for rendering services to and for the convenience`
  line `of the public for the purposes of gain or making a living.`
obj_root_law_sections_420_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_421:
  sectionId (31338)
  sectionNo (421)
  orderNo 477
  title `Eating houses, etc., not to be used without licence from the Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_421_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_421_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31338&sectionno=421&orderno=477&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_421_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person`
  line `shall, without or otherwise than in conformity with the terms of a licence granted by the Commissioner in`
  line `this behalf, keep any eating house, lodging house, hotel, boarding house, tea shop, coffee house, cafe,`
  line `restaurant, refreshment room or any place where the public are admitted for repose or for the consumption`
  line `of any food or drink or any place where food is sold or prepared for sale.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commissioner may at any time cancel or suspend any licence granted under sub-section (1) if`
  line `he is of the opinion that the premises covered thereby are not kept in conformity with the conditions of`
  line `such licence or with the provisions of any bye-law made in this behalf whether the licensee is prosecuted`
  line `under this Act or not.`
obj_root_law_sections_421_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_422:
  sectionId (31339)
  sectionNo (422)
  orderNo 478
  title `Licensing and control of theatres, circuses and places of public amusement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_422_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_422_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31339&sectionno=422&orderno=478&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_422_content:
  string
  line `No person`
  line `shall, without or otherwise than in confirmity with the terms of a licence granted by the Commissioner in`
  line `this behalf, keep open any theatre, circus, cinema house, dancing hall or other similar place of public`
  line `resort, recreation or amusement:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall apply to private performances in any such place.`
obj_root_law_sections_422_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_423:
  sectionId (31340)
  sectionNo (423)
  orderNo 479
  title `Power of Commissioner to stop use of premises used in contravention of licences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_423_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_423_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31340&sectionno=423&orderno=479&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_423_content:
  string
  line `If the`
  line `Commissioner is of opinion that any eating House, lodging house, hotel, boarding house, tea shop, coffee`
  line `house, cafe, restaurant, refreshment room or other place where the public are admitted for repose or for`
  line `consumption of any food or drink or where food is sold or prepared for sale or any theatre, circus, cinema`
  line `house, dancing hall or similar other place of public resort, recreation or amusement is kept open without a`
  line `licence or otherwise than in conformity with the terms of a licence granted in respect thereof, he may stop`
  line `the use of any such premises for any such purpose for a specified period by such means as he may`
  line `consider necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_423_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_424:
  sectionId (31341)
  sectionNo (424)
  orderNo 480
  title `Power of Commissioner to inspect places where unlawful slaughter of animals, etc., is suspected.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_424_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_424_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31341&sectionno=424&orderno=480&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_424_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Commissioner or any person authorised by him in this behalf has reason to believe`
  line `that any animal intended for human consumption is being slaughtered or that the flesh of any such animal`
  line `is being sold or exposed for sale, in any place or manner not duly authorised under this Act, he may, at`
  line `any time by day or night without notice, inspect such place for the purpose of satisfying himself as to`
  line `whether any provision of this Act or of any bye-law under this Act at the time in force is being`
  line `contravened thereat and may seize any such animal or the carcass of such animal or such flesh found`
  line therein.
  line
  line `(2) The Commissioner may remove and sell by auction or otherwise dispose of any animal or carcass`
  line `of any animal or any flesh seized under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) If within one month of such seizure the owner of the animal, carcass or flesh face to appear and`
  line `prove his claim to the satisfaction of the Commissioner or if the owner is convicted of an offence under`
  line `this Act in respect of such animal, carcass or flesh, the proceeds of any sale under sub-section (1) shall`
  line `vest in ^1[^2[the Corporation]].`
  line
  line `(4) Any person slaughtering any animal or selling or exposing for sale the flesh of any such animal in`
  line `any place or manner not duly authorised under the provisions of this Act may be arrested by any police`
  line `officer without a warrant.`
  line
  line `(5) No claim shall lie against any person for compensation for any damage necessarily caused by any`
  line `such entry or by the use of any force necessary for affecting such entry.`
obj_root_law_sections_424_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f.22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_425:
  sectionId (31342)
  sectionNo (425)
  orderNo 481
  title `Improvement scheme.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_425_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_425_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31342&sectionno=425&orderno=481&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_425_content:
  string
  line `Where the Commissioner upon information in his possession is`
  line `satisfied as respects any area—`
  line
  line `(a) that the buildings in that area are by reason or disrepair or sanitary defects unfit for human`
  line `habitation or are by reason of their bad arrangement, or the narrowness or bad arrangement of the`
  line `streets or the want of light, air, ventilation of proper conveniences, dangerous or injurious to the`
  line `health of the inhabitants of the area; and`
  line
  line `(b) that the most satisfactory method of dealing with the conditions in the area is the rearrangement and reconstruction of the streets and buildings in the area in accordance with an`
  line `improvement scheme, he may frame an improvement scheme in respect of the area in accordance`
  line `with the bye-laws made in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_425_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_426:
  sectionId (31343)
  sectionNo (426)
  orderNo 482
  title `Matters to be provided for in an improvement scheme.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_426_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for “Central Government” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31343&sectionno=426&orderno=482&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_426_content:
  string
  line `(1) An improvement scheme may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:`
  line
  line `(a) the acquisition by agreement or under the Land Acquisition Act, 1894 (1 of 1894), of any`
  line `property necessary for or affected by the execution of the scheme;`
  line
  line `(b) the relaying out of any land comprised in the scheme;`
  line
  line `(c) the redistribution of sites belonging to owners of property comprised in the scheme;`
  line
  line `(d) the closure or demolition of buildings or portions of buildings unfit for human habitation;`
  line
  line `(e) the demotion of obstructive buildings or portions thereof;`
  line
  line `(f) the construction and reconstruction of buildings;`
  line
  line `(g) the construction and alteration of streets;`
  line
  line `(h) the water supply, street lighting, drainage and other conveniences;`
  line
  line `(i) the provision of open spaces for the benefit of any area comprised in the scheme;`
  line
  line `(j) the sanitary arrangements required for the area comprised in the scheme;`
  line
  line `(k) the provision of accommodation for any class of the inhabitants;`
  line
  line `(l) the provision of facilities for communication;`
  line
  line `(m) the sale, letting or exchange of any property comprised in the scheme;`
  line
  line `(n) any other matter for which, in the opinion of the Commissioner it is expedient to make`
  line `provision with a view to the improvement of the area to which the scheme relates.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any land is designated in an improvement scheme as subject to acquisition or is required`
  line `by the scheme to be kept as an open space, then, if at the expiration of ten years from the date of sanction`
  line `of the scheme by the ^1[Government] under sub-section (2) of section 427, the land is not acquired by`
  line `the Commissioner, the owner of the land may serve on the Commissioner a notice requiring his interest in`
  line `the land to be so acquired.`
  line
  line `(3) If the Commissioner fails to acquire the land with a period of six months from the receipt of the`
  line `notice, the improvement scheme shall have effect after the expiration of the said six months as if the land`
  line `were not designated as subject to acquisition by the Commissioner or were not required to be kept as an`
  line `open space.`
obj_root_law_sections_427:
  sectionId (31344)
  sectionNo (427)
  orderNo 483
  title `Submission of improvement scheme to the Corporation for approval and to the Central Government for sanction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_427_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_427_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31344&sectionno=427&orderno=483&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_427_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every improvement scheme shall, as soon as may be after it has been`
  line `framed, be submitted by the Commissioner for approval to the Corporation and ^1[^2[the Corporation ]] may either approve the scheme without modifications or with such modifications as it may consider necessary`
  line `or reject the scheme with directions to the Commissioner to have a fresh scheme framed according to`
  line `such directions.`
  line
  line `(2) No improvement scheme approved by ^1[^2[the Corporation]] under sub-section (1) shall be valid unless`
  line `it has been sanctioned by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_427_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_428:
  sectionId (31345)
  sectionNo (428)
  orderNo 484
  title `Rehousing scheme.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_428_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_428_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31345&sectionno=428&orderno=484&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_428_content:
  string
  line `The Commissioner while framing an improvement scheme under this`
  line `Chapter for any area may also frame a scheme (hereafter in this Act referred to as the rehousing scheme)`
  line `for the construction, maintenance and management of such and so many buildings as he may consider`
  line `necessary for providing accommodation for persons who are likely to be displaced by the execution of the`
  line `improvement scheme.`
obj_root_law_sections_428_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_429:
  sectionId (31346)
  sectionNo (429)
  orderNo 485
  title `Improvement scheme and rehousing scheme to comply with the master plan and zonal development plan.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_429_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_429_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31346&sectionno=429&orderno=485&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_429_content:
  string
  line `No improvement scheme or rehousing scheme framed under this Chapter after a`
  line `master plan for Delhi or a zonal development plan for any part thereof has been prepared in accordance`
  line `with law shall be valid unless such scheme is in conformity with the provisions of the master plan or the`
  line `zonal development plan.`
obj_root_law_sections_429_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_430:
  sectionId (31347)
  sectionNo (430)
  orderNo 486
  title `Signature, conditions, duration, suspension, revocation, etc., of licences and written permissions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_430_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_430_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31347&sectionno=430&orderno=486&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_430_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever it is provided in this Act or any bye-law made thereunder that a licence or a`
  line `written permission may be granted for any purpose, such licence or written permission shall be signed by`
  line `the Commissioner or by the officer empowered to grant the same under this Act or the bye-laws made`
  line `thereunder or by any municipal officer authorised by the Commissioner or such officer in this behalf and`
  line `shall specify in addition to any other matter required to be specified under any other provision of this Act`
  line `or any provision of any bye-law made thereunder--`
  line
  line `(a) the date of the grant thereof;`
  line
  line `(b) the purpose and the period (if any) for which it is granted;`
  line
  line `(c) restrictions or conditions, if any, subject to which it is granted;`
  line
  line `(d) the name and address of the person to whom it is granted; and`
  line
  line `(e) the fee, if any, paid for the licence or written permission.`
  line
  line `(2) Except as otherwise provided in this Act or any bye-law made thereunder, for every such licence`
  line `or written permission a fee may be charged at such rate as may from time to time be fixed by the`
  line `Commissioner with the sanction of ^1[^2[the Corporation]] and such fee shall be payable by the person to whom`
  line `the licence or written permission is granted.`
  line
  line `(3) Save as otherwise provided in this Act or any bye-law made thereunder any licence or written`
  line `permission granted under this Act or any bye-law made thereunder may at any time be suspended or`
  line `revoked by the Commissioner or by the officer by whom it was granted, if he is satisfied that it has been`
  line `secured by the grantee through misrepresentation or fraud or if any of its restrictions or conditions has`
  line `been infringed or evaded by the grantee, or if the grantee has been convicted for the contravention of any`
  line `of the provisions of this Act or any bye-law made thereunder relating to any matter for which the licence`
  line `or permission has been granted.`
  line
  line `Provided that--`
  line
  line `(a) before making any order of suspension or revocation reasonable opportunity should be`
  line `accorded to the grantee of the licence or the written permission to show cause why it should not be`
  line `suspended or revoked;`
  line
  line `(b) every such order shall contain a brief statement of the reasons for the suspension or revocation`
  line `of the licence or the written permission.`
  line
  line `(4) When any such licence or written permission is suspended or revoked, or when the period for`
  line `which the same was granted has expired, the grantee shall, for all purposes of this Act or any bye-law`
  line `made thereunder, be deemed to be without a licence or written permission until such time as the order`
  line `suspending or revoking the licence or written permission is rescinded or until the licence or written`
  line `permission is renewed.`
  line
  line `(5) Every grantee of any licence or written permission granted under this Act shall at all reasonable`
  line `times, while such licence or written permission remains in force, if so required by the Commissioner or`
  line `the authority by whom it was granted, produce such licence or written permission.`
obj_root_law_sections_430_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_431:
  sectionId (31348)
  sectionNo (431)
  orderNo 487
  title `Powers of entry and inspection.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_431_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_431_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31348&sectionno=431&orderno=487&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_431_content:
  string
  line `The Commissioner, ^1`
  line `*** ^2`
  line `*** or any municipal officer or`
  line `other municipal employee authorised in this behalf by ^3`
  line `[him] or empowered in this behalf, by or under`
  line `any provision of this Act, may enter into or upon any land or building with or without assistants and`
  line workmen—
  line
  line `(a) for the purpose of ascertaining whether there is or has been on or in connection with the land`
  line `or building any contravention of the provisions of this Act or any bye-law made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(b) for the purpose of ascertaining whether or not circumstances exist which would authorise or`
  line `require the Commissioner, ^1`
  line `*** ^2`
  line `*** or any municipal officer or employee authorised or empowered`
  line `in this behalf to take any action or execute any work under this Act or any bye-law made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(c) for the purpose of taking any action or executing any work authorised or required by this Act`
  line `or any bye-law made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(d) to make any inquiry, inspection, examination, measurement, valuation or survey authorised or`
  line `required by or under this Act or necessary for the proper administration of this Act;`
  line
  line `(e) generally for the purpose of efficient discharge of the functions by any of the municipal`
  line `authorised under this Act or any bye-law made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_431_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words and brackets "the General Manager (Electricity)" omitted by Act 67 of 1993, s. 102 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `2. The words and brackets "or the General Manager (Transport)" omitted by Act 71 of 1971, s. 7(b) and the Second`
  line `Schedule (w.e.f. 3-11-1971).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 102, for "any of the aforesaid municipal authorities" (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_432:
  sectionId (31349)
  sectionNo (432)
  orderNo 488
  title `Power to enter land adjoining land in relation to any work.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_432_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_432_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31349&sectionno=432&orderno=488&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_432_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line ^1
  line `[The Commissioner or any`
  line `person authorised by him in this behalf or empowered in this behalf] by or under any provision of this`
  line `Act, may enter on any land within fifty yards of any work authorised by or under this Act, with or without`
  line `assistants and workmen for the purpose of depositing thereon any soil, gravel, stone or other materials or`
  line `for obtaining access to such work or for any other purposes connected with the execution of the same.`
  line
  line `(2) The person so authorised shall, before entering on any such land, state the purpose thereof, and`
  line `shall, if so required by the owner or occupier thereof, fence off so much of the land as may be required for`
  line `such purpose.`
  line
  line `(3) The person so authorised shall, in exercising any power conferred by this section, do as little`
  line `damage as may be, and compensation shall be payable by ^2[^3[the Corporation]] in accordance with bye-laws`
  line `made in this behalf to the owner or occupier of such land or to both for any such damage, whether`
  line `permanent or temporary.`
obj_root_law_sections_432_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 103, ibid., for certain words (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_433:
  sectionId (31350)
  sectionNo (433)
  orderNo 489
  title `Breaking into buildings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_433_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_433_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31350&sectionno=433&orderno=489&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_433_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall be lawful for ^1`
  line `[the Commissioner or any person`
  line `authorised by him in this behalf or empowered in this behalf] by or, under any provision of this Act, to`
  line `make any entry into any place, and to open or cause to be opened any door, gate or other barrier—`
  line
  line `(a) if he considers the opening thereof necessary for the purpose of such entry; and`
  line
  line `(b) if the owner or occupier is absent or being present refuses to open such door, gate or barrier.`
  line
  line `(2) Before making any entry into any such place or opening or causing to be opened any such door,`
  line `gate or other barrier, the Commissioner, ^2`
  line `*** ^3`
  line `*** or the person authorised or empowered in this behalf,`
  line `shall call upon two or more respectable in habitants of the locality in which the place to be entered into is`
  line `situate, to witness the entry or opening and may issue an order in writing to them or any of them so to do.`
  line
  line `(3) A report shall be made to the Standing Committee as soon as may be after any entry has been`
  line `made into any place or any door, gate or other barrier has been opened under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_433_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 104, ibid., for certain words (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `2. The words and brackets ", the General Manager (Electricity)" omitted by Act 67 of 1993, s. 104 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `3. The words and brackets "or the General Manager (Transport)" omitted by Act 71 of 1971, s. 7(b) and the Second`
  line `Schedule (w.e.f. 3-11-1971).`
obj_root_law_sections_434:
  sectionId (31351)
  sectionNo (434)
  orderNo 490
  title `Time of making entry.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_434_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_434_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31351&sectionno=434&orderno=490&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_434_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise provided in this Act or any bye-law made`
  line `thereunder, no entry authorised by or under this Act shall be made except between the hours of sunrise`
  line `and sunset.`
obj_root_law_sections_434_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_435:
  sectionId (31352)
  sectionNo (435)
  orderNo 491
  title `Consent ordinarily to be obtained.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_435_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_435_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31352&sectionno=435&orderno=491&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_435_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise provided in this Act or any bye-law`
  line `made thereunder, no land or building shall be entered without the consent of the occupier, or if there is no`
  line `occupier, of the owner thereof and no such entry shall be made without giving the said owner or occupier,`
  line `as the case may be, not less than twenty-four hours written notice of the intention to make such entry:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such notice shall be necessary if the place to be inspected is a factory or workshop or`
  line `trade premises or a place used for any of the purposes specified in section 417 or a stable for horses or a`
  line `shed for cattle or a latrine or urinal or a work under construction, or for the purpose of ascertaining`
  line `whether any animal intended for human food is slaughtered in that place in contravention of this Act or`
  line `any bye-law made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_435_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_436:
  sectionId (31353)
  sectionNo (436)
  orderNo 492
  title `Regard to be had to social or religious usages.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_436_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_436_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31353&sectionno=436&orderno=492&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_436_content:
  string
  line `When any place used as a human dwelling is`
  line `entered under this Act, due regard shall be paid to the social and religious customs and usages of the`
  line `occupants of the place entered, and no apartment in the actual occupancy of a female shall be entered or`
  line `broken open until she has been informed that she is at liberty to withdraw and every reasonable facility`
  line `has been afforded to her for withdrawing.`
obj_root_law_sections_436_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_437:
  sectionId (31354)
  sectionNo (437)
  orderNo 493
  title `Prohibition of obstruction or molestation in execution of work.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_437_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_437_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31354&sectionno=437&orderno=493&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_437_content:
  string
  line `No person shall obstract or`
  line `molest any person authorised or empowered by or under this Act or any person with whom ^1[^2[ the`
  line `Corporation]] or any of the municipal authorities specified in section 44 has lawfully contracted, in the`
  line `execution of his duty or of anything which he is authorised or empowered or required to do by virtue or`
  line `inconsequence of any of the provisions of this Act or any bye-law made thereunder, or in fulfilment of his`
  line `contract, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_437_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_438:
  sectionId (31355)
  sectionNo (438)
  orderNo 494
  title `Public notices how to be made known.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_438_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_438_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31355&sectionno=438&orderno=494&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_438_content:
  string
  line `Every public notice given under this Act or any byelaw made thereunder shall be in writing under the signature of ^1`
  line `[the Commissioner or of any municipal`
  line `officer authorised by him in this behalf] and shall be widely made known in the locality to be affected`
  line `thereby by affixing copies thereof in conspicuous public places within the said locality or by publishing`
  line `the same by beat of drum or by advertisement in local newspaper or by any two or more of these means`
  line `and by any other means that the ^2`
  line `[Commissioner] may think fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_438_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 105, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 105, ibid., for "appropriate municipal authority" (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_439:
  sectionId (31356)
  sectionNo (439)
  orderNo 495
  title `Newspaper in which advertisements or notices to be published.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_439_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_439_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31356&sectionno=439&orderno=495&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_439_content:
  string
  line `Whenever it is provided by`
  line `this Act or any bye-law made thereunder that notice shall be given by advertisement in local newspapers,`
  line `or that a notification or information shall be published in local newspapers, such notice, notification or`
  line `information shall be inserted, if practicable, in at least three newspapers in such languages as ^1[^2[the Corporation]] may from time to time specify in this behalf:`
  line
  line `Provided that if ^1[^2[the Corporation]] publishers a municipal journal, a publication in that journal shall be`
  line `deemed to be a publication in a newspaper of the language in which the said journal may be published.`
obj_root_law_sections_439_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_440:
  sectionId (31357)
  sectionNo (440)
  orderNo 496
  title `Proof of consent etc., of Commissioner, General Managers, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_440_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 106, for certain words and brackets (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31357&sectionno=440&orderno=496&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_440_content:
  string
  line `Whenever under this Act`
  line `or any rule, regulation or bye-law made thereunder, the doing of, or the omission to do, anything or the`
  line `validity of anything depends upon the approval, sanction, consent, concurrence, declaration, opinion or`
  line `satisfaction of the Commissioner ^1`
  line `[or of any municipal officer, a written document signed by the`
  line `Commissioner] or officer purporting to convey or set forth such approval, sanction, consent, concurrence,`
  line `declaration, opinion or satisfaction, shall be sufficient evidence thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_441:
  sectionId (31358)
  sectionNo (441)
  orderNo 497
  title `Notices, etc., to fix reasonable time.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_441_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_441_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31358&sectionno=441&orderno=497&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_441_content:
  string
  line `Where any notice, bill, order or requisition issued or`
  line `made under this Act or any rule, regulation or bye-law made thereunder requires anything to be done for`
  line `the doing of which no time is fixed in this Act or the rule, regulation or bye-law, the notice, bill, order or`
  line `requisition shall specify a reasonable time for doing the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_441_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_442:
  sectionId (31359)
  sectionNo (442)
  orderNo 498
  title `Signature on notices, etc., may be stamped`
  content obj_root_law_sections_442_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 107, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31359&sectionno=442&orderno=498&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_442_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[(1) Every licence, written permission, notice,`
  line `bill, summons or other document which is required by this Act or any rule, regulation or bye-law made`
  line `thereunder to bear the signature of the Commissioner or of any municipal officer, shall be deemed to be`
  line `properly signed if it bears a fascimile of the signature of the Commissioner or officer, as the case may be,`
  line `stamped thereupon.]`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in sub-section (1) shall be deemed to apply to a cheque drawn upon the Municipal Fund`
  line `under section 101.`
obj_root_law_sections_443:
  sectionId (31360)
  sectionNo (443)
  orderNo 499
  title `Notices, etc., by whom to be served or issued.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_443_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 108, for certain words and brackets (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31360&sectionno=443&orderno=499&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_443_content:
  string
  line `All notices, bills, summonses and other`
  line `documents required by this Act or any rule, regulation or bye-law made thereunder to be served upon, or`
  line `issued to, any person, shall be served or issued by municipal officers or other municipal employees or by`
  line `other persons authorised by ^1`
  line `[the Commissioner].`
obj_root_law_sections_444:
  sectionId (31361)
  sectionNo (444)
  orderNo 500
  title `Service of notices, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_444_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_444_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31361&sectionno=444&orderno=500&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_444_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every notice, bill, summons, order, requisition or other document`
  line `required or authorised by this Act or any rule, regulation or bye-law made thereunder to be served or`
  line `issued by or on behalf of ^1[^2[the Corporation]], or by any of the municipal authorities specified in section 44 or`
  line `any municipal officer, on any person shall, save as otherwise provided in this Act or such rule, regulation`
  line `or bye-law, be deemed to be duly served--`
  line
  line `(a) where the person to be served is a company, if the document is addressed to the secretary of`
  line `the company at its registered office or at its principal office or place of the business and is either---`
  line
  line `(i) sent by registered post, or`
  line
  line `(ii) delivered at the registered office or at the principal office or place of business of the`
  line company;
  line
  line `(b) where the person to be served is a partnership, if the document is addressed to the partnership`
  line `at its principal place of business, identifying it by the name or style under which its business is carried`
  line `on, and is either`
  line
  line `(i) sent by registered post, or`
  line
  line `(ii) delivered at the said place of business;`
  line
  line `(c) where the person to be served is a public body, or a corporation, society or other body, if the`
  line `document is addressed to the secretary, treasurer or other head officer of that body, corporation or`
  line `society at its principal office, and is either--`
  line
  line `(i) sent by registered post, or`
  line
  line `(ii) delivered at that office;`
  line
  line `(d) in any other case, if the document is addressed to the person to be served and`
  line
  line `(i) is given or tendered to him, or`
  line
  line `(ii) if such person cannot be found, is affixed on some conspicuous part of his last known`
  line `place of residence or business, if within the Union territory of Delhi, or is given or tendered to`
  line `some adult member of his family or is affixed on some conspicuous part of the land or building, if`
  line `any, to which it relates, or`
  line
  line `(iii) is sent by registered post to that person.`
  line
  line `^3[(1A) The service of notices, summons and other documents referred to in sub-section (1) may be made`
  line `by delivering or transmitting a copy thereof by registered post acknowledgment due, addressed to the`
  line `defendant or his agent empowered to accept the service or by speed post or by such courier services as are`
  line `approved by the High Court or by any other means of transmission of documents (including fax message`
  line `or electronic mail service) as may be provided by rules made by the High Court.]`
  line
  line `(2) Any document which is required or authorised to be served on the owner or occupier of any land`
  line `or building may be addressed the owner or the occupier, as the case may be, of that land or building`
  line `(naming that land or building) without further name or description, and shall be deemed to be duly`
  line served---
  line
  line `(a) if the document so addressed is sent or delivered in accordance with clause (d) of`
  line `sub-section (1); or`
  line
  line `(b) if the document so addressed or a copy thereof so addressed, is delivered to some person on`
  line `the land or building or, where there is no person on the land or building to whom it can be delivered,`
  line `is affixed to some conspicuous part of the land or building.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a document is served on a partnership in accordance with this section, the document shall`
  line `be deemed to be served on each partner.`
  line
  line `(4) For the purpose of enabling any document to be served on the owner of any premises the`
  line `Commissioner may by notice in writing require the occupier of the premises to state the name and address`
  line `of the owner thereof.`
  line
  line `(5) Where the person on whom a document is to be served is a minor, the service upon his guardian`
  line `or any adult member of his family shall be deemed to be service upon the minor.`
  line
  line `(6) Nothing in sections 442 and 443 and in this section shall apply to any summons issued under this`
  line `Act by a court.`
  line
  line `(7) A servant is not a member of the family within the meaning of this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_444_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 10 (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_445:
  sectionId (31362)
  sectionNo (445)
  orderNo 501
  title `Service of bills for tax or notice of demand by ordinary post.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_445_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_445_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31362&sectionno=445&orderno=501&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_445_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in sections 443 and 444 a bill for any tax or a notice of demand may be served by sending it by`
  line `ordinary post with a prepaid letter under a certificate of posting addressed to the appropriate person`
  line `specified in section 444 at his last known place of residence or business and in proving the service of`
  line `every bill or notice so sent it shall be sufficient to prove that the letter was properly addressed and posted`
  line `under a certificate of posting.`
obj_root_law_sections_445_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_446:
  sectionId (31363)
  sectionNo (446)
  orderNo 502
  title `Powers in case of non-compliance with notice, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_446_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_446_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31363&sectionno=446&orderno=502&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_446_content:
  string
  line `In the event of non-compliance with the`
  line `terms of any notice, order or requisition issued to any power under this Act or any rule, regulation or byelaw made thereunder, requiring such person to execute any work or to do any act it shall be lawful for the`
  line `authority or officer at whose instance the notice, order or requisition has been issued, whether or not the`
  line `person in default is liable to punishment for such default or has been prosecuted or sentenced to any`
  line `punishment therefor, after giving notice in writing to such person, to take such action or such steps as`
  line `may be necessary for the completion of the act or the work required to be done or executed by such`
  line `person and all the expenses incurred on such account shall be payable to the Commissioner on demand`
  line `and if not paid within ten days after such demand, shall be recoverable as an arrear of tax under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_446_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_447:
  sectionId (31364)
  sectionNo (447)
  orderNo 503
  title `Liability of occupier to pay in default of owner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_447_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_447_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31364&sectionno=447&orderno=503&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_447_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any notice, order or requisition has`
  line `been issued to any person in respect of property of which he is the owner, the authority or officer at`
  line `whose instance such notice, order or requisition has been issued, may require the occupier of such`
  line `property or of any part thereof to pay to him, instead of to the owner, any rent payable by him in respect`
  line `of such property, as it falls due up to the amount recoverable from the owner under section 446:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the occupier refuses to disclose the correct amount of the rent payable by him or the`
  line `name or address of the person to whom it is payable, the authority or officer may recover from the`
  line `occupier the whole amount recoverable under section 446 as an arrear of tax under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Any amount recovered from an occupier instead of from an owner under sub-section (1), shall, in`
  line `the absence of any contract between the owner and the occupier to the contrary, be deemed to have been`
  line `paid to the owner.`
obj_root_law_sections_447_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_448:
  sectionId (31365)
  sectionNo (448)
  orderNo 504
  title `Execution of work by occupier in default of owner and deduction of expenses from rent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_448_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_448_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31365&sectionno=448&orderno=504&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_448_content:
  string
  line `Whenever the owner of any land or building fails to execute any work which he is required to`
  line `execute under this Act or any bye-law made thereunder, the occupier, if any, of such land or building`
  line `may, with the approval of the Commissioner, execute the said work and he shall, subject to any contract`
  line `between the owner and occupier to the contrary, be entitled to recover from the owner the reasonable`
  line `expenses incurred by him in the execution of the work and may deduct the amount thereof from the rent`
  line `payable by him to the owner.`
obj_root_law_sections_448_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_449:
  sectionId (31366)
  sectionNo (449)
  orderNo 505
  title `Relief to agents and trustees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_449_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_449_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31366&sectionno=449&orderno=505&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_449_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any person, by reason of his receiving rent of`
  line `immovable property as a receiver, agent or trustee, or of his being as a receiver, agent or trustee the`
  line `person who would receive the rent if the property were let to a tenant, would under this Act or any byelaw made thereunder, be bound to discharge any obligation imposed on the owner of the property for the`
  line `discharge of which money is required, he shall not be bound to discharge the obligation unless he has, or`
  line `but for his own improper act or default might have had funds in his hands belonging to the owner`
  line `sufficient for the purpose.`
  line
  line `(2) The burden of proving any fact entitling a receiver, agent or trustee to relief under sub-section (1)`
  line `shall lie upon him.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any receiver, agent or trustee has claimed and established his right to relief under this`
  line `section, the Commissioner may, by notice in writing require him, to apply to the discharge of his`
  line `obligation as aforesaid the first moneys which may come to his hands on behalf, or for the use, of the`
  line `owner, and on failure to comply with the notice, he shall be deemed to be personally liable to discharge`
  line `the obligation.`
obj_root_law_sections_449_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_450:
  sectionId (31367)
  sectionNo (450)
  orderNo 506
  title `General power to pay compensation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_450_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 109, for section 450 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31367&sectionno=450&orderno=506&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_450_content:
  string
  line `^1[450. General power to pay compensation.—In any case not otherwise provided for in this Act or`
  line `in any bye-law made thereunder, the Commissioner, with the previous approval of the Standing`
  line `Committee, may pay compensation to any person who sustains damage by reason of the exercise of any`
  line `of the powers vested by this Act or any bye-law in the Commissioner or in any municipal officer or other`
  line `municipal employee.]`
obj_root_law_sections_451:
  sectionId (31368)
  sectionNo (451)
  orderNo 507
  title `Compensation to be paid by offenders for damage caused by them.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_451_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_451_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31368&sectionno=451&orderno=507&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_451_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person who`
  line `has been convicted of an offence against this Act or any bye-law made thereunder shall, notwithstanding`
  line `any punishment to which he may have been sentenced for the said offence, be liable to pay such`
  line `compensation for any damage to the property of ^1[^2[the Corporation]] resulting from the said offence as the`
  line `appropriate municipal authority may consider reasonable.`
  line
  line `(2) In the event of a dispute regarding the amount of compensation payable under sub-section (1)`
  line `such amount shall, on application made to him, be determined by the magistrate before whom the said`
  line `person was convicted of the said offence; and on non-payment of the amount of compensation so`
  line `determined the same shall be recovered under a warrant from the said magistrate as if it were a fine`
  line `imposed by him on the person liable therefor.`
obj_root_law_sections_451_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_452:
  sectionId (31369)
  sectionNo (452)
  orderNo 508
  title `Reference to the court of the district judge in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_452_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_452_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31369&sectionno=452&orderno=508&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_452_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, when the Commissioner`
  line `demands payment of any expenses referred to in section 446, his right to demand the same or the amount of the demand is disputed within ten days after such demand, the Commissioner shall ^1`
  line `[refer the case for`
  line determination—
  line
  line `(a) to the Appellate Tribunal, if such demand relates to the expenses incurred in taking necessary`
  line `action or steps for the completion of any act or work required to be done or executed in the event of`
  line `non-compliance with any notice, order or requisition under sections 317, 325, 343, 344 and 345;`
  line
  line `(b) to the court of the district judge of Delhi, in any other case.]`
  line
  line `(2) The Commissioner shall, pending the decision on any such reference, defer further proceedings`
  line `for the recovery of the sum claimed by him, and shall, after the decision, proceed to recover only such`
  line `amount, if any, as is thereby declared to be due in the manner referred to in section 446.`
obj_root_law_sections_452_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 42 of 1984, s. 8, for "refer the case for determination to the court of the district judge of Delhi."`
  line `(w.e.f. 10-2-1986).`
obj_root_law_sections_453:
  sectionId (31370)
  sectionNo (453)
  orderNo 509
  title `Application to the Court of the district judge in other cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_453_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_453_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31370&sectionno=453&orderno=509&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_453_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where, in any case not`
  line `provided for by section 452, ^1[^2[the Corporation]] or any municipal authority or any municipal officer or other`
  line `municipal employee is required by this Act or by any bye-law made thereunder to pay any expenses or`
  line `any compensation, the amount to be so paid and if necessary, the apportionment of the same, shall, in`
  line `case of dispute, be determined by the court of the district judge of Delhi on application having been made`
  line `to it for this purpose at any time within one year from the date when such expenses or compensation first`
  line `became claimable.`
  line
  line `(2) If the amount of any expenses or compensation ascertained in accordance with sub-section (1) is`
  line `not paid by the person liable therefor on demand, it shall be recoverable as if the same were due under a`
  line `decree passed by the court of the district judge in an original suit tried by it.`
obj_root_law_sections_453_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_454:
  sectionId (31371)
  sectionNo (454)
  orderNo 510
  title `Power to sue for expenses or compensation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_454_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_454_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31371&sectionno=454&orderno=510&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_454_content:
  string
  line `Instead of proceeding in the manner aforesaid`
  line `for the recovery of any expenses or compensation of which the amount due has been ascertained as`
  line `hereinbefore provided, or after such proceedings have been taken unsuccessfully or with only partial`
  line `success, the sum due or the balance of the sum due, as the case may be, may be recovered by a suit`
  line `brought against the person liable for the same in any court of competent jurisdiction.`
obj_root_law_sections_454_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_455:
  sectionId (31372)
  sectionNo (455)
  orderNo 511
  title `Mode of recovery of certain dues.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_455_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_455_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31372&sectionno=455&orderno=511&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_455_content:
  string
  line `In any case not expressly provided for in this Act or any`
  line `bye-law made thereunder any sum due to ^1[^2[the Corporation]] on account of any charge, costs, expenses, fees,`
  line `rates or rent or any other account under this Act or any such bye-law may be recoverable from any person`
  line `from whom such sum is due as an arrear of tax under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that no proceedings for the recovery of any sum under this section shall be commenced after`
  line `the expiry of three years from the date on which such sum becomes due.`
obj_root_law_sections_455_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_456:
  sectionId (31373)
  sectionNo (456)
  orderNo 512
  title `Right of owner to apply to the court of the district judge in case of obstruction by occupier.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_456_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_456_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31373&sectionno=456&orderno=512&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_456_content:
  string
  line `(1) The owner of any land or building may, if he is prevented by the occupier thereof from`
  line ^1
  line `[complying with`
  line
  line `(a) the provisions of section 317, section 325, section 343, section 344, section 345 or section 347`
  line `or any bye-law made thereunder or with any notice or order issued under any such provision, apply to`
  line `the Appellate Tribunal; and`
  line
  line `(b) any other provision or any bye-law made thereunder or with any notice, order or requisition`
  line `issued under such provision, apply to the court of the district judge of Delhi,`
  line
  line `and where such application is made] within any time that may be fixed for the compliance with such`
  line `provision or notice, order or requisition, the owner shall not be liable for his failure to comply with the`
  line `provision, or notice, order or requisition within the time so fixed.`
  line
  line `(2)`
  line ^2
  line `[The Appellate Tribunal or the court, as the case may be] on receipt of such application, may`
  line `make a written order requiring the occupier of the land or building to afford all reasonable facilities to the`
  line `owner for complying with the said provision or notice, order or requisition and may also, if it thinks fit`
  line `direct that the costs of such application and order be paid by the occupier.`
  line
  line `(3) After eight days from the date of the order referred to in sub-section (2), the occupier shall afford`
  line `all such reasonable facilities to the owner for the purpose, aforesaid as may be specified in the order; and`
  line `in the event of his continued refusal to do so, the owner shall be discharged during the continuance of`
  line `such refusal, from any liability which may have been otherwise incurred by reason of his failure to`
  line `comply with the said provision or notice, order or requisition.`
obj_root_law_sections_456_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 42 of 1984, s. 9, for certain words (w.e.f. 10-2-1986).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 42 of 1984, s. 9, for The court (w.e.f. 10-2-1986).`
obj_root_law_sections_457:
  sectionId (31374)
  sectionNo (457)
  orderNo 513
  title `General powers and procedure of the court of the district judge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_457_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_457_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31374&sectionno=457&orderno=513&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_457_content:
  string
  line `The procedure provided`
  line `in the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), in regard to suits shall be followed, as far as it can be`
  line `made applicable, in the disposal of applications, appeals or references that may be made to the court of`
  line `the district judge of Delhi under this Act or any bye-law made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_457_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_458:
  sectionId (31375)
  sectionNo (458)
  orderNo 514
  title `Fees in proceedings before the court of the district judge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_458_content
  footnotes `1. The word "Central" omitted by Act 67 of 1993, s. 110 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31375&sectionno=458&orderno=514&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_458_content:
  string
  line `(1) The ^1`
  line `*** Government may,`
  line `by notification in the Official Gazette, prescribe what fee shall be paid—`
  line
  line `(a) on any application, appeal or reference under this Act or any bye-law made thereunder to the`
  line `court of the district judge of Delhi; and`
  line
  line `(b) for the issue, in connection with any inquiry or proceedings before that court under this Act or`
  line `such bye-law, of any summons or other process:`
  line
  line `Provided that the fee, if any, prescribed under clause (a) shall not, in cases in which the value of the`
  line `claim or subject matter is capable of being estimated in money, exceed the fees leviable for the time being`
  line `under the provisions of the Court-Fees Act, 1870 (7 of 1870), in cases in which the amount of the claim`
  line `or subject matter is of a like amount.`
  line
  line `(2) The ^1`
  line `*** Government may, by like notification, determine the person by whom the fee, if any,`
  line `prescribed under clause (a) of sub-section (1), shall be payable.`
  line
  line `(3) No application, appeal or reference shall be received by the court of the district judge until the fee,`
  line `if any, prescribed therefor under clause (a) of sub-section (1) has been paid:`
  line
  line `Provided that the court may, in any case in which it thinks fit so to do,—`
  line
  line `(i) receive an application, appeal or reference made by or on behalf of a poor person, and`
  line
  line `(ii) issue process on behalf of any such person,`
  line
  line `without payment or on part payment of the fees prescribed under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_459:
  sectionId (31376)
  sectionNo (459)
  orderNo 515
  title `Repayment of half fees on settlement before hearing.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_459_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_459_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31376&sectionno=459&orderno=515&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_459_content:
  string
  line `Whenever any application, appeal or`
  line `reference made under this Act or any bye-law made thereunder to the court of the district judge is settled`
  line `by agreement between the parties before the hearing, half the amount of all fees paid up to that time shall`
  line `be repaid by the court to the parties by whom the same have respectively been paid.`
obj_root_law_sections_459_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_460:
  sectionId (31377)
  sectionNo (460)
  orderNo 516
  title `Power of the court of the district judge to delegate certain powers and to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_460_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_460_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31377&sectionno=460&orderno=516&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_460_content:
  string
  line The
  line `court of the district judge of Delhi may—`
  line
  line `(a) delegate, either generally or specially, to the court of any additional district judge, power to`
  line `receive applications, ^1`
  line `[election petitions,] appeals and references under this Act or any rule,`
  line `regulation or bye-law made thereunder, and to hear and determine such applications, ^1`
  line [election
  line `petitions,] appeals and references;`
  line
  line `(b) with the approval of the ^2`
  line `*** Government, make rules not inconsistent with this Act or any`
  line `rule, regulation or bye-law made thereunder, providing for any matter connected with the exercise of`
  line `jurisdiction conferred upon the court by this Act which is not herein specifically provided for.`
obj_root_law_sections_460_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 42 of 1961, s. 18 (w.e.f. 12-9-1961).`
  line
  line `2. The word "Central" omitted by Act 67 of 1993, s. 111 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_461:
  sectionId (31378)
  sectionNo (461)
  orderNo 517
  title `Punishment for certain offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_461_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_461_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31378&sectionno=461&orderno=517&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_461_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[(1)] Whoever—`
  line
  line `(a) contravenes any provision of any of the sections, sub-sections, clauses, provisos or other`
  line `provisions of this Act mentioned in the first column of the Table in the Twelfth Schedule; or`
  line
  line `(b) fails to comply with any order or direction lawfully given to him or any requisition lawfully`
  line `made upon him under any of the said sections, sub-sections, clauses, provisos or other provisions,`
  line `shall be punishable—`
  line
  line `(i) with fine which may extend to the amount, or with imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to the period, specified in that behalf third column of the said Table or with both; and`
  line
  line `(ii) in the case of a continuing contravention or failure, with an additional fine which may`
  line `extend to the amount specified in the fourth column of that Table for every day during which`
  line `such contravention or failure continues after conviction for the first such contravention or failure.`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), whoever contravenes the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 317 or sub-section (1) of section 320 or sub-section (1) of section 321 or subsection (1) of section 325 or section 339, in relation to any street which is a public street, shall be`
  line `punishable with simple imprisonment which may extend to six months or with fine which may extend to`
  line `five thousand rupees or with both.]`
obj_root_law_sections_461_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 461 re-numbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 42 of 1984, s. 10 (w.e.f. 10-12-1985).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 10, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-12-1985).`
obj_root_law_sections_462:
  sectionId (31379)
  sectionNo (462)
  orderNo 518
  title `Punishment for acquiring share or interest in contract, etc., with the Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_462_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_462_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31379&sectionno=462&orderno=518&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_462_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line [Any
  line `councillor or any person referred to in clause (b) of sub-section (3) of section 3 of any committee of ^2[^3[the`
  line `Corporation]]] who knowingly acquires, directly or indirectly, any share or interest in any contract made`
  line `with, or any work done for, ^2[^3[the Corporation]] not being a share or interest such as under section 9 it is`
  line `permissible for a councillor to have without being thereby disqualified for being a councillor ^4`
  line `***, and`
  line `the Commissioner, ^5`
  line `*** ^6`
  line `*** or any municipal officer or other municipal employee who knowingly`
  line `acquires, directly or indirectly, any share or interest in any contract made with, or any work done for, ^2[^3[the`
  line `Corporation]] not being a share or interest such as under clause (i) of sub-section (1) of section 9 or subclauses (ii) and (iii) of clause (c) of sub-section (2) of that section it is permissible for a councillor ^4`
  line `*** to`
  line `have, without being thereby disqualified for being a councillor ^4`
  line `***, shall be deemed to have committed`
  line `the offence made punishable under section 168of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_462_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 112, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "a Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `4. The words "or an alderman" omitted by s. 112, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `5. The words and brackets "the General Manager (Electricity)" omitted by s. 112, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `6. The words and brackets "the General Manager (Transport)" omitted by Act 71 of 1971, s. 7(b) and the Second Schedule`
  line `(w.e.f. 3-11-1971).`
obj_root_law_sections_463:
  sectionId (31380)
  sectionNo (463)
  orderNo 519
  title `Punishment for offences relating to terminal tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_463_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_463_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31380&sectionno=463&orderno=519&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_463_content:
  string
  line `Whoever brings within the Union territory`
  line `of Delhi any goods liable to terminal tax without the payment of such tax shall, on conviction, be`
  line `punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months or with fine which may extend`
  line `to one thousand rupees or with both, and the court trying an offence under this section may, on such`
  line `conviction, also confiscate the goods in respect of which the offence has been committed.`
obj_root_law_sections_463_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_464:
  sectionId (31381)
  sectionNo (464)
  orderNo 520
  title `Penalty for evasion of terminal taxes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_464_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_464_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31381&sectionno=464&orderno=520&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_464_content:
  string
  line `Where any goods imported into Delhi are liable to the`
  line `payment of terminal tax, any person who, with the intention of evading payment of the tax introduces or`
  line `attempts to introduce or causes or abets the introduction of any such goods within the Union territory of`
  line `Delhi, upon which payment of terminal tax due on such introduction, has neither been made nor tendered,`
  line `shall be punishable with fine which may extend to ten times the amount of such terminal tax.`
obj_root_law_sections_464_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_465:
  sectionId (31382)
  sectionNo (465)
  orderNo 521
  title `General penalty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_465_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_465_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31382&sectionno=465&orderno=521&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_465_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, in any case in which a penalty is not expressly provided by this`
  line `Act, fails to comply with any notice, order or requisition issued under any provision thereof, or otherwise`
  line `contravenes any of the provisions of this Act, shall be punishable with fine which may extend to one`
  line `hundred rupees, and in the case of a continuing failure or contravention, with an additional fine which`
  line `may extend to twenty rupees for every day after the first during which he has persisted in the failure or`
  line contravention.
obj_root_law_sections_465_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_466:
  sectionId (31383)
  sectionNo (466)
  orderNo 522
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_466_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_466_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31383&sectionno=466&orderno=522&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_466_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a`
  line `company, every person who, at the time of offence was committed, was in charge of, and was responsible`
  line `to, the company for the conduct of the business of the company, as well as the company, shall be deemed`
  line `to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment provided in this Act if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or`
  line `that he exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1) where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or connivance`
  line `of or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or other officer of the`
  line `company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to be guilty of that`
  line `offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation—For the purposes of this section—`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means a body corporate, and includes a firm or other association of individuals;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) "director" in relation to a firm means a partner in the firm,`
obj_root_law_sections_466_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_466_a:
  sectionId (31384)
  sectionNo 466A
  orderNo 523
  title `Certain offences to be cognizable`
  content obj_root_law_sections_466_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 42 of 1984, s. 11 (w.e.f. 10-12-1985).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31384&sectionno=466A&orderno=523&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_466_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[466A. Certain offences to be cognizable.—The Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974),`
  line `shall apply to,—`
  line
  line `(a) an offence under sub-section (5) of section 313 or section 332 or sub-section (1) of section`
  line `333 or sub-section (1) of section 334 or section 343 or section 344 or section 345 or section 347;`
  line
  line `(b) an offence under sub-section (1) of section 317 or sub-section (1) of section 320 or subsection (1) of section 321 or sub-section (1) of section 325 or section 339 in relation to any street`
  line `which is a public street,`
  line
  line `as if it were a cognizable offence—`
  line
  line `(i) for the purposes of investigation of such offence; and`
  line
  line `(ii) for the purposes of all matters other than—`
  line
  line `(1) matters referred to in section 42 of that Code, and`
  line
  line `(2) arrest of a person, except on the complaint of, or upon information received from, such`
  line `officer of the Corporation, not being below the rank of a Deputy Commissioner, as may be`
  line `appointed by the Administrator:`
  line
  line `Provided that no offence of the contravention of any condition subject of which sanction was`
  line `accorded for the erection of any building or the execution of any work shall be cognizable, if such`
  line `contravention relates to any deviation from any plan of such erection or execution sanctioned by the`
  line `Commissioner which is compoundable on payment of an amount under the bye-laws relating to buildings`
  line `made under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_467:
  sectionId (31385)
  sectionNo (467)
  orderNo 524
  title Prosecutions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_467_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_467_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31385&sectionno=467&orderno=524&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_467_content:
  string
  line `^1[467. Prosecutions.---Save as otherwise provided in this Act, no court shall proceed to the trial of`
  line `any offence,---`
  line
  line `(a) under sub-section (5) of section 313 or section 332 or sub-section (1) of section 333 or`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 334 or section 343 or section 344 or section 345 or section 347 except on`
  line `the complaint of or upon information received from, such officer of ^2[^3[the Corporation]], not being below`
  line `the rank of a Deputy Commissioner, as may be appointed by the Administrator;`
  line
  line `(b) under sub-section (1) of section 317 or sub-section (1) of section 320 or sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 321 or sub-section (1) of section 325 or section 339, if any such offence was committed in`
  line `relation to any street which is a public street, except on the complaint of, or upon information`
  line `received from, such officer of ^2[^3[the Corporation]], not being below the rank of a Deputy Commissioner,`
  line `as may be appointed by the Administrator;`
  line
  line `(c) other than those specified in clauses (a) and (b), except on the complaint of, or upon`
  line `information received from, ^4`
  line `[the Commissioner, or a person authorised by him] by a general or`
  line `special order in this behalf.]`
obj_root_law_sections_467_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 42 of 1984, s. 12, for section 467 (w.e.f. 10-12-1985).`
  line
  line `2. Subs.by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "a Corporation"(w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 113, for certain words and brackets (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_468:
  sectionId (31386)
  sectionNo (468)
  orderNo 525
  title `Composition of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_468_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_468_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31386&sectionno=468&orderno=525&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_468_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line ^1
  line `[The Commissioner or any person authorised by him] by`
  line `general or special order in this behalf, may either before or after the institution of the proceedings`
  line `compound any offence made punishable by or under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that no offence shall be compoundable which is committed by failure to comply with a`
  line `notice, order or requisition issued by or on behalf of ^2[^3[the Corporation]] or of any of the municipal authorities`
  line `specified in section 44 unless and until the same has been complied with so far as the compliance is`
  line possible.
  line
  line `(2) Where an offence has been compounded, the offender, if in custody, shall be discharged and no`
  line `further proceedings shall be taken against him in respect of the offence so compounded.`
obj_root_law_sections_468_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 114, ibid., for certain words and brackets (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `2. Subs.by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for the Corporation (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for a Corporation (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_469:
  sectionId (31387)
  sectionNo (469)
  orderNo 526
  title `Municipal magistrates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_469_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_469_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31387&sectionno=469&orderno=526&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_469_content:
  string
  line `(1) The ^1`
  line `*** Government may appoint one or more ^2`
  line [Metropolitan
  line `Magistrates] for the trial of offences against this Act and against any rule, regulation or bye-law made`
  line `thereunder and may prescribe the time and place at which such magistrate or magistrates shall sit for the`
  line `despatch of business.`
  line
  line `(2) Such magistrates shall be called municipal magistrates and shall besides the trial of offences as`
  line `aforesaid, exercise all other powers and discharge all other functions of a magistrate as provided in this`
  line `Act or any rule, regulation or bye-law made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(3) Such magistrates and the members of their staff shall be paid such salary, pension, leave and other`
  line `allowances as may, from time to time, be fixed by the ^1`
  line `*** Government.`
  line
  line `(4) ^3[^4[The Corporation]] shall, out of the Municipal Fund, pay to the ^1`
  line `*** Government the amounts of the`
  line `salary, pension, leave and other allowances as fixed under sub-section (3) together with all other`
  line `incidental charges in connection with the establishments of the said magistrates.`
  line
  line `(5) Each such magistrate shall have jurisdiction over the whole of Delhi.`
  line
  line `(6) For the purposes of ^5`
  line `[the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974)] all municipal magistrates`
  line `appointed under this Act shall be deemed to be magistrates appointed under ^6`
  line `[section 16] of the said`
  line Code.
  line
  line `(7) Nothing in this section shall be deemed to preclude any magistrate appointed hereunder from`
  line `trying any offence under any other law.`
obj_root_law_sections_469_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The word Central omitted by Act 67 of 1993, s. 115, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 115, ibid., for magistrates of the first class (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `3. Subs.by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "A Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 115, for "the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898" (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 115, ibid., for section 12 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_470:
  sectionId (31388)
  sectionNo (470)
  orderNo 527
  title `Cognizance of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_470_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_470_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31388&sectionno=470&orderno=527&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_470_content:
  string
  line `All offences against this Act or any rule, regulation or bye-law made`
  line `thereunder, whether committed within or without the limits of Delhi, shall be cognizable by a municipal`
  line `magistrate and such magistrate shall not be deemed to be incapable of taking cognizance of any such`
  line `offence or of any offence under any enactment which is repealed by, or which ceases to have effect under,`
  line `this Act by reason only of his being liable to pay any municipal tax or rate or benefited out of the`
  line `Municipal Fund.`
obj_root_law_sections_470_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_471:
  sectionId (31389)
  sectionNo (471)
  orderNo 528
  title `Limitation of time for prosecution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_471_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_471_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31389&sectionno=471&orderno=528&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_471_content:
  string
  line `No person shall be liable to punishment for any offence`
  line `against this Act or any rule, regulation or by-law made thereunder, unless complaint of such offence is`
  line `made before a municipal magistrate within six months next after—`
  line
  line `(a) the date of the commission of such offence, or`
  line
  line `(b) the date on which the commission or existence of such offence was first brought to the notice`
  line `of the complainant.`
obj_root_law_sections_471_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_472:
  sectionId (31390)
  sectionNo (472)
  orderNo 529
  title `Power of magistrate to hear cases in absence of accused when summoned to appear.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_472_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_472_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31390&sectionno=472&orderno=529&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_472_content:
  string
  line If
  line `any person summoned to appear before a magistrate to answer a charge of an offence against this Act or`
  line `any rule, regulation or bye-law made thereunder fails to appear at the time and place mentioned in the`
  line `summons, or on any date to which the hearing of case is adjourned, the magistrate may hear and`
  line `determine the case in his absence, if—`
  line
  line `(a) service of the summons is proved to his satisfaction, and`
  line
  line `(b) no sufficient cause is shown for the non-appearance of such person.`
obj_root_law_sections_472_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_473:
  sectionId (31391)
  sectionNo (473)
  orderNo 530
  title `Complaints concerning nuisances and procedure therefor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_473_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_473_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31391&sectionno=473&orderno=530&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_473_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commissioner, ^1`
  line `[or any`
  line `municipal officer or other municipal employee authorised by him] in this behalf or any person who`
  line `resides or owns property in Delhi, may complain to a municipal magistrate of the existence of any`
  line nuisance.
  line
  line `(2) Upon the receipt of any such complaint the magistrate, after making such inquiry as he thinks`
  line `necessary, may by written order direct the person responsible for the nuisance or the owner of the land or`
  line `building on which the nuisance has taken place, to take such measures as to such magistrate may seem`
  line `practicable and reasonable, and within such period as may be specified in the order, for abating,`
  line `preventing, removing or remedying such nuisance and may direct ^2`
  line `[the Commissioner] to put into force`
  line `any of the provisions of this Act or any bye-law made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(3) The magistrate may further direct the person found responsible for the nuisance to pay to the`
  line `complainant such reasonable costs of and relating to the said complaint as he shall determine, inclusive of`
  line `compensation for the complainant's loss of time in prosecuting such complaint.`
  line
  line `(4) Where in the opinion of the magistrate immediate action to prevent the nuisance is necessary he`
  line `may dispense with the inquiry as required by sub-section (2) and make such other as he considers`
  line `necessary forthwith.`
  line
  line `(5) If the person directed to take action by an order under sub-section (2) or sub-section (3) fails to do`
  line `so within the period specified in the order, the Commissioner ^3`
  line `*** may on the expiry of the said period`
  line `proceed to take action as directed in the order or may take such other measures to abate, prevent, remove`
  line `or remedy the nuisance as he considers necessary, and all expenses incurred in that connection shall be`
  line `recoverable from the person against whom the magistrate has made the order as an arrear of tax under this`
  line Act.
obj_root_law_sections_473_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 116, for certain words and brackets (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 116, ibid., for "any of the appropriate municipal authorities" (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `3. The words "or any other appropriate municipal authority" omitted by s. 116, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-1993)`
obj_root_law_sections_474:
  sectionId (31392)
  sectionNo (474)
  orderNo 531
  title `Arrest of offenders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_474_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_474_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31392&sectionno=474&orderno=531&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_474_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any police officer may arrest any person who commits in his view`
  line `any offence against this Act or against any rule, regulation or bye-law made thereunder, if—`
  line
  line `(a) the name and address of such person be unknown to him, and`
  line
  line `(b) such person on demand declines to give his name and address or gives a name and address`
  line `which such officer has reason to believe to be false.`
  line
  line `(2) No person so arrested shall be detained in custody after his true name and address are ascertained`
  line `or, without the order of the nearest magistrate, for a period longer than twenty-four hours from the time of`
  line `arrest exclusive of the time necessary for the journey from the place of arrest to the court of such`
  line magistrate.
obj_root_law_sections_474_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_475:
  sectionId (31393)
  sectionNo (475)
  orderNo 532
  title `Duties of police officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_475_content
  footnotes `1. The words "or any other appropriate municipal authority" omitted by Act 67 of 1993, s. 117 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31393&sectionno=475&orderno=532&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_475_content:
  string
  line `It shall be the duty of all police officers to give immediate`
  line `information to the Commissioner ^1`
  line `*** of the commission of, or the attempt to commit any offence against`
  line `this Act or any rule, regulation or bye-law made thereunder and to assist all municipal officers and other`
  line `municipal employees in the exercise of their lawful authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_476:
  sectionId (31394)
  sectionNo (476)
  orderNo 533
  title `Power to institute, etc., legal proceedings and obtain legal advice.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_476_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_476_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31394&sectionno=476&orderno=533&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_476_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commissioner`
  line may---
  line
  line `(a) take, or withdraw from, proceedings against any person who is charged with--`
  line
  line `(i) any offence against this Act or any rule, regulation or bye-law made thereunder; or`
  line
  line `(ii) any offence which affects or is likely to affect any property or interest of ^1[^2[the Corporation]]`
  line `or the due administration of this Act; or`
  line
  line `(iii) committing any nuisance whatsoever;`
  line
  line `(b) contest or compromise any appeal against rateable value or assessment of any tax or rate;`
  line
  line `(c) take, or withdraw from, or compromise, proceedings under sections 451, 452 and 453 for the`
  line `recovery of expenses or compensation claimed to be due to ^1[^2[the Corporation]];`
  line
  line `(d) withdraw or compromise any claim for a sum not exceeding one thousand rupees against any`
  line person;
  line
  line `(e) defend any suit or other legal proceeding brought against ^1[^2[the Corporation]] or against the`
  line `Commissioner or a municipal officer or other municipal employee in respect of anything done or`
  line `omitted to be done by any one of them in his official capacity;`
  line
  line `(f) with the approval of the Standing Committee^3`
  line `[or the Wards Committee] admit or compromise`
  line `any claim, suit or other legal proceeding brought against ^1[^2[the Corporation]] or against the Commissioner`
  line `or any municipal officer or other municipal employee in respect of anything done or omitted to be`
  line `done as aforesaid;`
  line
  line `(g) withdraw or compromise any claim against any person in respect of a penalty payable under a`
  line `contract entered into with such person by the Commissioner on behalf of ^1[^2[the Corporation]];`
  line
  line `(h) institute and prosecute any suit or other legal proceeding or with the approval of the Standing`
  line Committee^3
  line `[or the Wards Committee] withdraw from or compromise any suit or any claim for any`
  line `sum not exceeding five hundred rupees which has been instituted or made in the name of ^1[^2[the`
  line `Corporation]] or of the Commissioner;`
  line
  line `(i) obtain such legal advice and assistance as he from time to time thinks necessary or expedient`
  line `to obtain or as he may be required by the Corporation or the Standing Committee ^3`
  line `[or the Wards`
  line `Committee] to obtain, for any of the purposes mentioned in the foregoing clauses or for securing`
  line `lawful exercise or discharge of any power or duty vesting in or imposed upon any municipal authority`
  line `or any municipal officer or other municipal employee.`
  line
  line ^4
  line `* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_476_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs.by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 116, for “any of the appropriate municipal authorities” (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `4. Omitted by Act 67 of 1993, s. 118 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_477:
  sectionId (31395)
  sectionNo (477)
  orderNo 534
  title `Protection of action of the Corporation, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_477_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_477_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31395&sectionno=477&orderno=534&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_477_content:
  string
  line `477. Protection of action of ^1[^2[the Corporation]], etc.---No suit or prosecution shall be entertained in`
  line `any court against ^1[^2[the Corporation]] or against any municipal authority or against any municipal officer or`
  line `other municipal employee or against any person acting under the order or direction of any municipal authority or any municipal officer or other municipal employee, for anything which is in good faith done`
  line `or intended to be done, under this Act or any rule, regulation or bye-law made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_477_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs.by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "a Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_478:
  sectionId (31396)
  sectionNo (478)
  orderNo 535
  title `Notice to be given of suits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_478_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_478_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31396&sectionno=478&orderno=535&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_478_content:
  string
  line `(1) No suit shall be instituted against ^1[^2[the Corporation]] or against`
  line `any municipal authority or against any municipal officer or other municipal employee or against any`
  line `person acting under the order or direction of any municipal authority or any municipal officer or other`
  line `municipal employee, in respect of any act done, or purporting to have been done, in pursuance of this Act`
  line `or any rule, regulation or bye-law made thereunder until the expiration of two months after notice in`
  line `writing has been left at the municipal office and, in the case of such officer, employee or person, unless`
  line `notice in writing has also been delivered to him or left at his office or place of residence, and unless such`
  line `notice states explicitly the cause of action, the nature of the relief sought, the amount of compensation`
  line `claimed, and the name and place of residence of the intending plaintiff, and unless the plaint contains a`
  line `statement that such notice has been so left or delivered.`
  line
  line `(2) No suit, such as is described in sub-section (1), shall, unless it is a suit for the recovery of`
  line `immovable property or for a declaration of title thereto, be instituted after the expiry of six months from`
  line `the date on which the cause of action arises.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing in sub-section (1) shall be deemed to apply to a suit in which the only relief claimed is an`
  line `injunction of which the object would be defeated by the giving of the notice or the postponement of the`
  line `institution of the suit.`
obj_root_law_sections_478_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs.by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_479:
  sectionId (31397)
  sectionNo (479)
  orderNo 536
  title `Supplemental provisions respecting rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_479_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_479_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31397&sectionno=479&orderno=536&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_479_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any rule which the ^1[Government] is`
  line `empowered to make under this Act may provide that any contravention thereof shall be punishable with`
  line `fine which may extend to one hundred rupees.`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(2) ^3[Every rule made under clause (8) of section 22 and section 31 ^4[and every notification issued`
  line `under sub-section (2) of section 3A]] shall`
  line `be laid as soon as may be after it is made or issued before each House of Parliament, while it is in session`
  line `for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive`
  line `sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive`
  line `sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule, bye-law or notification or`
  line `both Houses agree that the rule, bye-law or notification should not be made or issued, the rule, bye-law or`
  line `notification shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be;`
  line `so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of`
  line `anything previously done under that rule, bye-law or notification.]`
  line
  line `^5[(3) Every rule made under this Act, except rules made under section 22(8) and section 31 of this Act,`
  line `every notification issued under ^6*** sub-section (2) of section 52 and bye-law made by the Government`
  line `under section 349A shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made or issued, before the Legislative`
  line `Assembly of Delhi, while it is in session for a total period of thirty days, which may be comprised in one`
  line `session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following`
  line `the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, the Legislative Assembly agrees in making any`
  line `modification in the rule, bye-laws or notification or the Legislative Assembly agrees that the rule, or byelaws or notification should not be made or issued, the rule or bye-laws or notification shall thereafter have`
  line `effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such`
  line `modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that`
  line `rule or bye-law or notification.]`
obj_root_law_sections_479_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for "Central Government" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 119, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 17, for certain words (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 11 (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 17 (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `6. The words, brackets, figures and letter sub-section (2) of section 3A and by Act 10 of 2022, s. 11 (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_480:
  sectionId (31398)
  sectionNo (480)
  orderNo 537
  title `Supplemental provisions respecting regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_480_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_480_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31398&sectionno=480&orderno=537&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_480_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any regulation which may be made by`
  line `^1[^2[the Corporation]] under this Act, may be made by the ^3[Government] within one year of the`
  line `establishment of ^1[^2[the Corporation]]; and any regulation so made may be altered or rescinded by ^1[^2[tthe`
  line `Corporation]] in the exercise of its powers under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) No regulation made by ^1[^2[the Corporation]] under this Act shall have effect until it has been approved`
  line `by the ^3[Government] and published in the Official Gazette.`
obj_root_law_sections_480_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022,s. 2, for "a Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for "Central Government" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
obj_root_law_sections_481:
  sectionId (31399)
  sectionNo (481)
  orderNo 538
  title `Power to make bye-laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_481_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_481_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31399&sectionno=481&orderno=538&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_481_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act the Corporation may, in`
  line `addition to any bye-laws which it is empowered to make by any other provision of this Act, make`
  line `bye-laws to provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `A. Bye-laws relating to taxation`
  line
  line `(1) the maintenance of tax books and registers by the Commissioner and the particulars which`
  line `such books and registers should contain;`
  line
  line `(2) the inspection of and the obtaining of copies and extracts from such books and registers and`
  line `fees, if any, to be charged for the same;`
  line
  line `(3) the publication of rates of taxes as determined by ^1[^2[the Corporation]] from time to time;`
  line
  line `(4) the requisition by the Commissioner of information and returns from persons liable to pay`
  line taxes;
  line
  line `(5) the notice to be given to the Commissioner by any person who becomes the owner or`
  line `possessor of a vehicle or animal in respect of which any tax is payable under this Act;`
  line
  line `(6) the wearing of badge by the driver of any such vehicle and the display of number plate on`
  line `such vehicle;`
  line
  line `(7) the submission of returns by persons liable to pay any tax under this Act;`
  line
  line `(8) the collection by the registrar or sub-registrar of ^3[^4[Delhi]] appointed under the Indian Registration`
  line `Act, 1908 (16 of 1908), of the additional stamp duty payable to ^1[^2[the Corporation]] under this Act, the`
  line `periodical payment of such duty to ^1[^2[the Corporation]] and the maintenance, by such registrar or sub-registrar of separate accounts in relation thereto;`
  line
  line `(9) any other matter relating to the levy, assessment, collection, refund or remission of taxes`
  line `under this Act;`
  line
  line ^5
  line `* * * * *`
  line
  line ^6
  line `* * * * *`
  line
  line `E. Bye-laws relating to streets`
  line
  line `(1) the closure of streets when any work is in progress and alternative passage during the progress`
  line `of such work;`
  line
  line `(2) the erections of a temporary nature during festivals;`
  line
  line `(3) the setting up of hoards on buildings adjacent to streets during their construction or repair;`
  line
  line `(4) the precautions to be taken when permission is granted to any private individual for opening`
  line `or breaking up any public street and the fees to be paid for the restoration of a street in its original`
  line condition;
  line
  line `(5) the permission, regulation or prohibition of use or occupation of any street or place by`
  line `intinerant vendors or hawkers or by any person for the sale of articles or the exercise of any calling or`
  line `the setting up of any booth or stall and the fees chargeable for such occupation;`
  line
  line `(6) any other matter in connection with the construction, repair, maintenance, naming, numbering`
  line `and lighting of streets for which provision is necessary or should be made;`
  line
  line ^7
  line `* * * * *`
  line
  line `G. Bye-laws relating to sanitation and public health`
  line
  line `(1) the position of latrines and urinals;`
  line
  line `(2) the provision of air spaces between latrines and buildings or places used for various purposes;`
  line
  line `(3) the white-washing of buildings;`
  line
  line `(4) the provision of living accommodation for sweepers in buildings newly erected requiring ten`
  line `or more latrines;`
  line
  line `(5) the regulation or prohibition of the stabling or herding of animals or any class of animals so as`
  line `to prevent danger to public health;`
  line
  line `(6) the seizure of ownerless animals straying within the limits of ^3[^4[Delhi]] and the regulation and`
  line `control of pounds;`
  line
  line `(7) the fixing and regulation of the use of public bathing and washing places;`
  line
  line `(8) the prevention of the spread of dangerous disease;`
  line
  line `(9) the segregation in or the removal or exclusion from any part of ^3[^4[Delhi]] or the destruction of`
  line `animals suffering or reasonably suspected to be suffering from any infectious or contagious disease;`
  line
  line `(10) the supervision, regulation, conservation and protection from injury, contamination or`
  line `trespass, of sources and means of public water supply and of appliances for the distribution of water;`
  line
  line `(11) the enforcement of compulsory vaccination and inoculation;`
  line
  line `(12) the proper disposal of corpses, the regulation and management of burning and burial places`
  line `and other places for the disposal of corpses and the fees chargeable for the use of such places where`
  line `the same are provided or maintained at the expense of the Municipal Fund;`
  line
  line `H. Bye-laws relating to vital statistics`
  line
  line `(1) the prescribing of qualifications of persons to be appointed as registrars under Chapter XVIII;`
  line
  line `(2) the registration of births, deaths and marriages and the taking of a census;`
  line
  line `I. Bye-laws relating to public safety and suppression of nuisances`
  line
  line `The regulation or prohibition for the purpose of sanitation or the prevention of disease or the`
  line `promotion of public safety or convenience, of any act which occasions or is likely to occasion a`
  line `nuisance and for the regulation or prohibition of which on provision is made elsewhere by this Act;`
  line
  line `J. Bye-laws relating to markets, slaughter houses, trades and occupations`
  line
  line `(1) the days on, and the hours during which any market or slaughter house may be kept open for`
  line use;
  line
  line `(2) the regulation of the design, ventilation and drainage of markets and slaughter houses and the`
  line `materials to be used in the construction thereof;`
  line
  line `(3) the keeping of markets and slaughter houses and the lands and buildings appertaining thereto`
  line `in a clean and sanitary condition, the removal of filth, rubbish and other polluted and obnoxious`
  line `matter therefrom and the supply therein of pure water and of a sufficient number of latrines and`
  line `urinals for the use of persons using or frequenting the same;`
  line
  line `(4) the manner in which animals shall be admitted in a slaughter house;`
  line
  line `(5) the manner in which animals may be slaughtered;`
  line
  line `(6) the provision of passages of sufficient width between the stalls in market buildings and market`
  line `places for the convenient use of the public and the prevention of encroachment of such passages;`
  line
  line `(7) the setting apart of separate areas for different classes of articles in market buildings and`
  line `market places;`
  line
  line `(8) the disposal or destruction of animals offered for slaughter which are, from disease or any`
  line `other cause, unfit for human consumption;`
  line
  line `(9) the destruction of carcasses which from any disease or any other cause are found after`
  line `slaughter to be unfit for human consumption;`
  line
  line `(10) the regulation of the entry of animals into slaughter house and the bringing out of the`
  line `carcasses of such animals after slaughter and the fee to be paid for use of slaughter houses;`
  line
  line `(11) the proper custody and care of animals for the keeping of which licences are granted under`
  line `section 417;`
  line
  line `(12) the regulation of the import of animals and flesh within ^3[^4[Delhi]];`
  line
  line `(13) the rendering necessary of licences for the use of premises within ^1[^2[Delhi]] as stables or`
  line `cow-houses or as an accommodation for sheep, goat or buffalo, and the fees payable for such licences`
  line `and the conditions subject to which such licences may be granted, refused, suspended or revoked;`
  line
  line `(14) the regulation of sarais, hotels, dak bungalows, lodging houses, boarding houses, buildings,`
  line `let-in-tenements, residential clubs, restaurants, eating houses, cafes, refreshment rooms and places of`
  line `public recreation, entertainment or resort;`
  line
  line `(15) the control and supervision of places where dangerous or offensive trades are carried on so`
  line `to secure cleanlines therein or to minimise injurious, offensive or dangerous effects arising or likely`
  line `to arise therefrom;`
  line
  line `(16) the regulation of the posting of bills and advertisements and of the position, size, shade or`
  line `style of the name boards, sign-boards and sign-posts;`
  line
  line `(17) the fixation of a method for the sale of articles whether by measure, weight; piece or any`
  line `other method;`
  line
  line `(18) the procedure regarding the grant of permit to establish a factory, workshop or trade`
  line premises;
  line
  line `(19) the regulation of smoke in factories workshops and trade premises;`
  line
  line `(20) the regulation of sanitary conditions in factories, workshops, and trade premises;`
  line
  line `(21) the regulation of the use in any factory, workshop or trade premises of whistle, trumpet,`
  line `siren, or horn worked by steam, compressed air, electricity or other mechanical means;`
  line
  line `(22) the prevention of nuisance in any market building, market place, slaughter house or any`
  line `factory, workshop or trade premises;`
  line
  line `K. Bye-laws relating to improvement`
  line
  line `(1) the form and content of an improvement scheme or a rehousing scheme;`
  line
  line `(2) the procedure to be followed in connection with the framing, submission, approval and`
  line `sanction of such schemes;`
  line
  line `(3) the local inquiries and other hearings that may be held before a scheme is framed, approved or`
  line sanctioned;
  line
  line `(4) the alteration of an improvement scheme or a rehousing scheme after approval and sanction;`
  line
  line `L. Bye-laws relating to miscellaneous matters`
  line
  line ^7
  line `* * * * *`
  line
  line `(2) the circumstances and the manner in which owners of land or building in ^3[^4[Delhi]] temporarily`
  line `absent therefrom or not resident therein may be required to appoint as their agents for all or any of the`
  line `purposes of this Act or of any bye-laws made thereunder, persons residing within or near ^3[^4[Delhi]];`
  line
  line `(3) the maintenance of schools and the furtherance of education generally;`
  line
  line `(4) the regulation and control of municipal hospitals and dispensaries;`
  line
  line `(5) the rendering necessary of licences--`
  line
  line `(a) for the proprietors or drivers of hackney-carriages, cycle-rickshaws, thelas and rehries`
  line `kept or plying for hire or used for hawking articles;`
  line
  line `(b) for persons working as job-porters for the conveyance of goods;`
  line
  line `(6) the classification of cinema theatres for the purposes of the Fourth Schedule;`
  line
  line `(7) any other matter which is to be or may be prescribed by bye-laws made under this Act or in`
  line `respect of which this Act makes no provision or makes insufficient provision and provision is, in the`
  line `opinion of ^1[^2[the Corporation]], necessary for the efficient municipal government of ^3[^4[Delhi]].`
  line
  line `(2) Any bye-law which may be made under sub-section (1) may be made by the ^8[Government]`
  line `within one year of the establishment of ^1[^2[the Corporation]]; and any bye-law so made may be altered`
  line `rescinded by ^1[^2[the Corporation]] in the exercise of its powers under sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_481_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022,s. 2, for "a Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for "Delhi" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "the area of the Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `5. Omitted by Act 67 of 1993, s. 120 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `6. Omitted by Act 71 of 1971, s. 7(b) and the Second Schedule (w.e.f. 3-11-1971).`
  line
  line `7. Omitted by Act 67 of 1993, s. 120 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for "Central Government" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
obj_root_law_sections_481_a:
  sectionId (31400)
  sectionNo 481A
  orderNo 539
  title `Regulations and bye-laws to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_481_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 20 of 1983, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 15-2-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31400&sectionno=481A&orderno=539&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_481_a_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[481A. Regulations and bye-laws to be laid before Parliament.The Central Government shall`
  line `cause every regulation made under this Act and every bye-law made under section 481 to be laid, as soon`
  line `as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of`
  line `thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before`
  line `the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid both`
  line `Houses agree in making any modification in the regulation or bye-law or both Houses agree that the`
  line `regulation or bye-law should not be made, the regulation or bye-law shall thereafter have effect only in`
  line `such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that regulation or`
  line bye-law.]
obj_root_law_sections_482:
  sectionId (31401)
  sectionNo (482)
  orderNo 540
  title `Penalty for breaches of bye-laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_482_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_482_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31401&sectionno=482&orderno=540&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_482_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any bye-law made under this Act may provide that a`
  line `contravention thereof shall be punishable—`
  line
  line `(a) with fine which may extend to five hundred rupees; or`
  line
  line `(b) with fine which may extend to five hundred rupees and in the case of a continuing`
  line `contravention, with an additional fine which may extend to twenty rupees for every day during which`
  line `such contravention continues after conviction for the first such contravention; or`
  line
  line `(c) with fine which may extend to twenty rupees for every day during which the contravention`
  line `continues, after the receipt of a notice from the Commissioner or any municipal officer duly`
  line `authorised in that behalf, by the person contravening the bye-law requiring such person to discontinue`
  line `such contravention:`
  line
  line `Provided that a contravention of any bye-law relating to the road transport services may be`
  line `punishable with imprisonment which may extend to three months, or with fine which may extend to`
  line `fifteen hundred rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `(2) Any such bye-law may also provide that a person contravening the same shall be required to`
  line `remedy so far as lies in his power, the mischief, if any, caused by such contravention.`
obj_root_law_sections_482_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_483:
  sectionId (31402)
  sectionNo (483)
  orderNo 541
  title `Supplemental provisions respecting bye-laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_483_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_483_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31402&sectionno=483&orderno=541&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_483_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any power to make bye-laws conferred`
  line `by this Act is conferred subject to the conditions of the bye-laws being made after previous publication`
  line `and in the case of such bye-laws being made by ^1[^2[the Corporation]] of their not taking effect until they have`
  line `been approved by the ^3`
  line `*** Government and published in the Official Gazette.`
  line
  line `(2) The ^3`
  line `*** Government in approving a bye-law may make any change therein which appears to it to`
  line `be necessary.`
  line
  line `(3) The ^3`
  line `*** Government may, after previous publication of its intention cancel any bye-law which it`
  line `has approved, and thereupon the bye-law shall cease to have effect.`
obj_root_law_sections_483_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `3. The word Central omitted by Act 67 of 1993, s. 121 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_484:
  sectionId (31403)
  sectionNo (484)
  orderNo 542
  title `Bye-laws to be available for inspection and purchase.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_484_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_484_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31403&sectionno=484&orderno=542&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_484_content:
  string
  line `(1) A copy of all bye-laws made`
  line `under this Act shall be kept at the municipal office and shall, during office hours, be open free of charge`
  line `to inspection by any inhabitant of Delhi.`
  line
  line `(2) Copies of all such bye-laws shall be kept at the municipal office and shall be sold to the public at`
  line `cost price either singly or in collections at the option of the purchaser.`
obj_root_law_sections_484_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_484_a:
  sectionId (67091)
  sectionNo 484A
  orderNo 543
  title Omitted..
  content obj_root_law_sections_484_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_484_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=67091&sectionno=484A&orderno=543&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_484_a_content:
  string
  line `484A. [Director of Local Bodies.] Omitted by the Delhi Municipal Corporation (Amendment) Act,`
  line `2022, s. 12 (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).Earlier it was inserted by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 19.`
obj_root_law_sections_484_a_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_485:
  sectionId (31404)
  sectionNo (485)
  orderNo 544
  title `Power of Central Government to require production of documents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_485_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_485_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31404&sectionno=485&orderno=544&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_485_content:
  string
  line `485. Power of Central Government ^1`
  line `[or the Government] to require production of`
  line `documents.---The Central Government ^1`
  line `[or the Government] may at any time require the`
  line Commissioner--
  line
  line `(a) to produce any record, correspondence, plan or other document in his possession or under his`
  line control;
  line
  line `(b) to furnish any return, plan, estimate, statement, account or statistics relating to the`
  line `proceedings, duties or works of ^2[^3[the Corporation]] or any of the municipal authorities;`
  line
  line `(c) to furnish or obtain and furnish any report.`
obj_root_law_sections_485_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins by Act 67 of 1993, s. 122 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993) .`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "a Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_486:
  sectionId (31405)
  sectionNo (486)
  orderNo 545
  title Inspection.
  content obj_root_law_sections_486_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_486_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31405&sectionno=486&orderno=545&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_486_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government ^1`
  line `[or the Government] may depute any person in the`
  line `service of Government to inspect or examine any municipal department or office or any service or work`
  line `undertaken by ^2[^3[the Corporation]] or any of the municipal authorities or any property belonging to ^2[^3[the`
  line `Corporation]] and to report thereon and ^2[^3[the Corporation]] and every municipal authority and all municipal`
  line `officers and other municipal employees shall be bound to afford the person so deputed access at all`
  line `reasonable times to the premises and properties of ^2[^3[the Corporation]] and to all records, accounts and other`
  line `documents the inspection of which he may consider necessary to enable him to discharge his duties.`
obj_root_law_sections_486_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins by Act 67 of 1993, s. 122 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_487:
  sectionId (31406)
  sectionNo (487)
  orderNo 546
  title `Directions by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_487_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_487_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31406&sectionno=487&orderno=546&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_487_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, ^1`
  line `[whether on receipt of a report or on receipt of]`
  line `any information or report obtained under section 485 or section 486 or otherwise, the Central Government`
  line `is of opinion--`
  line
  line `(a) that any duty imposed on ^2[^3[the Corporation]] or any municipal authority by or under this Act has`
  line `not been performed or has been performed in an imperfect, insufficient or unsuitable manner, or`
  line
  line `(b) that adequate financial provision has not been made for the performance or any such duty, it`
  line `may direct ^2[^3[the Corporation]] or the municipal authority concerned, within such period as it think fit, to`
  line `make arrangements to its satisfaction for the proper performance of the duty, or, as the case may be,`
  line `to make financial provision to its satisfaction for the performance of the duty and ^2[^3[the Corporation]] or`
  line `the municipal authority concerned shall comply with such direction:`
  line
  line `Provided that, unless in the opinion of the Central Government the immediate execution of such order`
  line `is necessary, it shall before making any direction under this section give ^2[^3[the Corporation]] or the municipal`
  line `authority concerned an opportunity of showing cause why such direction should not be made.`
  line
  line ^4
  line `* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_487_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 123, for "whether on receipt of" (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "a Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `4. Omitted by Act 67 of 1993, s. 123 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_488:
  sectionId (31407)
  sectionNo (488)
  orderNo 547
  title `Power to provide for enforcement of direction under section 487.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_488_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_488_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31407&sectionno=488&orderno=547&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_488_content:
  string
  line `If, within the period`
  line `fixed by a direction made under sub-section (1) of section 487, any action the taking of which has been`
  line `directed under that sub-section has not been duly taken, the Central Government may make arrangements`
  line `for the taking of such action and may direct that all expenses connected therewith shall be defrayed out of`
  line `the Municipal Fund.`
obj_root_law_sections_488_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_489:
  sectionId (31408)
  sectionNo (489)
  orderNo 548
  title `Power of Government to give directions in relation to primary schools, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_489_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_489_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31408&sectionno=489&orderno=548&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_489_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `The Central Government may give ^1[^2[the Corporation]] all such directions as it considers necessary in respect`
  line `of subjects, curricula, text books, standards and methods of teaching in primary schools vested in ^1[^2[the`
  line `Corporation]] or maintained wholly or partly by grants paid out of the Municipal Fund and in respect of`
  line `such other matters as that Government considers necessary and ^1[^2[the Corporation]] shall comply with all`
  line `such directions.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall be lawful for any officer appointed by the ^3[Government] in this behalf to inspect any`
  line `such school; and all reasonable facilities shall be given to such officer in connection with the inspection.`
  line
  line `(3) The ^3[Government], after considering the report of inspection made by such officer, may`
  line `give ^1[^2[the Corporation]] such directions as it considers necessary and ^1[^2[the Corporation]] shall comply with such`
  line directions.
obj_root_law_sections_489_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for "Central Government" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for "the Corporation"(w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "a Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_490:
  sectionId (31409)
  sectionNo (490)
  orderNo 549
  title `Dissolution of the Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_490_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_490_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31409&sectionno=490&orderno=549&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_490_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[490. Dissolution of ^2[^3[the Corporation]]--(1) If, in the opinion of the Central Government, ^2[^3[the`
  line `Corporation]] persistently makes default in the performance of the duties imposed on it by or under this Act`
  line `or exceeds or abuses its powers, the Central Government may by an order published, together with a`
  line `statement of reasons therefor, in the Official Gazette, dissolve ^2[^3[the Corporation:`
  line
  line `Provided that ^2[^3[the Corporation]] shall be given a reasonable opportunity of being heard before its`
  line dissolution.
  line
  line `(2) When ^2[^3[the Corporation]] is dissolved by an order under sub-section (1),--`
  line
  line `(a) all councillors shall, on the date of the dissolution, vacate their office as such councillors and`
  line `the persons referred to in clause (b) of sub-section (3) of section 3 shall cease to be represented in ^2[^3[the`
  line Corporation]];
  line
  line `(b) during the period of dissolution of ^2[^3[the Corporation]], all powers and duties conferred and`
  line `imposed upon ^2[^3[the Corporation]] by or under this Act or any other law, shall be exercised and`
  line `performed by such officer or authority as the Central Government may appoint in that behalf;`
  line
  line `(c) all property vested in ^2[^3[the Corporation]] shall, until it is re-constituted, vest in the ^4[Government].`
  line
  line `(3) An election to constitute ^2[^3[the Corporation]] shall be completed before the expiration of a period of`
  line `six months from the date of its dissolution.`
  line
  line `(4) An order of dissolution made under this section together with a statement of the reasons therefor`
  line `shall be laid before each House of Parliament and the Legislative Assembly of the National Capital`
  line `Territory of Delhi as soon as may be, after it has been made.`
obj_root_law_sections_490_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 124, for section 490 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for "the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for "a Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for "Central Government" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
obj_root_law_sections_490_a:
  sectionId (31410)
  sectionNo 490A
  orderNo 550
  title `Delegation of power by the Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_490_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 125, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31410&sectionno=490A&orderno=550&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_490_a_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[490A. Delegation of power by the Central Government.The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, direct that any power exercisable by it under this Act shall, subject to`
  line `such conditions, if any, as may be specified in the notification be exercisable by the Government or any`
  line `of its officers or by the Commissioner or any other authority.]`
obj_root_law_sections_490_b:
  sectionId (67092)
  sectionNo 490B
  orderNo 551
  title `Delegation of power by the Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_490_b_content
  footnotes `Ins. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 20 (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=67092&sectionno=490B&orderno=551&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_490_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[490B. Delegation of power by the Government.—The Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, direct that any power exercisable by it under this act shall, subject to such conditions, if`
  line `any, as may be specified in the notification, be exercisable by any of its officers or by Commissioner or by`
  line `any other authority.]`
obj_root_law_sections_491:
  sectionId (31411)
  sectionNo (491)
  orderNo 552
  title `Power to delegate functions of Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_491_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_491_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31411&sectionno=491&orderno=552&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_491_content:
  string
  line `The Commissioner may by order direct that`
  line `any power conferred or any duty imposed on him by or under this Act shall, in such circumstances and`
  line `under such conditions, if any, as may be specified in the order, be exercised and performed also by any`
  line `municipal officer or other municipal employee specified in the order.`
obj_root_law_sections_491_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_492:
  sectionId (31412)
  sectionNo (492)
  orderNo 553
  title `Validity of notices and other documents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_492_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_492_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31412&sectionno=492&orderno=553&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_492_content:
  string
  line `No notice, order, requisition, licence, permission in`
  line `writing or any other document issued under this Act shall be invalid merely by reason of defect of form.`
obj_root_law_sections_492_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_493:
  sectionId (31413)
  sectionNo (493)
  orderNo 554
  title `Admissibility of document or entry as evidence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_493_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_493_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31413&sectionno=493&orderno=554&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_493_content:
  string
  line `A copy of any receipt, application, plan,`
  line `notice, order or other document or of any entry in a register in the possession of any municipal authority`
  line `shall, if duly certified by the legal keeper thereof or other person authorised by the Commissioner in this`
  line `behalf, be admissible in evidence of the existence of the document or entry, and shall be admitted as`
  line `evidence of the matters and transactions therein recorded in every case where, and to the same extent to`
  line `which, the original document or entry would, if produced, have been admissible to prove such matters and`
  line transactions.
obj_root_law_sections_493_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_494:
  sectionId (31414)
  sectionNo (494)
  orderNo 555
  title `Evidence of Municipal officer or employee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_494_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_494_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31414&sectionno=494&orderno=555&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_494_content:
  string
  line `No Municipal officer or other municipal`
  line `employee shall, in any legal proceedings to which the Corporation is not a party, be required to produce`
  line `any register or document the contents of which can be proved under section 493 by a certified copy, or to appear as a witness to prove any matter or transaction recorded therein save by order of the court made`
  line `for special cause.`
obj_root_law_sections_494_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_495:
  sectionId (31415)
  sectionNo (495)
  orderNo 556
  title `Prohibition against obstruction of Mayor or any municipal authority, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_495_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_495_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31415&sectionno=495&orderno=556&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_495_content:
  string
  line `No person shall`
  line `obstruct or molest ^1[^2[the Corporation]] or any municipal authority, the Mayor or the Deputy Mayor, any`
  line `councillor or aldermen or any person employed by ^1[^2[the Corporation]] or any person with whom the`
  line `Commissioner has entered into a contract on behalf of ^1[^2[the Corporation]], in the performance of their duty`
  line `or of anything which they are empowered or required to do by virtue or in consequence of any provision`
  line `of this Act or of any rule, regulation or bye-law made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_495_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 2, , ibid., for “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_496:
  sectionId (31416)
  sectionNo (496)
  orderNo 557
  title `Prohibition against removal of mark.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_496_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_496_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31416&sectionno=496&orderno=557&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_496_content:
  string
  line `No person shall remove any mark set up for the`
  line `purpose of indicating any level or direction incidental to the execution of any work authorised by this Act`
  line `or of any rule or bye-law made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_496_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_497:
  sectionId (31417)
  sectionNo (497)
  orderNo 558
  title `Prohibition against removal or obliteration of notice.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_497_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_497_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31417&sectionno=497&orderno=558&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_497_content:
  string
  line `No person shall, without authority in`
  line `that behalf, remove, destroy, deface or otherwise obliterate any notice exhibited by or under orders of ^1[^2[the`
  line `Corporation]] or any municipal authority or any municipal officer or other municipal employee specified`
  line `by the Commissioner in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_497_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_498:
  sectionId (31418)
  sectionNo (498)
  orderNo 559
  title `Prohibition against unauthorised dealings with public place or materials.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_498_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_498_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31418&sectionno=498&orderno=559&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_498_content:
  string
  line `No person shall,`
  line `without authority in that behalf, remove earth, sand or other material or deposit any matter or make any`
  line `encroachment from, in, or on any land vested in ^1[^2[the Corporation]] or in any way obstruct the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_498_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for the Corporation (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for a Corporation (w.e.f. 22-5-2022)`
  line .
obj_root_law_sections_499:
  sectionId (31419)
  sectionNo (499)
  orderNo 560
  title `Liability of Commissioner, etc., for loss, waste or mis-application of Municipal Fund or property`
  content obj_root_law_sections_499_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_499_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31419&sectionno=499&orderno=560&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_499_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line ^1
  line `[Every councillor and every person referred to in clause (b) of sub-section (3) of section`
  line `3, the Commissioner,]`
  line ^2
  line `*** and every municipal officer and other municipal employee shall be liable for`
  line `the loss, waste or misapplication of any money or other property owned by or vested in Corporation, if`
  line `such loss, waste or misapplication is a direct consequence of his neglect or misconduct and a suit for`
  line `compensation may be instituted against him by ^3[^4[the Corporation]] with the previous sanction of the ^5`
  line ***
  line `^6[Central Government] or by the ^5`
  line `*** ^6[CentralGovernment].`
  line
  line `(2) Every such suit shall be instituted within three years after the date on which the cause of action`
  line arose.
obj_root_law_sections_499_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 67 of 1993, s. 126, for "Every councillor and alderman, the Commissioner, the General Manager`
  line `(Electricity)," (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `2. The words and brackets " , the General Manager (Transport)" omitted by Act 71 of 1971, s. 7(b) and the Second`
  line `Schedule (w.e.f. 3-11-1971).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for " the Corporation" (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for " a Corporation" (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
  line
  line `5. The word "Central" omitted by Act 67 of 1993, s. 126 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for " Government" (w.e.f.22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_500:
  sectionId (31420)
  sectionNo (500)
  orderNo 561
  title `Councillors and municipal officers and employees to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_500_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_500_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31420&sectionno=500&orderno=561&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_500_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line [Every
  line `Councillor and every person referred to in clause (b) of sub-section (3) of section 3, the Commissioner,]`
  line ^2
  line `*** and every municipal officer and other municipal employee shall be deemed to be a public servant`
  line `within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860), and in the definition of legal`
  line `remuneration in section 161 of that Code the word Government shall, for the purpose of this section,`
  line `be deemed to include ^3[^4[the Corporation]].`
obj_root_law_sections_500_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 127, ibid., for Every councillor and alderman, the Commissioner, the General Manager (Electricity),`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `2. The words and brackets , the General Manager (Transport) omitted by Act 71 of 1971, s. 7(b) and the Second`
  line `Schedule (w.e.f. 3-11-1971).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_501:
  sectionId (31421)
  sectionNo (501)
  orderNo 562
  title `Annual administration report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_501_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_501_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31421&sectionno=501&orderno=562&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_501_content:
  string
  line `(1) As soon as may be after the 1st day of April in every year`
  line `and not later than such date as may be fixed by the ^1`
  line `*** Government in this behalf, ^2[^3[the Corporation]] shall`
  line `submit to that Government a detailed report of the municipal government of Delhi during the preceding`
  line `year in such form as that Government may direct.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commissioner shall prepare such report and ^2[^3[the Corporation]] shall consider it and forward the`
  line `same to the ^1`
  line `*** Government with its resolution thereon, if any.`
  line
  line `(3) Copies of the report shall be kept for sale at the municipal office.`
obj_root_law_sections_501_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The word Central omitted by Act 67 of 1993, s. 128 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_502:
  sectionId (31422)
  sectionNo (502)
  orderNo 563
  title `Other laws not to be disregarded.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_502_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_502_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31422&sectionno=502&orderno=563&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_502_content:
  string
  line `Save as provided in this Act, nothing contained in this Act`
  line `shall be construed as authorising the disregard by ^1[^2[the Corporation]] or any municipal authority or any`
  line `municipal officer or other municipal employee of any law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_502_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_503:
  sectionId (31423)
  sectionNo (503)
  orderNo 564
  title `Exemption of diplomatic or consular missions from payment of tax etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_503_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_503_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31423&sectionno=503&orderno=564&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_503_content:
  string
  line `The Central`
  line `Government may, by order in the Official Gazette, exempt from the payment of any tax, rate, fee or other`
  line `charge payable under the provisions of this Act, any diplomatic or consular mission of a foreign State or`
  line `the High Commission of a Commonwealth country and any official of such mission or High Commission.`
obj_root_law_sections_503_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_504:
  sectionId (31424)
  sectionNo (504)
  orderNo 565
  title `Construction of references.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_504_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_504_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857&sectionId=31424&sectionno=504&orderno=565&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00028_195766_1517807321857
obj_root_law_sections_504_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `* * * * *`
  line
  line `(2) After the establishment of ^2[^3[the Corporation]] any reference in any enactment, rule, bye-law, order,`
  line `scheme, notification or other instrument having the force of law, to any of the bodies or local authorities`
  line `specified in the Second Schedule shall, unless the context or subject otherwise requires, be construed as a`
  line `reference to ^2[^3[the Corporation]].`
obj_root_law_sections_504_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Omitted by Act 67 of 1993, s. 129 (w.e.f. 1-10-1993).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Delhi Act 12 of 2011, s. 2, for “the Corporation” (w.e.f. 13-1-2012).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2022, s. 2, for “a Corporation” (w.e.f. 22-5-2022).`
